window.CONTENT["4870"] = {"meta":{"id":"4870","code":"COMP 4870","name":"Intranet Planning and Development","exam":"2026-04-24T10:30:00-07:00","room":"SE12-327","format":"60 MCQ + 10 match-two-columns + 1 coding · 80 marks · 60 min","cheatsheet_allowed":true,"instructor":"Medhat Elmasry","notes_html":"\u003cp\u003eCoverage: weeks 7–13 of the syllabus.\nTopic weights (marks): AI 13 · ML.NET 12 · Cache/Redis 8 · File-based apps 8 · gRPC 7 · TDD 6 · Aspire 5 · Localization 4 · Tag Helpers 3 · Blazor 2 · Excel/PDF/Chart 2 · coding question 10.\nYou may bring one hand-written 8.5&quot; × 11&quot; cheat sheet, both sides.\u003c/p\u003e"},"modules":[{"id":"module-1-ai-in-dotnet","name":"AI in .NET","topics":[{"id":"ai-agent-framework","name":"Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF) + tool calling","tags":["ai","maf","agent","tools","function-calling"],"prose":"Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF) wraps an `IChatClient` into a `ChatClientAgent` via\n`.AsAIAgent()`, registers C# delegates or lambdas as `AITool` values through\n`AIFunctionFactory.Create`, and drives turns with `RunAsync` or `RunStreamingAsync`.\nMulti-turn state lives in an `AgentSession` from `await agent.CreateSessionAsync()`,\nnot in a manual `ChatHistory`. Common exam traps: `.AsAgent()`, `agent.Invoke()`,\nand `AITool.Register()` do not exist.\n","cards":[{"id":"maf-base-package","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §NuGet Packages to Add","explanation":"The base package ships separately from the OpenAI integration. Both require --prerelease because MAF is not GA. Exam distractors swap the name to 'Microsoft.AgentFramework' or drop --prerelease.","example":"dotnet add package Microsoft.Agents.AI --prerelease","prompt":"The base NuGet package for MAF is {{Microsoft.Agents.AI}}, installed with the {{--prerelease}} flag.","answer":"Microsoft.Agents.AI --prerelease"},{"id":"maf-openai-package","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §NuGet Packages to Add","explanation":"The `.OpenAI` suffix is what pulls in the `ChatClient` type used for OpenAI-compatible endpoints. Missing this package means `.AsAIAgent()` compiles but nothing at the OpenAI layer does.","example":"dotnet add package Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI --prerelease","prompt":"To get the OpenAI-compatible `ChatClient` integration (GitHub Models, Azure OpenAI), install {{Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI}} with {{--prerelease}}.","answer":"Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI --prerelease"},{"id":"maf-as-ai-agent-method","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Create MAF Agent (Basic); flashcard #3","explanation":"The extension lives on `IChatClient` and accepts `name`, `instructions`, and `tools`. `.AsAgent()` is a common distractor and does not compile.","example":"var agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(instructions: \"You are a chef.\", name: \"RecipeAgent\");","prompt":"Name the extension method that wraps an `IChatClient` into a `ChatClientAgent`.","answer":".AsAIAgent()"},{"id":"maf-register-tool","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §Create MAF Agent with Tools; flashcard #2","explanation":"`AIFunctionFactory.Create` takes a delegate plus `name:` and `description:`. The description is the natural-language string the LLM reads to decide when to call the tool. `AITool.Register` and `AIFunction.Create` are distractors.","example":"AITool weatherTool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n    WeatherService.GetWeatherAsync,\n    name: \"GetWeather\",\n    description: \"Get the weather details of a location using city name\");\n","prompt":"Name the factory call that turns a C# method into an `AITool` for an MAF agent.","answer":"AIFunctionFactory.Create"},{"id":"maf-session-for-multiturn","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-ai.md §MAF Agent with Session (Multi-Turn); flashcard #6","explanation":"`ChatHistory` is a manual `List\u003cChatMessage\u003e` for raw `IChatClient` loops. MAF agents manage history and tool-call state inside an `AgentSession`. Passing both duplicates state.","example":"var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();\nvar reply = await agent.RunAsync(\"What did I ask first?\", session);\n","prompt":"You need conversation memory across five `RunAsync` calls against one MAF agent. Do you build a `ChatHistory` list or an `AgentSession`, and how do you get it?","answer":"`AgentSession`, via `var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();` — pass it into every `RunAsync` call."},{"id":"maf-run-method-name","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Create MAF Agent (Basic); flashcard #18","explanation":"`RunAsync` returns the full response after all tool round-trips complete. `Invoke` is a Semantic Kernel verb and a standard distractor on MAF questions.","example":"var response = await agent.RunAsync(\"A dessert for a rainy Tuesday.\");","prompt":"To execute an MAF agent turn and get the assembled reply, call {{agent.RunAsync(input)}} — not `agent.Invoke(input)`.","answer":"agent.RunAsync(input)"},{"id":"maf-streaming-method","type":"cloze","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §MAF Agent with Streaming; flashcard #9","explanation":"`RunStreamingAsync` yields updates as the model produces them. Swap it in for `RunAsync` when you want incremental output to the console or UI.","example":"await foreach (var update in agent.RunStreamingAsync(\"Which planet is closest to the sun?\")) {\n    Console.Write(update);\n}\n","prompt":"To stream tokens from an MAF agent, `await foreach` over {{agent.RunStreamingAsync(input)}}.","answer":"agent.RunStreamingAsync(input)"},{"id":"maf-lambda-tool","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §Tool Registration from Async Lambda","explanation":"`AIFunctionFactory.Create` accepts delegates, including async lambdas. The lambda parameters become the tool's parameter schema sent to the LLM.","example":"AITool poemTool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n    async (string city, string weather) =\u003e (await chatClient.GetResponseAsync($\"Poem for {city}, {weather}\")).Text,\n    name: \"WriteShortPoem\",\n    description: \"Write a short funny poem about clothes to wear based on city and weather\");\n","prompt":"You have an async lambda `(string city, string weather) =\u003e Task\u003cstring\u003e` that builds a prompt and calls `chatClient.GetResponseAsync`. How do you expose it as a tool to an MAF agent?","answer":"Wrap it with `AIFunctionFactory.Create(lambda, name: \"...\", description: \"...\")` and pass the result in the `tools:` array of `.AsAIAgent(...)`."},{"id":"maf-fake-method-as-agent","type":"name","bloom":"analyze","source":"research-ai.md §Fake Method Names in MCQ","explanation":"`.AsAgent()` is a documented exam trap — it resembles the real API and compiles if you define your own extension. MAF ships `.AsAIAgent()` only.","example":"var agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(name: \"Bot\", instructions: \"...\");","prompt":"A multiple-choice option shows `chatClient.AsAgent(instructions: \"...\")`. Correct or distractor?","answer":"Distractor. The real method is `.AsAIAgent()`."},{"id":"maf-fake-method-register","type":"name","bloom":"analyze","source":"research-ai.md §Fake Method Names in MCQ; MCQ #1","explanation":"MAF has no `AITool.Register`. All native and lambda tools flow through `AIFunctionFactory.Create`, which returns an `AITool` you pass in the `tools:` array.","example":"AITool tool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n    WeatherService.GetWeather,\n    name: \"Weather\",\n    description: \"Get weather\");\n","prompt":"A choice reads `AITool.Register(WeatherService.GetWeather, \"Weather\", \"Get weather\");`. Real or distractor?","answer":"Distractor. Use `AIFunctionFactory.Create(WeatherService.GetWeather, name: \"Weather\", description: \"Get weather\");`."},{"id":"maf-agent-reasoning-behavior","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-ai.md §MAF Stack; MCQ #6","explanation":"MAF agents are agentic — tool selection is implicit in the LLM's output. Tools execute only when the model emits a tool-call for them. Sequential execution of every registered tool is a distractor.","example":"Input 'What should I wear in Vancouver?' triggers GetWeather only if the model decides it needs weather data.","prompt":"When you call `agent.RunAsync(input, session)` on an MAF agent with three registered tools, what actually runs?","answer":"The LLM reads input and tool descriptions, decides which (if any) tools to call, MAF invokes those, tool results feed back into the LLM, and the final assistant message is returned. Not all tools run."},{"id":"maf-vs-sk-verbs","type":"name","bloom":"analyze","source":"research-ai.md §Semantic Kernel vs. MAF Differences","explanation":"MAF and SK are sibling SDKs with different vocabularies. Mixing `kernel.InvokeAsync` with `agent.RunAsync` on the same object is a classic exam trap — they do not interop directly.","example":"// SK\nkernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cWeatherPlugin\u003e();\nawait kernel.InvokeAsync(plugin[\"GetWeather\"], new(\"Vancouver\"));\n// MAF\nAITool t = AIFunctionFactory.Create(WeatherPlugin.GetWeather, name: \"GetWeather\", description: \"...\");\nawait agent.RunAsync(\"Weather in Vancouver?\", session);\n","prompt":"Sketch the verb mapping: for (a) tool registration, (b) turn execution, which method belongs to Semantic Kernel and which to MAF?","answer":"Registration — SK: `kernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e()`; MAF: `AIFunctionFactory.Create(method, name, description)`.\nExecution  — SK: `kernel.InvokeAsync(function, args)`; MAF: `agent.RunAsync(input, session)`.\n"}],"source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx; research-ai.md §MAF"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow","name":"ML.NET pipeline workflow — Load → Transform → Concatenate → Train → Evaluate → Predict","tags":["ml-net","pipeline"],"prose":"The canonical ML.NET program chains seven steps: create MLContext, load data into an IDataView, rename the target column to \"Label\", one-hot-encode categoricals, Concatenate features into a column named \"Features\", pick a trainer, and call Fit to get back an ITransformer. These cards drill the return types, magic column names, and trap answers the exam reuses.","cards":[{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-01","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §MLContext; card #2, #14","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`MLContext` exposes `Data`, `Transforms`, `Regression`, `MulticlassClassification`, and `Model`. Passing `seed: 0` pins the random-number generator so identical inputs produce identical models.","example":"`MLContext mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);` — every subsequent call starts `mlContext.Something`.","prompt":"The root object for every ML.NET program is `{{MLContext}}`, constructed with `new MLContext(seed: 0)` to make training {{deterministic}}.","answer":"`MLContext` / deterministic"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-02","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §IDataView; card #3","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The load call is lazy: rows are not pulled into memory until a downstream transform or `Fit` asks for them. The generic `T` carries `[LoadColumn(N)]` attributes that map CSV indices to fields.","example":"`IDataView trainingData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\"taxi-fare-train.csv\", hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');`","prompt":"`mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e(path, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',')` returns an `{{IDataView}}` — an immutable, streaming view over tabular data.","answer":"`IDataView`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-03","type":"name","source":"research-mlnet.md §Exam Traps #3; card #4; MCQ Q3","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`Fit` runs every transform and trains the final algorithm. It does not return `IDataView` (that is what `Transform` returns), not metrics, not a `PredictionEngine`. This is the single most common MCQ distractor.","example":"`ITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);` — never `IDataView model = pipeline.Fit(…)`.","prompt":"What does `pipeline.Fit(trainingData)` return?","answer":"`ITransformer` — the trained, stateless, serializable model."},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-04","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §Exam Traps #5; §Top 5 Exam Mistakes #2","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Trainers search the `IDataView` schema for a column named `\"Label\"`. If you leave `FareAmount` as the target name, the trainer cannot find it and `Fit` throws a \"column not found\" error.","example":"`mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")`","prompt":"The first step in a trainer pipeline renames the target column to the literal name `{{\"Label\"}}` using the `{{CopyColumns}}` transform.","answer":"`\"Label\"` / `CopyColumns`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-05","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §Exam Traps #6; card #7","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Trainers look up their input by the hard-coded name `\"Features\"`. `Concatenate` packs the encoded columns into one vector under that name so the trainer can consume it as a single numeric input.","example":"`.Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"TripDistance\"))`","prompt":"`Concatenate` must produce a single vector column named exactly `{{\"Features\"}}` — trainers refuse to run if the column is called `\"Input\"` or `\"X\"`.","answer":"`\"Features\"`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-06","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md card #6; MCQ Q5","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Trainers accept only numeric input. `OneHotEncoding` expands a categorical column into one indicator column per distinct value — `\"VTS\"` becomes `[1,0]`, `\"CMT\"` becomes `[0,1]`.","example":"`.Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(outputColumnName: \"VendorIdEncoded\", inputColumnName: \"VendorId\"))`","prompt":"To convert categorical text columns such as `\"VTS\"` or `\"CMT\"` into numeric binary vectors, apply the `{{OneHotEncoding}}` transform before `Concatenate`.","answer":"`OneHotEncoding`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-07","type":"name","source":"research-mlnet.md §Algorithms; card #9","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`FastTree` is the default regression trainer for numeric prediction. Regression namespace matters: using `mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Trainers.…` for a regression task produces wrong metrics or compile errors.","example":"`.Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());`","prompt":"Which trainer call sits at the end of a regression pipeline in the taxi-fare example, and which namespace does it come from?","answer":"`mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree()` — gradient-boosted decision trees from `Microsoft.ML.FastTree`."},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-08","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §Exam Traps #7","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`LoadColumn` takes a numeric index, not a header string. The index matches the CSV column position starting at zero; header names are ignored by this attribute.","example":"`[LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId;` maps to the first CSV column.","prompt":"`[LoadColumn({{0}})]` on a field maps it to the CSV column at {{0-based}} index — `[LoadColumn(6)]` reads the seventh column.","answer":"0 / 0-based"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-09","type":"name","source":"research-mlnet.md §Complete Workflow Step 6; card #10","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`Transform` applies the pipeline to new data and adds the `\"Score\"` column. `Regression.Evaluate` reads `\"Label\"` and `\"Score\"` to produce a `RegressionMetrics` with `RSquared`, `RootMeanSquaredError`, and `MeanAbsoluteError`.","example":"`Console.WriteLine($\"RSquared: {metrics.RSquared:0.##}\");`","prompt":"After `Fit`, how do you compute regression quality metrics on a test `IDataView`?","answer":"`var predictions = model.Transform(testData); var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-10","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §PredictionEngine; card #5; MCQ Q8","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`PredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e` handles one example at a time. For batch inference use `model.Transform(batch)` instead — calling `Predict` in a tight loop is the single-row API.","example":"`var engine = mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(model); var fare = engine.Predict(newTrip).FareAmount;`","prompt":"For single-row inference at runtime, wrap the trained model in a `{{PredictionEngine}}` via `mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTInput, TOutput\u003e(model)`, then call `.Predict(example)`.","answer":"`PredictionEngine`"},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-11","type":"name","source":"research-mlnet.md §Quick Reference Cheat Sheet","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Every ML.NET program follows this shape. The order matters: rename to `\"Label\"` before any transforms that touch features; encode categoricals before `Concatenate`; `Concatenate` must come before the trainer.","example":"Taxi-fare pipeline: load CSV → copy `FareAmount` to `\"Label\"` → one-hot `VendorId` → concatenate into `\"Features\"` → `FastTree` → `Fit` → `Evaluate` → predict.","prompt":"Name the seven canonical steps of an ML.NET training program in order.","answer":"1. `new MLContext(seed: 0)` — 2. `LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e` into `IDataView` — 3. `CopyColumns(\"Label\", target)` — 4. `OneHotEncoding` for categoricals — 5. `Concatenate(\"Features\", …)` — 6. append a trainer (`FastTree` etc.) — 7. `Fit` returns an `ITransformer`, then `Evaluate` or `CreatePredictionEngine`."},{"id":"ml-pipeline-workflow-card-12","type":"cloze","source":"research-mlnet.md §Exam Traps #4; §Top 5 Exam Mistakes #3","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"The trainer namespace and the evaluator namespace must match the task. Using `BinaryClassification` or `MulticlassClassification` for a numeric-prediction problem yields classification metrics or a compilation error.","example":"Taxi-fare (numeric target) uses `mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree()` and `mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(...)`.","prompt":"Calling `mlContext.{{Regression}}.Evaluate` on a regression pipeline returns `RSquared` and `RMSE`; calling `mlContext.{{MulticlassClassification}}.Evaluate` instead returns accuracy metrics — picking the wrong namespace is an exam trap.","answer":"`Regression` / `MulticlassClassification`"}],"source":"slides/ML.NET.pptx; notes/ML.NET_VSCODE_SCRIPT.docx; research-mlnet.md §Complete ML.NET Workflow"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel","name":"Semantic Kernel SDK","tags":["ai","orchestration","plugins"],"prose":"Semantic Kernel is Microsoft's orchestration SDK for LLMs in .NET. A Kernel — built by KernelBuilder — holds an IChatCompletionService and plugins. A plugin is a collection of callable functions: either a native C# class whose methods carry [KernelFunction] + [Description], or a prompt directory containing skprompt.txt with {{$variable}} placeholders. Invoke everything through kernel.InvokeAsync(). The core NuGet is Microsoft.SemanticKernel; add-on packages live under Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Plugins.*. Do not confuse with Microsoft Agent Framework — agent.RunAsync() and AIFunctionFactory.Create() belong to MAF, not Semantic Kernel.","cards":[{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-01","type":"name","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`KernelBuilder` configures services (LLM backend, logging) and constructs the `Kernel` via `Build()`. Variant `Kernel.Builder` does not exist.","example":"`var kernel = new KernelBuilder().AddOpenAIChatCompletion(\"gpt-4o\", apiKey).Build();`","source":"research-ai.md §Register Semantic Kernel in Program.cs","prompt":"Which class builds a Semantic Kernel `Kernel` instance fluently?","answer":"`KernelBuilder`"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-02","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`InvokeAsync` is the one call that runs any plugin function through the kernel. `kernel.Execute()` is a fake method that appears in distractors.","example":"`await kernel.InvokeAsync(plugin[\"RecipeGenerator\"], new(\"chocolate cake\"));`","source":"research-ai.md §Kernel, §Add Plugin to Kernel (Prompt-Based)","prompt":"To execute a Semantic Kernel function, call `kernel.{{InvokeAsync}}()`.","answer":"InvokeAsync"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-03","type":"name","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`[KernelFunction]` tags the method for kernel discovery; pair it with `[Description]` so the LLM can choose it during tool selection. `[SkillFunction]` is a distractor.","example":"`[KernelFunction(\"DescribeWeather\")] [Description(\"Get weather for a city\")] public static string GetWeatherDescription(string city) =\u003e ...;`","source":"research-ai.md flashcard #8, §Add Plugin to Kernel (Native C# Class)","prompt":"Which attribute marks a C# method as a Semantic Kernel function?","answer":"`[KernelFunction]`"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-04","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The kernel substitutes each `{{$var}}` with the argument passed to `InvokeAsync` before sending the rendered prompt to the LLM.","example":"`skprompt.txt`: `Identify the city in this input: {{$input}}` — called with `input = \"weather in Tokyo\"`.","source":"research-ai.md §skprompt.txt Template, flashcard #11","prompt":"In a Semantic Kernel prompt template, the placeholder syntax is `{{{{$variableName}}}}`.","answer":"{{$variableName}}"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`IChatCompletionService` lets you swap OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, or Ollama backends without changing calling code. Implementations register via extension methods on `KernelBuilder` like `AddOpenAIChatCompletion`.","example":"`kernelBuilder.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(\"phi3\", new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));` registers an Ollama-backed `IChatCompletionService`.","source":"research-ai.md §IChatCompletionService, flashcard #15","prompt":"Which interface abstracts the LLM backend in Semantic Kernel?","answer":"`IChatCompletionService`"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-06","type":"cloze","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e()` reflects over `T`, finds every `[KernelFunction]` method, and registers them. Use `ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory()` instead for directories containing `skprompt.txt`.","example":"`kernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cWeatherPlugin\u003e();` makes `WeatherPlugin.GetWeatherDescription` callable via `kernel.InvokeAsync`.","source":"research-ai.md §Add Plugin to Kernel (Native C# Class)","prompt":"To load a native C# plugin class `WeatherPlugin`, call `kernel.{{ImportPluginFromType}}\u003cWeatherPlugin\u003e()`.","answer":"ImportPluginFromType"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"understand","explanation":"A prompt-directory plugin is a folder containing `skprompt.txt` — the template with `{{$var}}` placeholders — and optional config. `ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory()` reads this layout.","example":"`Plugins/CakeRecipe/skprompt.txt` contains `Write a recipe for {{$input}}.`; the kernel renders it at invoke time.","source":"research-ai.md §skprompt.txt Template, flashcard #10","prompt":"What file name identifies a prompt-based Semantic Kernel plugin inside its directory?","answer":"`skprompt.txt`"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-08","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","explanation":"`ChatHistory` carries prior turns so the LLM has context on each call. It is distinct from Microsoft Agent Framework's `AgentSession`.","example":"`var history = new ChatHistory(); history.AddUserMessage(\"hi\"); history.AddAssistantMessage(\"hello\");`","source":"research-ai.md §ChatHistory, §Kernel → ChatHistory Flow","prompt":"The ordered list tracking multi-turn conversation state in Semantic Kernel is `{{ChatHistory}}` — a list of `ChatMessage` objects with a `ChatRole` (User, Assistant, System).","answer":"ChatHistory"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-09","type":"name","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory(path)` scans the directory for prompt templates and registers them as functions. `SkillFactory.Create()` is a distractor — it does not exist.","example":"`kernel.ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory(Path.Combine(pluginDir, \"CakeRecipe\"));`","source":"research-ai.md §Add Plugin to Kernel (Prompt-Based)","prompt":"Which Semantic Kernel method loads a plugin from a directory of `skprompt.txt` files?","answer":"`ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory()`"},{"id":"ai-semantic-kernel-card-10","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Install the core package first; add individual `Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Plugins.*` packages only when you need their integrations. The MAF package `Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI` is a separate SDK.","example":"`dotnet add package Microsoft.SemanticKernel` brings in `Kernel`, `KernelBuilder`, `[KernelFunction]`.","source":"research-ai.md §NuGet Packages to Add, §Package Naming Confusion","prompt":"The core Semantic Kernel NuGet package is `{{Microsoft.SemanticKernel}}`; add-on plugin packages live under `Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Plugins.*`.","answer":"Microsoft.SemanticKernel"}],"source":"slides/CSharp_Meets_AI.pptx; notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx; research-ai.md §Semantic Kernel"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms","name":"ML.NET data transforms","tags":["ml-net","feature-eng"],"prose":"Trainers in ML.NET consume two specific columns: a scalar named `\"Label\"` and a vector named `\"Features\"`. Three transforms produce them. `CopyColumns` renames your target to `\"Label\"`. `OneHotEncoding` converts each categorical text column into a numeric indicator vector under a name you choose. `Concatenate` stitches the surviving numeric columns — including every encoded output — into the single `\"Features\"` vector. Skip any step, misname a column, or forget an encoded column in the concatenate list and training breaks or silently loses a feature.","cards":[{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-01","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","prompt":"Trainers look up the target column by the literal name `\"{{Label}}\"` and the feature vector by the literal name `\"{{Features}}\"`.","answer":"Label","explanation":"Both names are hardcoded in ML.NET trainer lookups. Renaming either one breaks `Fit()` at runtime.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-02","type":"name","bloom":"understand","prompt":"What does `mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")` do, and why is it required?","answer":"It duplicates the `FareAmount` column under the name `\"Label\"`.","explanation":"It duplicates the `FareAmount` column under the name `\"Label\"`. Regression trainers look for a column named exactly `\"Label\"` as their target; without this rename, training fails.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-03","type":"name","bloom":"understand","prompt":"Why can't a regression trainer consume a raw `VendorId` column containing strings like `\"CMT\"` and `\"VTS\"` directly?","answer":"Trainers operate on numeric vectors.","explanation":"Trainers operate on numeric vectors. `OneHotEncoding` performs categorical encoding: each distinct text value becomes a slot in a binary-indicator vector (e.g. `\"VTS\"` → `[0, 1]`), which the trainer can then process.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-04","type":"cloze","bloom":"apply","prompt":"In `mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(outputColumnName: \"VendorIdEncoded\", inputColumnName: \"VendorId\")`, the name `\"VendorIdEncoded\"` is {{chosen by you}}, but whatever you pick must then appear in the {{`Concatenate` input list}}.","answer":"chosen by you","explanation":"Output names are arbitrary — `\"VendorIdOH\"` works equally well. The only hard constraint is matching that exact string when you reference the encoded column downstream.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"apply","prompt":"A pipeline calls `OneHotEncoding` on `VendorId`, `RateCode`, and `PaymentType`, then `Concatenate(\"Features\", \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"PassengerCount\", \"TripDistance\")`. What silent bug exists?","answer":"`RateCodeEncoded` and `PaymentTypeEncoded` are encoded but never listed in `Concatenate`, so they are dropped from …","explanation":"`RateCodeEncoded` and `PaymentTypeEncoded` are encoded but never listed in `Concatenate`, so they are dropped from the `\"Features\"` vector. The pipeline compiles and trains, but on fewer features than intended.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-06","type":"cloze","bloom":"apply","prompt":"When predicting taxi fare, you must exclude `TripTime` from the feature list to prevent {{data leakage}}, because trip duration is unknown at {{prediction time}}.","answer":"data leakage","explanation":"Time-dependent columns known only after the event you're predicting leak future information into training. The model learns an unrealistic shortcut and fails on real inputs.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"apply","prompt":"Order these pipeline steps correctly: trainer `FastTree()`, `OneHotEncoding` calls, `CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")`, `Concatenate(\"Features\", …)`.","answer":"`CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")` → `OneHotEncoding` calls → `Concatenate(\"Features\", …)` → `FastTree()`.","explanation":"`CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")` → `OneHotEncoding` calls → `Concatenate(\"Features\", …)` → `FastTree()`. Label rename and encoded-column setup must both occur before the trainer.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-08","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","prompt":"The `[LoadColumn(0)]` attribute uses a {{0-based}} CSV index, whereas ClosedXML cells are {{1-based}} — don't carry one convention into the other.","answer":"0-based","explanation":"ML.NET CSV column attributes start at 0 for the first column. ClosedXML's `Cell(1, 1)` addresses row 1, column 1. Mixing them causes off-by-one column mismatches.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-data-transforms-card-09","type":"name","bloom":"understand","prompt":"What does `NormalizeMinMax` do, and how does it differ in purpose from `OneHotEncoding`?","answer":"`NormalizeMinMax` scales numeric features to the `[0, 1]` range.","explanation":"`NormalizeMinMax` scales numeric features to the `[0, 1]` range. `OneHotEncoding` converts text categories into numeric indicator vectors. Normalization rescales existing numbers; one-hot encoding creates numbers from text.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"}],"source":"slides/ML.NET.pptx; notes/ML.NET_VSCODE_SCRIPT.docx; research-mlnet.md §Key Transform Classes"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation","name":"ML.NET regression evaluation — FastTree, RMSE, R²","tags":["ml-net","regression","metrics"],"prose":"Regression trainers live on mlContext.Regression.Trainers; FastTree (gradient-boosted trees in Microsoft.ML.FastTree) is the default. You split an IDataView with mlContext.Data.TrainTestSplit(data, testFraction: 0.2) or average across folds with mlContext.Regression.CrossValidate. Evaluation runs through mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\"), which returns a RegressionMetrics object. Read metrics.RSquared (variance explained, 0–1, unitless), metrics.RootMeanSquaredError (average error in the label's original units, lower is better), and metrics.MeanAbsoluteError (absolute error, more robust to outliers). The namespace must match the task: Regression.Evaluate produces regression metrics, MulticlassClassification.Evaluate does not. The score argument names the prediction column; FastTree writes to \"Score\".","cards":[{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-01","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-mlnet.md §Regression Trainers; card #9","explanation":"FastTree is the default choice for general regression. Its output column is named \"Score\". SdcaRegression and LightGbmRegression are alternatives; LightGbm additionally requires Microsoft.ML.LightGbm.","example":".Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree())","prompt":"The default gradient-boosted-trees regression trainer is created with ___ and ships in the ___ package.","answer":"mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree() ; Microsoft.ML.FastTree"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-02","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-mlnet.md §TrainTestSplit; card #15","explanation":"TrainTestSplit sits on mlContext.Data, not mlContext.Regression. You fit the pipeline on TrainSet and evaluate predictions from TestSet.","example":"var split = mlContext.Data.TrainTestSplit(dataView, testFraction: 0.2);\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(split.TrainSet);\nvar predictions = model.Transform(split.TestSet);\n","prompt":"Which call partitions an IDataView into 80% training and 20% test subsets?","answer":"mlContext.Data.TrainTestSplit(dataView, testFraction: 0.2)  — returns a DataOperationsCatalog.TrainTestData with TrainSet and TestSet."},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-03","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-mlnet.md §CrossValidate","explanation":"CrossValidate gives a tighter performance estimate than a single TrainTestSplit because every row serves as test data in exactly one fold.","example":"var cv = mlContext.Regression.CrossValidate(pipeline, data, numberOfFolds: 5);","prompt":"Call ___ to run k-fold cross-validation: it trains k models, each on (k-1) folds, and reports ___ metrics across all folds.","answer":"mlContext.Regression.CrossValidate(pipeline, data, numberOfFolds: 5) ; averaged"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-04","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-mlnet.md §Evaluation Metrics; card #10","explanation":"The first string is the label column (you renamed the target to \"Label\" via CopyColumns). The second is the score column — FastTree writes its prediction to \"Score\". Mismatched names break Evaluate.","example":"IDataView predictions = model.Transform(split.TestSet);\nvar metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"R²: {metrics.RSquared:0.##}\");\n","prompt":"Which line evaluates a regression model and returns a RegressionMetrics object?","answer":"var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-mlnet.md §Regression Metrics","explanation":"R² = 1 − (SS_residual / SS_total). It is unitless. 0.89 means the model explains 89% of the label's variance, not that it is 89% accurate.","example":"Console.WriteLine($\"RSquared: {metrics.RSquared:0.##}\");","prompt":"R² is exposed as ___ on RegressionMetrics, ranges from ___ to ___, and reports the fraction of ___ the model explains.","answer":"metrics.RSquared ; 0 ; 1 ; variance"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-06","type":"name","bloom":"evaluate","source":"research-mlnet.md §Regression Metrics example; MCQ #4","explanation":"RMSE inherits the label's units (dollars here). R² is unitless variance-explained. Distractors conflate the two — \"89% accurate with 3.3% error\" is wrong on both counts.","example":"metrics.RSquared = 0.89 ; metrics.RootMeanSquaredError = 3.30 ; label column = FareAmount (USD)","prompt":"A taxi-fare model reports RSquared = 0.89 and RootMeanSquaredError = 3.3 on the test set. What do those numbers mean?","answer":"The model explains 89% of variance in FareAmount, and predicted fares miss the actual fare by about $3.30 on average."},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-mlnet.md §Evaluation Metrics; §Exam Traps","explanation":"A uses the wrong namespace — MulticlassClassification returns accuracy metrics, not RSquared. B passes the wrong score-column name; FastTree emits \"Score\". D is not a real method — Evaluate lives on the task catalog (Regression), not on Trainers.","example":"var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");","prompt":"You trained a regression model and want to print R² and RMSE on a held-out test set. Which snippet is correct?\n\nA) var metrics = mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");\nB) var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Prediction\");\nC) var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");\nD) var metrics = mlContext.Regression.Trainers.Evaluate(predictions);\n","answer":"C"},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-08","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-mlnet.md §Regression Metrics","explanation":"RMSE = √(Σ(predicted − actual)² / n). It punishes large errors more than MeanAbsoluteError does. MAE is the robust-to-outliers alternative.","example":"RSquared = 0.89 (89% variance explained) ; RMSE = 3.30 (≈ $3.30 average miss)","prompt":"Why is RootMeanSquaredError a better reality check than RSquared when a stakeholder asks \"how far off are predictions?\"","answer":"RMSE is in the label's original units (dollars for fare, seconds for duration) so it answers the question directly. RSquared is unitless variance-explained and says nothing about the size of an individual miss."},{"id":"ml-regression-evaluation-card-09","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-mlnet.md §Regression Metrics; §Exam Traps","explanation":"Claiming \"RMSE = 3.3%\" or \"RSquared is in dollars\" swaps the two. RMSE inherits units; R² never does.","example":"metrics.RootMeanSquaredError = 3.30   // dollars, because FareAmount is in USD","prompt":"RootMeanSquaredError measures error in the label's ___ units, while RSquared is ___ and ranges 0 to 1.","answer":"original (e.g. dollars for fare) ; unitless"}],"source":"slides/ML.NET.pptx; notes/ML.NET_VSCODE_SCRIPT.docx; research-mlnet.md §Evaluation Metrics"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption","module":"AI in .NET","tags":["ml-net","inference"],"cards":[{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-01","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","prompt":"`pipeline.Fit(trainingData)` returns an instance of `{{ITransformer}}`, not an `IDataView`.","answer":"ITransformer","explanation":"`Fit` trains the pipeline and hands back the stateless, serializable trained model — the `ITransformer`. The `IDataView` is the input, not the output.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-02","type":"name","bloom":"understand","prompt":"You need to score one new `TaxiTrip` at inference time. Which ML.NET type do you create, and from which factory?","answer":"Create a `PredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e` via `mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e(model)`, then call `Predict(trip)`.","explanation":"Create a `PredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e` via `mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e(model)`, then call `Predict(trip)`. It is the single-row inference wrapper around an `ITransformer`.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-03","type":"cloze","bloom":"remember","prompt":"The prediction field on an ML.NET regression output class is decorated with `[ColumnName(\"{{Score}}\")]`.","answer":"Score","explanation":"Regression trainers write their output into a column literally named `Score`. Using `[ColumnName(\"Prediction\")]` leaves the field at its default value because the binding misses.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-04","type":"name","bloom":"apply","prompt":"Write the two-line C# to persist `model` (an `ITransformer`) to `model.zip` using `trainingData`'s schema.","answer":"```csharp mlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, \"model.zip\"); ``` One call.","explanation":"```csharp\nmlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, \"model.zip\");\n```\nOne call. Pass the model, the training `DataViewSchema`, and the path. Omitting the schema produces a zip that won't load correctly.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"apply","prompt":"You have `model.zip` on disk. Load it back into an `ITransformer` and capture its schema.","answer":"```csharp DataViewSchema schema; ITransformer loaded = mlContext.Model.Load(\"model.zip\", out schema); ``` `Load` returns the transformer; the …","explanation":"```csharp\nDataViewSchema schema;\nITransformer loaded = mlContext.Model.Load(\"model.zip\", out schema);\n```\n`Load` returns the transformer; the schema comes back through the `out` parameter.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-06","type":"cloze","bloom":"understand","prompt":"For batch inference on an entire `IDataView`, call `model.{{Transform}}(dataView)` — not `CreatePredictionEngine`.","answer":"Transform","explanation":"`PredictionEngine` is the single-row path. `Transform` is the batch path: it returns a new `IDataView` with the `Score` column appended.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"understand","prompt":"Why is sharing one `PredictionEngine` across threads a bug, and what is the recommended fix for a web API?","answer":"`PredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e` is not thread-safe — concurrent `Predict` calls corrupt its internal buffers.","explanation":"`PredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e` is not thread-safe — concurrent `Predict` calls corrupt its internal buffers. Use `PredictionEnginePool\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e` from `Microsoft.Extensions.ML`, or give each thread its own engine.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-prediction-consumption-card-08","type":"name","bloom":"apply","prompt":"A teammate writes `mlContext.Model.Save(model, null, \"model.zip\")` and the code compiles. What breaks, and when?","answer":"It breaks at load time.","explanation":"It breaks at load time. Without the `DataViewSchema`, the saved zip lacks the column-name and type metadata ML.NET needs to reconstruct inputs, so `Load` returns a transformer that can't be bound to a `PredictionEngine` correctly. Always pass `trainingData.Schema`.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"}],"name":"ML.NET inference and model persistence","source":"notes/ML.NET_VS2022_SCRIPT.docx; notes/ML.NET_VSCODE_SCRIPT.docx; research-mlnet.md §PredictionEngine, §Save & Load","prose":"Cards for the ML.NET inference and model persistence topic."},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local","name":"Chat completion with Ollama + SLMs","tags":["ai","slm","ollama","streaming"],"prose":"Ollama runs Small Language Models locally on port 11434 over HTTP. The OllamaSharp NuGet package exposes OllamaApiClient, which implements IChatClient from Microsoft.Extensions.AI. You feed it a List\u003cChatMessage\u003e (each message is a ChatRole plus content) and call GetStreamingResponseAsync for token-by-token output or GetResponseAsync for a buffered reply. No cloud, no API key, no internet after the initial ollama pull.","cards":[{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-01","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Ollama; §Endpoint URL Pitfalls","explanation":"Port 11434 on localhost, HTTP only. HTTPS is the GitHub Models endpoint; port 1143 is a one-digit typo trap.","example":"new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\")","prompt":"Ollama listens on the endpoint ___ using the ___ protocol.","answer":"http://localhost:11434/ ; HTTP (not HTTPS)"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-02","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Call Ollama via OllamaSharp; SLM.docx Demo #1","explanation":"OllamaApiClient takes a Uri and a model-id string. The returned object implements IChatClient from Microsoft.Extensions.AI.","example":"IChatClient chatClient = new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\");","prompt":"Which constructor call creates an OllamaSharp client for a local Phi-3 model?","answer":"new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\")"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-03","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Ollama Setup Commands; flashcard #19","explanation":"pull downloads weights. list/show inspect what is installed. run opens an interactive REPL against a model.","example":"ollama pull phi3:latest","prompt":"What command downloads a model into Ollama so it can be served locally?","answer":"ollama pull \u003cmodel\u003e  (e.g. ollama pull phi3:latest)"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-04","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-ai.md §Chat Completion; flashcard #16; MCQ #?","explanation":"Every ChatMessage carries a ChatRole plus content. A List\u003cChatMessage\u003e is the conversation history re-sent on each call.","example":"chatHistory.Add(new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, userPrompt));","prompt":"The ChatMessage constructor takes two arguments: a ___ enum value (User, Assistant, or System) and the message ___.","answer":"ChatRole ; content (string or structured data)"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-ai.md §Call Ollama via OllamaSharp; glossary §streaming","explanation":"GetStreamingResponseAsync yields ChatResponseUpdate items incrementally; GetResponseAsync blocks until the full response is ready.","example":"await foreach (ChatResponseUpdate item in\n    chatClient.GetStreamingResponseAsync(chatHistory))\n{\n    Console.Write(item.Text);\n}\n","prompt":"Which IChatClient method streams the reply as ChatResponseUpdate fragments instead of returning one buffered response?","answer":"GetStreamingResponseAsync(chatHistory)  — iterate with await foreach"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-06","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §Local vs Cloud SLM; MCQ #7","explanation":"GitHub Models and Azure OpenAI both require cloud credentials. Ollama serves a pulled SLM from localhost with no auth.","example":"IChatClient client = new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\");","prompt":"You want a chatbot that runs with no cloud dependency and no API key. Which setup fits?","answer":"Use Ollama locally: new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\")"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §Endpoint URL Pitfalls; MCQ #2","explanation":"A drops a digit (1143 vs 11434). B and C wrongly use HTTPS; /inference is the GitHub Models path. E invents a port. Only D matches the canonical course pattern.","example":"new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\")","prompt":"Which endpoint URL correctly connects OllamaSharp to a local Ollama server?\n\nA) http://localhost:1143/\nB) https://api.ollama.com\nC) https://localhost:11434/inference\nD) http://localhost:11434/\nE) http://localhost:5000/ollama\n","answer":"D"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-08","type":"name","bloom":"understand","source":"research-ai.md §Local vs Cloud SLM trap row","explanation":"After pull, the daemon loads weights from disk and serves requests from localhost. Airplane-mode demos are a common lecture point.","example":"ollama pull phi3:latest   # only this step needs the internet","prompt":"True or false: Ollama requires an internet connection to answer prompts.","answer":"False. Internet is needed only for ollama pull to download the model; inference is fully local."},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-09","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"research-ai.md §Endpoint URL Pitfalls (package confusion)","explanation":"The exam may test which name is the C# package. OllamaSharp = NuGet. ollama = the command-line binary you run to pull, list, or serve models.","example":"dotnet add package OllamaSharp","prompt":"The third-party NuGet package for the .NET Ollama client is ___ ; the CLI binary and daemon is ___ .","answer":"OllamaSharp ; ollama"},{"id":"ai-chat-completion-local-card-10","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"research-ai.md §appsettings.json for Ollama; §Call Ollama via ChatClient (Direct)","explanation":"Keeping URL and model id in config lets you switch SLMs without recompiling. The constructor signature is (Uri, string).","example":"string url = config[\"OllamaUrl\"];\nstring modelId = config[\"ModelId\"];\nIChatClient client = new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(url), modelId);\n","prompt":"Given OllamaUrl and ModelId in appsettings.json, what two values does the OllamaApiClient constructor consume?","answer":"A Uri built from OllamaUrl (\"http://localhost:11434/\") and the ModelId string (e.g. \"phi3:latest\")."}],"source":"slides/SLM.pptx; notes/SLM.docx; research-ai.md §Ollama, §Chat Completion"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models","name":"GitHub Models + Azure OpenAI endpoints","tags":["ai","cloud","auth"],"prose":"Wiring a hosted chat endpoint in .NET reduces to three knobs: endpoint URL,\ncredential object, and model name. GitHub Models uses\n`https://models.github.ai/inference` with a GitHub PAT wrapped in\n`AzureKeyCredential`, plus a vendor-prefixed model id like\n`openai/gpt-4o-mini`. Azure OpenAI uses your resource URL and a deployment\nname. Both reuse the same credential class despite the misleading name.\n","cards":[{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-01","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"What is the GitHub Models inference endpoint URL?","answer":"https://models.github.ai/inference","explanation":"HTTPS, and the `/inference` path is required. Dropping the path breaks routing.","example":"```json\n\"ApiEndpoint\": \"https://models.github.ai/inference\"\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-02","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"Which credential class authenticates GitHub Models calls from the OpenAI SDK?","answer":"`AzureKeyCredential(token)`","explanation":"Despite the `Azure` prefix, this class wraps any bearer token. No `GithubCredential` type exists in the SDK.","example":"```csharp\nnew AzureKeyCredential(config[\"GitHub:Token\"]!)\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-03","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"Which credential type does a GitHub Models `ChatClient` require?","answer":"`AzureKeyCredential(token)`","explanation":"`AzureKeyCredential` is reused for GitHub PATs. The other three are distractors — none exist in this SDK context.","example":"```csharp\nIChatClient chatClient = new ChatClient(\n    model,\n    new AzureKeyCredential(apiKey!),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(endpoint) }\n).AsIChatClient();\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-04","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"Complete the `ChatClient` wiring for GitHub Models: `new ChatClient(model, new ___(apiKey!), new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(endpoint) }).___();`","answer":"`AzureKeyCredential`; `AsIChatClient`","explanation":"`AzureKeyCredential` carries the PAT. `.AsIChatClient()` adapts the OpenAI `ChatClient` to `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`'s `IChatClient` so MAF can consume it.","example":"```csharp\nIChatClient chatClient = new ChatClient(\n    \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    new AzureKeyCredential(token),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(\"https://models.github.ai/inference\") }\n).AsIChatClient();\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-05","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"Which model-id string is correctly formatted for GitHub Models?","answer":"`openai/gpt-4o-mini`","explanation":"GitHub Models routes through vendor-prefixed ids. `openai/` identifies the publisher; the bare name gets rejected.","example":"```json\n\"Model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\"\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-06","type":"name","bloom":"remember","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx","prompt":"Which `appsettings.json` keys store the GitHub Models configuration?","answer":"`GitHub:Token`, `GitHub:ApiEndpoint`, `GitHub:Model`","explanation":"The PAT lives under `GitHub:Token`. Endpoint and model id live alongside it so `config[...]` binding stays tidy.","example":"```json\n{\n  \"GitHub\": {\n    \"Token\": \"PUT-GITHUB-PERSONAL-ACCESS-TOKEN-HERE\",\n    \"ApiEndpoint\": \"https://models.github.ai/inference\",\n    \"Model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\"\n  }\n}\n```\n"},{"id":"ai-cloud-models-card-07","type":"name","bloom":"apply","source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx; slides/CSharp_Meets_AI.pptx","prompt":"You need to differentiate a GitHub Models endpoint from a local Ollama endpoint in code review. Which pair is correct?","answer":"GitHub: `https://models.github.ai/inference`; Ollama: `http://localhost:11434/`","explanation":"GitHub is HTTPS with `/inference`. Ollama is HTTP on port `11434` with no path. Common traps: dropping `/inference`, typoing `1143` for `11434`, or swapping protocols.","example":"```csharp\n// GitHub Models\nnew Uri(\"https://models.github.ai/inference\");\n// Ollama (local)\nnew Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\");\n```\n"}],"source":"notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx; research-ai.md §Call GitHub Models, §Call Azure OpenAI"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli","cards":[{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-01","type":"cloze","tags":["ml-net","automl","naming"],"prompt":"The ML.NET AutoML command-line tool is named {{`mlnet`}} (lowercase, no dot); the framework it targets is written {{`ML.NET`}} (uppercase, dotted).","answer":"mlnet","explanation":"The CLI and the framework have different casing. `mlnet` is installed via `dotnet tool install -g mlnet-win-x64` (swap the suffix for `osx-x64` or `linux-x64`).","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-02","type":"name","tags":["ml-net","automl","cli"],"prompt":"What does this command do? `mlnet regression --dataset taxi-fare-train.csv --label-col 6 --train-time 60 --has-header true`","answer":"Runs AutoML for a regression task on `taxi-fare-train.csv`, predicts the column at index 6, explores …","explanation":"Runs AutoML for a regression task on `taxi-fare-train.csv`, predicts the column at index 6, explores 40+ algorithm/hyperparameter combinations for 60 seconds, and emits a console project wired to the best model. `--has-header true` says the CSV starts with a header row.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-03","type":"cloze","tags":["ml-net","automl","flags"],"prompt":"The `--label-col` flag accepts either a 0-based {{index}} (e.g. `6`) or a column {{name}} (e.g. `FareAmount`).","answer":"index","explanation":"Use the index when the header text is uncertain or missing — passing a name that does not match the CSV header causes silent failure.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-04","type":"name","tags":["ml-net","automl","flags"],"prompt":"Which `mlnet` flag sets the exploration budget, and what are its units?","answer":"`--train-time`, in seconds.","explanation":"`--train-time`, in seconds. A larger value generally surfaces better models, but returns diminish — doubling from 60 to 120 seconds rarely doubles RSquared.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-05","type":"name","tags":["ml-net","automl","output"],"prompt":"After `mlnet regression` finishes, what artifact does it emit?","answer":"A full console project — source files, a `.csproj`, and a `.zip` model — wired …","explanation":"A full console project — source files, a `.csproj`, and a `.zip` model — wired to the winning pipeline. You run it with `dotnet run`. The CLI does not emit a bare model file on its own.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"},{"id":"ml-automl-cli-card-06","type":"cloze","tags":["ml-net","automl","pitfall"],"prompt":"AutoML explores {{40+}} regression variants within the `--train-time` budget and ranks them; the ``top-5`` list is {{not guaranteed to be globally optimal}}.","answer":"40+","explanation":"AutoML searches the algorithm + hyperparameter space it has time to reach. Larger `--train-time` explores more combinations, but the winner is only the best model AutoML happened to try.","example":"\u003c!-- example: Stage 5 enrichment --\u003e"}],"name":"Ml Automl Cli","source":"notes/ML.NET_vscode_automl_SCRIPT.docx; research-mlnet.md §AutoML CLI","prose":"Cards for the Ml Automl Cli topic.","tags":[]}]},{"id":"module-2-distributed-services","name":"Distributed Services & Orchestration","topics":[{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts","name":"gRPC .proto contracts","tags":["grpc","protobuf","contract-first"],"source":"slides/gRPC.pptx; notes/gRPC_EF_SQLite_VSCode_SCRIPT.docx; research-grpc.md","prose":"These cards drill the proto3 syntax you must read and write on the exam — keywords, field-tag rules, and the defaults that trip students up.","cards":[{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"In a `.proto` file, the `{{1}}` keyword declares a gRPC service and each `{{2}}` keyword inside declares one callable method.","answer":"service; rpc","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The generator walks every `rpc` line inside a `service` block to emit one C# method per RPC on both the server base class and the client stub.","example":"service StudentRemote {\n  rpc GetStudentInfo (StudentLookupModel) returns (StudentModel);\n}"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-02","type":"cloze","prompt":"Proto field tags `1` through `{{1}}` encode in one byte; tags `{{2}}` and higher take two bytes.","answer":"15; 16","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Protobuf packs the wire-type and tag number into a varint. Values below 16 fit in the first byte's 4 available tag bits, so frequently-sent fields should live in the 1–15 range.","example":"message Person {\n  int32 id = 1;      // 1-byte tag\n  string bio = 16;   // 2-byte tag\n}"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-03","type":"name","prompt":"What is the default value of an unset `string` field in proto3?","answer":"The empty string \"\".","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Proto3 removed the `null` / `HasField` concept for scalars. The server cannot distinguish 'client sent nothing' from 'client sent an empty string' on a plain `string` field.","example":"message Reply { string result = 1; }  // unset Result is \"\""},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-04","type":"cloze","prompt":"The `{{1}}` keyword in a `message` definition maps to a `List\u003cT\u003e` in the generated C# code.","answer":"repeated","bloom":"understand","explanation":"`repeated` marks a field as a zero-or-more collection. `protoc` emits a `RepeatedField\u003cT\u003e` property that implements `IList\u003cT\u003e`, which is how you iterate or add items in C#.","example":"message StudentList {\n  repeated StudentModel items = 1;\n}"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-05","type":"name","prompt":"You delete the field `string school = 4;` from a deployed `.proto`. Can you safely reuse tag `4` for a new `int32 gradeLevel = 4;`?","answer":"No — reusing a tag number is forbidden. Old clients still sending tag 4 as a string will be misdecoded as the new `int32`.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Field tags are the immutable binary wire identifier. Changing a tag's type without changing its number silently corrupts any already-deployed client. Either pick a fresh tag or mark the old one `reserved`.","example":"message Student {\n  reserved 4;             // protect old tag\n  int32 gradeLevel = 5;   // new field, new tag\n}"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-06","type":"predict","prompt":"Given this proto, what does the generated C# class for `StudentLookupModel` expose, and what is the default value of `StudentId` on a freshly-constructed instance?","lang":"proto","code":"message StudentLookupModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n}\n","answer":"A C# class `StudentLookupModel` with a public `int StudentId { get; set; }` property. A `new StudentLookupModel()` has `StudentId == 0` because proto3 unset `int32` defaults to zero.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`protoc` PascalCases proto field names for C#, so `studentId` becomes `StudentId`. Proto3 scalar defaults are 0 / \"\" / false — there is no null option for plain scalars.","example":"var req = new StudentLookupModel();\n// req.StudentId == 0"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"In a `.csproj`, `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\x.proto\" GrpcServices=\"{{1}}\" /\u003e` generates the abstract base class your service implementation inherits from.","answer":"Server","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The `GrpcServices` attribute controls which half of the contract `protoc` emits. `Server` yields the `ServiceNameBase` class; `Client` yields the `ServiceNameClient` stub; `Both` yields both.","example":"\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-08","type":"name","prompt":"What does `option csharp_namespace = \"GrpcStudentsServer\";` do in a `.proto` file?","answer":"It sets the C# namespace that `protoc` wraps around every generated class for this `.proto`.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Without this option, `protoc` derives the namespace from the `package` directive, which may not match your C# project's conventions. The option lets the proto and C# namespaces diverge.","example":"option csharp_namespace = \"GrpcStudentsServer\";\npackage greet;"},{"id":"grpc-proto-contracts-card-09","type":"predict","prompt":"A client sends this proto message with `studentId` left unset. What does the server see?","lang":"proto","code":"message StudentLookupModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n}\n","answer":"The server reads `request.StudentId == 0`. Proto3 cannot distinguish 'unset' from 'explicit zero' for a plain `int32` — both serialize identically on the wire.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"This is the proto3-no-null trap. If you need to tell 'missing' from 'zero', wrap the field in a singleton `message` or use a `google.protobuf.Int32Value` wrapper, which does carry presence information.","example":"if (request.StudentId == 0) {\n  // could mean unset OR id = 0\n}"}]},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation","name":"gRPC server implementation","tags":["grpc","server","asp-net-core"],"source":"notes/gRPC_EF_SQLite_VSCode_SCRIPT.docx; Labs/W09 gRPC/; research-grpc.md","prose":"A gRPC server inherits from the auto-generated `[Service].[Service]Base` class and overrides one method per `rpc`. Each override takes the request type plus `ServerCallContext` and returns `Task\u003cResponse\u003e`. Services are registered with `AddGrpc()` and routed with `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()`.","cards":[{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"A gRPC service class inherits from `{{StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase}}` — the pattern is `[ServiceName].[ServiceName]{{Base}}`.","answer":"StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase; Base","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`Grpc.Tools` generates the base at build time. Inheriting from it is the only way to get your methods matched to the wire-level service dispatch.","example":"public class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase { … }"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Every gRPC server-side method takes two parameters. Name them in order for a unary call.","answer":"The request message type, then ServerCallContext.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The `ServerCallContext` carries cancellation tokens, deadlines, metadata, and peer info. Omitting it is a compile error because the `override` target requires it.","example":"public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request, ServerCallContext context) { ... }"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"Server-side unary methods return `{{Task\u003cResponse\u003e}}`. Wrap a synchronous value with `{{Task.FromResult}}(value)`.","answer":"Task\u003cResponse\u003e; Task.FromResult","bloom":"apply","explanation":"gRPC methods are always asynchronous on the wire. Even when your implementation is synchronous, you must return a `Task` — `Task.FromResult` wraps the value cheaply.","example":"return Task.FromResult(new StudentModel { StudentId = 3 });"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"Which two calls register gRPC services in `Program.cs`?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddGrpc()` plus `app.MapGrpcService\u003cYourService\u003e()`.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`AddGrpc` registers framework types (serialization, interceptors, resilience). `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e` wires routing so HTTP/2 requests reach your class.","example":"builder.Services.AddGrpc(); … app.MapGrpcService\u003cStudentsService\u003e();"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Forgetting the `{{override}}` keyword on a method shadows the base-class method. The server compiles, but client calls get back `RpcException: {{UNIMPLEMENTED}}`.","answer":"override; UNIMPLEMENTED","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Without `override`, your method is unrelated to the base class virtual method. The framework dispatches to the base's default, which throws UNIMPLEMENTED.","example":"public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(... — the override keyword is non-optional."},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"How does a server-streaming method signature differ from a unary method?","answer":"It returns `Task` (not `Task\u003cT\u003e`) and takes `IServerStreamWriter\u003cT\u003e` as a third parameter.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Streaming methods write each message via `responseStream.WriteAsync(...)` and return when the loop finishes. There is no single response object, so no `Task\u003cT\u003e` return.","example":"public override async Task RetrieveAllStudents(Empty r, IServerStreamWriter\u003cStudentModel\u003e stream, ServerCallContext ctx) { … }"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"To inject an EF Core DbContext into a gRPC service, register it with `{{builder.Services.AddDbContext}}\u003cT\u003e` in `Program.cs`, then accept it in the service constructor.","answer":"builder.Services.AddDbContext","bloom":"apply","explanation":"gRPC services use standard ASP.NET Core DI. Any service registered in the container can be constructor-injected, and gRPC services are instantiated per-request by default.","example":"public StudentsService(SchoolDbContext context) =\u003e _context = context;"},{"id":"grpc-server-implementation-card-08","type":"name","prompt":"What does the `ServerCallContext` parameter carry that you might use inside an override?","answer":"Cancellation tokens, deadlines, request metadata, and peer (client) info.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Use `context.CancellationToken` to short-circuit expensive work if the client disconnects. `context.Deadline` tells you when the client will time out. `context.RequestHeaders` carries metadata like auth tokens.","example":"if (context.CancellationToken.IsCancellationRequested) return Task.FromResult(new Reply { IsOk = false });"}]},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption","name":"gRPC client consumption","tags":["grpc","client","di","asp-net-core"],"source":"notes/gRPC_EF_SQLite_VSCode_SCRIPT.docx; Labs/W09 gRPC/; research-grpc.md","prose":"A gRPC client project shares the `.proto` file with the server but sets `GrpcServices=\"Client\"` in its `.csproj`. Clients are constructed from a long-lived `GrpcChannel.ForAddress(url)` or registered via `AddGrpcClient\u003cT\u003e()` for DI. Blazor pages awaiting gRPC calls must use `@rendermode InteractiveServer`.","cards":[{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"To generate only the client-side stub from a shared `.proto`, the `.csproj` entry is `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"…\" GrpcServices=\"{{Client}}\" /\u003e`.","answer":"Client","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`GrpcServices` chooses which code `Grpc.Tools` emits. `Server` produces the base class; `Client` produces the stub; `Both` produces both and is rarely needed.","example":"\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Client\" /\u003e"},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which method constructs a long-lived gRPC connection given a URL?","answer":"GrpcChannel.ForAddress(url)","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The channel holds the HTTP/2 connection. Creating one is expensive; reuse across many client stubs. Client stubs themselves are cheap throwaway objects bound to a channel.","example":"using var channel = GrpcChannel.ForAddress(\"http://localhost:5099\");"},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"For DI-based client registration in ASP.NET Core, use `builder.Services.{{AddGrpcClient}}\u003cStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003e(opts =\u003e opts.Address = new Uri(\"http://localhost:5099\"))` after adding the {{Grpc.Net.ClientFactory}} NuGet package.","answer":"AddGrpcClient; Grpc.Net.ClientFactory","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`AddGrpcClient` wires the client into the DI container with channel pooling, resilience handlers, and OpenTelemetry. Plain `new GrpcChannel` in Program.cs loses all those benefits.","example":"builder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003e(o =\u003e o.Address = new Uri(\"http://backend\"));"},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"What render mode must a Blazor page use so it can `await` a gRPC client call inside `OnInitializedAsync`?","answer":"`@rendermode InteractiveServer` (or `InteractiveWebAssembly` / `InteractiveAuto`).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Static server rendering completes before asynchronous work resolves. An interactive mode keeps the component alive and re-renders when the awaited task finishes.","example":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _g"},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"gRPC client methods are exposed in two forms: a blocking `{{Xxx}}(...)` and an asynchronous `{{XxxAsync}}(...)` that returns a `Task\u003cT\u003e` you await.","answer":"Xxx; XxxAsync","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Protocol Buffers generate both forms. The Async form is what you almost always call from managed code — the blocking form can deadlock in sync contexts.","example":"var reply = await client.GetStudentInfoAsync(request); // not client.GetStudentInfo(request)"},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"A Blazor client gets `ConnectionRefused` every time it calls the gRPC server. What is the first thing to check?","answer":"That the client's Uri matches the server's `launchSettings.json` applicationUrl (including port and http vs https).","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Port drift between server launch profile and client config is the single most common cause. Aspire service discovery via `http://backend/` eliminates this class of bug entirely.","example":"Server listens on https://localhost:7001. Client Uri must be exactly that URL — not http://localhost:5001."},{"id":"grpc-client-consumption-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"Once registered with `AddGrpcClient\u003cT\u003e()`, inject the stub anywhere with `{{@inject}}` (Razor) or constructor injection (plain C# services).","answer":"@inject","bloom":"apply","explanation":"DI-registered gRPC clients are transient by default. Each request gets a fresh stub bound to a pooled channel.","example":"@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpcClient"}]},{"id":"aspire-apphost","name":".NET Aspire AppHost","tags":["aspire","orchestration","apphost"],"source":"notes/aspire_SCRIPT.docx; Labs/W09 gRPC/; research-aspire.md","prose":"The Aspire AppHost is a separate project whose `Program.cs` builds a `DistributedApplication`. Four calls do the work: `CreateBuilder`, `AddProject\u003cProjects.X\u003e(name)`, `.WithReference(other)` for config injection, and `.WaitFor(other)` for startup ordering.","cards":[{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The Aspire orchestrator builder is created with `DistributedApplication.{{CreateBuilder}}(args)`, and the app runs with `builder.Build().{{Run}}()`.","answer":"CreateBuilder; Run","bloom":"remember","explanation":"AppHost `Program.cs` follows the same pattern as any other .NET host: builder → configure → build → run. The only difference is the type is `DistributedApplication`, not `WebApplication`.","example":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args); … builder.Build().Run();"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"What does `builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.StudentsGrpcApi\u003e(\"backend\")` do?","answer":"Registers the StudentsGrpcApi project as a service under the logical name \"backend\".","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Logical names (e.g. \"backend\") become the service-discovery identity. Consumers reach the service via `http://backend/` instead of a hardcoded localhost URL.","example":"var backend = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.StudentsGrpcApi\u003e(\"backend\");"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"To make the frontend aware of the backend's URL, call `.{{WithReference}}(backend)`. To delay the frontend's startup until the backend is healthy, also call `.{{WaitFor}}(backend)`.","answer":"WithReference; WaitFor","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`WithReference` injects env-vars with connection info. `WaitFor` adds a health-gated startup order. Pair them when the consumer cannot recover from a cold dependency.","example":"builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Frontend\u003e(\"frontend\").WithReference(backend).WaitFor(backend);"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"In an AppHost, how do you add a containerized SQL Server resource with one database called `cms`?","answer":"`builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\").AddDatabase(\"cms\")`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`AddSqlServer(\"sql\")` registers the server resource; `.AddDatabase(\"cms\")` chains a named database onto it. The service then `WithReference`s that database and gets `ConnectionStrings__cms` injected automatically.","example":"var cms = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\").AddDatabase(\"cms\"); api.WithReference(cms);"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Services reach each other via their logical name — `http://{{backend}}/` resolves to the actual host:port at runtime. This is called {{service discovery}}.","answer":"backend; service discovery","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Aspire's service-discovery protocol handler intercepts URLs whose host matches a registered logical name and swaps in the real address. This keeps client code identical across local dev, Docker, and cloud.","example":"In the Blazor app: `public const string ApiBaseUrl = \"http://backend/\";`"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Where does `AddServiceDefaults()` belong — in the AppHost's `Program.cs`, or in each service's `Program.cs`?","answer":"In each service's Program.cs, never in the AppHost's.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"AppHost is the orchestrator — it shouldn't register service-side concerns like OpenTelemetry or health checks on itself. Putting `AddServiceDefaults` in AppHost breaks boot.","example":"Service project: builder.AddServiceDefaults();  // in WebApi/Program.cs, NOT AppHost/Program.cs"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"The AppHost project must have a `\u003cProjectReference\u003e` to each service project — run `{{dotnet add reference}}` from the AppHost `.csproj` to each service.","answer":"dotnet add reference","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The `Projects.X` namespace used in `AddProject\u003cProjects.X\u003e` is generated from referenced projects. Without the reference, the type doesn't exist and the AppHost won't compile.","example":"dotnet add ./Cms.AppHost reference ./Cms.WebApi/Cms.WebApi.csproj"},{"id":"aspire-apphost-card-08","type":"name","prompt":"Which command runs the whole Aspire stack during development?","answer":"`dotnet watch` (or `dotnet run`) from the AppHost project directory.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The AppHost owns orchestration, so running it starts every declared service, database, and container. Other projects are not launched directly during dev.","example":"cd Cms.AppHost && dotnet watch"}]},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults","name":".NET Aspire ServiceDefaults","tags":["aspire","observability","health-checks"],"source":"notes/aspire_SCRIPT.docx; research-aspire.md","prose":"Every Aspire service calls `builder.AddServiceDefaults()` at configure time and `app.MapDefaultEndpoints()` at map time. Together they install service discovery, OpenTelemetry, `/health` + `/alive` endpoints, and HttpClient resilience.","cards":[{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"Every Aspire service's `Program.cs` calls `builder.{{AddServiceDefaults}}()` and `app.{{MapDefaultEndpoints}}()`.","answer":"AddServiceDefaults; MapDefaultEndpoints","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`AddServiceDefaults` registers services (discovery, OTel, health checks, resilience). `MapDefaultEndpoints` exposes the HTTP endpoints (`/health`, `/alive`). Both are required.","example":"builder.AddServiceDefaults(); … app.MapDefaultEndpoints();"},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"What four capabilities does `AddServiceDefaults()` install?","answer":"Service discovery, OpenTelemetry, default health checks, HttpClient resilience.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"These are the four Aspire primitives that every service is expected to have. Registering them manually in each service would produce dozens of lines; the extension consolidates them.","example":"ConfigureOpenTelemetry + AddDefaultHealthChecks + AddServiceDiscovery + ConfigureHttpClientDefaults(AddStandardResilienceHandler)"},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"Aspire exposes two health endpoints: `{{/health}}` for readiness (all checks pass) and `{{/alive}}` for liveness (checks tagged \"live\" only).","answer":"/health; /alive","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Readiness gates traffic routing; liveness gates container restarts. Kubernetes maps them to `readinessProbe` and `livenessProbe` respectively.","example":"curl http://backend/health → 200 when ready; curl http://backend/alive → 200 when the process is alive."},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"Which `.csproj` change connects a service to its ServiceDefaults library?","answer":"A `\u003cProjectReference\u003e` to the ServiceDefaults project (add via `dotnet add reference`).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"ServiceDefaults is a separate class library project in the solution. Each service project references it so the `AddServiceDefaults` extension method is available.","example":"dotnet add ./Cms.WebApi reference ./Cms.ServiceDefaults/Cms.ServiceDefaults.csproj"},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"`AddServiceDefaults()` belongs in {{each service's}} `Program.cs`, NOT in the {{AppHost's}} `Program.cs`.","answer":"each service's; AppHost's","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"AppHost is the orchestrator — it shouldn't register service-side concerns. Putting `AddServiceDefaults` there makes the orchestrator try to configure telemetry on itself and breaks boot.","example":"AppHost/Program.cs: DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder + AddProject calls only. WebApi/Program.cs: AddServiceDefaults here."},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"A new service appears red in the Aspire Dashboard. What is the single most likely cause?","answer":"The service is missing `builder.AddServiceDefaults()` so it has no `/health` endpoint.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"The dashboard polls `/health` for every registered project. Without default health checks, the endpoint returns 404 and the dashboard flags it red.","example":"Add builder.AddServiceDefaults(); and app.MapDefaultEndpoints(); to fix."},{"id":"aspire-service-defaults-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"`AddServiceDefaults` also configures HttpClientFactory: every `HttpClient` created through DI inherits {{AddStandardResilienceHandler}} and {{AddServiceDiscovery}}.","answer":"AddStandardResilienceHandler; AddServiceDiscovery","bloom":"understand","explanation":"This is why `HttpClient` calls to `http://backend/` work without per-client setup. The factory applies both resilience policies and name resolution globally.","example":"builder.Services.ConfigureHttpClientDefaults(http =\u003e { http.AddStandardResilienceHandler(); http.AddServiceDiscovery(); });"}]},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources","name":".NET Aspire orchestrated resources","tags":["aspire","sql-server","redis","orchestration"],"source":"notes/aspire_SCRIPT.docx; research-aspire.md","prose":"AppHost declares infrastructure resources with `AddSqlServer`, `AddRedis`, `AddPostgres`, etc. under logical names. `.WithReference(resource)` injects the resource's connection info into consuming services as environment variables. Services consume it via typed helpers like `AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cT\u003e(name)`.","cards":[{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"To register a SQL Server container with one database called `cms`: `builder.{{AddSqlServer}}(\"sql\").{{AddDatabase}}(\"cms\")`.","answer":"AddSqlServer; AddDatabase","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`AddSqlServer` registers the server resource under a logical name. `.AddDatabase` chains a named database onto it. The returned resource handle is what services `WithReference` to.","example":"var db = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\").AddDatabase(\"cms\");"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"How does a consuming service receive the connection string for an Aspire-managed SQL Server database named `cms`?","answer":"Aspire injects `ConnectionStrings__cms` as an environment variable when the service process launches.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The double-underscore is .NET's hierarchical-config convention — `ConnectionStrings__cms` equals `builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString(\"cms\")`. Aspire writes it; the service reads it.","example":"builder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cCmsDbContext\u003e(\"cms\"); // reads ConnectionStrings__cms automatically"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"A consuming service only receives a resource's connection info if the AppHost chains `.{{WithReference}}(resource)` onto `AddProject\u003c\u003e(...)`.","answer":"WithReference","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`AddProject` alone launches the service but shares no resource info. `WithReference` is the bridge that translates resource declarations into env-vars on the consumer.","example":"builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\").WithReference(db);"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"In a service's `Program.cs`, how do you wire EF Core to an Aspire-managed SQL Server database named `cms`?","answer":"`builder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cCmsDbContext\u003e(\"cms\")`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"This helper ships in `Aspire.Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer`. It reads `ConnectionStrings__cms` automatically and configures `DbContextOptions`.","example":"builder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cCmsDbContext\u003e(\"cms\"); // that's the only setup needed"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-05","type":"name","prompt":"How do you register a Redis cache resource in the AppHost?","answer":"`var cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\");`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"No `.AddDatabase` chain — Redis is a single key-value store per resource. Services consume it with `builder.AddRedisDistributedCache(\"cache\")`.","example":"AppHost: var cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\"); api.WithReference(cache);\nService: builder.AddRedisDistributedCache(\"cache\");"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-06","type":"cloze","prompt":"To pass an arbitrary env-var from AppHost to one specific service, use `.{{WithEnvironment}}(key, value)`.","answer":"WithEnvironment","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Scoped to that one project's process. Prefer this over leaking values globally. The service reads it via `IConfiguration` or `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable`.","example":"api.WithEnvironment(\"FeatureFlags__NewCheckout\", \"true\");"},{"id":"aspire-orchestrated-resources-card-07","type":"name","prompt":"Your service throws \"connection string not found\" at runtime even though AppHost has `AddSqlServer(\"sql\").AddDatabase(\"cms\")`. What's the most likely omission?","answer":"The consuming service's `AddProject\u003c\u003e(...)` call is missing `.WithReference(db)`.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Declaring the resource is not enough. Without `WithReference`, Aspire never injects the connection string into the target service's environment.","example":"builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\").WithReference(db).WaitFor(db);"}]}]},{"id":"module-3-performance-caching","name":"Performance & Caching","topics":[{"id":"cache-abstractions","name":"IMemoryCache vs IDistributedCache","tags":["cache","architecture"],"source":"notes/DataCache_SCRIPT.docx; research-cache.md §1-2","prose":"`IMemoryCache` lives per-process and fails in web farms — each server holds its own copy. `IDistributedCache` lives across the network (Redis is the canonical backend) and is the only choice for load-balanced deployments.","cards":[{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"`{{IMemoryCache}}` stores entries in-process; `{{IDistributedCache}}` stores entries across the network, typically in Redis.","answer":"IMemoryCache; IDistributedCache","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The interface you register decides where entries live. In-process is microseconds-fast but per-server. Distributed is milliseconds-fast but shared across every app instance.","example":"builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();  // vs  builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(...)"},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Why does `IMemoryCache` produce inconsistent data in a load-balanced web farm?","answer":"Each server instance holds its own separate cache — writes on Server A are invisible to Server B.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"In-process memory is not shared across app instances. Request 1 on Server A caches X; Request 2 on Server B finds no cache and refetches from DB. Users see different data depending on routing.","example":"Two pods behind a k8s service → two separate IMemoryCache instances → cache writes diverge."},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"Two fixes for `IMemoryCache` in a multi-server deployment are: switch to `{{IDistributedCache}}` (e.g. Redis) or configure {{sticky sessions}} to route each client to the same server.","answer":"IDistributedCache; sticky sessions","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Redis is the clean fix — one cache, all servers see it. Sticky sessions are the lazy fix — they work until the pinned server restarts or becomes unbalanced.","example":"k8s sessionAffinity: ClientIP gives sticky sessions; Redis gives a proper shared cache."},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"When is `IMemoryCache` still appropriate?","answer":"Per-process, ephemeral caching — single-server dev environments, precomputed lookup tables inside one app instance, data that does not need to survive a restart.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"For values that only need to be visible within one process, IMemoryCache wins on latency (microseconds) and simplicity (no container, no serialization). The rule: cross-request-cross-server = distributed; within-process = memory.","example":"Parsing appsettings.json once on boot and reusing the parsed object — IMemoryCache."},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Does `IMemoryCache` data survive an app restart? {{No}}. Does Redis-backed `IDistributedCache` survive? {{Yes}} (when Redis has AOF or RDB persistence enabled).","answer":"No; Yes","bloom":"remember","explanation":"IMemoryCache is RAM inside the app process — the restart wipes it. Redis runs as a separate process/container with configurable persistence, so it can survive app restarts and redeployments.","example":"A pod redeployment wipes IMemoryCache; the Redis container keeps serving entries across the swap."},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Which one-liner registers an in-memory cache in `Program.cs`?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`AddMemoryCache` wires `IMemoryCache` into DI. No options required for a basic setup.","example":"builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();"},{"id":"cache-abstractions-card-07","type":"name","prompt":"Which one-liner registers a Redis-backed distributed cache in `Program.cs`?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(opts =\u003e opts.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\");`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The helper reads from `Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.StackExchangeRedis` and registers `IDistributedCache`. Any service can then inject `IDistributedCache`.","example":"builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\");"}]},{"id":"cache-expiration","name":"Cache expiration — Absolute, Sliding, Priority","tags":["cache","ttl","expiration"],"source":"notes/DataCache_SCRIPT.docx; research-cache.md §2, §4","prose":"`MemoryCacheEntryOptions` exposes `AbsoluteExpiration` (hard deadline), `SlidingExpiration` (idle timeout that resets on access), and `Priority` (eviction order under memory pressure). Combining absolute + sliding gives a capped-and-refreshing window.","cards":[{"id":"cache-expiration-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"`AbsoluteExpiration` is a {{hard}} deadline; `SlidingExpiration` resets on each {{access}}.","answer":"hard; access","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Absolute kills the entry at a wall-clock moment regardless of traffic. Sliding keeps hot entries alive while aging out idle ones.","example":"Absolute: expires at 10:00 AM. Sliding: expires 5 minutes after last read/write."},{"id":"cache-expiration-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"When `AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = 50s` and `SlidingExpiration = 20s` are BOTH set and the entry is accessed at t=15s, when does it expire?","answer":"At t=50s, because Absolute is a hard ceiling that wins over the reset Sliding window.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Sliding resets the idle timer to run until t=35s when the access happens at t=15s. Absolute deadline at t=50s is still binding and farther out, so Absolute fires first. Without the access, the entry would have expired at t=20s from sliding.","example":"Access at 15s → sliding resets to 35s deadline → absolute 50s deadline fires first → entry dies at 50s."},{"id":"cache-expiration-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"`CacheItemPriority` controls {{eviction order}} under memory pressure — NOT the entry's expiration time.","answer":"eviction order","bloom":"understand","explanation":"A Low-priority entry with a 1-hour Absolute still lives 1 hour unless memory pressure forces eviction. A High-priority entry with a 30-second Absolute still expires at 30 seconds.","example":"Priority = Low does NOT mean 'expires sooner.' It means 'dropped first when the cache is over its size limit.'"},{"id":"cache-expiration-card-04","type":"cloze","prompt":"The four `CacheItemPriority` levels are `{{NeverRemove}}`, `{{High}}`, `{{Normal}}`, and `{{Low}}`.","answer":"NeverRemove; High; Normal; Low","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`NeverRemove` excludes an entry from automatic eviction (only explicit `Remove` or time-based expiration can free it). Use sparingly — it converts the cache into persistent state.","example":"_cache.Set(\"config\", cfg, new MemoryCacheEntryOptions { Priority = CacheItemPriority.NeverRemove });"},{"id":"cache-expiration-card-05","type":"name","prompt":"Which `MemoryCacheEntryOptions` setting is best for session-like data that should time out when the user goes idle?","answer":"`SlidingExpiration`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Sliding resets on each access, so active users stay in cache and idle ones age out. Pair with a loose Absolute ceiling if you want a hard refresh guarantee.","example":"new MemoryCacheEntryOptions { SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(15) };"},{"id":"cache-expiration-card-06","type":"cloze","prompt":"On `IDistributedCache`, the options type is `{{DistributedCacheEntryOptions}}` and you use the fluent setters `{{SetAbsoluteExpiration}}` and `{{SetSlidingExpiration}}`.","answer":"DistributedCacheEntryOptions; SetAbsoluteExpiration; SetSlidingExpiration","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The shape differs between IMemoryCache (property-bag) and IDistributedCache (fluent). Semantics are identical — absolute is a hard deadline; sliding resets on access.","example":"new DistributedCacheEntryOptions().SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1)).SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30));"}]},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern","name":"Cache-aside pattern","tags":["cache","pattern","getorset","invalidation"],"source":"notes/DataCache_SCRIPT.docx; notes/redis_SCRIPT.docx; research-cache.md §3","prose":"Cache-aside: check cache, on miss fetch from source, store result, return. `GetOrCreateAsync` on `IMemoryCache` and `GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` extension on `IDistributedCache` give a one-line form. Writers must invalidate affected keys via `Remove(key)`.","cards":[{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The three steps of cache-aside are: (1) {{look up}} in the cache, (2) on {{hit}} return cached, (3) on {{miss}} fetch, store, return.","answer":"look up; hit; miss","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The same sequence at every call site: check, hit/miss branch, store-and-return on miss. Wrappers like GetOrCreateAsync collapse this into one call.","example":"if (!cache.TryGetValue(k, out v)) { v = fetch(); cache.Set(k, v, opts); } return v;"},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which single `IMemoryCache` method checks the cache, runs a factory on miss, stores the result, and returns it?","answer":"`GetOrCreateAsync` (or `GetOrCreate` for synchronous factories).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The factory runs only on cache miss. This is the idiomatic .NET helper — prefer it over hand-rolled TryGetValue + Set pairs for readability.","example":"var p = await cache.GetOrCreateAsync(\"key\", entry =\u003e { entry.AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5); return FetchAsync(); });"},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"`IDistributedCache` works in raw {{byte arrays}}, so consumers typically wrap it with extension methods that serialize to {{JSON}}.","answer":"byte arrays; JSON","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The interface has Get/Set on byte[]. A JSON extension (SetAsync\u003cT\u003e, TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e, GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e) hides serialization and matches the IMemoryCache ergonomics.","example":"bytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(JsonSerializer.Serialize(value));"},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"After an `AddGame` write to the DB, what must you call on the cache to prevent stale reads?","answer":"`_cache.Remove(key)` for every affected cached key.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Cache-aside doesn't know when the source changes. The writer is responsible for invalidating affected keys after SaveChangesAsync — otherwise reads serve stale data until the TTL fires.","example":"await _db.SaveChangesAsync(); _cache.Remove(\"games\"); _cache.Remove($\"games:country:{game.Country}\");"},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"`TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e` takes an `{{out}}` parameter: `if (cache.TryGetValue\u003cProduct\u003e(\"key\", out var product)) { ... }`.","answer":"out","bloom":"apply","explanation":"TryGetValue returns bool; the value is set via the out parameter. `if (cache.TryGetValue(\"key\", product))` is wrong — the compiler requires `out var`.","example":"if (cache.TryGetValue\u003cProduct\u003e(\"key\", out var product)) return product!;"},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Why does JSON-round-tripping through `IDistributedCache` lose polymorphic type information by default?","answer":"System.Text.Json omits the runtime type — deserializing to a base type strips derived-type properties.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"A List\u003cDog\u003e : Animal cached as JSON and read back as List\u003cAnimal\u003e keeps only Animal properties. Fix: cache the concrete type, use a discriminator property, or enable TypeInfoResolver settings.","example":"Cache: new List\u003cDog\u003e{...} → JSON → read as List\u003cAnimal\u003e → breeds lost. Fix: keep the concrete type explicit in the cache signature."},{"id":"cache-aside-pattern-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"The helper `GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` defaults, in the course's example, to `{{SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1))}}` combined with `{{SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30))}}`.","answer":"SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1)); SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30))","bloom":"remember","explanation":"A 1-hour hard ceiling with a 30-minute idle window — sensible defaults for most read-heavy data. Override with your own `DistributedCacheEntryOptions` when finer control is needed.","example":"opts ??= new DistributedCacheEntryOptions().SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1)).SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30));"}]},{"id":"redis-configuration","name":"Redis configuration — Docker, StackExchange.Redis","tags":["redis","docker","stackexchange-redis"],"source":"slides/redis.pptx; notes/redis_SCRIPT.docx; research-cache.md §6","prose":"Start Redis with `docker run --name redis -d -p 6379:6379 redis`. Wire it to ASP.NET Core with `builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(opts =\u003e opts.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\")` after adding the `Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.StackExchangeRedis` NuGet package.","cards":[{"id":"redis-configuration-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"Redis's default port is {{6379}}. The conventional Docker invocation is `docker run --name redis -d -p {{6379}}:{{6379}} redis`.","answer":"6379; 6379; 6379","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Every Redis example in the course assumes 6379. `-d` runs detached; `-p host:container` maps the port; `redis` is the official Docker Hub image.","example":"docker run --name redis -d -p 6379:6379 redis"},{"id":"redis-configuration-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which NuGet package provides the `AddStackExchangeRedisCache` extension?","answer":"`Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.StackExchangeRedis`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Without this package, the extension method doesn't compile. `StackExchange.Redis` is the underlying client library; the `Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.*` package wraps it for `IDistributedCache`.","example":"dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.StackExchangeRedis"},{"id":"redis-configuration-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"In the Redis CLI, `{{SETEX}} destination 10 \"Tokyo\"` sets the key with a {{10-second}} expiration.","answer":"SETEX; 10-second","bloom":"remember","explanation":"SETEX = SET + EXpiration (seconds). Sub-second precision needs PSETEX, which takes milliseconds.","example":"SETEX greeting 60 \"hello for a minute\""},{"id":"redis-configuration-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"What does `AbortOnConnectFail = true` do when Redis is unreachable at startup?","answer":"It causes the app to fail fast at startup instead of silently running with a no-op cache.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"In production you want the orchestrator to notice and restart the pod. `false` (the default) silently retries in the background — fine for dev, hazardous for prod.","example":"new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions { AbortOnConnectFail = true, EndPoints = { \"localhost:6379\" } };"},{"id":"redis-configuration-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Under .NET Aspire, you skip the connection string and use `builder.{{AddRedisDistributedCache}}(\"cache\")` in the service's `Program.cs`; AppHost declares the resource with `builder.{{AddRedis}}(\"cache\")`.","answer":"AddRedisDistributedCache; AddRedis","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Aspire registers the Redis container resource and injects the connection string via environment variables. The typed helper reads the injected string automatically — no `opts.Configuration` literal needed.","example":"AppHost: var cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\"); api.WithReference(cache);\nApi: builder.AddRedisDistributedCache(\"cache\");"},{"id":"redis-configuration-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Name five Redis data structures.","answer":"String, Hash, List, Set, Sorted Set.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Recognition-level only — `IDistributedCache` just does byte-keyed `Get`/`Set`, which maps to the String type. The other types appear in Redis CLI usage and Redis-native C# clients.","example":"SET user:1 \"Alice\"  | HSET user:1 name Alice age 30  |  LPUSH feed p1 p2  |  SADD tags x y  |  ZADD board 100 alice"}]},{"id":"cache-tag-helper","name":"Cache Tag Helper","tags":["cache","razor","tag-helper"],"source":"notes/Cache_Tag_Helper_SCRIPT.docx; research-cache.md §5","prose":"`\u003ccache\u003e` is the built-in Razor Tag Helper for fragment caching. Attributes `expires-after`, `expires-on`, `expires-sliding` control TTL; `vary-by-user`, `vary-by-route`, `vary-by-query`, `vary-by-cookie`, `vary-by-header`, `vary-by` create per-dimension cache keys. Backs onto `IMemoryCache`, so the web-farm problem applies.","cards":[{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"`\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\u003e…\u003c/cache\u003e` caches the enclosed fragment for {{10}} minutes as an {{absolute}} TTL.","answer":"10; absolute","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`expires-after` is absolute-from-now. Use `expires-sliding` for a reset-on-access window, `expires-on` for a specific wall-clock deadline.","example":"\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e@DateTime.Now\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which `vary-by-*` attribute gives each logged-in user their own cached fragment?","answer":"`vary-by-user=\"true\"`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Without vary-by-user, the first visitor's personalized content leaks to every subsequent viewer until the TTL fires. `vary-by-user` keys the cache by authenticated identity.","example":"\u003ccache vary-by-user=\"true\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eHello, @User.Identity?.Name\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"`\u003ccache\u003e` uses `{{IMemoryCache}}` under the hood, so it has the same {{web-farm}} problem as raw in-memory caching.","answer":"IMemoryCache; web-farm","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Each server caches its own rendered HTML. Users routed round-robin across servers see diverging cached content. Workarounds: sticky sessions, short TTLs, or output caching middleware / CDN.","example":"Three pods → three separate \u003ccache\u003e fragments → same URL, three different HTML outputs depending on routing."},{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"List three `vary-by-*` attributes beyond `vary-by-user`.","answer":"`vary-by-route`, `vary-by-query`, `vary-by-cookie`, `vary-by-header` (any three).","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Each varies the cache key by a different request dimension. Combine freely — e.g. `vary-by-user + vary-by-route` produces one fragment per (user, route).","example":"\u003ccache vary-by-user=\"true\" vary-by-route=\"id\" expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5)\"\u003e...\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"To disable a `\u003ccache\u003e` block without deleting the markup, set `{{enabled}}=\"false\"` on the element.","answer":"enabled","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The `enabled` attribute short-circuits the caching behavior — the fragment re-renders on every request. Useful for toggling caching behind a feature flag.","example":"\u003ccache enabled=\"@cachingEnabled\" expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5)\"\u003e…\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"id":"cache-tag-helper-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"You want to cache a product detail view per user AND per product id, with a 10-minute absolute ceiling and a 2-minute sliding window. Write the tag.","answer":"`\u003ccache vary-by-user=\"true\" vary-by-route=\"id\" expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\" expires-sliding=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)\"\u003e…\u003c/cache\u003e`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Combine vary-by dimensions and both expiration modes on one tag. Sliding keeps hot fragments alive; absolute guarantees a refresh within the ceiling.","example":"Same as answer."}]},{"id":"taghelper-authoring","name":"Tag Helper authoring","tags":["tag-helper","razor","asp-net-core"],"source":"notes/TagHelpers_SCRIPT.docx; research-taghelpers-blazor.md","prose":"A custom Tag Helper inherits from `TagHelper`, is decorated with `[HtmlTargetElement(\"tag-name\")]`, and overrides `ProcessAsync(context, output)` (or `Process` for sync bodies). PascalCase C# properties bind to kebab-case HTML attributes.","cards":[{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"A custom Tag Helper inherits from the `{{TagHelper}}` base class and is decorated with `[{{HtmlTargetElement}}(\"tag-name\")]`.","answer":"TagHelper; HtmlTargetElement","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Both pieces are non-optional. Without the base class, the framework won't recognize the type. Without the attribute, Razor has no tag binding.","example":"[HtmlTargetElement(\"toon\")] public class ToonTagHelper : TagHelper { … }"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which override do you use when the Tag Helper body performs async I/O?","answer":"`ProcessAsync(TagHelperContext, TagHelperOutput)`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Overriding `Process` and calling `.Result` or `Task.Run` blocks the render thread and can deadlock. `ProcessAsync` lets the framework await without blocking.","example":"public override async Task ProcessAsync(TagHelperContext context, TagHelperOutput output) { var data = await FetchAsync(); … }"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"A C# property named `{{FontFamily}}` binds to the HTML attribute `{{font-family}}` — PascalCase → kebab-case is the Razor convention.","answer":"FontFamily; font-family","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The mapping is automatic, not configurable. `ForegroundColor` becomes `foreground-color`; `DataTestId` becomes `data-test-id`. Never use underscores in the HTML attribute.","example":"public string? FontFamily { get; set; }  →  \u003ctoon font-family=\"arial\"\u003e"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"Which `TagHelperOutput` call replaces the rendered tag's name?","answer":"`output.TagName = \"div\"` (set to `null` to suppress the element entirely).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`TagName` is the rendered-element name. Setting `null` renders only the inner content without wrapping tag — useful for conditional wrappers.","example":"output.TagName = \"span\";  // \u003cmy-tag\u003e → \u003cspan\u003e"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"`output.Content.{{SetHtmlContent}}(\"\u003cp\u003eHi\u003c/p\u003e\")` replaces the inner content, while `output.Content.{{AppendHtmlContent}}(\"\u003cp\u003eMore\u003c/p\u003e\")` preserves the existing inner content.","answer":"SetHtmlContent; AppendHtmlContent","bloom":"apply","explanation":"SetHtmlContent wipes what the page author wrote between the open and close tags. AppendHtmlContent keeps it and adds after.","example":"output.Content.AppendHtmlContent(\"\u003cp\u003eFooter\u003c/p\u003e\");  // keeps original inner"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"How do you bind a Tag Helper to an existing `\u003cdiv\u003e` only when a specific attribute is present?","answer":"`[HtmlTargetElement(\"div\", Attributes = \"toonie\")]`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The Attributes selector restricts binding to elements carrying the named attribute. You can stack multiple [HtmlTargetElement] attributes on one class to bind several patterns.","example":"[HtmlTargetElement(\"div\", Attributes = \"toonie\")] public class DivToonTagHelper : TagHelper { … }"},{"id":"taghelper-authoring-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"Use `output.{{SuppressOutput}}()` to render nothing at all from a Tag Helper — handy when a condition says the element should not appear.","answer":"SuppressOutput","bloom":"apply","explanation":"SuppressOutput removes both the wrapping tag and its content from the rendered HTML. A feature-flag helper often does this when the flag is off.","example":"if (!_flags.IsEnabled(Flag!)) output.SuppressOutput();"}]},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration","name":"Tag Helper output + _ViewImports registration","tags":["tag-helper","razor","view-imports"],"source":"notes/TagHelpers_SCRIPT.docx; research-taghelpers-blazor.md","prose":"Tag Helpers are registered globally in `_ViewImports.cshtml` via `@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName`. In the helper's `Process`/`ProcessAsync`, the `TagHelperOutput` exposes `TagName`, `Content`, `PreContent`, `PostContent`, `Attributes`, and `SuppressOutput`.","cards":[{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"Tag Helpers are registered in `{{_ViewImports.cshtml}}` with the directive `@addTagHelper *, {{AssemblyName}}`.","answer":"_ViewImports.cshtml; AssemblyName","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The `*` glob imports every Tag Helper in the assembly. Swap `*` for a fully qualified type name when you want to register only one.","example":"@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n@addTagHelper *, MyApp"},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Where should you register a Tag Helper assembly — in each .cshtml file, or in `_ViewImports.cshtml`?","answer":"In `_ViewImports.cshtml`. Individual .cshtml files inherit the registrations.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Registration is hierarchical — `_ViewImports.cshtml` in a subdirectory adds to the registrations from ancestor directories. Per-page registration is not the convention.","example":"Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml registers once; Pages/Admin/Dashboard.cshtml inherits automatically."},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"To scope a Tag Helper registration to pages under `Pages/Admin/` only, drop a `_ViewImports.cshtml` into `{{Pages/Admin/}}` with the `@addTagHelper` directive.","answer":"Pages/Admin/","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Sub-folder _ViewImports.cshtml files extend their parent. The admin page picks up both registrations; pages outside `Admin/` see only the root set.","example":"Pages/Admin/_ViewImports.cshtml: @addTagHelper *, MyApp.AdminHelpers"},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"Which `TagHelperOutput` method renders nothing at all from a helper?","answer":"`output.SuppressOutput()`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Suppresses both the tag and its content. Use when a condition says the element should not appear (feature gate, empty model, etc.).","example":"if (!_flags.IsEnabled(Flag!)) output.SuppressOutput();"},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Given `\u003cmytag\u003eexisting\u003c/mytag\u003e` plus `output.PreContent.SetHtmlContent(\"[pre]\"); output.Content.AppendHtmlContent(\"[appended]\");` the rendered inner block reads `{{[pre]existing[appended]}}`.","answer":"[pre]existing[appended]","bloom":"apply","explanation":"PreContent injects HTML at the start of the inner area. Content.AppendHtmlContent adds after existing content. PostContent goes at the end. PreElement / PostElement (not shown) inject OUTSIDE the tag.","example":"output.PreContent + output.Content + output.PostContent ordered inside the rendered element."},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Which call removes an HTML attribute the page author wrote on the tag?","answer":"`output.Attributes.RemoveAll(\"attribute-name\")`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"RemoveAll strips every attribute matching the name (supports case-insensitive match). SetAttribute replaces; this one deletes.","example":"output.Attributes.RemoveAll(\"data-legacy\");"},{"id":"taghelper-output-registration-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"To disable a globally-registered Tag Helper in one Razor file, use the directive `@{{removeTagHelper}} \"FullType, AssemblyName\"`.","answer":"removeTagHelper","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Rarely used but handy when a third-party package adds helpers you want to opt out of for specific pages. Pair @addTagHelper with @removeTagHelper at different scopes.","example":"@removeTagHelper \"Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.CacheTagHelper, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\""}]}]},{"id":"module-4-i18n-ui","name":"Internationalization & Modern UI","topics":[{"id":"localization-resources-cultures","name":"Localization resources + cultures","tags":["i18n","culture","resx"],"source":"notes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx; research-localization.md §2","prose":"Resource files live at `Resources/\u003cfolder\u003e/\u003cClassName\u003e.\u003cculture\u003e.resx` — the subfolder mirrors the class's project location. `CurrentCulture` controls formatting; `CurrentUICulture` controls which .resx loads. Culture providers run QueryString → Cookie → Accept-Language, first match wins.","cards":[{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The French resource file for `Pages/Index.cshtml.cs` (class `IndexModel`) lives at `Resources/{{Pages}}/IndexModel.{{fr}}.resx`.","answer":"Pages; fr","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Directory structure under `Resources/` mirrors the class location. The filename is `\u003cClassName\u003e.\u003cculture\u003e.resx` — not `\u003cPageName\u003e` and not flat.","example":"Pages/Courses.cshtml.cs (class CoursesModel) → Resources/Pages/CoursesModel.fr.resx"},{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"What is the difference between `Thread.CurrentCulture` and `Thread.CurrentUICulture`?","answer":"CurrentCulture controls date/number/currency formatting; CurrentUICulture controls which .resx file IStringLocalizer loads.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Setting only one produces a half-translated page — numbers in the right locale but strings in the wrong one, or vice versa. UseRequestLocalization sets both together.","example":"CurrentCulture=fr-FR → decimal '3,14'; CurrentUICulture=fr-FR → IndexModel.fr.resx selected."},{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"The three default culture providers run in this order: `{{QueryString}}` → `{{Cookie}}` → `{{AcceptLanguageHeader}}`. First match wins.","answer":"QueryString; Cookie; AcceptLanguageHeader","bloom":"remember","explanation":"QueryString beats cookie (useful for testing / deep links). Cookie beats header (persistent user selection overrides browser default). Order is configurable via options.RequestCultureProviders.","example":"?culture=fr in the URL overrides a stored cookie or a browser Accept-Language: en-US header."},{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"If a resource key has no match in any .resx file for the current culture, what does `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e[\"Key\"]` return?","answer":"The key itself, as a string.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"The indexer returns a `LocalizedString` whose `Name` equals `Value` equals the key, with `ResourceNotFound = true`. This makes it easy to stub a site in English before any .resx files exist.","example":"_localizer[\"Welcome\"] where no .resx has \"Welcome\" → string \"Welcome\"."},{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Fallback chain: a request for `{{fr-CA}}` falls back to `{{fr}}`, which falls back to the un-suffixed default `.resx` if one exists.","answer":"fr-CA; fr","bloom":"understand","explanation":"ASP.NET Core walks the parent culture chain. Ship a generic `fr.resx` and you can omit region-specific `.fr-CA.resx` unless you actually need Canadian-specific translations.","example":"Resources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx alone covers both fr-CA and fr-FR users."},{"id":"localization-resources-cultures-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Which culture provider persists a user's language choice across sessions?","answer":"CookieRequestCultureProvider (reads the `.AspNetCore.Culture` cookie).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"QueryString doesn't persist; Accept-Language reflects browser settings but not in-app selection. Only a cookie survives a browser restart and identifies the returning user.","example":"Response.Cookies.Append(CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName, CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(\"fr\")), new CookieOptions { Expires = ... });"}]},{"id":"localization-setup","name":"Localization setup — AddLocalization + UseRequestLocalization","tags":["i18n","middleware","program-cs"],"source":"notes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx; research-localization.md §3","prose":"Register services with `AddLocalization(opts =\u003e opts.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\")`, declare supported cultures via `Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e`, add `AddViewLocalization()` to the MVC/Razor builder, and — critically — call `app.UseRequestLocalization()` middleware.","cards":[{"id":"localization-setup-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The service registration for localization is `builder.Services.{{AddLocalization}}(opts =\u003e opts.ResourcesPath = \"{{Resources}}\")`.","answer":"AddLocalization; Resources","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`AddLocalization` registers IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e, IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e, and the factory. ResourcesPath points at the root folder where .resx files live.","example":"builder.Services.AddLocalization(opts =\u003e opts.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");"},{"id":"localization-setup-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which middleware call applies the detected culture to each incoming request?","answer":"`app.UseRequestLocalization()`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Without the middleware call, no culture provider ever runs, so CurrentCulture / CurrentUICulture stay at defaults. This is the #1 silent-failure cause for 'my app never translates anything.'","example":"app.UseRequestLocalization();   // must run early in the pipeline"},{"id":"localization-setup-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"Inside `RequestLocalizationOptions`, `{{SupportedCultures}}` controls the allowed `CurrentCulture` values (formatting); `{{SupportedUICultures}}` controls the allowed `CurrentUICulture` values (.resx selection).","answer":"SupportedCultures; SupportedUICultures","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Two separate lists because in theory an app could format dates as en-US while showing French UI. In practice, set both to the same list.","example":"opts.SupportedCultures = opts.SupportedUICultures = new[] { new CultureInfo(\"en\"), new CultureInfo(\"fr\") };"},{"id":"localization-setup-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"What does `builder.Services.AddMvc().AddViewLocalization()` enable?","answer":"`IViewLocalizer` injection directly in `.cshtml` files via `@inject`.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"AddLocalization alone gives you IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e in code-behind. AddViewLocalization adds the view-scoped IViewLocalizer used by @inject in Razor markup.","example":"builder.Services.AddRazorPages().AddViewLocalization();   // @inject IViewLocalizer Localizer now works"},{"id":"localization-setup-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"`UseRequestLocalization` must run {{before}} any endpoint routing / handler in the pipeline — typically just after `CreateBuilder().Build()`.","answer":"before","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Middleware runs in registration order. Put UseRequestLocalization after UseRouting and endpoint handlers run with the default culture even when the user's preferred culture could have been detected.","example":"app.UseRequestLocalization(); app.UseStaticFiles(); app.UseRouting(); ..."},{"id":"localization-setup-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"What's the single most likely missing line if services are registered but language never changes at runtime?","answer":"`app.UseRequestLocalization()` middleware call.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"Without the middleware, no request-culture provider executes. Every request uses DefaultRequestCulture. Adding the line at the top of the pipeline usually fixes it immediately.","example":"Add `app.UseRequestLocalization();` after `var app = builder.Build();`."}]},{"id":"localization-injection","name":"Localizer injection — IStringLocalizer, IHtmlLocalizer, IViewLocalizer","tags":["i18n","di"],"source":"notes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx; research-localization.md §2, §5","prose":"`IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` for code-behind plain text; `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` for code-behind HTML content that should NOT be encoded; `IViewLocalizer` for direct `.cshtml` use via `@inject`. Shared app-wide strings use a marker `SharedResource` class plus `IStringLocalizerFactory.Create`.","cards":[{"id":"localization-injection-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"In a Razor view (`.cshtml`), inject the view-scoped localizer with `@inject {{IViewLocalizer}} Localizer`.","answer":"IViewLocalizer","bloom":"remember","explanation":"IViewLocalizer picks up the resource file matching the view's generated class. IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e and IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e are for code-behind injection.","example":"@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n\u003ch1\u003e@Localizer[\"Welcome\"]\u003c/h1\u003e"},{"id":"localization-injection-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"When should you use `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` instead of `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e`?","answer":"When the translated string contains HTML markup that must render as HTML, not HTML-encoded text.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"IStringLocalizer returns a plain string that Razor HTML-encodes. IHtmlLocalizer returns IHtmlContent which Razor passes through verbatim. Use it for translations containing \u003ca\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e, etc.","example":".resx value: \"Read \u003ca href=\\\"/docs\\\"\u003ethe docs\u003c/a\u003e\" → use IHtmlLocalizer so the anchor renders as a link."},{"id":"localization-injection-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"A PageModel localizes plain text by constructor-injecting `{{IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e}}` and accessing values via the indexer: `_localizer[\"{{Key}}\"]`.","answer":"IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e; Key","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The generic parameter drives both DI resolution and the resource-file name mapping. The indexer returns a LocalizedString that implicitly converts to string.","example":"public IndexModel(IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e localizer) =\u003e _localizer = localizer; ... ViewData[\"Msg\"] = _localizer[\"Welcome\"];"},{"id":"localization-injection-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you implement app-wide shared strings used by many pages?","answer":"Create an empty marker class `SharedResource`, build a service using `IStringLocalizerFactory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), assemblyName)`, register it as a singleton, and inject where needed.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"This avoids duplicating the same translations across every per-class .resx. Pair with `Resources/SharedResource.\u003cculture\u003e.resx` files. DataAnnotations localization often targets this shared class too.","example":"builder.Services.AddSingleton\u003cSharedLocalizer\u003e(); ... @inject SharedLocalizer S ... @S.Get(\"CompanyName\")"},{"id":"localization-injection-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Localizers accept positional format arguments: `_localizer[\"{{GreetUser}}\", userName]` with a .resx value of `\"Hello, {0}!\"`.","answer":"GreetUser","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Positional args let translators reorder placeholders in languages with different word order. Prefer this over string concatenation which cannot express reorderings.","example":"_localizer[\"ItemsCount\", 3] with .resx \"{0} items\" → \"3 items\" (en) / \"3 articles\" (fr)"},{"id":"localization-injection-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"What error do you get if you use `@inject IViewLocalizer` without calling `AddViewLocalization()` in Program.cs?","answer":"A runtime exception: 'No service for type IViewLocalizer has been registered.'","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"AddLocalization registers IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e and IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e; it does NOT register IViewLocalizer. The view-scoped localizer requires AddViewLocalization() on the MVC/Razor Pages builder.","example":"builder.Services.AddRazorPages().AddViewLocalization();   // enables IViewLocalizer"}]},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid","name":"Blazor QuickGrid","tags":["blazor","ui","quickgrid"],"source":"notes/BlazorServer_QuickGrid.docx; notes/BlazorWasm_QuickGrid.docx; Labs/W07 QuickGrid/; research-taghelpers-blazor.md","prose":"`\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"IQueryable\u003cT\u003e\" Pagination=\"PaginationState\"\u003e` plus `\u003cPropertyColumn\u003e` for simple bindings and `\u003cTemplateColumn\u003e` with `SortBy` for custom markup. Live filter via `\u003cinput @bind @bind:event=\"oninput\"\u003e` + computed IQueryable. Host page needs an interactive render mode.","cards":[{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"A `QuickGrid` binds to an `{{IQueryable\u003cT\u003e}}` via `Items=\"@...\"`, with paging controlled by a `{{PaginationState}}` declared in `@code`.","answer":"IQueryable\u003cT\u003e; PaginationState","bloom":"apply","explanation":"IQueryable lets EF Core translate filtering / paging to SQL. PaginationState's `ItemsPerPage` decides page size; a sibling `\u003cPaginator State=\"@state\"\u003e` component renders the controls.","example":"private PaginationState _p = new() { ItemsPerPage = 10 };"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"How do you make a `PropertyColumn` sortable?","answer":"Add the `Sortable=\"true\"` attribute.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"PropertyColumn already knows which property to sort by — setting Sortable=\"true\" is sufficient. TemplateColumn needs an explicit SortBy because it has no implicit sort key.","example":"\u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"A `TemplateColumn` needs `{{SortBy}}` to be sortable; `Sortable=\"true\"` alone does nothing on a TemplateColumn.","answer":"SortBy","bloom":"apply","explanation":"TemplateColumn's render fragment might touch many properties, so QuickGrid can't infer a single sort key. SortBy takes a GridSort\u003cT\u003e you build fluently.","example":"\u003cTemplateColumn Title=\"Name\" SortBy=\"@GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e.ByAscending(s =\u003e s.LastName)\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e@context.FirstName @context.LastName\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you build a multi-key sort expression for a `TemplateColumn`?","answer":"`GridSort\u003cT\u003e.ByAscending(x =\u003e x.First).ThenAscending(x =\u003e x.Second)` (or `.ThenDescending(...)`).","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Chain as many .ThenAscending / .ThenDescending calls as you need. Each one tie-breaks equal rows from the previous key.","example":"GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e.ByAscending(s =\u003e s.FirstName).ThenAscending(s =\u003e s.LastName);"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"For a live-filter input, use `@bind=\"_filter\" @bind:event=\"{{oninput}}\"` — not the default onchange — so the filter updates on every keystroke.","answer":"oninput","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The default @bind event is onchange, which fires only when the input loses focus. Users typing in a search box expect instant filtering — oninput fires per keystroke.","example":"\u003cinput @bind=\"_filter\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" /\u003e"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"What render-mode directive must a page hosting a QuickGrid declare for sorting / paging / filtering to work?","answer":"`@rendermode InteractiveServer` (or `InteractiveWebAssembly` / `InteractiveAuto`).","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Static server rendering produces initial HTML but no client-side runtime. Interactive modes keep the component alive so clicks and input events trigger re-renders.","example":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer"},{"id":"blazor-quickgrid-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"Calling `{{.ToList()}}` on your data source before binding to QuickGrid breaks server-side SQL translation — keep the expression as `IQueryable\u003cT\u003e` all the way to the grid.","answer":".ToList()","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"ToList() materializes the entire result set into memory, after which filtering / paging happens in .NET. For large tables this wrecks performance. Let the grid see an IQueryable and EF Core builds an efficient SQL query per page.","example":"// wrong: _students.Where(...).ToList()\n// right: _students.Where(...)"}]}]},{"id":"module-5-dotnet10-reporting","name":".NET 10 Scripts & Reporting","topics":[{"id":"file-based-app-basics","name":"File-based .NET apps — basics","tags":["dotnet-10","scripting","file-based"],"source":"slides/file-based-apps.pptx; notes/file-based-apps.docx; research-file-based.md","prose":".NET 10 lets you run a single `.cs` file with `dotnet run file.cs` — no `.csproj`, no `bin/`, no `obj/`. Top-level statements replace `Main`. Implicit usings include System, System.Linq, System.Collections.Generic, System.Text, System.Threading.Tasks.","cards":[{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"A .NET 10 file-based app runs with `{{dotnet run}} filename.cs` — no `.csproj`, no `bin/`, no `obj/` directory.","answer":"dotnet run","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The CLI detects the .cs argument, creates an implicit project context, compiles in memory, and caches artifacts under `~/.dotnet/runfile/`.","example":"dotnet run greet.cs"},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"To pass command-line args to a file-based script, what separator must you use?","answer":"`--` (double-dash). Everything after it becomes `args` inside the script.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Without `--`, the CLI interprets trailing tokens as its own flags. `dotnet run greet.cs Kevin` gives you nothing; `dotnet run greet.cs -- Kevin` makes `args[0] == \"Kevin\"`.","example":"dotnet run greet.cs -- Kevin   // args[0] == \"Kevin\""},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"File-based apps use {{top-level statements}}, so no `Program` class or `Main` method is needed; the file body executes as if it were inside `Main`.","answer":"top-level statements","bloom":"understand","explanation":"C# 9+ top-level statements let you write `Console.WriteLine(\"Hi\");` as the first line of a file. File-based apps rely on this feature exclusively.","example":"// greet.cs\\nConsole.WriteLine(\"Hello!\");"},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"List three of the namespaces automatically imported in a file-based app.","answer":"System, System.Collections.Generic, System.Linq (also System.Text and System.Threading.Tasks).","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Implicit usings cover the most common BCL namespaces so short scripts don't need `using` directives. Others still require explicit `using`.","example":"No `using System.Linq;` needed: arr.Where(x =\u003e x \u003e 0) just works."},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Compiled file-based-app binaries are cached under `~/.dotnet/{{runfile}}/` on macOS/Linux and `%USERPROFILE%\\.dotnet\\{{runfile}}\\` on Windows, keyed by filename + content hash.","answer":"runfile; runfile","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The cache makes subsequent runs fast. Edit the .cs file and a new hash triggers a fresh compile; other files stay cached.","example":"~/.dotnet/runfile/greet-3faf7380.../bin/debug/greet.dll"},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Which command converts a file-based app into a traditional .NET project with a .csproj?","answer":"`dotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Use when the single-file form outgrows its use case (multi-file, tests, deployment). The command preserves `#:` directives as the equivalent MSBuild settings.","example":"dotnet project convert api.cs -o ApiProject"},{"id":"file-based-app-basics-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"File-based apps require .NET version {{10}} or higher; earlier SDKs either error or require a separate shim.","answer":"10","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The `dotnet run file.cs` flow was finalized in .NET 10. On .NET 8/9 the command fails; verify with `dotnet --version` if a script mysteriously refuses to run.","example":"dotnet --version   // should report 10.x.x or later"}]},{"id":"file-based-app-directives","name":"File-based app #: directives","tags":["dotnet-10","scripting","directives"],"source":"notes/file-based-apps.docx; research-file-based.md §2.4","prose":"Four directives put build metadata into a file-based `.cs` — `#:package` for NuGet, `#:property` for MSBuild properties, `#:sdk` for SDK selection, `#:project` for project references. No space after the colon.","cards":[{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The NuGet-package directive is `#:{{package}} PackageName@Version` — note: no space after the {{colon}}.","answer":"package; colon","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1` is legal; `#: package Spectre.Console@0.49.1` is not. The spaced form is a classic exam distractor.","example":"#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1"},{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which directive switches the file's SDK to support ASP.NET Core minimal APIs?","answer":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The default SDK (`Microsoft.NET.Sdk`) is console-only. `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` adds `WebApplication`, routing, middleware, etc.","example":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\\nvar app = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build();"},{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"To set an MSBuild property like the target framework, use `#:{{property}} TargetFramework={{net10.0}}`.","answer":"property; net10.0","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Stack multiple #:property directives for more settings (LangVersion, Nullable, etc.). The `=` has no spaces around it.","example":"#:property TargetFramework=net10.0\\n#:property Nullable=enable"},{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you reference a local .csproj from a file-based .cs?","answer":"`#:project ./Relative/Path/Lib.csproj`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The path is resolved relative to the file-based .cs's location. Useful when a one-off script consumes types from a shared library.","example":"#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj\\nusing MyLibrary;\\nvar p = new Person();"},{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"The four `#:` directives are: `#:{{package}}`, `#:{{property}}`, `#:{{sdk}}`, and `#:{{project}}`. Each has NO space after the colon.","answer":"package; property; sdk; project","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Each directive targets one build-configuration concern. Stack as many as needed; each must sit on its own line.","example":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\\n#:property Nullable=enable"},{"id":"file-based-app-directives-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Is `#: sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` (with a space after the colon) valid?","answer":"No. Directive names sit flush against `#:` with no whitespace between.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"The spaced form is the most common distractor in exams because it reads naturally. Always proofread for the zero-space rule.","example":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web   (correct)\\n#: sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web  (invalid)"}]},{"id":"file-based-app-web","name":"File-based web apps — #:sdk + minimal API","tags":["dotnet-10","scripting","web","minimal-api"],"source":"notes/file-based-apps.docx; research-file-based.md","prose":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` switches a file-based app from console mode to ASP.NET Core. `WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build()` plus `app.MapGet/Post/Put/Delete` gives a complete minimal-API web server in one file.","cards":[{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"To write a file-based web API, the first line is `#:sdk {{Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web}}` — without it, `WebApplication` is not resolvable.","answer":"Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The default file-based SDK is console-only. Switching to the Web SDK pulls in ASP.NET Core's implicit references so minimal-API types are available.","example":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\\nvar app = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build();\\napp.MapGet(\"/\", () =\u003e \"Hi\");\\napp.Run();"},{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"What runtime type does `WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build()` return?","answer":"`WebApplication` — which you then use to call `MapGet`, `MapPost`, etc., and `Run()`.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`WebApplication` is the minimal-API host. It replaces the historical `IHost` + `IApplicationBuilder` split with a single object exposing routing + lifecycle methods.","example":"var app = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build();"},{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"A GET endpoint mapping in a file-based web app reads `app.{{MapGet}}(\"/route\", () =\u003e result)`.","answer":"MapGet","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Map methods take a route template and a handler delegate. Delegates can be lambdas, method references, or typed handlers with DI via parameter injection.","example":"app.MapGet(\"/widgets\", (AppDb db) =\u003e db.Widgets.ToList());"},{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you include an additional NuGet package in a file-based web app?","answer":"Add a `#:package PackageName@Version` directive at the top of the file.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Directives stack: the SDK swap plus any number of package directives, all at the file's top. Each on its own line.","example":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0"},{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"The error `The name 'WebApplication' does not exist in the current context` on a file-based `.cs` almost always means the `{{#:sdk}}` directive is missing.","answer":"#:sdk","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"WebApplication lives in ASP.NET Core types that the default console SDK does not reference. Adding `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` fixes the resolution.","example":"Add `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` as the first line of the file."},{"id":"file-based-app-web-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"When should you convert a file-based web app to a proper .NET project?","answer":"When you need multiple files, test projects, complex deployment, or CI pipelines that expect a .csproj.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Single-file form is great for demos and one-off utilities. Anything requiring structure graduates via `dotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder`.","example":"dotnet project convert api.cs -o ApiProject"}]},{"id":"excel-export","name":"Excel export with ClosedXML","tags":["excel","closedxml","report"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/; research-excel-pdf-chart.md §3","prose":"Create `XLWorkbook`, add a worksheet, write cells with 1-based indexing, save to a `MemoryStream`, return a `FileResult` with MIME type `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`.","cards":[{"id":"excel-export-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"ClosedXML cell indexing is {{1-based}}: `sheet.Cell(1, 1)` is the top-left cell (A1), not `Cell(0, 0)`.","answer":"1-based","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The 1-based convention matches Excel's UI (row 1, column A = A1). Mixing it with C# arrays causes off-by-one bugs, especially when data loops start at row 2 (header in row 1).","example":"sheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Name\"; sheet.Cell(2, 1).Value = \"Alice\";"},{"id":"excel-export-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"What MIME type identifies an .xlsx file download?","answer":"`application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Long but precise — this is the OpenXML spreadsheet MIME. `application/excel` and `application/vnd.ms-excel` refer to older or incorrect formats.","example":"return File(bytes, \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\", \"Report.xlsx\");"},{"id":"excel-export-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"In ClosedXML, save the workbook to a `{{MemoryStream}}` with `workbook.SaveAs(stream)`, then call `stream.{{ToArray}}()` to get bytes for `File(...)`.","answer":"MemoryStream; ToArray","bloom":"apply","explanation":"The byte array form works with `File(byte[], mime, name)` which returns `FileContentResult`. For very large exports, return `FileStreamResult` and remember to rewind the stream — but `ToArray` is simpler for typical report sizes.","example":"using var ms = new MemoryStream(); workbook.SaveAs(ms); return File(ms.ToArray(), mime, name);"},{"id":"excel-export-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you style all cells in a header range (rows 1, columns 1-3) with a background fill?","answer":"`sheet.Range(sheet.Cell(1,1).Address, sheet.Cell(1,3).Address).Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.Almond);`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"IXLRange applies styles to all cells in the rectangular region. Single-cell styling works via `.Style` directly on `Cell(r, c)`.","example":"sheet.Range(sheet.Cell(1,1).Address, sheet.Cell(1,3).Address).Style.Font.Bold = true;"},{"id":"excel-export-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"After populating data, call `sheet.Columns().{{AdjustToContents}}()` to auto-fit every column's width before saving.","answer":"AdjustToContents","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Without autofit, users open your export and see all columns at the default ~8-character width. Call it once after all cells are written.","example":"sheet.Columns().AdjustToContents();  // before workbook.SaveAs(stream)"},{"id":"excel-export-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"What ASP.NET Core return type does an Excel-export handler typically produce?","answer":"`FileResult` — specifically constructed via `File(bytes, mime, filename)`.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"`File(...)` is a controller/PageModel helper that creates a `FileContentResult` (or `FileStreamResult` when streaming). Both inherit from `FileResult`.","example":"public FileResult OnGet() =\u003e File(bytes, mime, \"Report.xlsx\");"}]},{"id":"pdf-export","name":"PDF export with iText 7","tags":["pdf","itext7","report"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/; research-excel-pdf-chart.md §3","prose":"iText 7 plus `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter` are both required. Pipeline: `MemoryStream` → `PdfWriter` → `PdfDocument` → `Document`. Call `writer.SetCloseStream(false)` to keep the stream open for `FileStreamResult`, and reset `ms.Position = 0` before returning.","cards":[{"id":"pdf-export-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"iText 7 requires two NuGet packages: `{{itext7}}` and `{{itext.bouncy-castle-adapter}}` — the adapter is a runtime crypto dependency, not optional.","answer":"itext7; itext.bouncy-castle-adapter","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Installing just itext7 compiles fine but crashes at runtime when iText attempts hashing or signing. Add both packages together to avoid the late failure.","example":"\u003cPackageReference Include=\"itext7\" Version=\"9.6.0\" /\u003e\\n\u003cPackageReference Include=\"itext.bouncy-castle-adapter\" Version=\"9.6.0\" /\u003e"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Order the four iText 7 types you construct top-to-bottom in a PDF pipeline.","answer":"MemoryStream → PdfWriter(stream) → PdfDocument(writer) → Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Each layer wraps the previous. MemoryStream is the byte sink; PdfWriter writes PDF-shaped bytes; PdfDocument owns PDF file structure (pages, xref); Document is the layout engine that accepts Paragraphs and Tables.","example":"var ms = new MemoryStream(); var writer = new PdfWriter(ms); var pdfDoc = new PdfDocument(writer); var doc = new Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false);"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"Call `writer.{{SetCloseStream}}(false)` so `document.Close()` does NOT close the underlying `MemoryStream` — you still need to read from it when returning the response.","answer":"SetCloseStream","bloom":"apply","explanation":"By default, closing the Document cascades and closes the writer + stream. Flipping the flag keeps the MemoryStream open for `FileStreamResult`. An alternative is returning `File(ms.ToArray(), ...)` which materializes bytes and doesn't care about the stream state.","example":"writer.SetCloseStream(false);"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"What line do you need before returning a `FileStreamResult` wrapping your PDF `MemoryStream`?","answer":"`ms.Position = 0;`","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"After writing, the MemoryStream's position is at the end. FileStreamResult reads from current position, finds nothing, and serves an empty file. Rewinding to 0 fixes this.","example":"document.Close(); ms.Position = 0; return new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\");"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"In iText, page numbering is added AFTER layout by looping over `pdfDoc.{{GetNumberOfPages}}()` and calling `document.ShowTextAligned(...)` per page.","answer":"GetNumberOfPages","bloom":"apply","explanation":"You can't know the total page count until content is laid out. Loop from 1 to GetNumberOfPages() and add a page-N-of-total paragraph to each page.","example":"for (int i = 1; i \u003c= pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages(); i++) document.ShowTextAligned(new Paragraph($\"Page {i} of {pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages()}\"), 559, 806, i, TextAlignment.RIGHT, VerticalAlignment.TOP, 0);"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Which MIME type identifies a PDF download?","answer":"`application/pdf`","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Standard MIME — browsers recognize it and either render in a built-in viewer or save to disk. `FileStreamResult` takes it as a constructor argument.","example":"return new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\") { FileDownloadName = \"Report.pdf\" };"},{"id":"pdf-export-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"A simpler alternative to `FileStreamResult` + `ms.Position = 0` is `return {{File}}(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"name.pdf\")` — the `ToArray()` is position-insensitive.","answer":"File","bloom":"apply","explanation":"File(byte[], mime, name) materializes the bytes, bypassing the stream-position trap. Trade-off: materializing into memory uses more RAM for large PDFs.","example":"return File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"Report.pdf\");"}]},{"id":"chart-rendering","name":"Chart.js in Razor — CDN + Razor data injection","tags":["chart","chart-js","razor"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/; research-excel-pdf-chart.md §3","prose":"Chart.js is a client-side library loaded from a CDN. A Razor page exposes a `\u003ccanvas\u003e` element, builds JS data arrays by `@:` directives in a `\u003cscript\u003e` block, and calls `new Chart(ctx, { type, data })` to render.","cards":[{"id":"chart-rendering-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"Chart.js renders on a `\u003c{{canvas}}\u003e` element identified by `id`. In the script, grab it via `document.getElementById('pie-chart')` and pass it to `new Chart(ctx, config)`.","answer":"canvas","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Chart.js draws 2D graphics using the canvas's 2D context. The canvas has to be in the DOM when the script runs, so typically the \u003cscript\u003e block appears after the canvas element.","example":"\u003ccanvas id=\"pie-chart\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e"},{"id":"chart-rendering-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"Which Razor directive injects a JavaScript line per loop iteration inside a `\u003cscript\u003e` block?","answer":"`@:` (at-colon) at the start of each JS line.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"`@:` tells Razor \"treat this line as mixed content with @-expression substitutions.\" Without it, Razor may misparse the JS or produce malformed output.","example":"@foreach (var x in Model.Data) { @:labels.push('@x.Name'); }"},{"id":"chart-rendering-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"The Chart.js constructor takes two arguments: `new Chart({{ctx}}, {{config}})` — the canvas element (or its 2D context) and a config object with `type`, `data`, and optional `options`.","answer":"ctx; config","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Config.type picks the chart shape ('pie', 'bar', 'line', 'doughnut', etc.). Config.data has labels and datasets arrays. Options tune axes, legend, tooltips.","example":"new Chart(canvas, { type: 'pie', data: { labels, datasets: [{ data, backgroundColor }] } });"},{"id":"chart-rendering-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you load Chart.js into a Razor page?","answer":"Add `\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e` to the page.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The library is distributed via CDN; no NuGet package is involved because the chart runs client-side. Pin a version (e.g. @3.9.1) so updates don't silently change behavior.","example":"\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e"},{"id":"chart-rendering-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"For a pie chart, the dataset's `{{backgroundColor}}` is an array of colors — one entry per slice.","answer":"backgroundColor","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Unlike bar/line charts which typically use a single color across the dataset, pie slices want distinct colors. Pass an array aligned with the data array.","example":"datasets: [{ data: [10, 20, 30], backgroundColor: ['red', 'blue', 'green'] }]"},{"id":"chart-rendering-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"Can Chart.js render a chart at the server and include the PNG in a PDF export?","answer":"No. Chart.js runs only in the browser. Server-side chart rendering requires a different library (e.g. SkiaSharp, System.Drawing).","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"The chart lives in a browser \u003ccanvas\u003e. PDFs generated by iText 7 on the server cannot include a Chart.js-rendered image unless you first export the canvas from the browser (e.g. toDataURL) and POST it back to the server for embedding.","example":"Use SkiaSharp or ScottPlot for server-rendered images if you need charts embedded in PDFs."}]}]},{"id":"module-6-testing","name":"Testing Discipline","topics":[{"id":"tdd-cycle","name":"TDD cycle — Red, Green, Refactor + Three Laws","tags":["tdd","discipline"],"source":"slides/TDD_xunit.pptx; notes/TDD_xunit_SCRIPT.docx; research-tdd.md","prose":"TDD is a loop: write a failing test (Red), write the minimum code to make it pass (Green), then clean up without breaking the test (Refactor). Robert C. Martin's Three Laws enforce test-first discipline.","cards":[{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"The TDD cycle has three phases: `{{Red}}` (failing test), `{{Green}}` (minimum code to pass), `{{Refactor}}` (clean up without breaking the test).","answer":"Red; Green; Refactor","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Each phase has a single job. Skipping any phase defeats the purpose — no Red means you might be writing a tautological test; no Refactor means technical debt compounds.","example":"Red → Write Assert.Equal(4, calc.Add(2, 2));  // fails because Calculator doesn't exist\\nGreen → class Calculator { public int Add(int a, int b) =\u003e a + b; }\\nRefactor → rename, extract, simplify"},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"State Robert C. Martin's First Law of TDD.","answer":"You are not allowed to write any production code unless it is to make a failing test pass.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The First Law defines the relationship: production code exists to satisfy failing tests. Writing code without a failing test in hand breaks the TDD discipline.","example":"Failing test on table → you may write production code. No failing test → you may not."},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"During the {{Green}} phase, you write the {{minimum}} code necessary to make the failing test pass — not more, not less.","answer":"Green; minimum","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Resisting the urge to add 'just in case' logic is the hardest discipline. Extra code has no test backing it and accumulates as unverified complexity.","example":"Test expects Add(2, 2) → 4. Green code could be `return 4;` (passes the one test). Add more tests to force more general logic."},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"Why is writing the test first (the Red phase) important — what does it prove that a test written after the code cannot?","answer":"It proves the test can fail when the feature is missing, confirming the test's assertion is valid and the test framework can detect the failure.","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"A test written after the code might be tautological — it may check something the code trivially satisfies without you knowing. Watching it fail first eliminates that false-confidence.","example":"If you watch the test fail, then see it pass after implementing, you've proved: (a) the test detects absence, (b) your code fixes it."},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"In the Refactor phase, you clean up code while {{re-running tests}} after each change to ensure nothing breaks.","answer":"re-running tests","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Refactor happens under the safety net of green tests. Every structural change should leave all tests green. If a refactor breaks a test, undo and try a smaller step.","example":"Rename variable → run tests → still green → commit. Extract method → run tests → still green → commit."},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"When is TDD a poor fit?","answer":"Exploratory spikes, UI prototyping, research code — situations where the goal is learning, not regression-proof production code.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Test-first requires you to know what the test should check; exploratory work is about discovering what you don't know. After the spike, rewrite production-worthy parts with TDD.","example":"Prototyping 'does ML.NET support this feature?' — write code first, test viable outputs later."},{"id":"tdd-cycle-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"Robert Martin's Third Law: you are not allowed to write any more production code than is sufficient to make the {{currently failing test}} pass.","answer":"currently failing test","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Keeps production code tied to test coverage. Adding logic beyond the current failing test introduces untested behavior — exactly what TDD exists to prevent.","example":"Test: Divide(10, 2) → 5. Green body: `return 5;` — not `return a / b;`. The next test (Divide(6, 2) → 3) forces generalization."}]},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions","name":"xUnit attributes, assertions, AAA","tags":["tdd","xunit","assert"],"source":"slides/TDD_xunit.pptx; notes/TDD_xunit_SCRIPT.docx; research-tdd.md","prose":"xUnit uses `[Fact]` for single-scenario tests and `[Theory]` + `[InlineData]` for parameterized tests. Arrange/Act/Assert organizes the body. `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` argument order is expected-first, and `Assert.Throws\u003cT\u003e(() =\u003e action())` is the exception matcher.","cards":[{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"A single-scenario xUnit test is marked `[{{Fact}}]`; a parameterized test is marked `[{{Theory}}]` and paired with one or more `[{{InlineData}}]` rows.","answer":"Fact; Theory; InlineData","bloom":"remember","explanation":"Each [InlineData(...)] produces one test execution. Four [InlineData] rows = four runs of the same [Theory] method body. Individual failures are reported per-row.","example":"[Theory]\\n[InlineData(1, 2, 3)]\\n[InlineData(0, 0, 0)]\\npublic void Add(int a, int b, int expected) =\u003e Assert.Equal(expected, calc.Add(a, b));"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-02","type":"cloze","prompt":"The canonical test body structure is {{Arrange}} / {{Act}} / {{Assert}} — setup, the operation under test, then the verification.","answer":"Arrange; Act; Assert","bloom":"understand","explanation":"AAA keeps tests readable and makes failures diagnosable — a stack trace points to Arrange, Act, or Assert and you know immediately whether setup, behavior, or expectations broke.","example":"// Arrange\\nvar calc = new Calculator();\\n// Act\\nint r = calc.Add(2, 3);\\n// Assert\\nAssert.Equal(5, r);"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-03","type":"name","prompt":"What's the argument order for `Assert.Equal`?","answer":"Expected first, actual second: `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)`.","bloom":"remember","explanation":"The compiler doesn't enforce order. Reversing produces failure messages that lie — the Expected/Actual labels in the message will be swapped, and you'll chase the wrong value.","example":"Assert.Equal(5, calc.Add(2, 3));  // expected 5, actual is the result of Add"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"How do you test that a method throws `ArgumentException`?","answer":"`Assert.Throws\u003cArgumentException\u003e(() =\u003e method(args));`","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Assert.Throws runs the lambda and asserts a specific exception type was thrown. It returns the exception instance so you can also assert on Message or custom properties.","example":"var ex = Assert.Throws\u003cArgumentException\u003e(() =\u003e _service.DoThing(null));\\nAssert.Contains(\"cannot be null\", ex.Message);"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"When multiple derived exception types could match, use `Assert.{{ThrowsAny}}\u003cT\u003e(() =\u003e action())` to accept any subtype of `T`.","answer":"ThrowsAny","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Assert.Throws\u003cT\u003e matches T EXACTLY — a derived type fails the test. Assert.ThrowsAny\u003cT\u003e accepts T or any subclass. Use the strict form when the exact type matters; the any form when it doesn't.","example":"Assert.ThrowsAny\u003cArgumentException\u003e(() =\u003e action());  // ArgumentNullException and ArgumentOutOfRangeException both pass"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"What xUnit assertion compares two references for being the same object (not just value-equal)?","answer":"`Assert.Same(expected, actual)` (its negation: `Assert.NotSame`).","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Same compares by reference identity; Equal compares by value. For value types Equal is almost always what you want; for reference types, choose based on whether you care about identity or content.","example":"Assert.Same(obj, service.GetCached());  // must be the literal same instance"},{"id":"xunit-attributes-assertions-card-07","type":"cloze","prompt":"`[Theory]` tests require at least one data attribute. Common choices: `[{{InlineData}}(...)]` for literals, `[{{MemberData}}(nameof(Method))]` for computed data, `[{{ClassData}}(typeof(Cls))]` for typed data providers.","answer":"InlineData; MemberData; ClassData","bloom":"remember","explanation":"[InlineData] is simplest for small literal values. [MemberData] when data requires computation or doesn't fit in an attribute. [ClassData] when data provider needs its own class with complex logic.","example":"[Theory]\\n[MemberData(nameof(GetSamples))]\\npublic void RoundTrip(string json) { /* ... */ }\\npublic static IEnumerable\u003cobject[]\u003e GetSamples() { yield return new object[] { \"{}\" }; }"}]},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle","name":"xUnit fixtures and lifecycle","tags":["tdd","xunit","fixture","lifecycle"],"source":"notes/TDD_xunit_SCRIPT.docx; research-tdd.md","prose":"xUnit creates a fresh test-class instance per test. Constructor runs before each test; `IDisposable.Dispose` runs after each test. `IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e` shares one instance across all tests in a class; `ICollectionFixture\u003cT\u003e` + `[CollectionDefinition]` + `[Collection(\"Name\")]` shares across multiple classes.","cards":[{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-01","type":"cloze","prompt":"In xUnit, the test class's {{constructor}} runs before each test, and `{{IDisposable.Dispose}}` runs after — replacing older frameworks' `[SetUp]` / `[TearDown]` attributes.","answer":"constructor; IDisposable.Dispose","bloom":"remember","explanation":"xUnit uses standard C# object lifecycle instead of framework-specific attributes. Every [Fact] or [Theory] run gets a fresh test class instance, so state doesn't leak between tests.","example":"public class MyTests : IDisposable { public MyTests() { /* setup */ } public void Dispose() { /* cleanup */ } }"},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-02","type":"name","prompt":"How do you share an expensive setup (e.g. a seeded DbContext) across all tests in one test class?","answer":"Implement the setup as a fixture class and have the test class implement `IClassFixture\u003cTFixture\u003e`. xUnit injects the shared fixture via the test class constructor.","bloom":"apply","explanation":"IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e creates one fixture instance per test class, shared across all tests in that class. The test class's own lifetime (constructor/Dispose per test) is unchanged.","example":"public class MyTests : IClassFixture\u003cDbFixture\u003e { public MyTests(DbFixture fx) { _fx = fx; } }"},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-03","type":"cloze","prompt":"To share a fixture across multiple test classes, define `{{ICollectionFixture\u003cT\u003e}}` inside a `[{{CollectionDefinition}}(\"Name\")]` class, and decorate each participating test class with `[{{Collection}}(\"Name\")]`.","answer":"ICollectionFixture\u003cT\u003e; CollectionDefinition; Collection","bloom":"apply","explanation":"Three pieces: definition class declares the fixture, test classes join by [Collection(\"Name\")]. Tests within the collection run serially; the fixture is instantiated once per collection.","example":"[CollectionDefinition(\"Db\")] public class DbColl : ICollectionFixture\u003cDbFixture\u003e {}\\n[Collection(\"Db\")] public class UserTests { /* ... */ }\\n[Collection(\"Db\")] public class OrderTests { /* ... */ }"},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-04","type":"name","prompt":"By default, does xUnit run tests in the same class in parallel or serially?","answer":"Serially. Tests in one class run one at a time; different test classes run in parallel.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"This default prevents shared-fixture races within a class. Parallelism happens at the class level, so IClassFixture-shared state is safe (no two tests touch it concurrently). Opt into full parallelization via [assembly: CollectionBehavior(...)] if needed.","example":"TestsInClassA: serialized. TestsInClassB: serialized. ClassA vs ClassB: parallel."},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-05","type":"cloze","prompt":"Fixtures are {{not safe}} for tests that mutate the fixture's state — xUnit doesn't guarantee test ordering within a class, so one test's writes may or may not be visible to another.","answer":"not safe","bloom":"analyze","explanation":"If tests need to mutate shared state, either reset in the test class's own Dispose, or switch to fresh-per-test state (no fixture). IClassFixture is intended for read-only / idempotent setup.","example":"Bad: TestA adds a user, TestB counts users, result depends on execution order.\\nFix: each test manages its own state, or reset in Dispose."},{"id":"xunit-fixtures-lifecycle-card-06","type":"name","prompt":"When should you NOT use a fixture?","answer":"When setup is cheap (in-memory list, simple object graph). Fixtures add indirection; plain constructors are simpler for tests that don't need expensive shared setup.","bloom":"understand","explanation":"Fixtures trade test isolation for performance. For a few-line setup there's no perf benefit; fixture overhead (an extra class, [Collection] attribute for cross-class sharing) is net negative.","example":"`new Calculator()` in the constructor — no fixture needed. `new MyDbContext(...)` with seed data — fixture pays off."}]}]}],"mockExam":{"duration_seconds":3600,"pass_mark":0.5,"questions":[{"id":"mq-ai-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"Semantic Kernel credential (W02)","marks":1,"question":"W02 lab wires GitHub Models through `OpenAIClient`. Which credential class does it pass?","choices":["`AzureKeyCredential(pat)`","`ApiKeyCredential(pat)`","`BearerTokenCredential(pat)`","`GithubCredential(pat)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"W02 lab uses `new OpenAIClient(new ApiKeyCredential(githubPAT), new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(uri) })`. `ApiKeyCredential` lives in `System.ClientModel`. `AzureKeyCredential` (from `Azure.Core`) is for a different SDK (`ChatCompletionsClient` / `Azure.AI.Inference`). The other two options don't exist.","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/Program.cs","bloom":"remember","tags":["pretest"]},{"id":"mq-ai-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"GitHub Models endpoint URL","marks":1,"question":"Which endpoint URL goes into `OpenAIClientOptions.Endpoint` for GitHub Models?","choices":["`https://api.github.com/ai`","`https://models.github.ai/inference`","`https://api.openai.com/v1`","`http://localhost:11434/inference`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"GitHub Models exposes inference at `https://models.github.ai/inference` — HTTPS, with the `/inference` path segment. Without `/inference`, requests fail. Ollama is `http://localhost:11434/` (different path, different protocol).","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/appsettings.json","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-ai-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"Semantic Kernel service injection","marks":1,"question":"Which SK interface does W02's `IndexModel` inject through its constructor?","choices":["`IKernel`","`IChatCompletionService`","`IChatClient`","`IChatHistoryService`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"W02 PageModel has `public IndexModel(IChatCompletionService chat)` — that service is registered by `builder.Services.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client); builder.Services.AddKernel();` in Program.cs. `IChatClient` belongs to `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` (Ollama/MAF), not SK.","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-ai-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"SK ChatHistory constructor","marks":1,"question":"In W02 the PageModel creates `ChatHistory chat = new(\"You are an AI assistant...\");`. What does the string argument represent?","choices":["A user message appended to the history","The system prompt — instructions the model follows for the whole conversation","The model identifier","The assistant's initial greeting"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`ChatHistory`'s string-parameter constructor sets the system prompt. User turns are added via `chat.AddUserMessage(...)`; assistant turns via `chat.AddAssistantMessage(...)`. Model id was registered separately in `AddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client)`.","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-ai-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"SK streaming method","marks":1,"question":"How does W02's PageModel stream tokens from the chat service?","choices":["`await _chat.GetStreamAsync(chat)`","`await foreach (var m in _chat.GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync(chat)) sb.Append(m.Content);`","`await _chat.StreamAsync(chat, writer)`","`await _chat.CompleteStreamingAsync(chat, Console.Out)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The method is `GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync(chatHistory)`. It returns `IAsyncEnumerable\u003cStreamingChatMessageContent\u003e` — iterate with `await foreach`, concatenate each item's `.Content`. The other three are fabrications.","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-ai-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"MAF agent construction","marks":1,"question":"Which line wraps an `IChatClient` into a Microsoft Agent Framework agent?","choices":["`chatClient.AsAgent(name, instructions)`","`chatClient.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)`","`chatClient.ToAgent(name, instructions)`","`new ChatAgent(chatClient, options)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The extension method is `.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)`, from `Microsoft.Agents.AI`. `.AsAgent()` does not exist — common distractor. MAF also supports `new ChatClientAgent(client, ChatClientAgentOptions)` as an alternate shape, but `new ChatAgent(...)` is not real.","source":"code-examples/20260324_docker-slms/docker-slms/FunnyDockerMAF.cs","bloom":"remember","tags":["pretest"]},{"id":"mq-ai-07","type":"MCQ","topic":"MAF session for multi-turn","marks":1,"question":"To maintain context across multiple `agent.RunAsync` calls, what do you create?","choices":["A new `ChatHistory`","An `AgentSession` via `await agent.CreateSessionAsync()`","A `ConversationContext` singleton","Nothing — the agent retains state automatically"],"correct":1,"rationale":"FunnyDockerMAF demos `AgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();` then passes it into streaming calls. `ChatHistory` belongs to SK (not MAF). The agent has no server-side memory — you supply it via session.","source":"code-examples/20260324_docker-slms/docker-slms/FunnyDockerMAF.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-ai-08","type":"MCQ","topic":"MAF streaming method","marks":1,"question":"Which method streams an MAF agent's response incrementally?","choices":["`agent.StreamResponseAsync(input)`","`agent.RunStreamingAsync(input, options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(chatOptions))`","`agent.RunAsync(input, stream: true)`","`agent.GetStreamAsync(input)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"FunnyDockerMAF demos `await foreach (var update in agent.RunStreamingAsync(userInput, options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(chatOptions)))`. Each `update.Text` carries a token fragment. `RunAsync` returns a single response, not a stream.","source":"code-examples/20260324_docker-slms/docker-slms/FunnyDockerMAF.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-ai-09","type":"MCQ","topic":"Ollama endpoint","marks":1,"question":"Which URL does `OllamaApiClient` connect to for a locally-running Ollama daemon?","choices":["`https://localhost:11434`","`http://localhost:1143`","`http://localhost:11434/`","`http://ollama.local/inference`"],"correct":2,"rationale":"Ollama runs on port 11434 over HTTP (no TLS by default). Port 1143 is an off-by-one typo. `http://ollama.local/inference` confuses Ollama's path (none) with GitHub Models' `/inference`.","source":"code-examples/20260324_Ollama/Ollama/SLM.OllamaClient/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-ai-10","type":"MCQ","topic":"OllamaSharp + IChatClient","marks":1,"question":"What interface does `new OllamaApiClient(uri, modelId)` implement?","choices":["`IChatCompletionService`","`IChatClient`","`IOllamaClient`","`IAIAgent`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`OllamaApiClient` (from `OllamaSharp`) implements `IChatClient` from `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`. The demo types the variable as `IChatClient chatClient = new OllamaApiClient(...)`. `IChatCompletionService` is the SK interface. The other two options are fabrications.","source":"code-examples/20260324_Ollama/Ollama/SLM.OllamaClient/Program.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-ai-11","type":"MCQ","topic":"IChatClient streaming","marks":1,"question":"Which method on `IChatClient` yields `ChatResponseUpdate` items as tokens arrive?","choices":["`GetResponseAsync(messages)`","`GetStreamingResponseAsync(messages)`","`StreamResponseAsync(messages)`","`CompleteStreamingAsync(messages)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`GetStreamingResponseAsync` returns `IAsyncEnumerable\u003cChatResponseUpdate\u003e`. Iterate with `await foreach`, concatenate `.Text`. `GetResponseAsync` returns a single buffered `ChatResponse`.","source":"code-examples/20260324_Ollama/Ollama/SLM.OllamaClient/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-ai-12","type":"MCQ","topic":"Docker SLM credential","marks":1,"question":"In the Docker-SLM demo (`FunnyDockerMAF.cs`), what string is passed to `ApiKeyCredential` for a locally-hosted model?","choices":["The actual GitHub PAT","An environment variable `DOCKER_SLM_KEY`","The literal string `\"unused\"`","An empty string"],"correct":2,"rationale":"`new ApiKeyCredential(\"unused\")` — local OpenAI-compatible runtimes ignore the credential but the SDK constructor requires a non-null string. The placeholder keeps the shape identical to cloud paths.","source":"code-examples/20260324_docker-slms/docker-slms/FunnyDockerMAF.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-ai-13","type":"MCQ","topic":"MAF agent method confusion","marks":1,"question":"Which method name is REAL for invoking a Microsoft Agent Framework agent?","choices":["`agent.Invoke(input)`","`agent.Execute(input)`","`agent.RunAsync(input)`","`agent.CallAsync(input)`"],"correct":2,"rationale":"MAF uses `RunAsync` (sync one-shot) and `RunStreamingAsync` (streaming). `Invoke` belongs to Semantic Kernel (`kernel.InvokeAsync`). The other two don't exist.","source":"code-examples/20260324_Ollama/Ollama/MAF.Phi3/Program.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET Fit() return type","marks":1,"question":"What does `pipeline.Fit(trainingData)` return?","choices":["`IDataView`","`ITransformer`","`RegressionMetrics`","`MLContext`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`Fit` produces `ITransformer` — the trained, stateless, serializable model. `IDataView` is the INPUT (the training data). `RegressionMetrics` is what `Regression.Evaluate` returns. `MLContext` is the root container created at step one.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"remember","tags":["pretest"]},{"id":"mq-mlnet-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"Features column name is hardcoded","marks":1,"question":"Why does `mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Inputs\", \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"TripDistance\")` break training?","choices":["Concatenate requires at least three input columns","Trainers look up the feature vector by the literal name `\"Features\"` — other names break the lookup","The column `Inputs` conflicts with ASP.NET Core's `Inputs` keyword","Concatenate only accepts numeric columns, not one-hot vectors"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`FastTree` and every other regression trainer hardcode the lookup to the column named `\"Features\"`. Rename the Concatenate output to anything else and the trainer throws at fit time. Same story with `\"Label\"` — rename via `CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")` first.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"CopyColumns — rename target","marks":1,"question":"Why does every TaxiFarePrediction pipeline start with `CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")`?","choices":["Because `FareAmount` must be cloned before transformation","Trainers lookup the target column by the literal name `\"Label\"`; CopyColumns gives your target that name","To convert FareAmount from string to float","To force the column to be first in the schema"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`Label` is the hardcoded target column name. `CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")` duplicates the fare value under the name the trainer expects.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"OneHotEncoding purpose","marks":1,"question":"What does `Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\")` do?","choices":["Hashes the string to a single 32-bit integer","Expands each distinct text value into a binary-indicator vector","Replaces each text value with the mean fare for that vendor","Normalizes the string length to 8 characters"],"correct":1,"rationale":"One-hot encoding expands `\"VTS\"` to `[0, 1]` and `\"CMT\"` to `[1, 0]` (with more slots for more distinct values). Trainers only accept numeric input — string columns need encoding before reaching `Concatenate`.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"Regression.Evaluate metrics","marks":1,"question":"Which property reads the fraction of variance explained by a regression model?","choices":["`metrics.Accuracy`","`metrics.RSquared`","`metrics.F1Score`","`metrics.Precision`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`RegressionMetrics` exposes `RSquared` (0–1, unitless, variance explained), `RootMeanSquaredError` (label units), and `MeanAbsoluteError`. `Accuracy`, `F1Score`, `Precision` are classification metrics — wrong namespace.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"RMSE units","marks":1,"question":"A taxi-fare model reports `RSquared = 0.89, RootMeanSquaredError = 3.30`. What does RMSE = 3.30 mean?","choices":["The model is 3.30% accurate","Predictions miss the actual fare by about $3.30 on average","The model took 3.30 seconds to train","The model explains 3.30 of variance"],"correct":1,"rationale":"RMSE is in the label's original units — dollars here. On average a predicted fare misses the actual fare by about $3.30. RMSE is not a percentage. R² (0.89) is the variance-explained measure, also not \"accuracy.\"","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-07","type":"MCQ","topic":"Score column binding","marks":1,"question":"Your prediction class is `public class TaxiTripFarePrediction { [ColumnName(\"Prediction\")] public float FareAmount; }`. `Evaluate` returns `RSquared = 0`. Why?","choices":["The test data is empty","`FastTree` writes its prediction to a column named `\"Score\"`, not `\"Prediction\"`","The model file is corrupted","The label column is missing"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Regression trainers write predictions to `\"Score\"`. Marking the field `[ColumnName(\"Prediction\")]` leaves `FareAmount` at zero — binding fails silently. Use `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]`.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-08","type":"MCQ","topic":"Single-row prediction factory","marks":1,"question":"Which method creates a single-row inference wrapper over a trained `ITransformer`?","choices":["`mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e(model)`","`mlContext.Inference.CreateEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e(model)`","`model.CreatePredictor\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e()`","`new PredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e(model)`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(model)` is the factory. The wrapper exposes `.Predict(row)`. The constructor form is internal; the other two are fabrications.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-09","type":"MCQ","topic":"Model persistence — save","marks":1,"question":"Which overload saves a trained model so it can be reloaded later?","choices":["`mlContext.Model.Save(model, path)`","`mlContext.Model.Save(model, dataView.Schema, path)`","`model.Save(path)`","`mlContext.Model.Export(model, path)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`Save(model, schema, path)` is the canonical overload — `DataViewSchema` carries column names/types needed to rehydrate the pipeline. Demo: `mlContext.Model.Save(model, dataView.Schema, _modelPath);`.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-10","type":"MCQ","topic":"Model persistence — load","marks":1,"question":"Which signature loads a saved `.zip` model back into memory?","choices":["`ITransformer m = mlContext.Model.Load(path)`","`ITransformer m = mlContext.Model.Load(path, out DataViewSchema schema)`","`ITransformer m = ITransformer.Load(path)`","`ITransformer m = new Transformer(path)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`Load(path, out DataViewSchema schema)` returns the model + yields the schema via out-parameter. Demo: `ITransformer trainedModel = mlContext.Model.Load(_modelPath, out modelSchema);`.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-11","type":"MCQ","topic":"LoadColumn indexing","marks":1,"question":"`public class TaxiTrip { [LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId; ... }`. What is the `0`?","choices":["The 1-based CSV column position","The 0-based CSV column index","The size of the column in bytes","The column's priority rank"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`[LoadColumn(N)]` is 0-based — the first CSV column is index 0. Contrast with ClosedXML where `Cell(1, 1)` is A1 (1-based). Mixing conventions when copying between them is where off-by-one bugs hide.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Models/TaxiTrip.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-mlnet-12","type":"MCQ","topic":"AutoML CLI flag","marks":1,"question":"Which flag sets AutoML's exploration budget?","choices":["`--dataset`","`--label-col`","`--train-time`","`--max-models`"],"correct":2,"rationale":"`--train-time 60` allocates 60 seconds to explore algorithm+hyperparameter combinations. `--dataset` is the CSV path; `--label-col` is the target column (index or name); `--max-models` isn't a flag.","source":"code-examples/TaxiFareAutoML","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-cache-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"IMemoryCache registration","marks":1,"question":"Which `Program.cs` call registers `IMemoryCache`?","choices":["`builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();`","`builder.Services.AddDistributedMemoryCache();`","`builder.Services.AddCache();`","`builder.Services.AddScoped\u003cIMemoryCache, MemoryCache\u003e();`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`AddMemoryCache()` registers the interface `IMemoryCache`. DataCacheDemo uses this. `AddDistributedMemoryCache()` registers `IDistributedCache` with an in-memory adapter (different interface, different scenarios).","source":"code-examples/20260330_DataCacheDemo/DataCacheDemo/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-cache-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"IMemoryCache lookup pattern","marks":1,"question":"Which pattern does DataCacheDemo use to check-then-fetch with `IMemoryCache`?","choices":["`var p = _cache.GetOrCreateAsync(key, factory);`","`if (!_cache.TryGetValue(key, out Product[]? products)) { products = await fetch(); _cache.Set(key, products, options); }`","`_cache.Read(key) ?? await fetch();`","`await _cache.PopulateAsync(key, factory);`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"DataCacheDemo `Index.cshtml.cs` uses `TryGetValue(key, out T? v)` + `Set(key, v, options)`. On miss, fetch and set with `MemoryCacheEntryOptions`. `GetOrCreateAsync` exists in ML.NET+ but wasn't demoed in the lab.","source":"code-examples/20260330_DataCacheDemo/DataCacheDemo/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-cache-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"MemoryCacheEntryOptions expiration","marks":1,"question":"`new MemoryCacheEntryOptions { AbsoluteExpiration = DateTime.Now.AddSeconds(50), SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(20) }`. The entry is never accessed after being set. When does it expire?","choices":["At t+50 seconds","At t+20 seconds — sliding expiration fires since no access reset it","It never expires because Priority wasn't set","Immediately — both options conflict"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The entry dies at `min(absolute, idle-since-last-access + sliding)`. With no access, sliding at t+20 fires first. If accessed at t+15, sliding resets and absolute at t+50 would eventually win.","source":"code-examples/20260330_DataCacheDemo/DataCacheDemo/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-cache-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"Priority semantics","marks":1,"question":"What does `CacheItemPriority.Low` mean for a cached entry?","choices":["The entry expires sooner than `Normal` entries","The entry is evicted first when the cache is under memory pressure","The entry is stored on disk instead of in memory","The entry is only visible to admin users"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Priority controls EVICTION order under memory pressure, not TTL. A `Low`-priority entry with a 1-hour absolute still lives 1 hour unless memory pressure forces eviction.","source":"code-examples/20260330_DataCacheDemo/DataCacheDemo/Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-cache-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"Redis registration","marks":1,"question":"Which Program.cs call registers `IDistributedCache` backed by Redis (per WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final)?","choices":["`builder.Services.AddRedis(\"localhost\");`","`builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =\u003e { options.Configuration = \"localhost\"; options.ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions { AbortOnConnectFail = true, EndPoints = { options.Configuration } }; });`","`builder.Services.AddDistributedCache(\"redis://localhost:6379\");`","`builder.Services.AddRedisClient(\"localhost\");`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`AddStackExchangeRedisCache(opts =\u003e ...)` registers `IDistributedCache` backed by Redis. The demo sets both `Configuration` and a `ConfigurationOptions` block with `AbortOnConnectFail = true` so missing Redis crashes startup instead of silently swallowing writes.","source":"code-examples/20260330_WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-cache-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"AbortOnConnectFail behavior","marks":1,"question":"With `AbortOnConnectFail = false` (the default), what happens when Redis is not running at app startup?","choices":["The app crashes immediately","Cache writes silently no-op; reads return null","The framework spawns a local Redis instance automatically","Writes fall back to in-process memory"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Default `false` means Stack Exchange Redis retries in the background and swallows failures. Cache writes succeed with no exception but no data lands in Redis. `true` crashes fast so orchestrators (containers) replace the unhealthy app.","source":"code-examples/20260330_WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/Program.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-cache-07","type":"MCQ","topic":"DistributedCacheExtensions.GetOrSetAsync","marks":1,"question":"The WebApiFIFA lab's `GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` extension does what on cache MISS?","choices":["Throws `KeyNotFoundException`","Invokes the factory lambda, stores the result as JSON bytes via `SetAsync`, returns the value","Returns `default(T)` immediately","Re-runs the DB query on every call regardless of cache state"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Check `TryGetValue` → if miss, `await factory()` → if result non-null, `await cache.SetAsync\u003cT\u003e(key, value, options)` → return. Internally `SetAsync\u003cT\u003e` serializes to JSON bytes via `Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(JsonSerializer.Serialize(value, ...))`.","source":"code-examples/20260330_WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/Models/DistributedCacheExtensions.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-cache-08","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache invalidation","marks":1,"question":"Users see stale games after an admin adds a new one via `POST /api/games`. Which line is missing from the `Add` handler?","choices":["`await cache.RefreshAsync(\"games\");`","`cache.Remove(\"games\");` after `SaveChangesAsync()`","`await cache.ReloadAsync();`","Nothing — TTL handles it automatically"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The `GameService.Add` handler in the lab explicitly calls `cache.Remove(\"games\");` after `SaveChangesAsync()`. Cache-aside requires manual invalidation on writes — TTL alone serves stale data until expiration.","source":"code-examples/20260330_WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/Models/GameService.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-file-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"Running a file-based app","marks":1,"question":"How do you run `Locations.cs` and pass `Kevin` as its first argument?","choices":["`dotnet run Locations.cs Kevin`","`dotnet run Locations.cs -- Kevin`","`dotnet Locations.cs --args Kevin`","`dotnet run --script Locations.cs Kevin`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The `--` separator routes arguments to the script rather than to `dotnet run`. Without `--`, `Kevin` would be interpreted as a flag to `dotnet` and never reach the script's `args`.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-2/HelloScript.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-file-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"Directive syntax","marks":1,"question":"Which of the following is VALID file-based-app directive syntax?","choices":["`#: package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`","`#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`","`//:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`","`@package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The `#:` prefix must be immediately followed by the directive name — no space. `#: package` fails. `//` is a C# comment; `@` isn't a directive marker.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-4/Locations.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-file-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"#:package directive","marks":1,"question":"Which directive adds the `Spectre.Console` NuGet package to a file-based app?","choices":["`#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`","`#:nuget Spectre.Console@0.49.1`","`#:using Spectre.Console`","`#:reference Spectre.Console`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`#:package \u003cName\u003e@\u003cVersion\u003e`. Omit the `@version` to get the latest stable (risky for reproducibility). No such directive as `#:nuget` or `#:reference`.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-4/Locations.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-file-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"#:property directive","marks":1,"question":"Which directive sets the target framework on a file-based app?","choices":["`#:property TargetFramework=net10.0`","`#:target net10.0`","`#:framework TargetFramework:net10.0`","`#:sdk TargetFramework=net10.0`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`#:property \u003cName\u003e=\u003cValue\u003e` sets MSBuild properties. Example-2 uses `#:property TargetFramework=net9.0`. No spaces around the `=`.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-2/HelloScript.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-file-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"#:sdk directive for web apps","marks":1,"question":"Which directive turns a file-based app into an ASP.NET Core minimal-API web host?","choices":["`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk`","`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`","`#:sdk Microsoft.AspNetCore.Sdk`","`#:sdk WebApplication`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` pulls in ASP.NET Core, making `WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)` resolvable. The default SDK (`Microsoft.NET.Sdk`) is console-only. `FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs` uses this directive.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs","bloom":"remember","tags":["pretest"]},{"id":"mq-file-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"#:project directive","marks":1,"question":"Which directive references a sibling .NET class library project?","choices":["`#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj`","`#:reference ./MyLibrary.dll`","`#:import ./MyLibrary/`","`#:using MyLibrary`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`#:project \u003crelative-path-to-.csproj\u003e`. Example-3 `Where.cs` uses `#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj` and then `using MyLibrary;` makes the `Person` type available.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-3/Where.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-file-07","type":"MCQ","topic":"Default console SDK limitation","marks":1,"question":"Your file-based app has `var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);` but no `#:sdk` directive. What happens at build?","choices":["Everything works — ASP.NET Core types are always available","Compile error: `WebApplication` not found","Runtime error when the first request arrives","The CLI auto-imports the Web SDK"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Without `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`, the default console SDK lacks ASP.NET Core types. The compile error is `type or namespace name 'WebApplication' not found`. `using` directives alone cannot import types that aren't in the referenced SDK.","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-file-08","type":"MCQ","topic":"File-based app — convert to project","marks":1,"question":"You've outgrown a single-file script. Which CLI command creates a traditional project from it?","choices":["`dotnet new console -n MyProj --from-file file.cs`","`dotnet project convert file.cs -o MyProj`","`dotnet migrate file.cs MyProj`","`dotnet publish file.cs --project MyProj`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`dotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder` creates a folder containing the `.csproj`, moves the `.cs` into it, and preserves each `#:` directive as its MSBuild equivalent.","source":"notes/file-based-apps.docx","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-grpc-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"Proto version syntax","marks":1,"question":"Which line declares the Protobuf version at the top of the W09 `students.proto`?","choices":["`version \"3\";`","`syntax = \"proto3\";`","`proto = \"3.0\";`","`#:proto 3`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`syntax = \"proto3\";` is the mandatory first line. Without it, `protoc` assumes proto2 (different defaults, different semantics).","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/Protos/students.proto","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-grpc-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"Proto field tags are permanent","marks":1,"question":"Your service has `message Person { string name = 1; int32 age = 2; }` deployed. You want to drop `age` and add `string email`. What is the SAFE rewrite?","choices":["`message Person { string name = 1; string email = 2; }`","`message Person { string name = 1; reserved 2; string email = 3; }`","`message Person { string email = 1; string name = 2; }`","`message Person { string name = 1; string email = 2; deprecated int32 age = 3; }`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Tags are permanent wire contracts. Reusing tag 2 for a new `string email` breaks every deployed client that interprets tag 2 as `int32 age`. Mark removed tags `reserved`, allocate a fresh tag (3) for new fields.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/Protos/students.proto","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-grpc-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"Server implementation — inheritance","marks":1,"question":"Which class does `StudentsService` inherit from in W09?","choices":["`StudentRemoteService`","`StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase`","`GrpcService\u003cStudentRemote\u003e`","`ServiceBase`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`Grpc.Tools` generates `[ServiceName].[ServiceName]Base` per service. The lab: `public class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase`.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/Services/StudentsService.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-grpc-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"Server method signature","marks":1,"question":"What is the signature of `GetStudentInfo` override in `StudentsService`?","choices":["`public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request)`","`public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request, ServerCallContext context)`","`public override StudentModel GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request)`","`public override async Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(HttpContext context)`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Every unary override takes `(Request, ServerCallContext)` and returns `Task\u003cResponse\u003e`. `ServerCallContext` is mandatory — it carries cancellation tokens, deadlines, and metadata.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/Services/StudentsService.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-grpc-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC server registration","marks":1,"question":"Which two calls register the gRPC stack and route to `StudentsService`?","choices":["`builder.Services.AddGrpc(); app.MapGrpcService\u003cStudentsService\u003e();`","`builder.Services.AddGrpcCore(); app.UseGrpcService\u003cStudentsService\u003e();`","`builder.Services.AddGrpc\u003cStudentsService\u003e(); app.MapGrpc();`","`builder.Services.AddService\u003cStudentsService\u003e(); app.UseGrpc();`"],"correct":0,"rationale":"`AddGrpc()` registers framework types. `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()` routes requests matching `/StudentRemote/...` to your service.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-grpc-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"Client project .csproj config","marks":1,"question":"A Blazor client project has `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e`. Build fails with `StudentRemoteClient not found`. Fix?","choices":["Add `\u003cGenerateClient\u003etrue\u003c/GenerateClient\u003e`","Flip to `GrpcServices=\"Client\"`","Rename the file to `client.proto`","Add `using Grpc.Client;`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`GrpcServices=\"Server\"` generates only the server base class. `\"Client\"` generates the callable stub. Use `\"Both\"` only when one project hosts both roles.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/BlazorGrpcClient/BlazorGrpcClient.csproj","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-grpc-07","type":"MCQ","topic":"Client DI with Aspire","marks":1,"question":"Which URL does the W09 Blazor client pass to `AddGrpcClient\u003cStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003e(opts =\u003e opts.Address = ...)`?","choices":["`new Uri(\"http://localhost:5099\")`","`new Uri(\"http://backend\")`","`new Uri(\"grpc://localhost\")`","`new Uri(builder.Configuration[\"GrpcUrl\"])`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"The lab uses `http://backend` — the Aspire logical name matching `AddProject\u003cProjects.GrpcStudentsServer\u003e(\"backend\")` in AppHost. Aspire's service discovery resolves it to the actual port at runtime.","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/BlazorGrpcClient/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-tdd-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD cycle","marks":1,"question":"In strict TDD, what is the correct order for each cycle?","choices":["Write code, write test, clean up","Red (failing test), Green (minimum code to pass), Refactor","Design, implement, test","Plan, prototype, harden"],"correct":1,"rationale":"TDD cycle: write a failing test (Red), write the minimum production code to pass (Green), refactor while tests stay green. Tests drive design, not the other way around.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-tdd-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"xUnit one-run test","marks":1,"question":"Which attribute marks an xUnit test method that runs once with no parameters?","choices":["`[Test]`","`[Fact]`","`[TestMethod]`","`[Case]`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`[Fact]` is xUnit's one-run attribute. `[Test]` is NUnit. `[TestMethod]` is MSTest. `[Case]` isn't a real attribute in any of the three frameworks.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.BackendTests/Financial/AccountTests.cs","bloom":"remember","tags":["pretest"]},{"id":"mq-tdd-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"xUnit parameterized test","marks":1,"question":"How do you parameterize an xUnit test with three inline input sets?","choices":["`[Fact]` three times with different suffixes","`[Theory]` + three `[InlineData(...)]` rows","`[TestCase(...)]` three times","`[DataRow(...)]` within a `[Fact]`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"xUnit's `[Theory]` + `[InlineData(args)]`. `[TestCase]` is NUnit; `[DataRow]` is MSTest. GoodBooks BaseServiceTests uses this pattern for the three `SequenceNumberTypes`.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.ServicesTests/BaseServiceTests.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-tdd-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"Assert argument order","marks":1,"question":"Which call order is correct for `Assert.Equal` in xUnit?","choices":["`Assert.Equal(actual, expected)`","`Assert.Equal(expected, actual)`","Either order works — the framework compares them","`Assert.Equal(value)` (single-arg)"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Expected first, actual second: `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)`. The compiler doesn't enforce order, but failure messages read `\"Expected: X, but was: Y\"` — swapped arguments mean the failure message blames the wrong value.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.BackendTests/Financial/AccountTests.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-tdd-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"Moq stub","marks":1,"question":"Which Moq call stubs a `Table` property to return an in-memory list?","choices":["`_mockRepo.Returns(r =\u003e r.Table, banks.AsQueryable());`","`_mockRepo.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(banks.AsQueryable());`","`_mockRepo.Stub(r =\u003e r.Table = banks.AsQueryable());`","`_mockRepo.Mock(r =\u003e r.Table, banks);`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(banks.AsQueryable())`. `Setup` expresses which member call to intercept (via expression tree); `Returns` supplies the value. Access the fake via `.Object`.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.ServicesTests/BaseServiceTests.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-tdd-06","type":"MCQ","topic":"Moq verification","marks":1,"question":"Which assertion fails the test if `Update` was never called?","choices":["`_mockRepo.Called(r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()));`","`_mockRepo.Verify(r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()), Times.Once);`","`Assert.Mock(_mockRepo, r =\u003e r.Update(...));`","`_mockRepo.Assert(r =\u003e r.Update(...));`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`.Verify(expr, Times.Once)` asserts the method was called exactly once. Other `Times` values: `Never`, `AtLeast(n)`, `AtMost(n)`, `Exactly(n)`.","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.ServicesTests/BaseServiceTests.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-aspire-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"AppHost builder type","marks":1,"question":"Which line creates the Aspire AppHost builder?","choices":["`var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);`","`var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);`","`var builder = Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args);`","`var builder = AspireApplication.Create(args);`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)` creates an orchestrator builder specifically for Aspire. `WebApplication.CreateBuilder` is for service projects, not the AppHost.","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/SoccerFIFA.AppHost/AppHost.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-aspire-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"WithReference + WaitFor","marks":1,"question":"What do `.WithReference(db)` and `.WaitFor(db)` do respectively?","choices":["Both inject the connection string; redundant","`WithReference` injects config as env-var; `WaitFor` delays startup until dependency reports healthy","`WithReference` runs migrations; `WaitFor` polls the DB","`WithReference` creates a firewall rule; `WaitFor` sets a timeout"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`WithReference` wires configuration (writes `ConnectionStrings__X` into the consumer's env); `WaitFor` delays the consumer's startup until the resource is healthy. Both are needed when the consumer can't survive a cold dependency.","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/SoccerFIFA.AppHost/AppHost.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-aspire-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"ServiceDefaults location","marks":1,"question":"Where does `builder.AddServiceDefaults()` belong?","choices":["In the AppHost's `Program.cs`","In each service project's `Program.cs`","In the `ServiceDefaults` class library's `Program.cs`","In `appsettings.json`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Each service project calls `builder.AddServiceDefaults()` at configure-time and `app.MapDefaultEndpoints()` at map-time. Putting it in AppHost breaks boot — the orchestrator tries to register OpenTelemetry + health checks on itself.","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/SoccerFIFA.ServiceDefaults/Extensions.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-aspire-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"/health vs /alive","marks":1,"question":"What is the difference between `/health` and `/alive` endpoints registered by `MapDefaultEndpoints`?","choices":["`/health` is for humans, `/alive` is for bots","`/health` requires all checks to pass (readiness); `/alive` requires only checks tagged `\"live\"` (liveness)","`/health` uses HTTPS, `/alive` uses HTTP","They are aliases — both do the same thing"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`/health` is readiness (route traffic or not). `/alive` is liveness (restart container or not) — only `\"live\"`-tagged checks count. Kubernetes maps them to `readinessProbe` and `livenessProbe`.","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/SoccerFIFA.ServiceDefaults/Extensions.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-aspire-05","type":"MCQ","topic":"Typed resource consumption","marks":1,"question":"AppHost has `builder.AddSqlServer(\"theserver\").AddDatabase(\"sqldata\")`. Which service-side call consumes the DB?","choices":["`builder.Services.AddDbContext\u003cT\u003e(opts =\u003e opts.UseSqlServer(\"sqldata\"));`","`builder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e(\"sqldata\");`","`builder.Services.AddSingleton\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e();`","`builder.Services.AddAspireDb(\"sqldata\");`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cT\u003e(\"sqldata\")` reads the Aspire-injected `ConnectionStrings__sqldata` env-var and wires EF Core with zero manual configuration. WebApiFIFA uses exactly this line.","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/WebApiFIFA/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-loc-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"AddLocalization resources path","marks":1,"question":"W10 registers `builder.Services.AddLocalization(options =\u003e options.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");`. What does `ResourcesPath` set?","choices":["The single `.resx` file to load","The root folder containing all `.resx` files","The namespace of the generated resource classes","The culture fallback chain"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`ResourcesPath` is the root folder under which the framework looks for per-class `.resx` files. `Resources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx` sits under this root.","source":"Labs/W10 Localization/Sports/Program.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-loc-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture","marks":1,"question":"Which statement is TRUE about `CurrentCulture` vs `CurrentUICulture`?","choices":["They are synonyms — setting one sets the other","`CurrentCulture` controls formatting (dates/numbers); `CurrentUICulture` controls which `.resx` loads","`CurrentCulture` is global; `CurrentUICulture` is per-request","`CurrentUICulture` is for server-side; `CurrentCulture` is for client-side"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`CurrentCulture` drives formatting (`.ToString()`, `decimal.ToString(\"C\")`). `CurrentUICulture` drives resource-file selection (`IStringLocalizer[...]`). Setting only one leaves the other at default — why `SupportedCultures` AND `SupportedUICultures` must both be configured.","source":"Labs/W10 Localization/Sports/Program.cs","bloom":"understand"},{"id":"mq-loc-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"UseRequestLocalization missing","marks":1,"question":"`AddLocalization`, `Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e`, `AddViewLocalization` are all registered. Users report language never switches. What is the single most likely missing line?","choices":["`app.UseLocalization();`","`app.UseRequestLocalization();`","`app.UseCulture();`","`app.MapLocalization();`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`UseRequestLocalization()` is the middleware that actually runs the culture providers per request and sets `CurrentCulture` + `CurrentUICulture`. Without it, every request falls through to the default culture silently.","source":"Labs/W10 Localization/Sports/Program.cs","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-loc-04","type":"MCQ","topic":"IViewLocalizer injection site","marks":1,"question":"Which directive injects `IViewLocalizer` into a `.cshtml` file?","choices":["`@using IViewLocalizer`","`@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer`","`@addTagHelper IViewLocalizer`","`@model IViewLocalizer`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`@inject TypeName Name` — here `@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer`. Then use as `@Localizer[\"Key\"]`. Requires `AddViewLocalization()` in Program.cs.","source":"notes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-tag-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"Base class","marks":1,"question":"Which class does ToonTagDemo's `ToonTag` inherit from?","choices":["`Controller`","`TagHelper`","`Component`","`RazorComponent`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"All custom Tag Helpers inherit from `TagHelper` (in `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers`).","source":"code-examples/ToonTagDemo/ToonTagDemo/TagHelpers/ToonTag.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-tag-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"PascalCase to kebab-case","marks":1,"question":"A Tag Helper has `public string? FontFamily { get; set; }`. Which HTML attribute binds to it?","choices":["`fontfamily`","`FontFamily`","`font-family`","`font_family`"],"correct":2,"rationale":"Razor auto-translates PascalCase to kebab-case. `FontFamily` → `font-family`. Usage: `\u003ctoon font-family=\"arial\"\u003e`.","source":"code-examples/ToonTagDemo/ToonTagDemo/TagHelpers/ToonTag.cs","bloom":"apply"},{"id":"mq-tag-03","type":"MCQ","topic":"_ViewImports registration","marks":1,"question":"Which directive in `_ViewImports.cshtml` registers a specific Tag Helper type by name?","choices":["`@using ToonTagDemo.TagHelpers`","`@addTagHelper \"ToonTagDemo.TagHelpers.ToonTag, ToonTagDemo\"`","`@registerTagHelper ToonTag`","`@inject ToonTag`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`@addTagHelper \"FullTypeName, AssemblyName\"` registers one helper. Wildcard form: `@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName`. `_ViewImports.cshtml` is the canonical location — not per-page.","source":"code-examples/ToonTagDemo/ToonTagDemo/Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-quickgrid-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"Paginator binding","marks":1,"question":"The W07 server lab declares `private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 15 };`. Which line renders the paginator controls?","choices":["`\u003cPaginator Pagination=\"@pagination\" /\u003e`","`\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e`","`\u003cPaginator Items=\"@pagination\" /\u003e`","`\u003cPaginationControl State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"Server lab uses `\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e`. The BlazorSchool WASM variant uses `Value=\"@pages\"\u003e` — both valid, attribute name differs per template.","source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/BlazorStudents/Components/Pages/StudentPages/Index.razor","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-quickgrid-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"Live filter binding","marks":1,"question":"Why does the W07 lab pair `@bind=\"FilterValue\"` with `@bind:event=\"oninput\"`?","choices":["Performance optimization","`@bind` alone defaults to `onchange` which only fires on focus loss — `oninput` fires on each keystroke for live filtering","Required by `QuickGrid` framework","To enable server-side validation"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`@bind` defaults to `onchange` — binding only updates when the input loses focus. Live filtering needs `@bind:event=\"oninput\"` so each keystroke refreshes `FilterValue` and triggers re-evaluation of `FilteredStudents`.","source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/BlazorStudents/Components/Pages/StudentPages/Index.razor","bloom":"analyze"},{"id":"mq-report-01","type":"MCQ","topic":"ClosedXML cell indexing","marks":1,"question":"In W13's `Excel.cshtml.cs`, `worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Game Id\"` writes to which Excel cell?","choices":["`A0`","`A1`","`B1`","`B2`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"ClosedXML is 1-based and matches Excel's UI labels. `Cell(row=1, col=1)` = A1. Contrast with `[LoadColumn(N)]` in ML.NET which is 0-based — easy confusion when copying between readers.","source":"Labs/w13/FifaWorldCup/Pages/Excel.cshtml.cs","bloom":"remember"},{"id":"mq-report-02","type":"MCQ","topic":"PDF MemoryStream rewind","marks":1,"question":"Your iText 7 handler constructs a `PdfWriter(ms)` → `PdfDocument` → `Document`, adds content, calls `document.Close()`, then returns `new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\")`. Users download zero-byte files. What is missing?","choices":["Adding `await` before `document.Close()`","Setting `ms.Position = 0` after `document.Close()` and before constructing `FileStreamResult`","Calling `writer.Flush()` before `Close`","Passing `PageSize.A4` to `PdfDocument`"],"correct":1,"rationale":"`PdfWriter` advances `MemoryStream.Position` to the end. `FileStreamResult` reads from current position to end — zero bytes. Always `ms.Position = 0` before returning, or use `File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"name.pdf\")` which is position-insensitive.","source":"Labs/w13/FifaWorldCup/Pages/PdfReport.cshtml.cs","bloom":"analyze"}]},"lessons":[{"n":0,"id":"4870-exam-strategy","title":"Exam strategy and pitfalls","hook":"Time allocation, top pitfalls, when to skip.","tags":["strategy","exam-prep"],"module":"Exam prep","kind":"strategy","source":"courses/COMP4870/4870 final exam details.txt + materials/past-exams/midterm_exam_questions.md + materials/notes/* + generated/exam-study/research-*.md","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"The exam in one sentence","text":"The exam in one sentence"},{"kind":"p","html":"80 marks, 60 minutes, single room (SE12-327), Friday 2026-04-24 10:30–11:30 AM. Bring one hand-written 8.5&quot; × 11&quot; cheat sheet — both sides fair game.","text":"80 marks, 60 minutes, single room (SE12-327), Friday 2026-04-24 10:30–11:30 AM. Bring one hand-written 8.5\" × 11\" cheat sheet — both sides fair game."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Format and marks","text":"Format and marks"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eSection\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth align=\"right\"\u003eCount\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth align=\"right\"\u003eMarks each\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth align=\"right\"\u003eSection marks\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth align=\"right\"\u003eTime budget\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMultiple choice\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e60\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e60\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e~40 min\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMatch two columns\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e~5 min\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCoding question\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e~12 min\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eReview / skipped\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e—\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e—\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e—\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e~3 min\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTotal\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e71\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e—\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e80\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd align=\"right\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e60 min\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"The MCQ + match pool covers 11 pre-announced topics. The coding question&#39;s topic is not announced — assume it comes from one of the heavy buckets (AI, ML.NET, Cache/Redis, File-based apps, or gRPC).","text":"The MCQ + match pool covers 11 pre-announced topics. The coding question's topic is not announced — assume it comes from one of the heavy buckets (AI, ML.NET, Cache/Redis, File-based apps, or gRPC)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Topic weights — where the marks live","text":"Topic weights — where the marks live"},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"AI ................ 13 marks (16%)   ← heaviest; MAF + Semantic Kernel + SLM/Ollama\nML.NET ............ 12 marks (15%)   ← pipeline + metrics\nCache/Redis ....... 8 marks  (10%)\nFile-based apps ... 8 marks  (10%)\ngRPC .............. 7 marks  (9%)\nTDD ............... 6 marks  (8%)\nAspire ............ 5 marks  (6%)\nLocalization ...... 4 marks  (5%)\nTag Helpers ....... 3 marks  (4%)\nBlazor (QuickGrid)  2 marks  (3%)\nExcel/PDF/Chart ... 2 marks  (3%)"},{"kind":"p","html":"Study proportionally. If the cheat sheet is 8.5&quot; × 11&quot; double-sided, AI + ML.NET + Cache/Redis together deserve ~40% of the real estate.","text":"Study proportionally. If the cheat sheet is 8.5\" × 11\" double-sided, AI + ML.NET + Cache/Redis together deserve ~40% of the real estate."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Time allocation per question","text":"Time allocation per question"},{"kind":"p","html":"The 60-minute clock breaks down as 45 seconds per mark. In practice, not every mark burns 45 seconds — MCQ/match questions average ~40 seconds; the coding question gets the remaining block.","text":"The 60-minute clock breaks down as 45 seconds per mark. In practice, not every mark burns 45 seconds — MCQ/match questions average ~40 seconds; the coding question gets the remaining block."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMCQ rhythm.\u003c/strong\u003e Read the stem twice. If the answer leaps out within 15 seconds, commit and move on. If not, eliminate the two most obviously wrong choices, mark the remaining two with a dot on the paper, and move on. Come back to dotted questions in the review pass.","text":"**MCQ rhythm.** Read the stem twice. If the answer leaps out within 15 seconds, commit and move on. If not, eliminate the two most obviously wrong choices, mark the remaining two with a dot on the paper, and move on. Come back to dotted questions in the review pass."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMatch rhythm.\u003c/strong\u003e Scan all 10 pairs before committing to any. Start with pairs where one side is unique jargon (e.g. a specific CLI command, a specific NuGet package). Work from certainty outward.","text":"**Match rhythm.** Scan all 10 pairs before committing to any. Start with pairs where one side is unique jargon (e.g. a specific CLI command, a specific NuGet package). Work from certainty outward."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eCoding rhythm.\u003c/strong\u003e Read the prompt fully before touching the pen. Sketch the signature, write the body, then cross-check edge cases. Twelve minutes is tight — don&#39;t aim for the most elegant solution, aim for the most correct one.","text":"**Coding rhythm.** Read the prompt fully before touching the pen. Sketch the signature, write the body, then cross-check edge cases. Twelve minutes is tight — don't aim for the most elegant solution, aim for the most correct one."},{"kind":"h2","html":"When to skip and return","text":"When to skip and return"},{"kind":"p","html":"Skip any question that:","text":"Skip any question that:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBurns more than 90 seconds without a clear path. Two skipped questions cost ~90 seconds; two wrong-but-committed questions cost 2 marks. Skipping is cheaper.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHinges on a term you genuinely don&#39;t recognize. Distractors target confusion; without a foothold, guessing among five options is a 20% hit rate.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUses a code-fence stem longer than five lines. These are traps dressed as tests — come back when your head is fresh.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Burns more than 90 seconds without a clear path. Two skipped questions cost ~90 seconds; two wrong-but-committed questions cost 2 marks. Skipping is cheaper.\n- Hinges on a term you genuinely don't recognize. Distractors target confusion; without a foothold, guessing among five options is a 20% hit rate.\n- Uses a code-fence stem longer than five lines. These are traps dressed as tests — come back when your head is fresh."},{"kind":"p","html":"Mark skips with a single dot in the margin. At minute 45, do a focused review pass on dotted questions only.","text":"Mark skips with a single dot in the margin. At minute 45, do a focused review pass on dotted questions only."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Top pitfalls — by topic","text":"Top pitfalls — by topic"},{"kind":"p","html":"Every pitfall below is sourced from lecture scripts, research notes, or the midterm&#39;s distractor patterns. No invented hazards.","text":"Every pitfall below is sourced from lecture scripts, research notes, or the midterm's distractor patterns. No invented hazards."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall 1 — \u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e has no space after the colon.\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003e#: package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\u003c/code\u003e is a syntax error. The correct form is \u003ccode\u003e#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\u003c/code\u003e. Expect at least one distractor option presenting the spaced form as plausible. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/file-based-apps.docx\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eresearch-file-based.md §directives\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Pitfall 1 — `#:package` has no space after the colon.**\n`#: package Spectre.Console@0.49.1` is a syntax error. The correct form is `#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1`. Expect at least one distractor option presenting the spaced form as plausible. Source: `notes/file-based-apps.docx`; `research-file-based.md §directives`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall 2 — \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e does not survive a web farm.\u003c/strong\u003e\nWhen asked &quot;which cache abstraction works across multiple app servers behind a load balancer,&quot; the answer is \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e (backed by Redis), not \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e is per-process; each server holds its own copy, so data written on server A is invisible on server B. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/DataCache_SCRIPT.docx\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eresearch-cache.md §architecture\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Pitfall 2 — `IMemoryCache` does not survive a web farm.**\nWhen asked \"which cache abstraction works across multiple app servers behind a load balancer,\" the answer is `IDistributedCache` (backed by Redis), not `IMemoryCache`. `IMemoryCache` is per-process; each server holds its own copy, so data written on server A is invisible on server B. Source: `notes/DataCache_SCRIPT.docx`; `research-cache.md §architecture`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall 3 — ML.NET trainers look for a column literally named \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003emlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(outputColumnName: &quot;Features&quot;, …)\u003c/code\u003e — the string \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e is not a convention, it&#39;s a contract. Rename it to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Input&quot;\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e&quot;X&quot;\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eFastTree()\u003c/code\u003e cannot find the input. Same goes for \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e on the target side. Source: \u003ccode\u003eslides/ML.NET.pptx p.14\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eresearch-mlnet.md §transforms\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Pitfall 3 — ML.NET trainers look for a column literally named `\"Features\"`.**\n`mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(outputColumnName: \"Features\", …)` — the string `\"Features\"` is not a convention, it's a contract. Rename it to `\"Input\"` or `\"X\"` and `FastTree()` cannot find the input. Same goes for `\"Label\"` on the target side. Source: `slides/ML.NET.pptx p.14`; `research-mlnet.md §transforms`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall 4 — \u003ccode\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e are not the same thing.\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e drives date, number, and currency formatting. \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e drives which \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e file loads. Setting only one produces a page where numbers are translated but text is not (or vice versa). \u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e sets both when configured correctly; forgetting the middleware call leaves both at system default. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eresearch-localization.md\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Pitfall 4 — `CurrentCulture` and `CurrentUICulture` are not the same thing.**\n`CurrentCulture` drives date, number, and currency formatting. `CurrentUICulture` drives which `.resx` file loads. Setting only one produces a page where numbers are translated but text is not (or vice versa). `UseRequestLocalization()` sets both when configured correctly; forgetting the middleware call leaves both at system default. Source: `notes/razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx`; `research-localization.md`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall 5 — \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e belongs in each service&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e, NOT in the AppHost.\u003c/strong\u003e\nThe AppHost&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e calls \u003ccode\u003eDistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)\u003c/code\u003e and then \u003ccode\u003e.AddProject&lt;&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e. Each individual service&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e calls \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.AddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e to pick up service discovery, OpenTelemetry, and health endpoints. Swapping these breaks the boot. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/aspire_SCRIPT.docx\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eresearch-aspire.md §defaults\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Pitfall 5 — `AddServiceDefaults()` belongs in each service's `Program.cs`, NOT in the AppHost.**\nThe AppHost's `Program.cs` calls `DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)` and then `.AddProject\u003c\u003e()`. Each individual service's `Program.cs` calls `builder.AddServiceDefaults()` to pick up service discovery, OpenTelemetry, and health endpoints. Swapping these breaks the boot. Source: `notes/aspire_SCRIPT.docx`; `research-aspire.md §defaults`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Domain-specific traps — beyond the top 5","text":"Domain-specific traps — beyond the top 5"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMemoryStream position.\u003c/strong\u003e When returning a \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e for a PDF or XLSX you just wrote into a \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e, set \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e before returning. Skip the reset and the client downloads an empty file. Source: \u003ccode\u003eresearch-excel-pdf-chart.md §pdf\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**MemoryStream position.** When returning a `FileStreamResult` for a PDF or XLSX you just wrote into a `MemoryStream`, set `ms.Position = 0` before returning. Skip the reset and the client downloads an empty file. Source: `research-excel-pdf-chart.md §pdf`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eiText7 + bouncy-castle-adapter.\u003c/strong\u003e iText7 alone won&#39;t run — you need both \u003ccode\u003eiText7\u003c/code\u003e AND \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e NuGet packages. Forgetting the adapter produces a cryptic runtime error, not a build error. Source: \u003ccode\u003eresearch-excel-pdf-chart.md\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**iText7 + bouncy-castle-adapter.** iText7 alone won't run — you need both `iText7` AND `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter` NuGet packages. Forgetting the adapter produces a cryptic runtime error, not a build error. Source: `research-excel-pdf-chart.md`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003exUnit \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e argument order.\u003c/strong\u003e Expected first, actual second. Reversing produces backwards error messages that waste debugging time. The argument order is not enforced by the compiler. Source: \u003ccode\u003eslides/TDD_xunit.pptx\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**xUnit `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` argument order.** Expected first, actual second. Reversing produces backwards error messages that waste debugging time. The argument order is not enforced by the compiler. Source: `slides/TDD_xunit.pptx`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eProtocol Buffer field tags are permanent.\u003c/strong\u003e Reusing a tag number for a different field breaks every deployed client that hasn&#39;t recompiled. Tags 1–15 are also special — they encode in one byte; tags 16+ take two. Source: \u003ccode\u003eresearch-grpc.md\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Protocol Buffer field tags are permanent.** Reusing a tag number for a different field breaks every deployed client that hasn't recompiled. Tags 1–15 are also special — they encode in one byte; tags 16+ take two. Source: `research-grpc.md`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eClosedXML cell indexing is 1-based.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eworksheet.Cell(1, 1)\u003c/code\u003e is the top-left cell. Not \u003ccode\u003e(0, 0)\u003c/code\u003e. Source: \u003ccode\u003eLabs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail.html\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**ClosedXML cell indexing is 1-based.** `worksheet.Cell(1, 1)` is the top-left cell. Not `(0, 0)`. Source: `Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail.html`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eRoute attribute syntax uses parentheses, not brackets.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e[Route(&quot;api/[controller]&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e is correct. \u003ccode\u003e[Route[&quot;api/[controller]&quot;]]\u003c/code\u003e is a midterm distractor pattern (Q7) — it uses C# indexer syntax instead of method-call syntax. Carries forward into any final-exam routing question. Source: \u003ccode\u003ematerials/past-exams/midterm_exam_questions.md Q7\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Route attribute syntax uses parentheses, not brackets.** `[Route(\"api/[controller]\")]` is correct. `[Route[\"api/[controller]\"]]` is a midterm distractor pattern (Q7) — it uses C# indexer syntax instead of method-call syntax. Carries forward into any final-exam routing question. Source: `materials/past-exams/midterm_exam_questions.md Q7`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eBlazor \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e needs \u003ccode\u003eSortBy=\u003c/code\u003e, not \u003ccode\u003eSortable=\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003e accepts \u003ccode\u003eSortable=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e directly. \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e ignores \u003ccode\u003eSortable\u003c/code\u003e — you must supply \u003ccode\u003eSortBy=&quot;@GridSort&lt;T&gt;.ByAscending(x =&gt; x.Name)&quot;\u003c/code\u003e to make it sortable. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/BlazorServer_QuickGrid.docx\u003c/code\u003e; Labs/W07.","text":"**Blazor `TemplateColumn` needs `SortBy=`, not `Sortable=`.** `PropertyColumn` accepts `Sortable=\"true\"` directly. `TemplateColumn` ignores `Sortable` — you must supply `SortBy=\"@GridSort\u003cT\u003e.ByAscending(x =\u003e x.Name)\"` to make it sortable. Source: `notes/BlazorServer_QuickGrid.docx`; Labs/W07."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eAI endpoint confusion.\u003c/strong\u003e Ollama runs at \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:11434\u003c/code\u003e (HTTP, no path). GitHub Models runs at \u003ccode\u003ehttps://models.github.ai/inference\u003c/code\u003e (HTTPS, has \u003ccode\u003e/inference\u003c/code\u003e path). Azure OpenAI uses your deployment-specific URL plus a deployment name. Mixing these is a distractor gift. Source: \u003ccode\u003enotes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**AI endpoint confusion.** Ollama runs at `http://localhost:11434` (HTTP, no path). GitHub Models runs at `https://models.github.ai/inference` (HTTPS, has `/inference` path). Azure OpenAI uses your deployment-specific URL plus a deployment name. Mixing these is a distractor gift. Source: `notes/AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent()\u003c/code\u003e, not \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The MAF method to wrap an \u003ccode\u003eIChatClient\u003c/code\u003e into an agent is literally \u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent()\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e doesn&#39;t exist. Source: \u003ccode\u003eresearch-ai.md §maf\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**`.AsAIAgent()`, not `.AsAgent()`.** The MAF method to wrap an `IChatClient` into an agent is literally `.AsAIAgent()`. `.AsAgent()` doesn't exist. Source: `research-ai.md §maf`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Off-by-one, unit, and ordering traps specific to this course","text":"Off-by-one, unit, and ordering traps specific to this course"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eClosedXML\u003c/code\u003e cells are 1-based\u003c/strong\u003e; C# arrays and \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e are 0-based. Mixing these breaks row/column math.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(0)]\u003c/code\u003e on the first column\u003c/strong\u003e of a CSV in ML.NET is 0-based despite ClosedXML&#39;s opposite convention. Don&#39;t generalize across libraries.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProtobuf field tags start at 1\u003c/strong\u003e, not 0. Tag 0 is reserved.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePort 11434 for Ollama, 6379 for Redis, 1433 for SQL Server, 5432 for Postgres.\u003c/strong\u003e Aspire tends to pick ephemeral ports unless overridden — don&#39;t memorize ports for Aspire-managed services; memorize for stand-alone Docker runs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- **`ClosedXML` cells are 1-based**; C# arrays and `List\u003cT\u003e` are 0-based. Mixing these breaks row/column math.\n- **`[LoadColumn(0)]` on the first column** of a CSV in ML.NET is 0-based despite ClosedXML's opposite convention. Don't generalize across libraries.\n- **Protobuf field tags start at 1**, not 0. Tag 0 is reserved.\n- **Port 11434 for Ollama, 6379 for Redis, 1433 for SQL Server, 5432 for Postgres.** Aspire tends to pick ephemeral ports unless overridden — don't memorize ports for Aspire-managed services; memorize for stand-alone Docker runs."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Cheat-sheet packing priorities","text":"Cheat-sheet packing priorities"},{"kind":"p","html":"Given one 8.5&quot; × 11&quot; page, two sides, prioritize this order. Items above the cut line are high-leverage per mark; below the cut line are nice-to-haves if space permits.","text":"Given one 8.5\" × 11\" page, two sides, prioritize this order. Items above the cut line are high-leverage per mark; below the cut line are nice-to-haves if space permits."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eML.NET pipeline skeleton\u003c/strong\u003e — every token of \u003ccode\u003eLoadFromTextFile → Concatenate(&quot;Features&quot;) → FastTree().Fit(data)\u003c/code\u003e. Boilerplate you shouldn&#39;t derive under time pressure.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMAF + Ollama 10-line boot snippet\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eOllamaApiClient\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.AsIChatClient()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eChatClientAgent\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.RunAsync\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGetOrSetAsync\u003c/code\u003e signature + absolute/sliding expiration option object.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e file template\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003esyntax = &quot;proto3&quot;; service Foo { rpc Bar (X) returns (Y); } message X { int32 id = 1; }\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAspire AppHost skeleton\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eCreateBuilder → AddProject&lt;&gt;(&quot;name&quot;) → WithReference → WaitFor\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement]\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eProcessAsync\u003c/code\u003e signature\u003c/strong\u003e for a tag helper.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLocalization setup three calls\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddViewLocalization\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFile-based apps directive quick-reference\u003c/strong\u003e — four directive forms, no-space-after-colon reminder.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003exUnit attribute cheat row\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData(...)]\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eQuickGrid column syntax\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eClosedXML \u003ccode\u003eworksheet.Cell(r, c).Value = x; wb.SaveAs(stream)\u003c/code\u003e one-liner.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eiText7 \u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter → PdfDocument → Document\u003c/code\u003e three-line open; \u003ccode\u003edoc.Close()\u003c/code\u003e close.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **ML.NET pipeline skeleton** — every token of `LoadFromTextFile → Concatenate(\"Features\") → FastTree().Fit(data)`. Boilerplate you shouldn't derive under time pressure.\n2. **MAF + Ollama 10-line boot snippet** — `OllamaApiClient` → `.AsIChatClient()` → `ChatClientAgent` → `.RunAsync`.\n3. **`GetOrSetAsync` signature + absolute/sliding expiration option object.**\n4. **`.proto` file template** — `syntax = \"proto3\"; service Foo { rpc Bar (X) returns (Y); } message X { int32 id = 1; }`.\n5. **Aspire AppHost skeleton** — `CreateBuilder → AddProject\u003c\u003e(\"name\") → WithReference → WaitFor`.\n6. **`[HtmlTargetElement]` + `ProcessAsync` signature** for a tag helper.\n7. **Localization setup three calls** — `AddLocalization`, `AddViewLocalization`, `UseRequestLocalization`.\n8. **File-based apps directive quick-reference** — four directive forms, no-space-after-colon reminder.\n9. **xUnit attribute cheat row** — `[Fact]`, `[Theory]` + `[InlineData(...)]`.\n10. **QuickGrid column syntax** — `PropertyColumn` vs `TemplateColumn` with `SortBy`.\n11. **ClosedXML `worksheet.Cell(r, c).Value = x; wb.SaveAs(stream)` one-liner.**\n12. **iText7 `PdfWriter → PdfDocument → Document` three-line open; `doc.Close()` close.**"},{"kind":"p","html":"Do NOT waste space on:","text":"Do NOT waste space on:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAnything you can reason about in under 30 seconds from a memorized concept (e.g. &quot;what&#39;s a Bloom filter&quot; — no, skip that, it&#39;s not on the exam anyway).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFull paragraphs of prose — the cheat sheet is for code skeletons and naming conventions, not textbook passages.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTopics from the midterm (Razor, MVC, EF foundations, Identity, JWT, SignalR) — they&#39;re \u003cstrong\u003eout of scope\u003c/strong\u003e for the final.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Anything you can reason about in under 30 seconds from a memorized concept (e.g. \"what's a Bloom filter\" — no, skip that, it's not on the exam anyway).\n- Full paragraphs of prose — the cheat sheet is for code skeletons and naming conventions, not textbook passages.\n- Topics from the midterm (Razor, MVC, EF foundations, Identity, JWT, SignalR) — they're **out of scope** for the final."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eThe midterm covered Razor Pages, MVC, Entity Framework foundations, Identity, JWT, and SignalR — none of those are on the final. If the cheat sheet you prepared for midterms is still in your head, consciously drop it. Re-studying midterm material costs time you need for AI + ML.NET.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"The midterm covered Razor Pages, MVC, Entity Framework foundations, Identity, JWT, and SignalR — none of those are on the final. If the cheat sheet you prepared for midterms is still in your head, consciously drop it. Re-studying midterm material costs time you need for AI + ML.NET."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eThe final rewards \u003cem\u003especific\u003c/em\u003e recall of NuGet names, CLI shapes, and API method names. 70% of MCQ distractors are subtle renames of the correct answer. A cheat sheet that lists exact names and exact call signatures beats a cheat sheet that explains concepts. Teach yourself to flip to the sheet fast enough that the 60-second-per-question budget holds.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"The final rewards *specific* recall of NuGet names, CLI shapes, and API method names. 70% of MCQ distractors are subtle renames of the correct answer. A cheat sheet that lists exact names and exact call signatures beats a cheat sheet that explains concepts. Teach yourself to flip to the sheet fast enough that the 60-second-per-question budget holds."}]},{"n":1,"id":"ai-semantic-kernel","title":"Semantic Kernel + GitHub Models","hook":"Wire GitHub Models into Razor Pages with `AddKernel()` and inject `IChatCompletionService`.","tags":["ai","semantic-kernel","github-models"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"Labs/W02 AI on Github/GitHubAiModelSK/Program.cs + Pages/Index.cshtml.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"W02 wiring — Program.cs","text":"W02 wiring — Program.cs"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.SemanticKernel;\nusing OpenAI;\nusing System.ClientModel;\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar modelId   = builder.Configuration[\"AI:Model\"]!;\nvar uri       = builder.Configuration[\"AI:Endpoint\"]!;\nvar githubPAT = builder.Configuration[\"AI:PAT\"]!;\n\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(githubPAT),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(uri) });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client);\nbuilder.Services.AddKernel();\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages();\nbuilder.Services.AddDistributedMemoryCache();\nbuilder.Services.AddSession();"},{"kind":"p","html":"Five moves:","text":"Five moves:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRead \u003ccode\u003eAI:Model\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAI:Endpoint\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAI:PAT\u003c/code\u003e from \u003ccode\u003eappsettings.json\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild \u003ccode\u003eOpenAIClient\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e (from \u003ccode\u003eSystem.ClientModel\u003c/code\u003e) + \u003ccode\u003eEndpoint\u003c/code\u003e override.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client)\u003c/code\u003e registers chat service.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddKernel()\u003c/code\u003e registers Kernel + deps in DI.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddSession()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eAddDistributedMemoryCache()\u003c/code\u003e persist \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e across HTTP requests.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. Read `AI:Model`, `AI:Endpoint`, `AI:PAT` from `appsettings.json`.\n2. Build `OpenAIClient` with `ApiKeyCredential` (from `System.ClientModel`) + `Endpoint` override.\n3. `AddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client)` registers chat service.\n4. `AddKernel()` registers Kernel + deps in DI.\n5. `AddSession()` + `AddDistributedMemoryCache()` persist `ChatHistory` across HTTP requests."},{"kind":"p","html":"Only one NuGet: \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.SemanticKernel\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Only one NuGet: `Microsoft.SemanticKernel`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"PageModel — inject \u003ccode\u003eIChatCompletionService\u003c/code\u003e","text":"PageModel — inject `IChatCompletionService`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.SemanticKernel.ChatCompletion;\n\npublic class IndexModel : PageModel\n{\n    private readonly IChatCompletionService _chat;\n    public IndexModel(IChatCompletionService chat) =\u003e _chat = chat;\n\n    [BindProperty] public string? UserMessage { get; set; }\n    public List\u003cChatEntry\u003e ChatMessages { get; set; } = new();\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Build ChatHistory + stream","text":"Build ChatHistory + stream"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e constructor takes system prompt directly:","text":"`ChatHistory` constructor takes system prompt directly:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"ChatHistory chat = new(@\"\n    You are an AI assistant that helps people find information.\n    The response must be brief and should not exceed one paragraph.\n    If you do not know the answer then simply say 'I do not know the answer'.\");\n\nforeach (var entry in chatEntries)\n{\n    if (entry.Role == \"User\") chat.AddUserMessage(entry.Message);\n    else                      chat.AddAssistantMessage(entry.Message);\n}\n\nchat.AddUserMessage(UserMessage);\n\nStringBuilder sb = new();\nawait foreach (var message in _chat.GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync(chat))\n{\n    sb.Append(message.Content);\n}\nvar response = sb.ToString();"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Session persistence","text":"Session persistence"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var historyJson = HttpContext.Session.GetString(\"ChatHistory\");\nvar chatEntries = string.IsNullOrEmpty(historyJson)\n    ? new List\u003cChatEntry\u003e()\n    : System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cChatEntry\u003e\u003e(historyJson)!;\n\n// ... run turn, append User + Assistant entries ...\n\nHttpContext.Session.SetString(\"ChatHistory\",\n    System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(chatEntries));"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eChatEntry\u003c/code\u003e is a local POCO (\u003ccode\u003eRole\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eMessage\u003c/code\u003e).","text":"`ChatEntry` is a local POCO (`Role`, `Message`)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"GitHub Models endpoint config","text":"GitHub Models endpoint config"},{"kind":"code","lang":"json","code":"{\n  \"AI\": {\n    \"Model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"Endpoint\": \"https://models.github.ai/inference\",\n    \"PAT\": \"github_pat_...\"\n  }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHTTPS + \u003ccode\u003e/inference\u003c/code\u003e suffix required\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eModel id format: vendor prefix (\u003ccode\u003eopenai/gpt-4o-mini\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCredential: GitHub PAT passed through \u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- HTTPS + `/inference` suffix required\n- Model id format: vendor prefix (`openai/gpt-4o-mini`)\n- Credential: GitHub PAT passed through `ApiKeyCredential`"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Which credential class authenticates GitHub Models in W02?","a":"`ApiKeyCredential` (from `System.ClientModel`). `OpenAIClient` ctor takes it + `OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(uri) }`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eLab does NOT use \u003ccode\u003eKernelBuilder\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder()\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eImportPluginFromType&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[KernelFunction]\u003c/code\u003e, or \u003ccode\u003eskprompt.txt\u003c/code\u003e. Those are SK features but out of scope of what was demoed.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Lab does NOT use `KernelBuilder`, `Kernel.CreateBuilder()`, `ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e()`, `[KernelFunction]`, or `skprompt.txt`. Those are SK features but out of scope of what was demoed."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003eAzureKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eAzureKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e belongs to \u003ccode\u003eAzure.AI.Inference\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eChatCompletionsClient\u003c/code\u003e — different SDK.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`ApiKeyCredential` NOT `AzureKeyCredential`. `AzureKeyCredential` belongs to `Azure.AI.Inference` / `ChatCompletionsClient` — different SDK."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eSK wiring in W02: \u003ccode\u003eOpenAIClient(ApiKeyCredential(pat), { Endpoint })\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eAddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eAddKernel()\u003c/code\u003e → inject \u003ccode\u003eIChatCompletionService\u003c/code\u003e → build \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory(systemPrompt)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eGetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"SK wiring in W02: `OpenAIClient(ApiKeyCredential(pat), { Endpoint })` → `AddOpenAIChatCompletion(modelId, client)` → `AddKernel()` → inject `IChatCompletionService` → build `ChatHistory(systemPrompt)` → `GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync`."}]},{"n":2,"id":"ai-local-models","title":"MAF + Ollama + Docker SLMs","hook":"Same `OpenAIClient` shape for any OpenAI-compatible URL. MAF wraps any `IChatClient` as an agent.","tags":["ai","maf","ollama","slm","docker"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"code-examples/20260324_Ollama/Ollama/SLM.OllamaClient/Program.cs + MAF.Phi3/Program.cs; code-examples/20260324_docker-slms/docker-slms/FunnyDockerMAF.cs + SentimentDockerOpenAI.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Ollama — local SLM via OllamaSharp","text":"Ollama — local SLM via OllamaSharp"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;\nusing OllamaSharp;\n\nIChatClient chatClient = new OllamaApiClient(\n    new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\");\n\nList\u003cChatMessage\u003e chatHistory = new();\nchatHistory.Add(new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, userPrompt));\n\nawait foreach (var item in chatClient.GetStreamingResponseAsync(chatHistory))\n    Console.Write(item.Text);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePackage: \u003ccode\u003eOllamaSharp\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.Extensions.AI\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eOllamaApiClient(uri, modelId)\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003ccode\u003eIChatClient\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eChatMessage(ChatRole.User|Assistant|System, content)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eList&lt;ChatMessage&gt;\u003c/code\u003e = conversation history — full list re-sent each call (no server memory)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGetStreamingResponseAsync\u003c/code\u003e yields \u003ccode\u003eChatResponseUpdate\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003e.Text\u003c/code\u003e fragments\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGetResponseAsync\u003c/code\u003e returns one buffered \u003ccode\u003eChatResponse\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Package: `OllamaSharp` + `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`\n- `OllamaApiClient(uri, modelId)` returns `IChatClient`\n- `ChatMessage(ChatRole.User|Assistant|System, content)`\n- `List\u003cChatMessage\u003e` = conversation history — full list re-sent each call (no server memory)\n- `GetStreamingResponseAsync` yields `ChatResponseUpdate` with `.Text` fragments\n- `GetResponseAsync` returns one buffered `ChatResponse`"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eCLI:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eollama pull phi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eollama list\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eollama run phi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eEndpoint:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:11434/\u003c/code\u003e — HTTP, port 11434, no auth, fully local after pull","text":"**CLI:** `ollama pull phi3:latest` · `ollama list` · `ollama run phi3:latest`\n**Endpoint:** `http://localhost:11434/` — HTTP, port 11434, no auth, fully local after pull"},{"kind":"h2","html":"MAF agent — shape 1: constructor with options","text":"MAF agent — shape 1: constructor with options"},{"kind":"p","html":"From \u003ccode\u003eMAF.Phi3/Program.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"From `MAF.Phi3/Program.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.AI;\nusing OllamaSharp;\n\nIChatClient ollamaClient = new OllamaApiClient(\"http://localhost:11434/\", \"phi3:latest\");\n\nChatClientAgent agent = new ChatClientAgent(\n    ollamaClient,\n    new ChatClientAgentOptions\n    {\n        Name = \"Astronomer\",\n        ChatOptions = new ChatOptions\n        {\n            Instructions = \"You are an astronomer who specializes in the solar system.\",\n            Temperature = 0.7f\n        }\n    });\n\nConsole.WriteLine(await agent.RunAsync(\"How far is earth from the sun?\"));"},{"kind":"h2","html":"MAF agent — shape 2: \u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e + session","text":"MAF agent — shape 2: `.AsAIAgent` + session"},{"kind":"p","html":"From \u003ccode\u003eFunnyDockerMAF.cs\u003c/code\u003e (Docker-hosted OpenAI-compatible SLM):","text":"From `FunnyDockerMAF.cs` (Docker-hosted OpenAI-compatible SLM):"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:package Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI@*-*\n\nusing System.ClientModel;\nusing Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.AI;\nusing OpenAI;\n\nvar openAIClient = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(\"unused\"),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(\"http://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1\") });\nvar chatClient = openAIClient.GetChatClient(\"ai/ministral3:latest\");\n\nAIAgent agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(\n    name: \"FunnyChatbot\",\n    instructions: \"You are a useful chatbot. Always reply in a funny way with short answers.\");\n\nAgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();\nvar chatOptions = new ChatOptions { Temperature = 1f, MaxOutputTokens = 500 };\n\nwhile (true) {\n    Console.Write(\"\\nUser: \");\n    var userInput = Console.ReadLine();\n    if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(userInput)) break;\n\n    await foreach (var update in agent.RunStreamingAsync(\n        userInput, options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(chatOptions)))\n    {\n        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(update.Text)) Console.Write(update.Text);\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Docker SLM — direct ChatClient without MAF","text":"Docker SLM — direct ChatClient without MAF"},{"kind":"p","html":"From \u003ccode\u003eSentimentDockerOpenAI.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"From `SentimentDockerOpenAI.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:package OpenAI@*-*\n\nusing OpenAI;\nusing OpenAI.Chat;\nusing System.ClientModel;\n\nOpenAIClientOptions options = new OpenAIClientOptions();\noptions.Endpoint = new Uri(\"http://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1\");\nApiKeyCredential credential = new ApiKeyCredential(\"unused\");\nChatClient client = new OpenAIClient(credential, options).GetChatClient(\"ai/llama3.2:latest\");\n\nvar response = await client.CompleteChatAsync(prompt);\nConsole.WriteLine(response.Value.Content[0].Text);"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Endpoint + credential matrix","text":"Endpoint + credential matrix"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eBackend\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eEndpoint\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eCredential\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eModel id format\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eGitHub Models\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ehttps://models.github.ai/inference\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential(PAT)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eopenai/gpt-4o-mini\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eOllama\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:11434/\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e(none — OllamaApiClient)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ephi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eDocker SLM\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential(&quot;unused&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eai/ministral3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Which extension wraps an `IChatClient` as an `AIAgent`?","a":"`.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)`. `.AsAgent()` does not exist."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eagent.RunAsync(...)\u003c/code\u003e is MAF. \u003ccode\u003ekernel.InvokeAsync(...)\u003c/code\u003e is Semantic Kernel. Not interchangeable.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`agent.RunAsync(...)` is MAF. `kernel.InvokeAsync(...)` is Semantic Kernel. Not interchangeable."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create(...)\u003c/code\u003e + tool registration — NOT in any lab or demo for 4870.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`AIFunctionFactory.Create(...)` + tool registration — NOT in any lab or demo for 4870."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eOllama is HTTP port 11434, no path. Docker SLM is HTTP port 12345 + \u003ccode\u003e/engines/llama.cpp/v1\u003c/code\u003e. GitHub is HTTPS + \u003ccode\u003e/inference\u003c/code\u003e. Mixing paths breaks requests.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Ollama is HTTP port 11434, no path. Docker SLM is HTTP port 12345 + `/engines/llama.cpp/v1`. GitHub is HTTPS + `/inference`. Mixing paths breaks requests."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eOllama: \u003ccode\u003enew OllamaApiClient(uri, modelId)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eIChatClient\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eGetStreamingResponseAsync\u003c/code\u003e. MAF: \u003ccode\u003enew ChatClientAgent(client, options)\u003c/code\u003e OR \u003ccode\u003eclient.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eRunAsync\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003eRunStreamingAsync\u003c/code\u003e. Multi-turn: \u003ccode\u003eawait agent.CreateSessionAsync()\u003c/code\u003e. Docker SLM: \u003ccode\u003eOpenAIClient(ApiKeyCredential(&quot;unused&quot;), { Endpoint = docker-url })\u003c/code\u003e then \u003ccode\u003e.GetChatClient(model)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Ollama: `new OllamaApiClient(uri, modelId)` → `IChatClient` → `GetStreamingResponseAsync`. MAF: `new ChatClientAgent(client, options)` OR `client.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)` → `RunAsync`/`RunStreamingAsync`. Multi-turn: `await agent.CreateSessionAsync()`. Docker SLM: `OpenAIClient(ApiKeyCredential(\"unused\"), { Endpoint = docker-url })` then `.GetChatClient(model)`."}]},{"n":3,"id":"ml-pipeline","title":"ML.NET pipeline — Load, Transform, Fit","hook":"MLContext → LoadFromTextFile → CopyColumns → OneHotEncoding → Concatenate → FastTree → Fit.","tags":["ml-net","pipeline","feature-eng"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"The seven-step shape","text":"The seven-step shape"},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"MLContext → LoadFromTextFile → CopyColumns(\"Label\") → OneHotEncoding\n          → Concatenate(\"Features\") → Trainer → Fit"},{"kind":"p","html":"Each step has one purpose. Miss one and training breaks.","text":"Each step has one purpose. Miss one and training breaks."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 1 — \u003ccode\u003eMLContext\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Step 1 — `MLContext`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.ML;\n\nMLContext mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);"},{"kind":"p","html":"Single entry point. Reach \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Data\u003c/code\u003e (loaders), \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Transforms\u003c/code\u003e (feature eng), \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Regression\u003c/code\u003e (trainers + eval), \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Model\u003c/code\u003e (save/load/predict). \u003ccode\u003eseed: 0\u003c/code\u003e makes training deterministic.","text":"Single entry point. Reach `mlContext.Data` (loaders), `mlContext.Transforms` (feature eng), `mlContext.Regression` (trainers + eval), `mlContext.Model` (save/load/predict). `seed: 0` makes training deterministic."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 2 — Load into \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Step 2 — Load into `IDataView`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"IDataView trainingData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\n    trainDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e is immutable, streaming, lazy. Generic parameter maps CSV columns to class fields:","text":"`IDataView` is immutable, streaming, lazy. Generic parameter maps CSV columns to class fields:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class TaxiTrip\n{\n    [LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId;\n    [LoadColumn(1)] public string RateCode;\n    [LoadColumn(2)] public float PassengerCount;\n    [LoadColumn(3)] public float TripTime;\n    [LoadColumn(4)] public float TripDistance;\n    [LoadColumn(5)] public string PaymentType;\n    [LoadColumn(6)] public float FareAmount;\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(N)]\u003c/code\u003e is 0-based; matches CSV column index (not header name).","text":"`[LoadColumn(N)]` is 0-based; matches CSV column index (not header name)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 3 — Rename target to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Step 3 — Rename target to `\"Label\"`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":".CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")"},{"kind":"p","html":"Trainers look up target by exact string \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. Rename with \u003ccode\u003eCopyColumns\u003c/code\u003e BEFORE the trainer step.","text":"Trainers look up target by exact string `\"Label\"`. Rename with `CopyColumns` BEFORE the trainer step."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 4 — Encode text categories with \u003ccode\u003eOneHotEncoding\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Step 4 — Encode text categories with `OneHotEncoding`"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eVendorId = &quot;VTS&quot;\u003c/code\u003e becomes \u003ccode\u003e[0, 1]\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eVendorId = &quot;CMT&quot;\u003c/code\u003e becomes \u003ccode\u003e[1, 0]\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"`VendorId = \"VTS\"` becomes `[0, 1]`. `VendorId = \"CMT\"` becomes `[1, 0]`."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":".Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\"))\n.Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"RateCodeEncoded\", \"RateCode\"))\n.Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"PaymentTypeEncoded\", \"PaymentType\"))"},{"kind":"p","html":"Output name is your choice. Name matters because the next step references it.","text":"Output name is your choice. Name matters because the next step references it."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 5 — Pack features into \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e vector","text":"Step 5 — Pack features into `\"Features\"` vector"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":".Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\",\n    \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"RateCodeEncoded\", \"PassengerCount\",\n    \"TripDistance\", \"PaymentTypeEncoded\"))"},{"kind":"p","html":"Output name MUST be literal \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. Trainers hardcode that lookup.","text":"Output name MUST be literal `\"Features\"`. Trainers hardcode that lookup."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMissing from the Concatenate list:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eTripTime\u003c/code\u003e. Fare is predicted BEFORE trip ends — trip time is not known at prediction time. Including causes data leakage.","text":"**Missing from the Concatenate list:** `TripTime`. Fare is predicted BEFORE trip ends — trip time is not known at prediction time. Including causes data leakage."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 6 — Add the trainer","text":"Step 6 — Add the trainer"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":".Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree())"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eFastTree\u003c/code\u003e = gradient-boosted decision-tree ensemble. Default regression trainer in TaxiFarePrediction + the winner AutoML picked.","text":"`FastTree` = gradient-boosted decision-tree ensemble. Default regression trainer in TaxiFarePrediction + the winner AutoML picked."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Step 7 — \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Step 7 — `Fit` returns `ITransformer`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"ITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);\nmlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, \"Data/Model.zip\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eFit()\u003c/code\u003e trains and returns a trained, stateless, serializable model. \u003cstrong\u003eNOT\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"`Fit()` trains and returns a trained, stateless, serializable model. **NOT** `IDataView`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Full pipeline (TaxiFarePrediction)","text":"Full pipeline (TaxiFarePrediction)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var pipeline = mlContext.Transforms\n    .CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"RateCodeEncoded\", \"RateCode\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"PaymentTypeEncoded\", \"PaymentType\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\",\n        \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"RateCodeEncoded\", \"PassengerCount\",\n        \"TripDistance\", \"PaymentTypeEncoded\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"What does `pipeline.Fit(trainingData)` return?","a":"`ITransformer`. Not `IDataView`, not `RegressionMetrics`, not `PredictionEngine`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"You add a `OneHotEncoding(\"StoreAndFwdFlagEncoded\", \"StoreAndFwdFlag\")` but forget to list it in `Concatenate`. What breaks?","a":"Nothing compiles wrong and model still trains — but the encoded column never reaches `FastTree`. Every encoded output must appear in `Concatenate` input list."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e are hardcoded strings — typos silently break training.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`\"Label\"` and `\"Features\"` are hardcoded strings — typos silently break training."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(N)]\u003c/code\u003e is 0-based. \u003ccode\u003eCell(r, c)\u003c/code\u003e in ClosedXML is 1-based. Confusing the two is where off-by-one bugs live.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`[LoadColumn(N)]` is 0-based. `Cell(r, c)` in ClosedXML is 1-based. Confusing the two is where off-by-one bugs live."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eOne \u003ccode\u003eMLContext\u003c/code\u003e, one \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e, one pipeline: \u003ccode\u003eCopyColumns(&quot;Label&quot;, target)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eOneHotEncoding\u003c/code\u003e per text column → \u003ccode\u003eConcatenate(&quot;Features&quot;, ...)\u003c/code\u003e → trainer. \u003ccode\u003eFit()\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e. Save with \u003ccode\u003eModel.Save(model, data.Schema, path)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"One `MLContext`, one `IDataView`, one pipeline: `CopyColumns(\"Label\", target)` → `OneHotEncoding` per text column → `Concatenate(\"Features\", ...)` → trainer. `Fit()` returns `ITransformer`. Save with `Model.Save(model, data.Schema, path)`."}]},{"n":4,"id":"ml-regression-evaluation","title":"ML.NET evaluation — FastTree, RMSE, R²","hook":"Separate test file, Regression.Evaluate, read RSquared + RootMeanSquaredError.","tags":["ml-net","regression","metrics"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Train on one file, evaluate on another","text":"Train on one file, evaluate on another"},{"kind":"p","html":"TaxiFarePrediction splits by using two separate CSVs — not by calling a split function:","text":"TaxiFarePrediction splits by using two separate CSVs — not by calling a split function:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"string trainDataPath = Path.Combine(Environment.CurrentDirectory, \"Data\", \"taxi-fare-train.csv\");\nstring testDataPath  = Path.Combine(Environment.CurrentDirectory, \"Data\", \"taxi-fare-test.csv\");\n\nIDataView trainingData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\n    trainDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);"},{"kind":"p","html":"Test rows never seen during \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e → metrics measure generalisation.","text":"Test rows never seen during `Fit` → metrics measure generalisation."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eRegression.Evaluate\u003c/code\u003e — three requirements","text":"`Regression.Evaluate` — three requirements"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"IDataView testData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\n    testDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\nvar predictions = model.Transform(testData);\n\nvar metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"RSquared Score:          {metrics.RSquared:0.##}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Root Mean Squared Error: {metrics.RootMeanSquaredError:#.##}\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNamespace matches task\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Regression.Evaluate\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eRegressionMetrics\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003emlContext.MulticlassClassification.Evaluate\u003c/code\u003e is wrong shape for regression.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLabel column name\u003c/strong\u003e — renamed to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003eCopyColumns\u003c/code\u003e, so pass \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScore column name\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eFastTree\u003c/code\u003e writes to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Score&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **Namespace matches task** — `mlContext.Regression.Evaluate` → `RegressionMetrics`. `mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Evaluate` is wrong shape for regression.\n2. **Label column name** — renamed to `\"Label\"` via `CopyColumns`, so pass `\"Label\"`.\n3. **Score column name** — `FastTree` writes to `\"Score\"`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Output class — \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Score&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Output class — `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class TaxiTripFarePrediction\n{\n    [ColumnName(\"Score\")] public float FareAmount;\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Regression trainers write prediction to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Score&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. Mark \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Prediction&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e and the field stays zero — binding fails silently.","text":"Regression trainers write prediction to `\"Score\"`. Mark `[ColumnName(\"Prediction\")]` and the field stays zero — binding fails silently."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Two metrics to read","text":"Two metrics to read"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eProperty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eRange\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eMeaning\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eR²\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003emetrics.RSquared\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e0 to 1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFraction of variance explained. Closer to 1 = better. Unitless.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRMSE\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003emetrics.RootMeanSquaredError\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e≥ 0\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAvg prediction error in label units (dollars for fare). Lower = better.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"R² = \u003ccode\u003e1 - (SS_residual / SS_total)\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003e0.89\u003c/code\u003e = 89% variance explained. RMSE squares errors before averaging, so large misses count more. Units match the label.","text":"R² = `1 - (SS_residual / SS_total)`. `0.89` = 89% variance explained. RMSE squares errors before averaging, so large misses count more. Units match the label."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Interpreting output","text":"Interpreting output"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eRSquared = 0.89, RMSE = 3.30\u003c/code\u003e on taxi-fare (dollars):","text":"`RSquared = 0.89, RMSE = 3.30` on taxi-fare (dollars):"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eModel explains 89% of fare variance. Strong fit.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePredictions miss actual fare by about $3.30 on average.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Model explains 89% of fare variance. Strong fit.\n- Predictions miss actual fare by about $3.30 on average."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eWrong reading:\u003c/strong\u003e &quot;89% accurate with 3.3% error.&quot; R² is not accuracy. RMSE is not percentage.","text":"**Wrong reading:** \"89% accurate with 3.3% error.\" R² is not accuracy. RMSE is not percentage."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Output class has `[ColumnName(\"Prediction\")] public float FareAmount;`. `Evaluate` returns `RSquared = 0`. Why?","a":"`FastTree` writes to `\"Score\"`, not `\"Prediction\"`. Evaluate cannot find the prediction column. Use `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003emlContext.MulticlassClassification.Evaluate(...)\u003c/code\u003e on a regression model — wrong namespace, wrong metrics class. \u003ccode\u003eRSquared\u003c/code\u003e not a member.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Calling `mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Evaluate(...)` on a regression model — wrong namespace, wrong metrics class. `RSquared` not a member."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e&quot;\u003ccode\u003eRSquared = 0.89\u003c/code\u003e means 89% accurate.&quot; Accuracy is classification. R² is unitless variance-explained.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"\"`RSquared = 0.89` means 89% accurate.\" Accuracy is classification. R² is unitless variance-explained."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eTrain with \u003ccode\u003eFastTree()\u003c/code\u003e, load separate test CSV, \u003ccode\u003emodel.Transform(testData)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eRegression.Evaluate(predictions, &quot;Label&quot;, &quot;Score&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e → read \u003ccode\u003eRSquared\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eRootMeanSquaredError\u003c/code\u003e. Output class needs \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Score&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Train with `FastTree()`, load separate test CSV, `model.Transform(testData)` → `Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\")` → read `RSquared` + `RootMeanSquaredError`. Output class needs `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]`."}]},{"n":5,"id":"ml-prediction-consumption","title":"ML.NET inference + model persistence","hook":"CreatePredictionEngine for one row. Save/Load for across processes.","tags":["ml-net","inference","save-load"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"code-examples/TaxiFarePrediction/Program.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Single-row inference — \u003ccode\u003ePredictionEngine\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Single-row inference — `PredictionEngine`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var engine = mlContext.Model\n    .CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(model);\n\nvar sample = new TaxiTrip\n{\n    VendorId = \"VTS\",\n    RateCode = \"1\",\n    PassengerCount = 1,\n    TripTime = 1140,\n    TripDistance = 3.75f,\n    PaymentType = \"CRD\",\n    FareAmount = 0          // placeholder — what you predict\n};\n\nvar prediction = engine.Predict(sample);\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Predicted fare: {prediction.FareAmount:0.####}\");"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Batch inference — \u003ccode\u003eTransform\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Batch inference — `Transform`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"IDataView scored = model.Transform(batchDataView);"},{"kind":"p","html":"Returns new \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eScore\u003c/code\u003e column appended. Use for tabular inputs.","text":"Returns new `IDataView` with `Score` column appended. Use for tabular inputs."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Save — needs schema","text":"Save — needs schema"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"mlContext.Model.Save(model, dataView.Schema, \"Data/Model.zip\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"Without \u003ccode\u003eDataViewSchema\u003c/code\u003e, the zip does not rehydrate into a working pipeline.","text":"Without `DataViewSchema`, the zip does not rehydrate into a working pipeline."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Load — schema out-param","text":"Load — schema out-param"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"DataViewSchema modelSchema;\nITransformer trainedModel = mlContext.Model.Load(\"Data/Model.zip\", out modelSchema);\n\nvar engine = mlContext.Model\n    .CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(trainedModel);"},{"kind":"p","html":"Loaded model behaves identically to freshly-fit one.","text":"Loaded model behaves identically to freshly-fit one."},{"kind":"h2","html":"End-to-end demo sequence","text":"End-to-end demo sequence"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Train\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);\nmlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, _modelPath);\n\n// Later — load + predict\nmlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);\nDataViewSchema modelSchema;\nITransformer trainedModel = mlContext.Model.Load(_modelPath, out modelSchema);\nvar engine = mlContext.Model\n    .CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(trainedModel);\nvar prediction = engine.Predict(sample);"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"What type does `Fit` return? Which factory builds a single-row predictor? What attribute decorates the prediction field?","a":"`ITransformer`; `mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e`; `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e, not \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e. Demo sequence: \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eSave(model, schema, path)\u003c/code\u003e → later \u003ccode\u003eLoad(path, out schema)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eCreatePredictionEngine\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePredict\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`Fit` returns `ITransformer`, not `IDataView`. Demo sequence: `Fit` → `Save(model, schema, path)` → later `Load(path, out schema)` → `CreatePredictionEngine` → `Predict`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eSaving without schema. \u003ccode\u003eModel.Save(model, null, path)\u003c/code\u003e compiles but strips metadata needed to rebuild input columns. Always pass \u003ccode\u003edataView.Schema\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Saving without schema. `Model.Save(model, null, path)` compiles but strips metadata needed to rebuild input columns. Always pass `dataView.Schema`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eFit()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e. Wrap with \u003ccode\u003eCreatePredictionEngine&lt;TIn, TOut&gt;\u003c/code\u003e for single rows. \u003ccode\u003emodel.Transform\u003c/code\u003e for batches. Persist with \u003ccode\u003eSave(model, schema, path)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`Fit()` → `ITransformer`. Wrap with `CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn, TOut\u003e` for single rows. `model.Transform` for batches. Persist with `Save(model, schema, path)`."}]},{"n":6,"id":"ml-automl-cli","title":"ML.NET AutoML CLI","hook":"One command explores 40+ regression models, emits a ready-to-run project.","tags":["ml-net","automl","cli"],"module":"AI in .NET","source":"code-examples/TaxiFareAutoML/TaxiFareModel/Program.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Run the CLI","text":"Run the CLI"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"mlnet regression --dataset taxi-fare-train.csv --label-col 6 --train-time 60 --has-header true"},{"kind":"p","html":"Task: regression. Dataset: CSV. Label: column at index 6 (0-based). Budget: 60 seconds of exploration.","text":"Task: regression. Dataset: CSV. Label: column at index 6 (0-based). Budget: 60 seconds of exploration."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Install once per machine","text":"Install once per machine"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"dotnet tool install -g mlnet-win-x64"},{"kind":"p","html":"Swap \u003ccode\u003emlnet-osx-x64\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003emlnet-linux-x64\u003c/code\u003e on other platforms. Installed command: \u003ccode\u003emlnet\u003c/code\u003e (lowercase, no dot).","text":"Swap `mlnet-osx-x64` or `mlnet-linux-x64` on other platforms. Installed command: `mlnet` (lowercase, no dot)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"What AutoML does","text":"What AutoML does"},{"kind":"p","html":"Fits dozens of regression variants (FastTree, FastTreeTweedie, LightGbm, Sdca, FastForest, etc.) with different hyperparameter combos, ranks by metric.","text":"Fits dozens of regression variants (FastTree, FastTreeTweedie, LightGbm, Sdca, FastForest, etc.) with different hyperparameter combos, ranks by metric."},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"Exploration time: 60 seconds\nModels tested: 42\nTop 5 models (by RSquared):\n  1. FastTreeRegression         0.951\n  2. FastTreeTweedieRegression  0.944\n  3. LightGbmRegression         0.938\n  4. FastForestRegression       0.930\n  5. SdcaRegression             0.812"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Key flags","text":"Key flags"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eFlag\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e--dataset\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTraining CSV path\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e--label-col\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTarget column — 0-based index (\u003ccode\u003e6\u003c/code\u003e) or name (\u003ccode\u003eFareAmount\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e--train-time\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBudget in seconds\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e--has-header\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003etrue\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003efalse\u003c/code\u003e — does CSV have header row\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Output","text":"Output"},{"kind":"p","html":"CLI generates a full console project — source files, \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e.zip\u003c/code\u003e model — wired to the winning pipeline. Use with:","text":"CLI generates a full console project — source files, `.csproj`, `.zip` model — wired to the winning pipeline. Use with:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Generated wrapper\nvar sampleData = new TaxiFareModel.ModelInput()\n{\n    Vendor_id = \"CMT\",\n    Rate_code = 1F,\n    Passenger_count = 1F,\n    Trip_time_in_secs = 1271F,\n    Trip_distance = 3.8F,\n    Payment_type = \"CRD\",\n};\n\nvar predictionResult = TaxiFareModel.Predict(sampleData);\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Predicted Fare_amount: {predictionResult.Score}\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003edotnet run\u003c/code\u003e the generated project — no manual pipeline code.","text":"`dotnet run` the generated project — no manual pipeline code."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Which flag sets exploration budget? Which flag chooses target column and what two forms does it accept?","a":"`--train-time` in seconds; `--label-col` takes 0-based index (`6`) or column name (`FareAmount`)."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003emlnet\u003c/code\u003e (lowercase, no dot) is the CLI. \u003ccode\u003eML.NET\u003c/code\u003e (uppercase, dotted) is the framework. Mixing casing loses marks.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`mlnet` (lowercase, no dot) is the CLI. `ML.NET` (uppercase, dotted) is the framework. Mixing casing loses marks."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e--label-col FareAmount\u003c/code\u003e fails if CSV lacks headers or spelling differs. Use 0-based index when header text is uncertain.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`--label-col FareAmount` fails if CSV lacks headers or spelling differs. Use 0-based index when header text is uncertain."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003emlnet regression --dataset &lt;csv&gt; --label-col &lt;index|name&gt; --train-time &lt;seconds&gt;\u003c/code\u003e explores 40+ regression variants and emits a console project wired to the best model found.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`mlnet regression --dataset \u003ccsv\u003e --label-col \u003cindex|name\u003e --train-time \u003cseconds\u003e` explores 40+ regression variants and emits a console project wired to the best model found."}]},{"n":7,"id":"grpc","title":"gRPC — proto contracts, server, client","hook":"Write .proto first. Inherit generated Base class. Register with AddGrpc + MapGrpcService.","tags":["grpc","protobuf","asp-net-core"],"module":"Distributed Services & Orchestration","source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/GrpcBasics/GrpcStudentsServer/ + BlazorGrpcClient/ + GrpcBasics.AppHost/","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"The \u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e contract (W09 lab)","text":"The `.proto` contract (W09 lab)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"proto","code":"syntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"GrpcStudentsServer\";\npackage greet;\n\nservice StudentRemote {\n  rpc GetStudentInfo (StudentLookupModel) returns (StudentModel);\n  rpc InsertStudent (StudentModel) returns (Reply);\n  rpc UpdateStudent (StudentModel) returns (Reply);\n  rpc DeleteStudent (StudentLookupModel) returns (Reply);\n  rpc RetrieveAllStudents (Empty) returns (StudentList);\n}\n\nmessage Reply {\n    string result = 1;\n    bool isOk = 2;\n}\n\nmessage Empty {}\n\nmessage StudentLookupModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n}\n\nmessage StudentModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n  string firstName = 2;\n  string lastName = 3;\n  string school = 4;\n}\n\nmessage StudentList {\n   repeated StudentModel items = 1;\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Keywords:","text":"Keywords:"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eKeyword\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003esyntax = &quot;proto3&quot;;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eVersion pin\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eoption csharp_namespace = &quot;X&quot;;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eGenerated C# namespace\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eservice\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003egRPC service declaration\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003erpc\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eOne method. Shape: \u003ccode\u003erpc Name (Request) returns (Response);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003emessage\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eStructured payload. Each field has type + name + \u003cstrong\u003etag\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003erepeated T\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eList — maps to \u003ccode\u003eRepeatedField&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003e.Add(...)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eEmpty\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eZero-field message for &quot;no input&quot; rpc\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Field tags — permanent wire contract","text":"Field tags — permanent wire contract"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTags 1–15 encode in 1 byte; 16+ take 2 bytes. Put hot fields in 1–15.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTags are permanent. Never reuse. \u003ccode\u003ereserved 2;\u003c/code\u003e marks removed slots.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUnset proto3 scalars = zero-values (\u003ccode\u003e0\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&quot;&quot;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003efalse\u003c/code\u003e). No \u003ccode\u003enull\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Tags 1–15 encode in 1 byte; 16+ take 2 bytes. Put hot fields in 1–15.\n- Tags are permanent. Never reuse. `reserved 2;` marks removed slots.\n- Unset proto3 scalars = zero-values (`0`, `\"\"`, `false`). No `null`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e — client vs server","text":"`.csproj` — client vs server"},{"kind":"code","lang":"xml","code":"\u003cItemGroup\u003e\n  \u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e\n\u003c/ItemGroup\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eGrpcServices\u003c/code\u003e controls code generation: \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Server&quot;\u003c/code\u003e for service implementations, \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Client&quot;\u003c/code\u003e for callable stubs, \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Both&quot;\u003c/code\u003e when one project hosts both roles.","text":"`GrpcServices` controls code generation: `\"Server\"` for service implementations, `\"Client\"` for callable stubs, `\"Both\"` when one project hosts both roles."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Server — inherit + override","text":"Server — inherit + override"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Grpc.Core;\n\npublic class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\n{\n    private readonly ILogger\u003cStudentsService\u003e _logger;\n    private readonly SchoolDbContext _context;\n\n    public StudentsService(ILogger\u003cStudentsService\u003e logger, SchoolDbContext context)\n    {\n        _logger = logger;\n        _context = context;\n    }\n\n    public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(\n        StudentLookupModel request, ServerCallContext context)\n    {\n        var c = _context.Students!.Find(request.StudentId);\n        if (c is null) return Task.FromResult(new StudentModel());\n\n        return Task.FromResult(new StudentModel {\n            StudentId = c.StudentId,\n            FirstName = c.FirstName,\n            LastName = c.LastName,\n            School = c.School\n        });\n    }\n\n    public override Task\u003cReply\u003e InsertStudent(StudentModel request, ServerCallContext context)\n    {\n        var s = new Student {\n            StudentId = request.StudentId,\n            LastName = request.LastName,\n            FirstName = request.FirstName,\n            School = request.School,\n        };\n        _context.Students!.Add(s);\n        _context.SaveChanges();\n\n        return Task.FromResult(new Reply {\n            Result = $\"Student {request.FirstName} inserted.\",\n            IsOk = true\n        });\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Three rules:","text":"Three rules:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInherit from \u003ccode\u003e[Service].[Service]Base\u003c/code\u003e (e.g. \u003ccode\u003eStudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOverride takes \u003ccode\u003e(Request, ServerCallContext)\u003c/code\u003e — the context is NOT optional.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReturn \u003ccode\u003eTask&lt;Response&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eTask.FromResult(...)\u003c/code\u003e for sync; \u003ccode\u003easync/await\u003c/code\u003e for awaiting bodies.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. Inherit from `[Service].[Service]Base` (e.g. `StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase`).\n2. Override takes `(Request, ServerCallContext)` — the context is NOT optional.\n3. Return `Task\u003cResponse\u003e` — `Task.FromResult(...)` for sync; `async/await` for awaiting bodies."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Server streaming override","text":"Server streaming override"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public override async Task RetrieveAllStudents(\n    Empty request,\n    IServerStreamWriter\u003cStudentModel\u003e responseStream,\n    ServerCallContext context)\n{\n    foreach (var s in _context.Students!)\n        await responseStream.WriteAsync(new StudentModel { /* ... */ });\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Streaming: return type \u003ccode\u003eTask\u003c/code\u003e (no response), extra \u003ccode\u003eIServerStreamWriter&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e parameter.","text":"Streaming: return type `Task` (no response), extra `IServerStreamWriter\u003cT\u003e` parameter."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Server — \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Server — `Program.cs`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nbuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\nbuilder.Services.AddDbContext\u003cSchoolDbContext\u003e(opts =\u003e\n    opts.UseSqlite(builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString(\"DefaultConnection\")!));\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cStudentsService\u003e();\napp.MapDefaultEndpoints();\napp.Run();"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Client — DI + Aspire logical name","text":"Client — DI + Aspire logical name"},{"kind":"p","html":"From \u003ccode\u003eBlazorGrpcClient/Program.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"From `BlazorGrpcClient/Program.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorComponents()\n    .AddInteractiveServerComponents();\n\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003e(options =\u003e\n{\n    options.Address = new Uri(\"http://backend\");       // Aspire logical name\n});"},{"kind":"p","html":"Blazor page consumes via \u003ccode\u003e@inject\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"Blazor page consumes via `@inject`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpc\n\n@code {\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()\n    {\n        var reply = await _grpc.GetStudentInfoAsync(\n            new StudentLookupModel { StudentId = 3 });\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"AppHost wiring","text":"AppHost wiring"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar grpc = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.GrpcStudentsServer\u003e(\"backend\");\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.BlazorGrpcClient\u003e(\"frontend\")\n    .WithReference(grpc).WaitFor(grpc);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();"},{"kind":"p","html":"The \u003ccode\u003ehttp://backend\u003c/code\u003e URL in the client resolves to whichever port gRPC server bound to — Aspire service discovery handles it.","text":"The `http://backend` URL in the client resolves to whichever port gRPC server bound to — Aspire service discovery handles it."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Blazor client project has `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e`. You get \"`StudentRemoteClient` could not be found.\" Why?","a":"`GrpcServices=\"Server\"` generates only the server base class. Flip to `GrpcServices=\"Client\"`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003egRPC requires HTTP/2. Kestrel misconfigured for HTTP/1.1 → cryptic connection error, not &quot;protocol mismatch.&quot;\u003c/p\u003e","text":"gRPC requires HTTP/2. Kestrel misconfigured for HTTP/1.1 → cryptic connection error, not \"protocol mismatch.\""},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eForgetting \u003ccode\u003eoverride\u003c/code\u003e on a service method silently shadows the base. Server compiles, starts, but clients get \u003ccode\u003eRpcException: UNIMPLEMENTED\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Forgetting `override` on a service method silently shadows the base. Server compiles, starts, but clients get `RpcException: UNIMPLEMENTED`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e is the contract (\u003ccode\u003esyntax = &quot;proto3&quot;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eservice\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003erpc\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003emessage\u003c/code\u003e). Server: inherit \u003ccode\u003e[Service].[Service]Base\u003c/code\u003e, override with \u003ccode\u003e(Request, ServerCallContext)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eTask&lt;Response&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. Register: \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpc()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMapGrpcService&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e. Client: \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e \u003ccode\u003eGrpcServices=&quot;Client&quot;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpcClient&lt;T&gt;(opts =&gt; opts.Address = new Uri(&quot;http://backend&quot;))\u003c/code\u003e. Aspire logical name for service discovery.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`.proto` is the contract (`syntax = \"proto3\"` + `service` + `rpc` + `message`). Server: inherit `[Service].[Service]Base`, override with `(Request, ServerCallContext)` → `Task\u003cResponse\u003e`. Register: `AddGrpc()` + `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()`. Client: `.csproj` `GrpcServices=\"Client\"` + `AddGrpcClient\u003cT\u003e(opts =\u003e opts.Address = new Uri(\"http://backend\"))`. Aspire logical name for service discovery."}]},{"n":8,"id":"aspire","title":".NET Aspire — AppHost, ServiceDefaults, resources","hook":"AppHost orchestrates. Each service calls AddServiceDefaults + MapDefaultEndpoints. AddSqlServer + WithReference wires resources.","tags":["aspire","orchestration","observability"],"module":"Distributed Services & Orchestration","source":"code-examples/SoccerFIFA_Aspire/SoccerFIFA/SoccerFIFA.AppHost/AppHost.cs + SoccerFIFA.ServiceDefaults/Extensions.cs + WebApiFIFA/Program.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"AppHost — the orchestration entry point","text":"AppHost — the orchestration entry point"},{"kind":"p","html":"From SoccerFIFA \u003ccode\u003eAppHost.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"From SoccerFIFA `AppHost.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar sqlServerDb = builder.AddSqlServer(\"theserver\")\n                         .AddDatabase(\"sqldata\");\n\nvar api = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.WebApiFIFA\u003e(\"backend\")\n    .WithReference(sqlServerDb)\n    .WaitFor(sqlServerDb)\n    .WithEnvironment(\"ParentCompany\", builder.Configuration[\"Company\"]);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.BlazorFIFA\u003e(\"frontend\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();"},{"kind":"p","html":"Four calls:","text":"Four calls:"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eCall\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eDistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eOrchestrator builder\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.X&gt;(&quot;logical-name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRegister service — consumers reach as \u003ccode\u003ehttp://logical-name/\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.WithReference(other)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eInject connection info as env-var\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.WaitFor(other)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eDelay startup until dependency healthy\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Logical names replace hardcoded URLs","text":"Logical names replace hardcoded URLs"},{"kind":"p","html":"The string in \u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;&gt;(&quot;backend&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e is the service&#39;s \u003cstrong\u003elogical name\u003c/strong\u003e. Consumers use \u003ccode\u003ehttp://backend/\u003c/code\u003e. Aspire intercepts and resolves to the actual port at runtime.","text":"The string in `AddProject\u003c\u003e(\"backend\")` is the service's **logical name**. Consumers use `http://backend/`. Aspire intercepts and resolves to the actual port at runtime."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Resources — declare once, consume by name","text":"Resources — declare once, consume by name"},{"kind":"h3","html":"SQL Server","text":"SQL Server"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var sqlServerDb = builder.AddSqlServer(\"theserver\")\n                         .AddDatabase(\"sqldata\");\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.WebApiFIFA\u003e(\"backend\")\n    .WithReference(sqlServerDb)\n    .WaitFor(sqlServerDb);"},{"kind":"p","html":"Service consumes via typed helper:","text":"Service consumes via typed helper:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// WebApiFIFA/Program.cs\nbuilder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e(\"sqldata\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"No connection string in \u003ccode\u003eappsettings.json\u003c/code\u003e. Aspire writes \u003ccode\u003eConnectionStrings__sqldata\u003c/code\u003e into env. Typed helper reads it.","text":"No connection string in `appsettings.json`. Aspire writes `ConnectionStrings__sqldata` into env. Typed helper reads it."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Arbitrary env-vars","text":"Arbitrary env-vars"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":".WithEnvironment(\"ParentCompany\", builder.Configuration[\"Company\"])"},{"kind":"p","html":"Value read from AppHost&#39;s config, injected into service&#39;s env. Service reads via \u003ccode\u003eIConfiguration[&quot;ParentCompany&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Value read from AppHost's config, injected into service's env. Service reads via `IConfiguration[\"ParentCompany\"]`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Service — ServiceDefaults boilerplate","text":"Service — ServiceDefaults boilerplate"},{"kind":"p","html":"Every service project in an Aspire solution calls exactly two methods:","text":"Every service project in an Aspire solution calls exactly two methods:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nbuilder.AddServiceDefaults();          // 1. at configure time\n\nbuilder.Services.AddControllers();\nvar app = builder.Build();\n\napp.MapDefaultEndpoints();             // 2. at map time\napp.MapControllers();\napp.Run();"},{"kind":"h2","html":"What \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults\u003c/code\u003e registers","text":"What `AddServiceDefaults` registers"},{"kind":"p","html":"From \u003ccode\u003eSoccerFIFA.ServiceDefaults/Extensions.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"From `SoccerFIFA.ServiceDefaults/Extensions.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public static TBuilder AddServiceDefaults\u003cTBuilder\u003e(this TBuilder builder)\n    where TBuilder : IHostApplicationBuilder\n{\n    builder.ConfigureOpenTelemetry();\n    builder.AddDefaultHealthChecks();\n    builder.Services.AddServiceDiscovery();\n\n    builder.Services.ConfigureHttpClientDefaults(http =\u003e\n    {\n        http.AddStandardResilienceHandler();\n        http.AddServiceDiscovery();\n    });\n\n    return builder;\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Four capabilities:","text":"Four capabilities:"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eCapability\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eService discovery\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ehttp://backend/\u003c/code\u003e resolves at runtime\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eOpenTelemetry\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTraces, metrics, logs to dashboard\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eHealth checks\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e/health\u003c/code\u003e readiness + \u003ccode\u003e/alive\u003c/code\u003e liveness\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eResilience\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eDefault retry + timeout on outbound \u003ccode\u003eHttpClient\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e/health\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003e/alive\u003c/code\u003e","text":"`/health` vs `/alive`"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e/health\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — readiness. Returns 200 only when every check passes. Decides whether to route traffic.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e/alive\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — liveness. Returns 200 for checks tagged \u003ccode\u003e&quot;live&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (process-is-running probe). Decides whether to restart container.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- **`/health`** — readiness. Returns 200 only when every check passes. Decides whether to route traffic.\n- **`/alive`** — liveness. Returns 200 for checks tagged `\"live\"` (process-is-running probe). Decides whether to restart container."},{"kind":"p","html":"Kubernetes maps these to \u003ccode\u003ereadinessProbe\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003elivenessProbe\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Kubernetes maps these to `readinessProbe` and `livenessProbe`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eMapDefaultEndpoints\u003c/code\u003e — only in Development","text":"`MapDefaultEndpoints` — only in Development"},{"kind":"p","html":"From lab&#39;s Extensions.cs:","text":"From lab's Extensions.cs:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public static WebApplication MapDefaultEndpoints(this WebApplication app)\n{\n    if (app.Environment.IsDevelopment())\n    {\n        app.MapHealthChecks(\"/health\");\n        app.MapHealthChecks(\"/alive\", new HealthCheckOptions\n        {\n            Predicate = r =\u003e r.Tags.Contains(\"live\")\n        });\n    }\n    return app;\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Endpoints only mapped in dev — production exposure requires explicit opt-in (security implications).","text":"Endpoints only mapped in dev — production exposure requires explicit opt-in (security implications)."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Your API has `builder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e(\"sqldata\")`. At runtime EF fails \"connection string not found.\" AppHost has `AddSqlServer(\"theserver\").AddDatabase(\"sqldata\")`. What did you forget?","a":"`.WithReference(sqlServerDb)` on the API's `AddProject\u003c\u003e`. Without it, Aspire never writes `ConnectionStrings__sqldata` into env."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"You added a new service. Dashboard shows it always red. Other services green. What's missing?","a":"`builder.AddServiceDefaults()` in the new service's `Program.cs`. Without it, no default health checks, no `/health` endpoint, dashboard gets 404."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e goes in EACH service&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e, NEVER in AppHost. Putting it in AppHost breaks boot — orchestrator tries to register OTel + health checks on itself.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`AddServiceDefaults()` goes in EACH service's `Program.cs`, NEVER in AppHost. Putting it in AppHost breaks boot — orchestrator tries to register OTel + health checks on itself."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAppHost\u003c/code\u003e cannot find sibling service projects automatically. Run \u003ccode\u003edotnet add reference\u003c/code\u003e from AppHost&#39;s \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e to each service project. Without that, \u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.X&gt;\u003c/code\u003e fails — \u003ccode\u003eProjects\u003c/code\u003e namespace generated from references.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`AppHost` cannot find sibling service projects automatically. Run `dotnet add reference` from AppHost's `.csproj` to each service project. Without that, `AddProject\u003cProjects.X\u003e` fails — `Projects` namespace generated from references."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003e.AddDatabase(&quot;sqldata&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e on builder directly. \u003ccode\u003eAddDatabase\u003c/code\u003e only chains off \u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServer(...)\u003c/code\u003e. Not a top-level method.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Calling `.AddDatabase(\"sqldata\")` on builder directly. `AddDatabase` only chains off `AddSqlServer(...)`. Not a top-level method."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eAppHost: \u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.X&gt;(&quot;name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e.WithReference(resource)\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e.WaitFor(resource)\u003c/code\u003e. Resources: \u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServer(&quot;name&quot;).AddDatabase(&quot;name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e. Service: \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMapDefaultEndpoints()\u003c/code\u003e + typed consumers (\u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServerDbContext&lt;T&gt;(&quot;name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e). \u003ccode\u003eWithEnvironment(key, value)\u003c/code\u003e for arbitrary env-vars. \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults\u003c/code\u003e lives in each service — never in AppHost.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"AppHost: `AddProject\u003cProjects.X\u003e(\"name\")` + `.WithReference(resource)` + `.WaitFor(resource)`. Resources: `AddSqlServer(\"name\").AddDatabase(\"name\")`. Service: `AddServiceDefaults()` + `MapDefaultEndpoints()` + typed consumers (`AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cT\u003e(\"name\")`). `WithEnvironment(key, value)` for arbitrary env-vars. `AddServiceDefaults` lives in each service — never in AppHost."}]},{"n":9,"id":"cache-redis","title":"Caching — IMemoryCache, IDistributedCache, Redis, Cache Tag Helper","hook":"TryGetValue+Set for memory. GetOrSetAsync extension for distributed. Redis backs IDistributedCache.","tags":["cache","redis","tag-helper"],"module":"Performance & Caching","source":"code-examples/20260330_DataCacheDemo/DataCacheDemo/Program.cs + Pages/Index.cshtml.cs; code-examples/20260330_WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final/Program.cs + Models/GameService.cs + Models/DistributedCacheExtensions.cs; notes/Cache_Tag_Helper_SCRIPT.docx","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Two cache abstractions","text":"Two cache abstractions"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// DataCacheDemo — in-process, per-server\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();          // resolves IMemoryCache\n\n// WebApiFIFA — network-backed, shared across servers\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =\u003e\n{\n    options.Configuration = \"localhost\";\n    options.ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions\n    {\n        AbortOnConnectFail = true,\n        EndPoints = { options.Configuration }\n    };\n});                                         // resolves IDistributedCache"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e — microseconds, per-process, lost on restart.\n\u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e — milliseconds, shared via Redis, survives restart.","text":"`IMemoryCache` — microseconds, per-process, lost on restart.\n`IDistributedCache` — milliseconds, shared via Redis, survives restart."},{"kind":"p","html":"Choose based on: &quot;does this value need to be visible to other servers or after a restart?&quot;","text":"Choose based on: \"does this value need to be visible to other servers or after a restart?\""},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e — TryGetValue + Set (DataCacheDemo)","text":"`IMemoryCache` — TryGetValue + Set (DataCacheDemo)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class IndexModel : PageModel\n{\n    private readonly IMemoryCache _memoryCache;\n    public IndexModel(IMemoryCache memoryCache) =\u003e _memoryCache = memoryCache;\n\n    private async Task\u003cProduct[]\u003e GetProductsAsync()\n    {\n        var cacheKey = \"productList\";\n        if (!_memoryCache.TryGetValue(cacheKey, out Product[]? productList))\n        {\n            HttpClient client = new HttpClient();\n            var stream = client.GetStreamAsync(\"https://northwind.vercel.app/api/products\");\n            productList = await JsonSerializer.DeserializeAsync\u003cProduct[]\u003e(await stream);\n\n            var cacheExpiryOptions = new MemoryCacheEntryOptions\n            {\n                AbsoluteExpiration  = DateTime.Now.AddSeconds(50),\n                Priority            = CacheItemPriority.High,\n                SlidingExpiration   = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(20)\n            };\n            _memoryCache.Set(cacheKey, productList, cacheExpiryOptions);\n        }\n        return productList!;\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eTryGetValue(key, out T? value)\u003c/code\u003e returns bool. On miss, fetch, set with options, return. On hit, out-parameter carries payload.","text":"`TryGetValue(key, out T? value)` returns bool. On miss, fetch, set with options, return. On hit, out-parameter carries payload."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eGetOrSetAsync&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e extension","text":"`IDistributedCache` — `GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` extension"},{"kind":"p","html":"The \u003ccode\u003eDistributedCacheExtensions.cs\u003c/code\u003e helper JSON-serializes under the hood:","text":"The `DistributedCacheExtensions.cs` helper JSON-serializes under the hood:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public static async Task\u003cT?\u003e GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e(this IDistributedCache cache, string key,\n    Func\u003cTask\u003cT\u003e\u003e task, DistributedCacheEntryOptions? options = null)\n{\n    options ??= new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n        .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30))\n        .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1));\n\n    if (cache.TryGetValue(key, out T? value) && value is not null)\n        return value;\n\n    value = await task();\n    if (value is not null)\n        await cache.SetAsync\u003cT\u003e(key, value, options);\n\n    return value;\n}\n\npublic static Task SetAsync\u003cT\u003e(this IDistributedCache cache, string key, T value,\n    DistributedCacheEntryOptions options)\n{\n    var bytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(JsonSerializer.Serialize(value, serializerOptions));\n    return cache.SetAsync(key, bytes, options);\n}\n\npublic static bool TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e(this IDistributedCache cache, string key, out T? value)\n{\n    var val = cache.Get(key);\n    value = default;\n    if (val == null) return false;\n    value = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cT\u003e(val, serializerOptions);\n    return true;\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eGameService\u003c/code\u003e — consumer pattern (primary ctor)","text":"`GameService` — consumer pattern (primary ctor)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class GameService(ApplicationDbContext context,\n                        IDistributedCache cache,\n                        ILogger\u003cGameService\u003e logger)\n{\n    public async Task\u003cList\u003cGame\u003e\u003e GetByCountry(string country)\n    {\n        var cacheKey = $\"games:country:{country}\";\n        var cacheOptions = new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n            .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(20))\n            .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2));\n\n        var games = await cache.GetOrSetAsync(\n            cacheKey,\n            async () =\u003e await context.Games\n                .Where(g =\u003e g.Country!.ToLower() == country.ToLower())\n                .ToListAsync(),\n            cacheOptions)!;\n\n        return games!;\n    }\n\n    public async Task Add(Game game)\n    {\n        await context.Games.AddAsync(game);\n        await context.SaveChangesAsync();\n\n        // Invalidate\n        cache.Remove(\"games\");\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Three pieces: key (with parameter), factory lambda (runs on miss), per-call options.","text":"Three pieces: key (with parameter), factory lambda (runs on miss), per-call options."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Expiration options","text":"Expiration options"},{"kind":"h3","html":"MemoryCacheEntryOptions (object init)","text":"MemoryCacheEntryOptions (object init)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"new MemoryCacheEntryOptions\n{\n    AbsoluteExpiration  = DateTime.Now.AddSeconds(50),\n    SlidingExpiration   = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(20),\n    Priority            = CacheItemPriority.High\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"DistributedCacheEntryOptions (fluent)","text":"DistributedCacheEntryOptions (fluent)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n    .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(20))\n    .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2));"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eOption\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eMeaning\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAbsoluteExpiration\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eHard deadline at wall-clock moment\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSlidingExpiration\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eIdle timeout, resets on each access\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePriority\u003c/code\u003e (memory only)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eEviction order under memory pressure (\u003ccode\u003eNeverRemove\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003eHigh\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003eNormal\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003eLow\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Combined: entry dies at \u003ccode\u003emin(absolute, idle-since-last-access + sliding)\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Combined: entry dies at `min(absolute, idle-since-last-access + sliding)`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePriority is NOT TTL\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eLow\u003c/code\u003e doesn&#39;t mean &quot;expires sooner.&quot;","text":"**Priority is NOT TTL** — `Low` doesn't mean \"expires sooner.\""},{"kind":"h2","html":"Docker Redis","text":"Docker Redis"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"docker run --name redis -d -p 6379:6379 redis\ndocker exec -it redis redis-cli"},{"kind":"p","html":"CLI quick-check:","text":"CLI quick-check:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"\u003e SET greeting \"hello\"\nOK\n\u003e SETEX tempkey 10 \"gone in 10s\"    # seconds, not ms\nOK\n\u003e TTL tempkey\n(integer) 10\n\u003e KEYS games:*\n\u003e GET games:country:France"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eAbortOnConnectFail = true\u003c/code\u003e crashes app if Redis unreachable at startup. Default \u003ccode\u003efalse\u003c/code\u003e → writes silently swallowed.","text":"`AbortOnConnectFail = true` crashes app if Redis unreachable at startup. Default `false` → writes silently swallowed."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Cache Tag Helper — \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (from course notes)","text":"Cache Tag Helper — `\u003ccache\u003e` (from course notes)"},{"kind":"p","html":"Built-in Razor Tag Helper. Wrap any block:","text":"Built-in Razor Tag Helper. Wrap any block:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003ccache vary-by-user=\"true\"\n       vary-by-route=\"id\"\n       expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\n       expires-sliding=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)\"\u003e\n    @await Html.PartialAsync(\"_ProductDetail\", Model)\n\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Attributes:","text":"Attributes:"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eAttribute\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eexpires-after=&quot;@TimeSpan&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAbsolute TTL\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eexpires-on=&quot;@DateTime&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAbsolute wall-clock\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eexpires-sliding=&quot;@TimeSpan&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eIdle timeout\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-user=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePer authenticated user\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-route=&quot;id&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePer route param value\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-query=&quot;search&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePer query-string key value\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-cookie=&quot;SessionId&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePer cookie value\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-header=&quot;User-Agent&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePer HTTP header value\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by=&quot;@Model.Key&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCustom key\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Backs onto \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e — same per-server problem as raw \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Backs onto `IMemoryCache` — same per-server problem as raw `IMemoryCache`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"App runs 3 API instances behind a load balancer with `AddMemoryCache()`. Users report stale data after updates. Cause?","a":"Each instance has its own `IMemoryCache`. Writes on A don't propagate to B/C. Fix: switch to `AddStackExchangeRedisCache(...)` + inject `IDistributedCache`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Cache writes silently succeed (no exception) but `redis-cli KEYS *` shows nothing. Cause?","a":"Redis isn't running. `AbortOnConnectFail` defaults to false → swallow writes. Set `AbortOnConnectFail = true` to crash at startup instead."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eTryGetValue\u003c/code\u003e is an out-parameter, not return: \u003ccode\u003eif (_cache.TryGetValue(key, out var v)) { ... }\u003c/code\u003e. Non-generic overload infers type from out-variable declaration.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`TryGetValue` is an out-parameter, not return: `if (_cache.TryGetValue(key, out var v)) { ... }`. Non-generic overload infers type from out-variable declaration."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eInvalidation is manual. After every write (\u003ccode\u003eSaveChangesAsync\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddAsync\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eUpdate\u003c/code\u003e), call \u003ccode\u003ecache.Remove(affectedKey)\u003c/code\u003e. TTL alone leaves stale data visible until expiration.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Invalidation is manual. After every write (`SaveChangesAsync`, `AddAsync`, `Update`), call `cache.Remove(affectedKey)`. TTL alone leaves stale data visible until expiration."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSETEX key 10 &quot;val&quot;\u003c/code\u003e in redis-cli is 10 \u003cstrong\u003eseconds\u003c/strong\u003e, not milliseconds. \u003ccode\u003ePSETEX\u003c/code\u003e uses ms.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`SETEX key 10 \"val\"` in redis-cli is 10 **seconds**, not milliseconds. `PSETEX` uses ms."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003evary-by-*\u003c/code\u003e on user-specific \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e blocks. First user&#39;s render shows for every subsequent visitor until TTL.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Omitting `vary-by-*` on user-specific `\u003ccache\u003e` blocks. First user's render shows for every subsequent visitor until TTL."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddMemoryCache()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eTryGetValue+Set\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eAddStackExchangeRedisCache(opts =&gt; { opts.Configuration = &quot;localhost&quot;; opts.ConfigurationOptions = new() { AbortOnConnectFail = true, ... }; })\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eGetOrSetAsync&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e extension. Options: \u003ccode\u003eAbsoluteExpiration\u003c/code\u003e (hard) + \u003ccode\u003eSlidingExpiration\u003c/code\u003e (idle reset); \u003ccode\u003ePriority\u003c/code\u003e is eviction-order, NOT TTL. Invalidate with \u003ccode\u003ecache.Remove(key)\u003c/code\u003e on every write. \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e tag helper for fragment caching with \u003ccode\u003evary-by-*\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`AddMemoryCache()` → `IMemoryCache` + `TryGetValue+Set`. `AddStackExchangeRedisCache(opts =\u003e { opts.Configuration = \"localhost\"; opts.ConfigurationOptions = new() { AbortOnConnectFail = true, ... }; })` → `IDistributedCache` + `GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` extension. Options: `AbsoluteExpiration` (hard) + `SlidingExpiration` (idle reset); `Priority` is eviction-order, NOT TTL. Invalidate with `cache.Remove(key)` on every write. `\u003ccache\u003e` tag helper for fragment caching with `vary-by-*`."}]},{"n":10,"id":"tag-helpers","title":"Custom Tag Helpers — TagHelper, ProcessAsync, _ViewImports","hook":"Inherit TagHelper. Decorate with [HtmlTargetElement]. Register in _ViewImports.cshtml.","tags":["tag-helper","razor"],"module":"Performance & Caching","source":"code-examples/ToonTagDemo/ToonTagDemo/TagHelpers/ToonTag.cs + Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"The recipe (ToonTagDemo)","text":"The recipe (ToonTagDemo)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers;\n\n[HtmlTargetElement(\"toon\")]\n[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = \"toonie\")]        // stacked — two bindings\npublic class ToonTag : TagHelper\n{\n    public string? FontFamily { get; set; }         // kebab-case: font-family\n    public string? FontSize { get; set; }\n    public string? ForegroundColor { get; set; }\n\n    public async override Task ProcessAsync(\n        TagHelperContext context,\n        TagHelperOutput output)\n    {\n        IEnumerable\u003cToon\u003e toons = await GetToonsAsync();\n\n        string customStyle =\n            $\"font-family: {FontFamily};font-size: {FontSize};color: {ForegroundColor};\";\n        output.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"style\", customStyle);\n\n        string html = \"\u003ctable\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth\u003eName\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth\u003ePicture\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\";\n        foreach (var item in toons)\n            html += $\"\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e{item.FirstName} {item.LastName}\u003c/td\u003e\" +\n                    $\"\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg src='{item.PictureUrl}' style='width:50px'/\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\";\n        html += \"\u003c/table\u003e\";\n\n        output.Content.SetHtmlContent(html);\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Usage in Razor:","text":"Usage in Razor:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003ctoon font-family=\"arial\" font-size=\"larger\" foreground-color=\"purple\"\u003e\u003c/toon\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Three pieces","text":"Three pieces"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInherit \u003ccode\u003eTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e (\u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDecorate with \u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement(...)]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — one or more bindings. Stack multiple attributes to match several patterns.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOverride \u003ccode\u003eProcessAsync\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e for async work (HTTP, DB, file I/O). Override \u003ccode\u003eProcess\u003c/code\u003e for CPU-only.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **Inherit `TagHelper`** (`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers`).\n2. **Decorate with `[HtmlTargetElement(...)]`** — one or more bindings. Stack multiple attributes to match several patterns.\n3. **Override `ProcessAsync`** for async work (HTTP, DB, file I/O). Override `Process` for CPU-only."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement]\u003c/code\u003e — tag OR attribute","text":"`[HtmlTargetElement]` — tag OR attribute"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[HtmlTargetElement(\"toon\")]                  // matches \u003ctoon ...\u003e\n[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = \"toonie\")]   // matches any element with toonie=\"..\""},{"kind":"p","html":"ToonTagDemo stacks both — the helper binds to both patterns.","text":"ToonTagDemo stacks both — the helper binds to both patterns."},{"kind":"h2","html":"PascalCase ↔ kebab-case","text":"PascalCase ↔ kebab-case"},{"kind":"p","html":"Razor auto-translates property names. \u003ccode\u003eFontFamily\u003c/code\u003e in C# binds to \u003ccode\u003efont-family\u003c/code\u003e in markup. \u003ccode\u003eForegroundColor\u003c/code\u003e ↔ \u003ccode\u003eforeground-color\u003c/code\u003e. Automatic — no config.","text":"Razor auto-translates property names. `FontFamily` in C# binds to `font-family` in markup. `ForegroundColor` ↔ `foreground-color`. Automatic — no config."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Output manipulation (demo uses two)","text":"Output manipulation (demo uses two)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"output.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"style\", customStyle);    // add/replace attribute\noutput.Content.SetHtmlContent(html);                     // replace inner HTML"},{"kind":"p","html":"ToonTagDemo does not rewrite \u003ccode\u003eoutput.TagName\u003c/code\u003e — rendered element stays \u003ccode\u003e&lt;toon&gt;\u003c/code\u003e with computed style + injected table.","text":"ToonTagDemo does not rewrite `output.TagName` — rendered element stays `\u003ctoon\u003e` with computed style + injected table."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Registration — \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Registration — `_ViewImports.cshtml`"},{"kind":"p","html":"Razor does NOT auto-discover Tag Helpers. From \u003ccode\u003eToonTagDemo/Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"Razor does NOT auto-discover Tag Helpers. From `ToonTagDemo/Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@using ToonTagDemo\n@namespace ToonTagDemo.Pages\n@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n@addTagHelper \"ToonTagDemo.TagHelpers.ToonTag, ToonTagDemo\""},{"kind":"p","html":"Two \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e forms:","text":"Two `@addTagHelper` forms:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWildcard\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName\u003c/code\u003e — every helper in assembly.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpecific type\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper &quot;FullTypeName, AssemblyName&quot;\u003c/code\u003e — one helper.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **Wildcard** — `@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName` — every helper in assembly.\n2. **Specific type** — `@addTagHelper \"FullTypeName, AssemblyName\"` — one helper."},{"kind":"p","html":"Built-ins always via: \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\u003c/code\u003e (includes \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&lt;environment&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&lt;partial&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003easp-for\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003easp-controller\u003c/code\u003e, etc.).","text":"Built-ins always via: `@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers` (includes `\u003ccache\u003e`, `\u003cenvironment\u003e`, `\u003cpartial\u003e`, `asp-for`, `asp-controller`, etc.)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Scoping","text":"Scoping"},{"kind":"p","html":"Drop additional \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e into subdirectory to scope registrations to pages under it. Files inherit parent \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e files. No re-registration per page.","text":"Drop additional `_ViewImports.cshtml` into subdirectory to scope registrations to pages under it. Files inherit parent `_ViewImports.cshtml` files. No re-registration per page."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"You write `\u003ctoon\u003e` in a Razor page. Razor outputs literal `\u003ctoon\u003e` in the rendered HTML — no table, no style. Most likely missing step?","a":"`@addTagHelper` entry in `_ViewImports.cshtml`. Without it, Razor treats `\u003ctoon\u003e` as unknown HTML."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Property `BorderColor` stays null when page has `\u003cwidget bordercolor=\"red\"\u003e`. Why?","a":"PascalCase ↔ kebab-case. `BorderColor` binds to `border-color`, not `bordercolor`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eBlocking \u003ccode\u003e.Result\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.Wait()\u003c/code\u003e inside \u003ccode\u003eProcess\u003c/code\u003e on an async API — Razor renders on thread pool that starves. Override \u003ccode\u003eProcessAsync\u003c/code\u003e whenever helper awaits.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Blocking `.Result` or `.Wait()` inside `Process` on an async API — Razor renders on thread pool that starves. Override `ProcessAsync` whenever helper awaits."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eRegistering helper in a per-page \u003ccode\u003e.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e file instead of \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e. Works for one page, forces repetition everywhere else.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Registering helper in a per-page `.cshtml` file instead of `_ViewImports.cshtml`. Works for one page, forces repetition everywhere else."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eInherit \u003ccode\u003eTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e → decorate with \u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement(&quot;name&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = &quot;attr&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e (stackable) → override \u003ccode\u003eProcessAsync(context, output)\u003c/code\u003e. PascalCase property ↔ kebab-case attribute. Manipulate via \u003ccode\u003eoutput.Attributes.SetAttribute(...)\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eoutput.Content.SetHtmlContent(...)\u003c/code\u003e. Register in \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e: \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper *, Assembly\u003c/code\u003e (wildcard) or \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper &quot;FullType, Assembly&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (specific).\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Inherit `TagHelper` → decorate with `[HtmlTargetElement(\"name\")]` or `[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = \"attr\")]` (stackable) → override `ProcessAsync(context, output)`. PascalCase property ↔ kebab-case attribute. Manipulate via `output.Attributes.SetAttribute(...)` + `output.Content.SetHtmlContent(...)`. Register in `_ViewImports.cshtml`: `@addTagHelper *, Assembly` (wildcard) or `@addTagHelper \"FullType, Assembly\"` (specific)."}]},{"n":11,"id":"localization","title":"Localization — AddLocalization, cultures, IStringLocalizer","hook":"Five registrations + UseRequestLocalization middleware. Skip the middleware → silent no-op.","tags":["i18n","culture","resx"],"module":"Internationalization & Modern UI","source":"Labs/W10 Localization/Sports/Program.cs + SharedResource.cs + Services/SharedResourceService.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"W10 Sports lab — full \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e","text":"W10 Sports lab — full `Program.cs`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using System.Globalization;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Localization;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.Options;\nusing Sports;\nusing Sports.Services;\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages();\n\nbuilder.Services.AddDbContext\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e(options =\u003e\n    options.UseSqlite(builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString(\"DefaultConnection\")));\n\n// 1. Register localization services\nbuilder.Services.AddLocalization(options =\u003e options.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\n\n// 2. Declare supported cultures + default\nbuilder.Services.Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(options =\u003e\n{\n    var supportedCultures = new[] {\n        new CultureInfo(\"en\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"de\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"fr\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"zh\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"en-US\")\n    };\n    options.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n    options.SupportedCultures     = supportedCultures;\n    options.SupportedUICultures   = supportedCultures;\n});\n\n// 3. Turn on view + data-annotation localization\nbuilder.Services.AddMvc()\n    .AddViewLocalization()\n    .AddDataAnnotationsLocalization(options =\u003e\n    {\n        options.DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (type, factory) =\u003e\n            factory.Create(typeof(SharedResource));\n    });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddSingleton\u003cSharedResourceService\u003e();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\n\n// 4. Apply detected culture to each request (lab uses explicit opts via scope)\nusing (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())\n{\n    var localizationOptions = scope.ServiceProvider\n        .GetRequiredService\u003cIOptions\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e\u003e().Value;\n    app.UseRequestLocalization(localizationOptions);\n}\n\napp.MapRazorPages();\napp.Run();"},{"kind":"p","html":"Skip any call (especially \u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization\u003c/code\u003e) → every request uses default culture silently.","text":"Skip any call (especially `UseRequestLocalization`) → every request uses default culture silently."},{"kind":"h2","html":"What each line does","text":"What each line does"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — registers \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, factory. \u003ccode\u003eResourcesPath\u003c/code\u003e = root folder for \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e files.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eConfigure&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — allowed cultures + fallback. \u003ccode\u003eSupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e → formatting (\u003ccode\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e). \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e → resource file picks (\u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddViewLocalization\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — wires \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e for \u003ccode\u003e.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e \u003ccode\u003e@inject\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddDataAnnotationsLocalization\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — translates \u003ccode\u003e[Required(ErrorMessage = &quot;X&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e. W10 routes through \u003ccode\u003eSharedResource\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003eDataAnnotationLocalizerProvider\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — middleware runs culture providers per request, sets \u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- **`AddLocalization`** — registers `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e`, `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e`, factory. `ResourcesPath` = root folder for `.resx` files.\n- **`Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e`** — allowed cultures + fallback. `SupportedCultures` → formatting (`CurrentCulture`). `SupportedUICultures` → resource file picks (`CurrentUICulture`).\n- **`AddViewLocalization`** — wires `IViewLocalizer` for `.cshtml` `@inject`.\n- **`AddDataAnnotationsLocalization`** — translates `[Required(ErrorMessage = \"X\")]` via `IStringLocalizer`. W10 routes through `SharedResource` via `DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider`.\n- **`UseRequestLocalization()`** — middleware runs culture providers per request, sets `Thread.CurrentCulture` + `CurrentUICulture`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture","text":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eProperty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eControls\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eDate/number/currency formatting (\u003ccode\u003e.ToString()\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003edecimal.ToString(&quot;C&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eWhich \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e gets loaded by \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Set both via \u003ccode\u003eSupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e. Setting only one leaves either formatting OR translations at default.","text":"Set both via `SupportedCultures` + `SupportedUICultures`. Setting only one leaves either formatting OR translations at default."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Resource file paths","text":"Resource file paths"},{"kind":"p","html":"For \u003ccode\u003ePages/Index.cshtml.cs\u003c/code\u003e (class \u003ccode\u003eIndexModel\u003c/code\u003e):","text":"For `Pages/Index.cshtml.cs` (class `IndexModel`):"},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"Resources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx"},{"kind":"p","html":"Rules:","text":"Rules:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRoot\u003c/strong\u003e matches \u003ccode\u003eoptions.ResourcesPath\u003c/code\u003e (conventionally \u003ccode\u003eResources\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSubfolder\u003c/strong\u003e mirrors the class&#39;s folder (\u003ccode\u003ePages/\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFilename\u003c/strong\u003e = \u003ccode\u003e&lt;ClassName&gt;.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **Root** matches `options.ResourcesPath` (conventionally `Resources`).\n2. **Subfolder** mirrors the class's folder (`Pages/`).\n3. **Filename** = `\u003cClassName\u003e.\u003cculture\u003e.resx`."},{"kind":"p","html":"Examples:","text":"Examples:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eController \u003ccode\u003eControllers/HomeController.cs\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eResources/Controllers/HomeController.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eShared marker class → \u003ccode\u003eResources/SharedResource.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e (no subfolder if at root namespace)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- Controller `Controllers/HomeController.cs` → `Resources/Controllers/HomeController.fr.resx`\n- Shared marker class → `Resources/SharedResource.fr.resx` (no subfolder if at root namespace)"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Shared resource pattern","text":"Shared resource pattern"},{"kind":"p","html":"Empty marker class at root namespace:","text":"Empty marker class at root namespace:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Sports/SharedResource.cs\nnamespace Sports;\npublic class SharedResource { }"},{"kind":"p","html":"Service that uses \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizerFactory\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"Service that uses `IStringLocalizerFactory`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Sports/Services/SharedResourceService.cs\nusing System.Reflection;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.Localization;\n\nnamespace Sports.Services;\n\npublic class SharedResourceService\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer localizer;\n    public SharedResourceService(IStringLocalizerFactory factory)\n    {\n        var assemblyName = new AssemblyName(\n            typeof(SharedResource).GetTypeInfo().Assembly.FullName!);\n        localizer = factory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), assemblyName.Name!);\n    }\n\n    public string Get(string key) =\u003e localizer[key];\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Register + inject:","text":"Register + inject:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.Services.AddSingleton\u003cSharedResourceService\u003e();\n\n// Razor page\n@inject SharedResourceService Shared\n\u003cfooter\u003e© @Shared.Get(\"CompanyName\")\u003c/footer\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Culture providers (default order)","text":"Culture providers (default order)"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization\u003c/code\u003e runs three providers in order. First match wins:","text":"`UseRequestLocalization` runs three providers in order. First match wins:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eQueryString\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e?culture=fr\u003c/code\u003e in URL. Highest priority.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCookie\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e cookie (persistent user selection).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAcceptLanguageHeader\u003c/strong\u003e — browser&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eAccept-Language\u003c/code\u003e header.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **QueryString** — `?culture=fr` in URL. Highest priority.\n2. **Cookie** — `.AspNetCore.Culture` cookie (persistent user selection).\n3. **AcceptLanguageHeader** — browser's `Accept-Language` header."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Switch cookie on POST","text":"Switch cookie on POST"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public IActionResult OnPost(string culture, string returnUrl)\n{\n    Response.Cookies.Append(\n        CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName,\n        CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(culture)),\n        new CookieOptions { Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddYears(1) });\n\n    return LocalRedirect(returnUrl);\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Three localizer interfaces","text":"Three localizer interfaces"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eInterface\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eWhere\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eReturns\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eUse when\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAny DI-aware class\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePlain text\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCode-behind text\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAny DI-aware class\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSafe HTML\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTranslation contains markup (anchors, \u003ccode\u003e&lt;strong&gt;\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003e@inject\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePlain text\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRendering straight from markup\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"All use indexer: \u003ccode\u003elocalizer[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e. Positional args: \u003ccode\u003elocalizer[&quot;Greet&quot;, name]\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e value \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Hello, {0}!&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"All use indexer: `localizer[\"Key\"]`. Positional args: `localizer[\"Greet\", name]` → `.resx` value `\"Hello, {0}!\"`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"PageModel injection","text":"PageModel injection"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class IndexModel : PageModel\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e _localizer;\n    public IndexModel(IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e localizer) =\u003e _localizer = localizer;\n\n    public void OnGet()\n    {\n        ViewData[\"Message\"] = _localizer[\"Message\"];\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Generic parameter drives which \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e to load (\u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e).","text":"Generic parameter drives which `.resx` to load (`Resources/Pages/IndexModel.\u003cculture\u003e.resx`)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e in \u003ccode\u003e.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e","text":"`IViewLocalizer` in `.cshtml`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@page\n@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n@model IndexModel\n\n\u003ch1\u003e@Localizer[\"Welcome\"]\u003c/h1\u003e"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"`AddLocalization` + `Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e` + `AddViewLocalization` are all in `Program.cs`. Users report language never switches. Single most likely missing line?","a":"`app.UseRequestLocalization()`. Without middleware, no provider runs, `CurrentCulture` / `CurrentUICulture` never set — app behaves as if every user prefers default culture."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"`IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e[\"Welcome\"]` returns literal `\"Welcome\"` though `Resources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx` has it as `\"Bienvenue\"`. Two possible reasons?","a":"(1) User's culture isn't French — no `?culture=fr`, no cookie, `Accept-Language` is `en-US`. (2) `UseRequestLocalization()` missing → `CurrentUICulture` stays at default."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eNaming file \u003ccode\u003eResources/IndexModel.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e (no \u003ccode\u003ePages/\u003c/code\u003e subfolder) for class in \u003ccode\u003ePages/\u003c/code\u003e. Build succeeds but lookup returns key unchanged — folder must mirror class&#39;s folder.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Naming file `Resources/IndexModel.fr.resx` (no `Pages/` subfolder) for class in `Pages/`. Build succeeds but lookup returns key unchanged — folder must mirror class's folder."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e on translation containing HTML markup → \u003ccode\u003e&quot;&lt;a href=\\&quot;/\\&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&quot;\u003c/code\u003e renders as literal text. Use \u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e@Html.Raw(...)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` on translation containing HTML markup → `\"\u003ca href=\\\"/\\\"\u003eHome\u003c/a\u003e\"` renders as literal text. Use `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` or `@Html.Raw(...)`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization(o =&gt; o.ResourcesPath = &quot;Resources&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eConfigure&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eSupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eDefaultRequestCulture\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eAddViewLocalization\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eAddDataAnnotationsLocalization(opts =&gt; opts.DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (t, f) =&gt; f.Create(typeof(SharedResource)))\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eapp.UseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e. Resource path: \u003ccode\u003eResources/&lt;folder&gt;/&lt;ClassName&gt;.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e. Shared: \u003ccode\u003eSharedResource\u003c/code\u003e marker + \u003ccode\u003eSharedResourceService\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizerFactory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), asmName)\u003c/code\u003e. Inject: \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (code), \u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (HTML), \u003ccode\u003e@inject IViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e (view). Providers: QueryString → Cookie → Accept-Language.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`AddLocalization(o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\")` → `Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e` with `SupportedCultures` + `SupportedUICultures` + `DefaultRequestCulture` → `AddViewLocalization` + `AddDataAnnotationsLocalization(opts =\u003e opts.DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (t, f) =\u003e f.Create(typeof(SharedResource)))` → `app.UseRequestLocalization()`. Resource path: `Resources/\u003cfolder\u003e/\u003cClassName\u003e.\u003cculture\u003e.resx`. Shared: `SharedResource` marker + `SharedResourceService` with `IStringLocalizerFactory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), asmName)`. Inject: `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` (code), `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` (HTML), `@inject IViewLocalizer` (view). Providers: QueryString → Cookie → Accept-Language."}]},{"n":12,"id":"blazor-quickgrid","title":"Blazor QuickGrid — PropertyColumn, TemplateColumn, PaginationState","hook":"Bind IQueryable. Declare PaginationState. Pair with \u003cPaginator State=\u003e.","tags":["blazor","ui","quickgrid"],"module":"Internationalization & Modern UI","source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/BlazorStudents/Components/Pages/StudentPages/Index.razor; code-examples/BlazorQuickGrid/BlazorQuickGrid/BlazorSchool/Pages/Index.razor","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"W07 lab — Blazor Server + IDbContextFactory","text":"W07 lab — Blazor Server + IDbContextFactory"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore\n@using BlazorStudents.Models\n@using BlazorStudents.Data\n@implements IAsyncDisposable\n@inject IDbContextFactory\u003cBlazorStudents.Data.ApplicationDbContext\u003e DbFactory\n@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager\n\n\u003cinput type=\"search\" @bind=\"FilterValue\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" placeholder=\"Search...\" /\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Class=\"table\" Items=\"@FilteredStudents\" Pagination=\"@pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.FirstName\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.LastName\"  Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.School\"    Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.Gender\"    Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.DateOfBirth\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\n    \u003cTemplateColumn Context=\"student\"\u003e\n        \u003ca href=\"@($\"students/edit?studentid={student.StudentId}\")\"\u003eEdit\u003c/a\u003e |\n        \u003ca href=\"@($\"students/details?studentid={student.StudentId}\")\"\u003eDetails\u003c/a\u003e |\n        \u003ca href=\"@($\"students/delete?studentid={student.StudentId}\")\"\u003eDelete\u003c/a\u003e\n    \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private ApplicationDbContext context = default!;\n    private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n    private string FilterValue = string.Empty;\n\n    IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e? FilteredStudents\n    {\n        get\n        {\n            var students = context.Students.AsQueryable();\n            if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(FilterValue))\n            {\n                var q = FilterValue.ToLower();\n                students = students.Where(s =\u003e\n                    s.FirstName!.ToLower().Contains(q) ||\n                    s.LastName!.ToLower().Contains(q) ||\n                    s.School!.ToLower().Contains(q));\n            }\n            return students;\n        }\n    }\n\n    protected override void OnInitialized()\n        =\u003e context = DbFactory.CreateDbContext();\n\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() =\u003e await context.DisposeAsync();\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Six moving parts:","text":"Six moving parts:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e — QuickGrid needs interactivity.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIDbContextFactory&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — server lab creates scoped context per page lifetime.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;QuickGrid Items=&quot;...&quot; Pagination=&quot;...&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — binds \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e source.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;PropertyColumn Property=&quot;x =&gt; x.Field&quot; Sortable=&quot;true&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — one per displayed property.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;TemplateColumn Context=&quot;student&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — free-form markup with row access via \u003ccode\u003estudent\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@pagination&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — renders pager controls.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. `@rendermode InteractiveServer` — QuickGrid needs interactivity.\n2. `IDbContextFactory\u003cT\u003e` — server lab creates scoped context per page lifetime.\n3. `\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"...\" Pagination=\"...\"\u003e` — binds `IQueryable\u003cT\u003e` source.\n4. `\u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"x =\u003e x.Field\" Sortable=\"true\"\u003e` — one per displayed property.\n5. `\u003cTemplateColumn Context=\"student\"\u003e` — free-form markup with row access via `student`.\n6. `\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\"\u003e` — renders pager controls."},{"kind":"h2","html":"PropertyColumn vs TemplateColumn","text":"PropertyColumn vs TemplateColumn"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003e\u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBinding\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eProperty=&quot;x =&gt; x.Field&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFree-form markup with \u003ccode\u003eContext=&quot;name&quot;\u003c/code\u003e row access\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSortability\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSortable=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e sorts by bound expression\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNot automatic\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eUse when\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eStraight property display\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCustom markup, action links, multi-property\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Pagination — \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Pagination — `PaginationState`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 15 };"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@pagination&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e renders first/prev/next/last controls + updates \u003ccode\u003eCurrentPageIndex\u003c/code\u003e. Server lab uses \u003ccode\u003eState=&quot;@pagination&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"`\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\"\u003e` renders first/prev/next/last controls + updates `CurrentPageIndex`. Server lab uses `State=\"@pagination\"`."},{"kind":"p","html":"WASM variant (BlazorQuickGrid/BlazorSchool): \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator Value=&quot;@pages&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — same state object, attribute name differs per template.","text":"WASM variant (BlazorQuickGrid/BlazorSchool): `\u003cPaginator Value=\"@pages\"\u003e` — same state object, attribute name differs per template."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Live filter — \u003ccode\u003e@bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e","text":"Live filter — `@bind:event=\"oninput\"`"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003cinput type=\"search\" @bind=\"FilterValue\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" placeholder=\"Search...\" /\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Two mechanics:","text":"Two mechanics:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e — updates on each keystroke. Default \u003ccode\u003e@bind\u003c/code\u003e listens for \u003ccode\u003eonchange\u003c/code\u003e (only on focus loss).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReturn \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e from filter so EF translates \u003ccode\u003e.Where\u003c/code\u003e into SQL.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- `@bind:event=\"oninput\"` — updates on each keystroke. Default `@bind` listens for `onchange` (only on focus loss).\n- Return `IQueryable\u003cT\u003e` from filter so EF translates `.Where` into SQL."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Per-column filter (WASM variant)","text":"Per-column filter (WASM variant)"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eBlazorSchool/Pages/Index.razor\u003c/code\u003e uses \u003ccode\u003e&lt;ColumnOptions&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eResizableColumns=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"`BlazorSchool/Pages/Index.razor` uses `\u003cColumnOptions\u003e` + `ResizableColumns=\"true\"`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@filteredStudents\" ResizableColumns=\"true\" Pagination=\"@pages\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" Sortable=\"true\" title=\"First Name\"\u003e\n        \u003cColumnOptions\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"search-box\"\u003e\n                \u003cinput type=\"search\" @bind=\"firstNameFilter\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" /\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/ColumnOptions\u003e\n    \u003c/PropertyColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Filter appears as dropdown on column header.","text":"Filter appears as dropdown on column header."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"`\u003cinput @bind=\"FilterValue\"\u003e` updates `FilterValue` but grid doesn't refresh while typing. What's missing?","a":"`@bind:event=\"oninput\"`. Without it, `@bind` defaults to `onchange` — only fires on focus loss."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;...&quot; /&gt;\u003c/code\u003e in Server vs \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator Value=&quot;...&quot; /&gt;\u003c/code\u003e in WASM. Both valid — attribute name varies per template.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`\u003cPaginator State=\"...\" /\u003e` in Server vs `\u003cPaginator Value=\"...\" /\u003e` in WASM. Both valid — attribute name varies per template."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eForgetting \u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e. Grid renders but clicks do nothing.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Forgetting `@rendermode InteractiveServer`. Grid renders but clicks do nothing."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;QuickGrid Items=&quot;IQueryable&lt;T&gt;&quot; Pagination=&quot;@state&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@state&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (server) or \u003ccode\u003eValue=&quot;@state&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (WASM template) + \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn Property=&quot;x =&gt; x.Field&quot; Sortable=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e for direct; \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn Context=&quot;x&quot;\u003c/code\u003e for action links. Live filter: \u003ccode\u003e@bind + @bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e + computed \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"IQueryable\u003cT\u003e\" Pagination=\"@state\"\u003e` + `\u003cPaginator State=\"@state\"\u003e` (server) or `Value=\"@state\"` (WASM template) + `PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }`. `PropertyColumn Property=\"x =\u003e x.Field\" Sortable=\"true\"` for direct; `TemplateColumn Context=\"x\"` for action links. Live filter: `@bind + @bind:event=\"oninput\"` + computed `IQueryable\u003cT\u003e`."}]},{"n":13,"id":"file-based-apps","title":"File-based .NET apps — dotnet run file.cs + #: directives","hook":"One file, one command, no csproj. Four directives for package/property/sdk/project.","tags":["dotnet-10","scripting","directives"],"module":".NET 10 Scripts & Reporting","source":"code-examples/20260324_file-based-apps/file-based-apps/example-1/HelloDevs.cs + example-2/HelloScript.cs + example-3/Where.cs + example-4/Locations.cs + FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"One file, one command","text":"One file, one command"},{"kind":"p","html":".NET 10 runs a standalone \u003ccode\u003e.cs\u003c/code\u003e without a \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e. Save as \u003ccode\u003eHelloDevs.cs\u003c/code\u003e:","text":".NET 10 runs a standalone `.cs` without a `.csproj`. Save as `HelloDevs.cs`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"Console.WriteLine(\"Hello Devs\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"Then:","text":"Then:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"dotnet run HelloDevs.cs"},{"kind":"p","html":"CLI detects the \u003ccode\u003e.cs\u003c/code\u003e arg, generates implicit project context, compiles in memory, executes. Artifacts cached under \u003ccode\u003e~/.dotnet/runfile/\u003c/code\u003e keyed by file hash.","text":"CLI detects the `.cs` arg, generates implicit project context, compiles in memory, executes. Artifacts cached under `~/.dotnet/runfile/` keyed by file hash."},{"kind":"p","html":"No \u003ccode\u003ebin/\u003c/code\u003e, no \u003ccode\u003eobj/\u003c/code\u003e, no \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e. One file.","text":"No `bin/`, no `obj/`, no `.csproj`. One file."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Top-level statements + args","text":"Top-level statements + args"},{"kind":"p","html":"File body IS \u003ccode\u003eMain\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"File body IS `Main`:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#!/usr/bin/env dotnet\n#:property TargetFramework=net9.0\nvar name = args.Length \u003e 0 ? args[0] : \"World\";\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Hello, {name}!\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"Implicit usings: \u003ccode\u003eSystem\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Collections.Generic\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Linq\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Text\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Threading.Tasks\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Implicit usings: `System`, `System.Collections.Generic`, `System.Linq`, `System.Text`, `System.Threading.Tasks`."},{"kind":"p","html":"Pass args with \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e separator:","text":"Pass args with `--` separator:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"dotnet run greet.cs -- Kevin\n# → Hello, Kevin!"},{"kind":"p","html":"Without \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e, CLI interprets \u003ccode\u003eKevin\u003c/code\u003e as flag to itself → \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Hello, World!&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Without `--`, CLI interprets `Kevin` as flag to itself → `\"Hello, World!\"`."},{"kind":"h2","html":"The four \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e directives","text":"The four `#:` directives"},{"kind":"p","html":"All share shape \u003ccode\u003e#:&lt;kind&gt; &lt;value&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — NO space after colon. \u003ccode\u003e#: package\u003c/code\u003e fails.","text":"All share shape `#:\u003ckind\u003e \u003cvalue\u003e` — NO space after colon. `#: package` fails."},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eDirective\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:package Name@Version\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNuGet dependency\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:property Key=Value\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMSBuild property\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:sdk SdkName\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSDK selection\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:project ./path.csproj\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eLocal project reference\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Directives at top of file, above \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e and code.","text":"Directives at top of file, above `using` and code."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e (example-4 Locations.cs)","text":"`#:package` (example-4 Locations.cs)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\n\nusing Spectre.Console;\n\nvar cities = new[] {\n    new { City = \"New York\", Country = \"USA\" },\n    new { City = \"Tokyo\",    Country = \"Japan\" },\n};\n\nvar table = new Table();\ntable.Title = new TableTitle(\"[bold red]Cities and Countries[/]\");\ntable.Border = TableBorder.Rounded;\ntable.AddColumn(new TableColumn(\"[bold]City[/]\"));\ntable.AddColumn(new TableColumn(\"[bold]Country[/]\"));\nforeach (var c in cities) table.AddRow(c.City, c.Country);\nAnsiConsole.Write(table);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:package &lt;Name&gt;@&lt;Version&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. CLI downloads + caches. Omit \u003ccode\u003e@version\u003c/code\u003e → latest stable (reproducibility risk).","text":"`#:package \u003cName\u003e@\u003cVersion\u003e`. CLI downloads + caches. Omit `@version` → latest stable (reproducibility risk)."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:property\u003c/code\u003e (example-2 HelloScript.cs)","text":"`#:property` (example-2 HelloScript.cs)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:property TargetFramework=net9.0\n#:property Nullable=enable\n#:property LangVersion=preview"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:property &lt;Name&gt;=&lt;Value&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (no spaces around \u003ccode\u003e=\u003c/code\u003e). Stack multiple lines.","text":"`#:property \u003cName\u003e=\u003cValue\u003e` (no spaces around `=`). Stack multiple lines."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:sdk\u003c/code\u003e (FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs)","text":"`#:sdk` (FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#!/usr/bin/env dotnet\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\n\nusing System.Text.Json.Serialization;\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nbuilder.Services.ConfigureHttpJsonOptions(options =\u003e\n{\n    options.SerializerOptions.TypeInfoResolverChain.Insert(0, AppJsonSerializerContext.Default);\n});\n\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenApi();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGet(\"/\", () =\u003e new HelloResponse { Message = \"Hello, World!\" })\n   .WithName(\"HelloWorld\");\napp.Run();\n\n[JsonSerializable(typeof(HelloResponse))]\ninternal partial class AppJsonSerializerContext : JsonSerializerContext { }\n\npublic record HelloResponse { public string Message { get; init; } = string.Empty; }"},{"kind":"p","html":"SDKs:","text":"SDKs:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk\u003c/code\u003e — default console (no directive)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e — ASP.NET Core / minimal APIs\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly\u003c/code\u003e — Blazor WASM\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` — default console (no directive)\n- `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` — ASP.NET Core / minimal APIs\n- `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly` — Blazor WASM"},{"kind":"p","html":"Without \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eWebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)\u003c/code\u003e fails — default SDK lacks ASP.NET Core types.","text":"Without `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`, `WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)` fails — default SDK lacks ASP.NET Core types."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003e#:project\u003c/code\u003e (example-3 Where.cs)","text":"`#:project` (example-3 Where.cs)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj\n\nusing MyLibrary;\n\nvar person = new Person {\n    FirstName = \"John\",\n    LastName  = \"Doe\",\n    Email     = \"john.doe@example.com\",\n    DateOfBirth = new DateTime(1990, 1, 1)\n};\nConsole.WriteLine($\"{person.FirstName} {person.LastName}\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"Adds project reference — script can use types from referenced \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e. Reverse (\u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e referencing a \u003ccode\u003e.cs\u003c/code\u003e) not supported.","text":"Adds project reference — script can use types from referenced `.csproj`. Reverse (`.csproj` referencing a `.cs`) not supported."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Convert to traditional project","text":"Convert to traditional project"},{"kind":"code","lang":"bash","code":"dotnet project convert HelloDevs.cs -o HelloDevsProject"},{"kind":"p","html":"Creates folder with \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e, moves \u003ccode\u003e.cs\u003c/code\u003e in, preserves \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e directives as MSBuild equivalents.","text":"Creates folder with `.csproj`, moves `.cs` in, preserves `#:` directives as MSBuild equivalents."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"`dotnet run greet.cs Kevin` outputs `Hello, World!` not `Hello, Kevin!`. What did you forget?","a":"The `--` separator. `dotnet run greet.cs -- Kevin` passes `Kevin` to script."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"`var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);` fails with \"`WebApplication` not found.\" Missing?","a":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` at top. Default console SDK lacks ASP.NET Core."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#: package ...\u003c/code\u003e (space after colon) → parse error. Directive names case-sensitive. One directive per line.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`#: package ...` (space after colon) → parse error. Directive names case-sensitive. One directive per line."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e.NET 8/9 do NOT fully support file-based flow. \u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs\u003c/code\u003e errors or shims differently. Course targets .NET 10.\u003c/p\u003e","text":".NET 8/9 do NOT fully support file-based flow. `dotnet run file.cs` errors or shims differently. Course targets .NET 10."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs\u003c/code\u003e compiles + runs a \u003ccode\u003e.cs\u003c/code\u003e without project. Top-level statements = \u003ccode\u003eMain\u003c/code\u003e. Implicit usings cover System/Linq/etc. Args via \u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs -- arg1 arg2\u003c/code\u003e. Four directives at top (no space after \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e): \u003ccode\u003e#:package Name@Ver\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:property Key=Val\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:project ./path.csproj\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003edotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder\u003c/code\u003e graduates to traditional project.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`dotnet run file.cs` compiles + runs a `.cs` without project. Top-level statements = `Main`. Implicit usings cover System/Linq/etc. Args via `dotnet run file.cs -- arg1 arg2`. Four directives at top (no space after `#:`): `#:package Name@Ver`, `#:property Key=Val`, `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`, `#:project ./path.csproj`. `dotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder` graduates to traditional project."}]},{"n":14,"id":"excel-export","title":"Excel export with ClosedXML","hook":"XLWorkbook → Worksheet → 1-based Cell writes → MemoryStream → FileResult.","tags":["excel","closedxml","report"],"module":".NET 10 Scripts & Reporting","source":"Labs/w13/FifaWorldCup/Pages/Excel.cshtml.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Five-step export (W13 FifaWorldCup)","text":"Five-step export (W13 FifaWorldCup)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using ClosedXML.Excel;\nusing FifaWorldCup.Models;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.RazorPages;\n\npublic class ExcelModel : PageModel\n{\n    public FileResult OnGet()\n    {\n        var data = Game.GetGames();\n\n        using (var workbook = new XLWorkbook())\n        {\n            IXLWorksheet worksheet = workbook.Worksheets.Add(\"Games\");\n\n            // 1. Headers (1-BASED indexing)\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Game Id\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Year\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 3).Value = \"Gender\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 4).Value = \"City\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 5).Value = \"Country\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 6).Value = \"Continent\";\n            worksheet.Cell(1, 7).Value = \"Winner\";\n\n            // 2. Header styling\n            IXLRange range = worksheet.Range(\n                worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Address,\n                worksheet.Cell(1, 7).Address);\n            range.Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.Almond);\n\n            // 3. Data rows\n            int index = 1;\n            foreach (var item in data)\n            {\n                index++;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 1).Value = item.GameId;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 2).Value = item.Year;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 3).Value = item.Gender;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 4).Value = item.City;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 5).Value = item.Country;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 6).Value = item.Continent;\n                worksheet.Cell(index, 7).Value = item.Winner;\n            }\n\n            // 4. Save to MemoryStream\n            using (var stream = new MemoryStream())\n            {\n                workbook.SaveAs(stream);\n                var content = stream.ToArray();\n                string contentType = \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\";\n\n                var strDate = DateTime.Now.ToString(\"yyyyMMdd\");\n                string filename = $\"FifaWorldCup_{strDate}.xlsx\";\n\n                // 5. Return as FileResult\n                return File(content, contentType, filename);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Five moving parts","text":"Five moving parts"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eXLWorkbook()\u003c/code\u003e — in-memory workbook. \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e disposes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eWorksheets.Add(&quot;Name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e — named sheet.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eCell(row, col)\u003c/code\u003e — \u003cstrong\u003e1-BASED\u003c/strong\u003e indexing (matches Excel UI labels: \u003ccode\u003eA1\u003c/code\u003e = \u003ccode\u003eCell(1, 1)\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSaveAs(stream)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003estream.ToArray()\u003c/code\u003e → bytes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eFile(bytes, mimeType, filename)\u003c/code\u003e → ASP.NET Core serves as download.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. `XLWorkbook()` — in-memory workbook. `using` disposes.\n2. `Worksheets.Add(\"Name\")` — named sheet.\n3. `Cell(row, col)` — **1-BASED** indexing (matches Excel UI labels: `A1` = `Cell(1, 1)`).\n4. `SaveAs(stream)` → `stream.ToArray()` → bytes.\n5. `File(bytes, mimeType, filename)` → ASP.NET Core serves as download."},{"kind":"h2","html":"MIME type (exact)","text":"MIME type (exact)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"text","code":"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet"},{"kind":"p","html":"Wrong: \u003ccode\u003eapplication/excel\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eapplication/vnd.ms-excel\u003c/code\u003e (old \u003ccode\u003e.xls\u003c/code\u003e binary). Wrong MIME → browser confusion.","text":"Wrong: `application/excel`, `application/vnd.ms-excel` (old `.xls` binary). Wrong MIME → browser confusion."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003eRange\u003c/code\u003e for bulk styling","text":"`Range` for bulk styling"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"IXLRange header = worksheet.Range(\n    worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Address,\n    worksheet.Cell(1, 7).Address);\nheader.Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.Almond);\nheader.Style.Font.Bold = true;"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Auto-fit columns","text":"Auto-fit columns"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"worksheet.Columns().AdjustToContents();"},{"kind":"p","html":"Call after filling data, before saving.","text":"Call after filling data, before saving."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Row counter pattern","text":"Row counter pattern"},{"kind":"p","html":"Demo uses \u003ccode\u003eint index = 1; foreach { index++; ...Cell(index, ...) }\u003c/code\u003e — pre-increment before each data write. Row 1 = headers, row 2 = first data. No off-by-one.","text":"Demo uses `int index = 1; foreach { index++; ...Cell(index, ...) }` — pre-increment before each data write. Row 1 = headers, row 2 = first data. No off-by-one."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Users report downloaded Excel has trailing blank row, totals formula breaks. Handler has `for (int i = 0; i \u003c games.Count; i++) sheet.Cell(i, 1).Value = games[i].Name;`. What's wrong?","a":"Loop starts at `i = 0`, but `Cell(0, 1)` is invalid (ClosedXML 1-based). First write lands in row 1, overwriting headers. Start at `i = 1`, write to `Cell(i + 1, 1)`, OR pre-increment row counter starting at 1."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eTreating \u003ccode\u003eCell(row, col)\u003c/code\u003e as 0-based like C# arrays. Excel + ClosedXML use 1-based — \u003ccode\u003eCell(1, 1)\u003c/code\u003e is A1.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Treating `Cell(row, col)` as 0-based like C# arrays. Excel + ClosedXML use 1-based — `Cell(1, 1)` is A1."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(N)]\u003c/code\u003e in ML.NET is 0-based. \u003ccode\u003eCell(r, c)\u003c/code\u003e in ClosedXML is 1-based. Mixing conventions between readers and writers = off-by-one.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`[LoadColumn(N)]` in ML.NET is 0-based. `Cell(r, c)` in ClosedXML is 1-based. Mixing conventions between readers and writers = off-by-one."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eXLWorkbook()\u003c/code\u003e in \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eWorksheets.Add(&quot;name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e → fill with 1-based \u003ccode\u003eCell(row, col)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eRange(start, end).Style\u003c/code\u003e for bulk → \u003ccode\u003eSaveAs(MemoryStream)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003estream.ToArray()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eFile(bytes, &quot;application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet&quot;, &quot;name.xlsx&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`XLWorkbook()` in `using` → `Worksheets.Add(\"name\")` → fill with 1-based `Cell(row, col)` → `Range(start, end).Style` for bulk → `SaveAs(MemoryStream)` → `stream.ToArray()` → `File(bytes, \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\", \"name.xlsx\")`."}]},{"n":15,"id":"pdf-export","title":"PDF export with iText 7","hook":"PdfWriter → PdfDocument → Document → SetCloseStream(false) → add content → ms.Position = 0.","tags":["pdf","itext7","report"],"module":".NET 10 Scripts & Reporting","source":"Labs/w13/FifaWorldCup/Pages/PdfReport.cshtml.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Two packages (not one)","text":"Two packages (not one)"},{"kind":"p","html":"iText 7 needs both:","text":"iText 7 needs both:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"xml","code":"\u003cPackageReference Include=\"itext7\" Version=\"9.6.0\" /\u003e\n\u003cPackageReference Include=\"itext.bouncy-castle-adapter\" Version=\"9.6.0\" /\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Missing \u003ccode\u003ebouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e → runtime crash first time iText hashes/signs (embeds fonts, produces encrypted output). NOT a build error.","text":"Missing `bouncy-castle-adapter` → runtime crash first time iText hashes/signs (embeds fonts, produces encrypted output). NOT a build error."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Four-layer constructor pipeline","text":"Four-layer constructor pipeline"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\nusing iText.Kernel.Geom;\nusing iText.Kernel.Colors;\n\npublic IActionResult OnGet()\n{\n    var ms = new MemoryStream();\n\n    var writer   = new PdfWriter(ms);                         // 1. stream sink\n    var pdfDoc   = new PdfDocument(writer);                    // 2. PDF structure\n    var document = new Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false);   // 3. layout engine\n\n    writer.SetCloseStream(false);                              // 4. keep MemoryStream open\n\n    // ... add content ...\n\n    document.Close();\n    ms.Position = 0;                                           // CRITICAL — rewind\n\n    return new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\")\n    {\n        FileDownloadName = $\"Report_{DateTime.Now:yyyyMMdd}.pdf\"\n    };\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Each layer:","text":"Each layer:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter\u003c/code\u003e — writes bytes to a stream (\u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePdfDocument\u003c/code\u003e — PDF file structure (pages, cross-reference table, metadata)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eDocument\u003c/code\u003e — high-level layout (paragraphs, tables, separators)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSetCloseStream(false)\u003c/code\u003e — keeps MemoryStream open after \u003ccode\u003edocument.Close()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- `PdfWriter` — writes bytes to a stream (`MemoryStream`)\n- `PdfDocument` — PDF file structure (pages, cross-reference table, metadata)\n- `Document` — high-level layout (paragraphs, tables, separators)\n- `SetCloseStream(false)` — keeps MemoryStream open after `document.Close()`"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Adding content","text":"Adding content"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"document.Add(new Paragraph(\"Report Title\")\n    .SetTextAlignment(iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.CENTER)\n    .SetFontSize(20));\n\ndocument.Add(new LineSeparator(new SolidLine()));\n\nvar table = new Table(3);\ntable.AddCell(new Cell(1, 1)\n    .SetBackgroundColor(ColorConstants.LIGHT_GRAY)\n    .Add(new Paragraph(\"Column 1\")));\n// ... fill row-major ...\ndocument.Add(table);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eTable(n)\u003c/code\u003e = n-column table. \u003ccode\u003eAddCell\u003c/code\u003e fills left-to-right, wrapping on row fill.","text":"`Table(n)` = n-column table. `AddCell` fills left-to-right, wrapping on row fill."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Page numbers — post-layout loop","text":"Page numbers — post-layout loop"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"int total = pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages();\nfor (int i = 1; i \u003c= total; i++)\n{\n    document.ShowTextAligned(\n        new Paragraph($\"Page {i} of {total}\"),\n        559, 806, i,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.RIGHT,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.VerticalAlignment.TOP,\n        0);\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e559, 806\u003c/code\u003e = X/Y coordinates in points on A4 (595 × 842 points). Near top-right corner.","text":"`559, 806` = X/Y coordinates in points on A4 (595 × 842 points). Near top-right corner."},{"kind":"h2","html":"The \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e trap","text":"The `ms.Position = 0` trap"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter\u003c/code\u003e advances \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream.Position\u003c/code\u003e to end. \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e reads from current position to end — finds zero bytes → client downloads empty file.","text":"`PdfWriter` advances `MemoryStream.Position` to end. `FileStreamResult` reads from current position to end — finds zero bytes → client downloads empty file."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eAlways \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e before returning.\u003c/strong\u003e","text":"**Always `ms.Position = 0` before returning.**"},{"kind":"p","html":"Alternative: \u003ccode\u003eFile(ms.ToArray(), &quot;application/pdf&quot;, &quot;name.pdf&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e — position-insensitive, materializes bytes.","text":"Alternative: `File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"name.pdf\")` — position-insensitive, materializes bytes."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Handler compiles, runs, returns `.pdf`. Users open → \"document is empty or corrupted.\" Handler correct up to `new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\")`. What's missing?","a":"`ms.Position = 0` before constructing `FileStreamResult`. Stream's position is at end after writing → reads zero bytes."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eInstalling \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e without \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e. Project compiles fine. Runtime crash when hashing/signing.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Installing `itext7` without `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter`. Project compiles fine. Runtime crash when hashing/signing."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eMIME type is \u003ccode\u003eapplication/pdf\u003c/code\u003e (simple). Filename goes in \u003ccode\u003eFileDownloadName\u003c/code\u003e property of \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e, not constructor.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"MIME type is `application/pdf` (simple). Filename goes in `FileDownloadName` property of `FileStreamResult`, not constructor."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eInstall both \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter(ms)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfDocument(writer)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eDocument(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ewriter.SetCloseStream(false)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003edocument.Add(new Paragraph(...))\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003enew Table(cols)\u003c/code\u003e → page numbers via \u003ccode\u003epdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages()\u003c/code\u003e loop → \u003ccode\u003edocument.Close()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003enew FileStreamResult(ms, &quot;application/pdf&quot;) { FileDownloadName = &quot;name.pdf&quot; }\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Install both `itext7` + `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter`. `MemoryStream` → `PdfWriter(ms)` → `PdfDocument(writer)` → `Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)` → `writer.SetCloseStream(false)` → `document.Add(new Paragraph(...))` + `new Table(cols)` → page numbers via `pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages()` loop → `document.Close()` → `ms.Position = 0` → `new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\") { FileDownloadName = \"name.pdf\" }`."}]},{"n":16,"id":"chart-rendering","title":"Chart.js in Razor — CDN script, Razor data injection","hook":"Server computes numbers. Razor writes them into JS arrays via @:. Chart.js draws on canvas.","tags":["chart","chart-js","razor"],"module":".NET 10 Scripts & Reporting","source":"Labs/w13/FifaWorldCup/Pages/Chart.cshtml","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"Three pieces","text":"Three pieces"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;canvas&gt;\u003c/code\u003e element with an \u003ccode\u003eid\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eChart.js from CDN\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e block constructing chart referencing canvas + data\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. `\u003ccanvas\u003e` element with an `id`\n2. Chart.js from CDN\n3. `\u003cscript\u003e` block constructing chart referencing canvas + data"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Pie chart skeleton","text":"Pie chart skeleton"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@page\n@model IndexModel\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGames by Continent\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"chart-container\"\u003e\n    \u003ccanvas id=\"pie-chart\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\n    const Counts     = [];\n    const Continents = [];\n\n    @foreach (var item in Model.ChartData)\n    {\n        @:Counts.push(@item.Count);\n        @:Continents.push('@item.Name');\n    }\n\n    const ctx = document.getElementById('pie-chart');\n\n    new Chart(ctx, {\n        type: 'pie',\n        data: {\n            labels: Continents,\n            datasets: [{\n                label: 'Games',\n                data: Counts,\n                backgroundColor: [\n                    'rgba(255, 99, 132, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(255, 206, 86, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(153, 102, 255, 0.7)'\n                ]\n            }]\n        }\n    });\n\u003c/script\u003e"},{"kind":"h2","html":"The \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e Razor directive","text":"The `@:` Razor directive"},{"kind":"p","html":"Inside \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, Razor treats content as JS text. \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e forces a whole line to be mixed Razor-plus-JS:","text":"Inside `\u003cscript\u003e`, Razor treats content as JS text. `@:` forces a whole line to be mixed Razor-plus-JS:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@foreach (var item in Model.ChartData)\n{\n    @:Counts.push(@item.Count);\n    @:Continents.push('@item.Name');\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Each iteration emits a JS line: \u003ccode\u003eCounts.push(42);\u003c/code\u003e. The inner \u003ccode\u003e@item.Count\u003c/code\u003e is a Razor expression substituted by the server.","text":"Each iteration emits a JS line: `Counts.push(42);`. The inner `@item.Count` is a Razor expression substituted by the server."},{"kind":"h2","html":"\u003ccode\u003enew Chart(ctx, config)\u003c/code\u003e — Chart.js v3+","text":"`new Chart(ctx, config)` — Chart.js v3+"},{"kind":"p","html":"Two args:","text":"Two args:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ectx\u003c/code\u003e — canvas element (or 2D context)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003econfig\u003c/code\u003e — JS object with \u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003edata\u003c/code\u003e, optional \u003ccode\u003eoptions\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- `ctx` — canvas element (or 2D context)\n- `config` — JS object with `type`, `data`, optional `options`"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e: \u003ccode\u003e&#39;pie&#39;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&#39;bar&#39;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&#39;line&#39;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&#39;doughnut&#39;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&#39;radar&#39;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&#39;scatter&#39;\u003c/code\u003e","text":"`type`: `'pie'`, `'bar'`, `'line'`, `'doughnut'`, `'radar'`, `'scatter'`"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003edata\u003c/code\u003e:","text":"`data`:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003elabels\u003c/code\u003e — array of strings\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003edatasets\u003c/code\u003e — array of dataset objects, each with \u003ccode\u003elabel\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003edata\u003c/code\u003e (aligned with labels), styling like \u003ccode\u003ebackgroundColor\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- `labels` — array of strings\n- `datasets` — array of dataset objects, each with `label`, `data` (aligned with labels), styling like `backgroundColor`"},{"kind":"p","html":"For pie, \u003ccode\u003ebackgroundColor\u003c/code\u003e is array — one color per slice.","text":"For pie, `backgroundColor` is array — one color per slice."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Bar chart variant","text":"Bar chart variant"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003ccanvas id=\"scores\" width=\"500\" height=\"300\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\n    const names  = [];\n    const scores = [];\n    @foreach (var p in Model.Top5)\n    {\n        @:names.push('@p.Name');\n        @:scores.push(@p.Score);\n    }\n\n    new Chart(document.getElementById('scores'), {\n        type: 'bar',\n        data: {\n            labels: names,\n            datasets: [{ label: 'Score', data: scores }]\n        }\n    });\n\u003c/script\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Same pattern. Only \u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e changes.","text":"Same pattern. Only `type` changes."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Client-side only","text":"Client-side only"},{"kind":"p","html":"Chart.js runs in browser. No server-side PNG fallback in course toolkit. Canvas is empty until client-side JS runs. JS-disabled users see nothing.","text":"Chart.js runs in browser. No server-side PNG fallback in course toolkit. Canvas is empty until client-side JS runs. JS-disabled users see nothing."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Pie chart \"flashes\" empty for a moment before slices appear. Wrong?","a":"Nothing — correct sequence: server sends HTML + canvas + `\u003cscript\u003e`, browser fetches `chart.min.js` from CDN, JS executes, Chart.js draws. The flash is HTML-paint-to-script-execution. Improve with `\u003cscript src=\"...\" defer\u003e` in `\u003chead\u003e`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eWriting \u003ccode\u003eCounts.push(&quot;@item.Name&quot;);\u003c/code\u003e without \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e prefix. Razor tries to interpret whole line → compile error or malformed \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. Use \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e for any line mixing JS + Razor expressions.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Writing `Counts.push(\"@item.Name\");` without `@:` prefix. Razor tries to interpret whole line → compile error or malformed `\u003cscript\u003e`. Use `@:` for any line mixing JS + Razor expressions."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;canvas id=&quot;c&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script src=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e block. Inside the block, use \u003ccode\u003e@foreach { @:jsArray.push(@razorExpr); }\u003c/code\u003e to inject per-iteration data. \u003ccode\u003enew Chart(ctx, { type: &#39;pie&#39;|&#39;bar&#39;|&#39;line&#39;, data: { labels, datasets } })\u003c/code\u003e. Client-side only.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`\u003ccanvas id=\"c\"\u003e` + `\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e` + `\u003cscript\u003e` block. Inside the block, use `@foreach { @:jsArray.push(@razorExpr); }` to inject per-iteration data. `new Chart(ctx, { type: 'pie'|'bar'|'line', data: { labels, datasets } })`. Client-side only."}]},{"n":17,"id":"tdd","title":"TDD — Red/Green/Refactor, xUnit, Moq","hook":"Write failing test first. Minimum code to pass. Refactor green. Moq for dependencies.","tags":["tdd","xunit","moq"],"module":"Testing Discipline","source":"materials/project/GoodBooks/test/GoodBooks.BackendTests/Financial/AccountTests.cs + JournalEntryTests.cs; GoodBooks.ServicesTests/BaseServiceTests.cs + Fixtures/MockRepositoryFixtures.cs","blocks":[{"kind":"h2","html":"TDD cycle","text":"TDD cycle"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRed\u003c/strong\u003e — write failing test describing next requirement. Confirms test infrastructure works.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGreen\u003c/strong\u003e — write MINIMUM code to pass. No extras.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRefactor\u003c/strong\u003e — clean up while tests stay green.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. **Red** — write failing test describing next requirement. Confirms test infrastructure works.\n2. **Green** — write MINIMUM code to pass. No extras.\n3. **Refactor** — clean up while tests stay green."},{"kind":"p","html":"Repeat. Every line of production code exists because a failing test demanded it.","text":"Repeat. Every line of production code exists because a failing test demanded it."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Three Laws (Robert Martin)","text":"Three Laws (Robert Martin)"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo production code without a failing test.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo more test than needed to fail (compile errors count).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo more production code than needed to pass.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1. No production code without a failing test.\n2. No more test than needed to fail (compile errors count).\n3. No more production code than needed to pass."},{"kind":"h2","html":"xUnit attributes","text":"xUnit attributes"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — one-run test, no parameters:","text":"**`[Fact]`** — one-run test, no parameters:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[Fact]\npublic void ChildAccounts_DefaultsToEmptyList()\n{\n    var account = new Account();\n\n    Assert.NotNull(account.ChildAccounts);\n    Assert.Empty(account.ChildAccounts);\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — parameterized:","text":"**`[Theory]` + `[InlineData]`** — parameterized:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[Theory]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.JournalEntry)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.PurchaseOrder)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.SalesOrder)]\npublic void WithDifferentTypes_ShouldHandleAllTypes(SequenceNumberTypes type)\n{\n    // ... one run per InlineData row\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Each \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData(...)]\u003c/code\u003e = one execution. Shows separately in test report.","text":"Each `[InlineData(...)]` = one execution. Shows separately in test report."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Arrange / Act / Assert","text":"Arrange / Act / Assert"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[Fact]\npublic void TotalBalance_SumsAllDescendantBalances()\n{\n    // Arrange\n    var account = new Account\n    {\n        Balance = 100m,     // root ignored by DTO logic\n        ChildAccounts =\n        {\n            new Account { Balance = 50m },\n            new Account\n            {\n                Balance = 25m,\n                ChildAccounts =\n                {\n                    new Account { Balance = 10m },\n                    new Account { Balance = 5m }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    };\n\n    // Act (property access in this case)\n\n    // Assert\n    Assert.Equal(90m, account.TotalBalance);\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"One test, one conceptual assertion. Three Assert calls on unrelated properties → split into three tests.","text":"One test, one conceptual assertion. Three Assert calls on unrelated properties → split into three tests."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Assertions (demos use)","text":"Assertions (demos use)"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eAssertion\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eValue equality (primitives, strings, collections) — \u003cstrong\u003eexpected FIRST\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.NotNull(obj)\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Null(obj)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNull checks\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.Empty(collection)\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eAssert.NotEmpty(...)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCollection size\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.Single(collection)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eExactly one element\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"Expected-first convention: \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(4, calc.Add(2, 2))\u003c/code\u003e. Swapped → &quot;Expected: 5, but was: 4&quot; messages lie.","text":"Expected-first convention: `Assert.Equal(4, calc.Add(2, 2))`. Swapped → \"Expected: 5, but was: 4\" messages lie."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Lifecycle — constructor per test","text":"Lifecycle — constructor per test"},{"kind":"p","html":"xUnit creates a FRESH test-class instance per \u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e run:","text":"xUnit creates a FRESH test-class instance per `[Fact]` or `[Theory]` run:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConstructor\u003c/strong\u003e runs before each test (think \u003ccode\u003e[SetUp]\u003c/code\u003e without attribute)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIDisposable.Dispose()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e runs after each test (think \u003ccode\u003e[TearDown]\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo test sees state from another\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"- **Constructor** runs before each test (think `[SetUp]` without attribute)\n- **`IDisposable.Dispose()`** runs after each test (think `[TearDown]`)\n- No test sees state from another"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class BaseServiceTests\n{\n    private readonly Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e\u003e _mockSequenceNumberRepo;\n    private readonly Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cBank\u003e\u003e _mockBankRepo;\n\n    public BaseServiceTests()                     // fresh mocks per test\n    {\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e\u003e();\n        _mockBankRepo = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cBank\u003e\u003e();\n    }\n\n    // [Fact] tests use _mockSequenceNumberRepo and _mockBankRepo\n}"},{"kind":"h2","html":"Moq — three patterns from GoodBooks","text":"Moq — three patterns from GoodBooks"},{"kind":"h3","html":"\u003ccode\u003eSetup(...).Returns(...)\u003c/code\u003e — stub return value","text":"`Setup(...).Returns(...)` — stub return value"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var banks = new List\u003cBank\u003e\n{\n    new Bank { Id = 1, BankName = \"Bank A\" },\n    new Bank { Id = 2, BankName = \"Bank B\" }\n};\n\n_mockBankRepo.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(banks.AsQueryable());\n\n// Use the fake\nvar result = _mockBankRepo.Object.Table;\n\nAssert.Equal(2, result.Count());"},{"kind":"h3","html":"\u003ccode\u003eSetup(...).Callback&lt;T&gt;(...)\u003c/code\u003e — record side effects","text":"`Setup(...).Callback\u003cT\u003e(...)` — record side effects"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var sequenceList = new List\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e();\n\n_mockSequenceNumberRepo\n    .Setup(r =\u003e r.Insert(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()))\n    .Callback\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e(s =\u003e sequenceList.Add(s));\n\n_mockSequenceNumberRepo.Object.Insert(newSequence);\n\nAssert.Single(sequenceList);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIt.IsAny&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e matches any value. \u003ccode\u003eCallback&lt;T&gt;(Action&lt;T&gt;)\u003c/code\u003e captures what the SUT passed in.","text":"`It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()` matches any value. `Callback\u003cT\u003e(Action\u003cT\u003e)` captures what the SUT passed in."},{"kind":"h3","html":"\u003ccode\u003eVerify(..., Times.Once)\u003c/code\u003e — assert a call happened","text":"`Verify(..., Times.Once)` — assert a call happened"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"_mockSequenceNumberRepo.Object.Update(existingSequence);\n\n_mockSequenceNumberRepo.Verify(\n    r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()),\n    Times.Once);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eTimes.Once\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eTimes.Never\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eTimes.Exactly(3)\u003c/code\u003e. Verify fails test if expression wasn&#39;t satisfied.","text":"`Times.Once`, `Times.Never`, `Times.Exactly(3)`. Verify fails test if expression wasn't satisfied."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Static factory for mock setup — MockRepositoryFixtures","text":"Static factory for mock setup — MockRepositoryFixtures"},{"kind":"p","html":"GoodBooks uses static factories (NOT \u003ccode\u003eIClassFixture&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e):","text":"GoodBooks uses static factories (NOT `IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e`):"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public static class MockRepositoryFixtures\n{\n    public static Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e CreateEmptyRepository\u003cT\u003e() where T : BaseEntity\n    {\n        var mock = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e();\n        mock.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(new List\u003cT\u003e().AsQueryable());\n        return mock;\n    }\n\n    public static Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e CreateRepositoryWithData\u003cT\u003e(List\u003cT\u003e data)\n        where T : BaseEntity\n    {\n        var mock = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e();\n        mock.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(data.AsQueryable());\n        return mock;\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"Tests call \u003ccode\u003eMockRepositoryFixtures.CreateEmptyRepository&lt;Bank&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e — cuts boilerplate, still fresh mock per test.","text":"Tests call `MockRepositoryFixtures.CreateEmptyRepository\u003cBank\u003e()` — cuts boilerplate, still fresh mock per test."},{"kind":"h2","html":"Full example — mock + arrange/act/assert + verify","text":"Full example — mock + arrange/act/assert + verify"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[Fact]\npublic void SequenceNumberRepository_WithExistingSequence_ShouldUpdate()\n{\n    // Arrange\n    var existingSequence = new SequenceNumber { Id = 1, NextNumber = 42 };\n    var sequenceList = new List\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e { existingSequence };\n\n    _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(() =\u003e sequenceList.AsQueryable());\n    _mockSequenceNumberRepo\n        .Setup(r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()))\n        .Callback\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e(s =\u003e {\n            var existing = sequenceList.FirstOrDefault(x =\u003e x.Id == s.Id);\n            if (existing != null) existing.NextNumber = s.NextNumber;\n        });\n\n    // Act\n    existingSequence.NextNumber = 43;\n    _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Object.Update(existingSequence);\n\n    // Assert\n    Assert.Equal(43, existingSequence.NextNumber);\n    _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Verify(\n        r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()),\n        Times.Once);\n}"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Colleague suggests moving test-class mock fields from constructor to `static` to \"save allocations.\" What's the risk?","a":"Moq `.Setup(...)` calls accumulate on the mock. Test A's stub persists into Test B. Fresh per-test instances eliminate cross-test state."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"Test reports \"Expected: 4, but was: 5\". Code is `Assert.Equal(actualResult, 4)` with `actualResult == 5`. What's the subtle bug?","a":"Arguments swapped. Convention is `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)`. Failure message blames the wrong value. Fix: expected first."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003eForgetting \u003ccode\u003e.Object\u003c/code\u003e when passing mock to SUT. \u003ccode\u003enew BankService(_mockBankRepo)\u003c/code\u003e fails type-check — need \u003ccode\u003e_mockBankRepo.Object\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"Forgetting `.Object` when passing mock to SUT. `new BankService(_mockBankRepo)` fails type-check — need `_mockBankRepo.Object`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIt.IsAny&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e in \u003ccode\u003eSetup\u003c/code\u003e accepts any; \u003ccode\u003eIt.IsAny&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e in \u003ccode\u003eVerify\u003c/code\u003e asserts any. Same syntax, two roles. For specific value: \u003ccode\u003eIt.Is&lt;T&gt;(x =&gt; x.Id == 1)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"`It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()` in `Setup` accepts any; `It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()` in `Verify` asserts any. Same syntax, two roles. For specific value: `It.Is\u003cT\u003e(x =\u003e x.Id == 1)`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"pitfall","html":"\u003cp\u003e&quot;Write test right after code&quot; isn&#39;t TDD — retrofit tests often pass on first run without ever failing. Test might be wrong and you&#39;d never know. Red phase exists to prove tests can fail.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"\"Write test right after code\" isn't TDD — retrofit tests often pass on first run without ever failing. Test might be wrong and you'd never know. Red phase exists to prove tests can fail."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"takeaway","html":"\u003cp\u003eTDD = Red → Green → Refactor. xUnit: \u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e one-run · \u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData]\u003c/code\u003e parameterized · constructor fresh per test · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e expected FIRST. Moq: \u003ccode\u003enew Mock&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Setup(r =&gt; r.Method(It.IsAny&lt;...&gt;())).Returns(...)\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.Callback&lt;T&gt;(...)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Object\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Verify(..., Times.Once)\u003c/code\u003e. Static factories for shared mock-setup boilerplate.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"TDD = Red → Green → Refactor. xUnit: `[Fact]` one-run · `[Theory]` + `[InlineData]` parameterized · constructor fresh per test · `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` expected FIRST. Moq: `new Mock\u003cT\u003e()` → `.Setup(r =\u003e r.Method(It.IsAny\u003c...\u003e())).Returns(...)` or `.Callback\u003cT\u003e(...)` → `.Object` → `.Verify(..., Times.Once)`. Static factories for shared mock-setup boilerplate."}]}],"practice":[{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":1,"id":"ai-agent-wire-up-console","title":"Wire a single-tool MAF agent in a console app","lang":"csharp","tags":["ai","maf","agent","tools","console"],"source":"Assignment 2 (variant — console-only MAF agent registering one tool via AIFunctionFactory.Create, simpler than A2's full-stack AI-integrated Blazor)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eWrite \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e for a console app that uses the Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF) to answer weather questions with one tool.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRequirements:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStart from an existing \u003ccode\u003eIChatClient chatClient\u003c/code\u003e (assume it is already constructed against GitHub Models).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDefine a static C# method \u003ccode\u003eWeatherService.GetWeatherForCity(string city)\u003c/code\u003e that returns a plain string like \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Vancouver: 8C, rainy&quot;\u003c/code\u003e for any input.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRegister that method as an \u003ccode\u003eAITool\u003c/code\u003e using \u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003ename: &quot;GetWeatherForCity&quot;\u003c/code\u003e and a description the LLM can read.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild a \u003ccode\u003eChatClientAgent\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent(...)\u003c/code\u003e, passing the tool in the \u003ccode\u003etools:\u003c/code\u003e array plus an \u003ccode\u003einstructions:\u003c/code\u003e string and a \u003ccode\u003ename:\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCreate an \u003ccode\u003eAgentSession\u003c/code\u003e once via \u003ccode\u003eawait agent.CreateSessionAsync()\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLoop: read a line from the console, call \u003ccode\u003eagent.RunAsync(input, session)\u003c/code\u003e, and print the \u003ccode\u003e.Text\u003c/code\u003e property.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo not use \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eagent.Invoke()\u003c/code\u003e, or \u003ccode\u003eAITool.Register()\u003c/code\u003e — none exist in MAF.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"using Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.AI;\n\npublic static class WeatherService\n{\n    public static string GetWeatherForCity(string city)\n    {\n        // TODO: return a stub string like \"Vancouver: 8C, rainy\"\n        throw new NotImplementedException();\n    }\n}\n\npublic class Program\n{\n    public static async Task Main(string[] args)\n    {\n        IChatClient chatClient = BuildChatClient(); // assume provided\n\n        // TODO 1: wrap WeatherService.GetWeatherForCity as an AITool using AIFunctionFactory.Create.\n        // TODO 2: build the agent with chatClient.AsAIAgent(name, instructions, tools).\n        // TODO 3: create an AgentSession with await agent.CreateSessionAsync().\n        // TODO 4: loop — read input, call agent.RunAsync(input, session), print response.Text.\n    }\n\n    private static IChatClient BuildChatClient() =\u003e throw new NotImplementedException();\n}","solution":"using Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nusing Microsoft.Extensions.AI;\n\npublic static class WeatherService\n{\n    public static string GetWeatherForCity(string city)\n    {\n        return $\"{city}: 8C, rainy\";\n    }\n}\n\npublic class Program\n{\n    public static async Task Main(string[] args)\n    {\n        IChatClient chatClient = BuildChatClient();\n\n        AITool weatherTool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n            WeatherService.GetWeatherForCity,\n            name: \"GetWeatherForCity\",\n            description: \"Get the current weather summary for a given city name.\");\n\n        AIAgent agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(\n            name: \"WeatherAgent\",\n            instructions: \"You answer weather questions. Call GetWeatherForCity whenever the user asks about a city's weather.\",\n            tools: [weatherTool]);\n\n        var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();\n\n        while (true)\n        {\n            Console.Write(\"User \u003e \");\n            string? input = Console.ReadLine();\n            if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(input)) continue;\n\n            var response = await agent.RunAsync(input, session);\n            Console.WriteLine(response.Text);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static IChatClient BuildChatClient() =\u003e throw new NotImplementedException();\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe LLM decides when to call \u003ccode\u003eGetWeatherForCity\u003c/code\u003e based on the description string. That is the entire function-calling contract — the description is metadata the model reads, not a comment for humans.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA common wrong approach: build a \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;ChatMessage&gt; history\u003c/code\u003e and append each user and assistant message manually, passing the list into every \u003ccode\u003eRunAsync\u003c/code\u003e call. That is the raw \u003ccode\u003eIChatClient\u003c/code\u003e pattern. MAF agents use \u003ccode\u003eAgentSession\u003c/code\u003e from \u003ccode\u003eawait agent.CreateSessionAsync()\u003c/code\u003e; passing both a manual \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e and a session duplicates state.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA second wrong approach: register the method with \u003ccode\u003eAITool.Register(WeatherService.GetWeatherForCity)\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003echatClient.AsAgent(...)\u003c/code\u003e. Neither compiles — MAF ships \u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent()\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eAITool.Register()\u003c/code\u003e are documented exam distractors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA third wrong approach: call \u003ccode\u003eagent.Invoke(input)\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003ekernel.InvokeAsync(...)\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eInvoke\u003c/code\u003e is Semantic Kernel vocabulary; MAF agents expose \u003ccode\u003eRunAsync\u003c/code\u003e (buffered) and \u003ccode\u003eRunStreamingAsync\u003c/code\u003e (token-by-token). Mixing the two SDKs&#39; verbs on the same object does not interop.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":2,"id":"grpc-crud-student","title":"Implement InsertStudent on a gRPC service","lang":"cs","tags":["grpc","server","asp-net-core","ef-core"],"source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/ Q5 (variant — implement a single InsertStudent override plus its DI setup, simpler than the full 4-method CRUD in the lab)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eComplete the \u003ccode\u003eStudentsService\u003c/code\u003e class below so that \u003ccode\u003eInsertStudent\u003c/code\u003e persists the request into the \u003ccode\u003eSchoolDbContext\u003c/code\u003e, saves changes, and returns a \u003ccode\u003eReply\u003c/code\u003e whose \u003ccode\u003eIsOk\u003c/code\u003e is \u003ccode\u003etrue\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eResult\u003c/code\u003e is \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Inserted&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. The \u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e service and messages already exist and generate \u003ccode\u003eStudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eStudentModel\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eReply\u003c/code\u003e for you.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"public class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\n{\n    private readonly SchoolDbContext _context;\n\n    public StudentsService(SchoolDbContext context) =\u003e _context = context;\n\n    public override Task\u003cReply\u003e InsertStudent(\n        StudentModel request,\n        ServerCallContext context)\n    {\n        // TODO: add a new Student to _context.Students based on request,\n        // save changes, and return a successful Reply.\n        throw new NotImplementedException();\n    }\n}","solution":"public class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\n{\n    private readonly SchoolDbContext _context;\n\n    public StudentsService(SchoolDbContext context) =\u003e _context = context;\n\n    public override async Task\u003cReply\u003e InsertStudent(\n        StudentModel request,\n        ServerCallContext context)\n    {\n        _context.Students!.Add(new Student\n        {\n            FirstName = request.FirstName,\n            LastName  = request.LastName,\n            School    = request.School\n        });\n\n        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();\n\n        return new Reply { Result = \"Inserted\", IsOk = true };\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe override takes \u003ccode\u003eStudentModel\u003c/code\u003e (the request) plus \u003ccode\u003eServerCallContext\u003c/code\u003e and returns \u003ccode\u003eTask&lt;Reply&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. Because \u003ccode\u003eSaveChangesAsync\u003c/code\u003e is awaited, the method must be declared \u003ccode\u003easync\u003c/code\u003e — the compiler will flag any \u003ccode\u003easync\u003c/code\u003e method that returns \u003ccode\u003eTask.FromResult(...)\u003c/code\u003e or a non-awaited value.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReturning \u003ccode\u003eTask.FromResult(new Reply { … })\u003c/code\u003e while still calling \u003ccode\u003eSaveChanges()\u003c/code\u003e synchronously.\u003c/strong\u003e The student ends up persisted, but the method blocks the gRPC thread pool for the duration of the write. Under concurrent load this throttles unrelated requests. Always prefer \u003ccode\u003easync\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eSaveChangesAsync\u003c/code\u003e when any I/O happens.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003eoverride\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Without it the method does not replace the base-class virtual method; the generated base&#39;s default throws \u003ccode\u003eUNIMPLEMENTED\u003c/code\u003e when the client calls \u003ccode\u003eInsertStudentAsync\u003c/code\u003e. The code compiles and the service starts successfully, which makes this trap especially sharp.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMapping \u003ccode\u003erequest.StudentId\u003c/code\u003e into the new \u003ccode\u003eStudent\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The database auto-generates the primary key. Forcing a specific \u003ccode\u003eStudentId\u003c/code\u003e from the client either collides with existing rows or overrides the sequence unexpectedly — return \u003ccode\u003eInserted\u003c/code\u003e but tell the client the generated id, if anything.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":3,"id":"grpc-client-di","title":"Register a gRPC client in Program.cs","lang":"cs","tags":["grpc","client","di","asp-net-core"],"source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/ Q1 (variant — register a single ToonRemoteClient against localhost:5099, simpler than the lab's multi-client Aspire AppHost wiring)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eComplete the \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e snippet below so that the \u003ccode\u003eToonRemote.ToonRemoteClient\u003c/code\u003e (generated from \u003ccode\u003eProtos\\toon.proto\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eGrpcServices=&quot;Client&quot;\u003c/code\u003e) is registered in the DI container, pointing at \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:5099\u003c/code\u003e. Assume \u003ccode\u003eGrpc.Net.ClientFactory\u003c/code\u003e is already added as a NuGet package.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// TODO: register ToonRemote.ToonRemoteClient in the DI container,\n// pointing at http://localhost:5099 so that any component can @inject it.\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorComponents()\n    .AddInteractiveServerComponents();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapRazorComponents\u003cApp\u003e()\n   .AddInteractiveServerRenderMode();\napp.Run();","solution":"var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cToonRemote.ToonRemoteClient\u003e(opts =\u003e\n{\n    opts.Address = new Uri(\"http://localhost:5099\");\n});\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorComponents()\n    .AddInteractiveServerComponents();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapRazorComponents\u003cApp\u003e()\n   .AddInteractiveServerRenderMode();\napp.Run();","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddGrpcClient&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e registers a typed gRPC client with the factory. The factory manages channel lifetime so every injection of \u003ccode\u003eToonRemote.ToonRemoteClient\u003c/code\u003e reuses the same pooled HTTP/2 connection. The \u003ccode\u003eopts.Address\u003c/code\u003e assignment is the only per-client configuration you typically need; additional options (timeouts, interceptors) chain off the returned \u003ccode\u003eIHttpClientBuilder\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003enew GrpcChannel.ForAddress(...)\u003c/code\u003e in \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e and passing it to \u003ccode\u003eAddSingleton\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e You end up with a hand-rolled channel that bypasses the factory — no resilience handlers, no OpenTelemetry hooks, no service discovery. Under Aspire, this also misses out on \u003ccode\u003ehttp://backend/\u003c/code\u003e name resolution.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting the NuGet package reference to \u003ccode\u003eGrpc.Net.ClientFactory\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The extension method does not exist without it, so \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpcClient&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e fails to compile.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHardcoding \u003ccode\u003elocalhost:5099\u003c/code\u003e into the deployed app.\u003c/strong\u003e In a local-only demo this is fine; once the service runs elsewhere (Aspire, Docker Compose, Kubernetes), replace the literal with \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Configuration[&quot;Services:Toon:Address&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e or an Aspire logical name like \u003ccode\u003ehttp://toon\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":4,"id":"grpc-blazor-inject","title":"Call a gRPC service from a Blazor component","lang":"cs","tags":["grpc","blazor","interactive-server"],"source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/ Q2 (variant — inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient into a Blazor page, call GetStudentInfoAsync, render the result, simpler single-call version of the lab's full CRUD UI)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eComplete the Blazor component \u003ccode\u003eStudentLookup.razor\u003c/code\u003e so that it injects the gRPC client (already registered in \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e), calls \u003ccode\u003eGetStudentInfoAsync(new StudentLookupModel { StudentId = 3 })\u003c/code\u003e when the page initializes, and renders the returned \u003ccode\u003eFirstName\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eLastName\u003c/code\u003e. Set the render mode explicitly so the async call runs. Assume the \u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e has been compiled and \u003ccode\u003eStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eStudentLookupModel\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eStudentModel\u003c/code\u003e are available.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"@page \"/student-lookup\"\n@using Grpc.Net.Client\n\n// TODO: set the render mode and inject the gRPC client.\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudent lookup\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n@if (_student is null)\n{\n    \u003cp\u003eLoading…\u003c/p\u003e\n}\nelse\n{\n    \u003cp\u003eFound: @_student.FirstName @_student.LastName\u003c/p\u003e\n}\n\n@code {\n    private StudentModel? _student;\n\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()\n    {\n        // TODO: call GetStudentInfoAsync on the injected client and\n        // assign the result to _student.\n    }\n}","solution":"@page \"/student-lookup\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpcClient\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudent lookup\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n@if (_student is null)\n{\n    \u003cp\u003eLoading…\u003c/p\u003e\n}\nelse\n{\n    \u003cp\u003eFound: @_student.FirstName @_student.LastName\u003c/p\u003e\n}\n\n@code {\n    private StudentModel? _student;\n\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()\n    {\n        _student = await _grpcClient.GetStudentInfoAsync(\n            new StudentLookupModel { StudentId = 3 });\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThree directives carry the weight. \u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e keeps the component alive after the initial render so the awaited gRPC call can complete and trigger a re-render. \u003ccode\u003e@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpcClient\u003c/code\u003e pulls the typed stub from DI — the stub was registered in \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpcClient&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e. The call itself uses the \u003ccode\u003eAsync\u003c/code\u003e suffix (\u003ccode\u003eGetStudentInfoAsync\u003c/code\u003e), not the blocking form, which is the only form safe to await in an async method.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Under static server rendering, \u003ccode\u003eOnInitializedAsync\u003c/code\u003e still runs once, but any post-render updates never reach the client — the page shows &quot;Loading…&quot; forever because the component was torn down before the awaited task completed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003e_grpcClient.GetStudentInfo(...).Result\u003c/code\u003e to &quot;simplify&quot; the async flow.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e.Result\u003c/code\u003e blocks the SignalR circuit thread and can deadlock under load. Always await the \u003ccode\u003eAsync\u003c/code\u003e form inside an async method.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInjecting \u003ccode\u003eGrpcChannel\u003c/code\u003e and constructing the client inside \u003ccode\u003eOnInitializedAsync\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e This works but throws away the factory&#39;s channel pooling. Once DI registration is in place, inject the typed client directly.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":5,"id":"aspire-wire-grpc-backend","title":"Wire a gRPC backend into an Aspire AppHost","lang":"cs","tags":["aspire","grpc","apphost"],"source":"Labs/W09 gRPC/ Q4 (variant — single-backend + single-frontend orchestration with WithReference + WaitFor, simpler than the lab's full multi-service CRUD)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eYou have two projects in your solution: \u003ccode\u003eStudentsGrpcApi\u003c/code\u003e (a gRPC backend) and \u003ccode\u003eStudentsBlazor\u003c/code\u003e (a Blazor Server frontend). The AppHost project already has \u003ccode\u003e&lt;ProjectReference&gt;\u003c/code\u003e to both. Fill in \u003ccode\u003eAppHost/Program.cs\u003c/code\u003e so Aspire starts the backend first, waits for it to report healthy, then starts the frontend with the backend&#39;s URL injected as an environment variable.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// TODO: register the gRPC backend under the logical name \"backend\".\n// Then register the Blazor frontend under \"frontend\" so it waits for\n// the backend and receives its URL via service discovery.\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","solution":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar backend = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.StudentsGrpcApi\u003e(\"backend\");\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.StudentsBlazor\u003e(\"frontend\")\n    .WithReference(backend)\n    .WaitFor(backend);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.StudentsGrpcApi&gt;(&quot;backend&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e both launches the backend and assigns it the logical name \u003ccode\u003ebackend\u003c/code\u003e. The frontend&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eWithReference(backend)\u003c/code\u003e injects an environment variable (something like \u003ccode\u003eservices__backend__http__0\u003c/code\u003e) that the frontend&#39;s service-discovery handler reads whenever the app resolves \u003ccode\u003ehttp://backend/\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eWaitFor(backend)\u003c/code\u003e prevents the frontend from starting until the backend passes its \u003ccode\u003e/health\u003c/code\u003e check — without this, the first gRPC calls fire against a server that hasn&#39;t finished booting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHardcoding \u003ccode\u003eopts.Address = new Uri(&quot;http://localhost:5099&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e in the frontend&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e and skipping \u003ccode\u003eWithReference\u003c/code\u003e in the AppHost.\u003c/strong\u003e It works in local dev but loses every benefit of Aspire — no dynamic port allocation, no environment-specific overrides, no dashboard telemetry. The right move is \u003ccode\u003eopts.Address = new Uri(&quot;http://backend&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e on the client plus \u003ccode\u003eWithReference\u003c/code\u003e in the AppHost.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003eWaitFor(backend)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The frontend can boot, be reachable, and issue its first gRPC call before the backend has finished migrations or health checks. The failure reads as a network error; the real cause is ordering.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e in the AppHost.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults\u003c/code\u003e belongs in each individual service&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e. Putting it in the AppHost is a boot-break — the orchestrator tries to register OpenTelemetry and health checks on itself and fails.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":6,"id":"aspire-multi-project-a2","title":"Orchestrate an Assignment-2-style multi-project stack","lang":"cs","tags":["aspire","apphost","sql-server"],"source":"Assignment 2 (variant — WebAPI + Server-Blazor admin + Client-Blazor public against one SQL Server, simpler than A2's full-stack which also adds AI integration and role-based auth)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eAssignment 2&#39;s architecture: one WebAPI (the data tier), one Server-Blazor project (admin site for authors + admins), one Client-Blazor WASM project (public-facing reader). All three share one SQL Server database named \u003ccode\u003ecms\u003c/code\u003e. Write the AppHost \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e that wires this up: the API depends on the database; both Blazor sites depend on the API.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// TODO: register SQL Server + a database called \"cms\".\n// TODO: register the WebAPI under \"api\" with the database injected.\n// TODO: register the Server-Blazor admin site and the Client-Blazor\n// public site, both depending on the api.\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","solution":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar db = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\")\n                .AddDatabase(\"cms\");\n\nvar api = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Cms_Api\u003e(\"api\")\n    .WithReference(db)\n    .WaitFor(db);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Cms_Admin\u003e(\"admin\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Cms_Public\u003e(\"public\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe dependency graph is explicit: \u003ccode\u003edb → api → (admin, public)\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServer(&quot;sql&quot;).AddDatabase(&quot;cms&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e gives the API a connection string via \u003ccode\u003eConnectionStrings__cms\u003c/code\u003e. The API&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e calls \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.AddSqlServerDbContext&lt;CmsDbContext&gt;(&quot;cms&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e and EF Core picks up the injected value — no \u003ccode\u003eappsettings.json\u003c/code\u003e edits per environment. Each Blazor project reaches the API as \u003ccode\u003ehttp://api/\u003c/code\u003e; the admin site uses that for admin-only endpoints, the public site uses it for anonymous reads.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRegistering two separate databases, one for admin and one for public.\u003c/strong\u003e A2 explicitly requires a shared database so content authored in admin appears on the public site. Registering \u003ccode\u003eAddDatabase(&quot;admin-cms&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eAddDatabase(&quot;public-cms&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e produces two isolated SQL Server databases that never sync.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSkipping \u003ccode\u003eWaitFor(api)\u003c/code\u003e on the Blazor projects.\u003c/strong\u003e Both sites launch, hit the API on first render, and fail because the API hasn&#39;t finished EF migrations yet. The user sees a spinner or an error; the root cause is startup-order, not code.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAdding AI integration at the AppHost level via \u003ccode\u003eWithEnvironment(&quot;OPENAI_KEY&quot;, ...)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e A2 does require AI, but AI config belongs inside each service that needs it — via that service&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eappsettings.json\u003c/code\u003e or its own \u003ccode\u003eWithEnvironment\u003c/code\u003e call in AppHost scoped to one project, not leaked as a global env var. Scoping secrets to the service that uses them limits blast radius.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":7,"id":"quickgrid-pagination","title":"Paginate a Blazor QuickGrid to 15 rows per page","lang":"cs","tags":["blazor","quickgrid","pagination"],"source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/ Q1 (variant — pure pagination wiring, no filter or sort, simpler than the lab's combined Q1+Q2+Q3)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eYou have a Blazor Server page with an \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e and a \u003ccode\u003e&lt;QuickGrid&gt;\u003c/code\u003e already bound to it. The grid currently shows every row. Add pagination so the grid displays 15 rows per page, with a \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator&gt;\u003c/code\u003e control under the grid that lets the user move through pages.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudents\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@_students\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.Id)\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.LastName)\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n@* TODO: add a \u003cPaginator\u003e component under the grid. *@\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n\n    // TODO: declare a PaginationState set to 15 items per page\n    //       and wire it into the QuickGrid via its Pagination attribute.\n}","solution":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudents\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@_students\" Pagination=\"@_pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.Id)\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.LastName)\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@_pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n    private PaginationState _pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e is a stateful object that tracks \u003ccode\u003eCurrentPageIndex\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eItemsPerPage\u003c/code\u003e. Binding the QuickGrid&#39;s \u003ccode\u003ePagination\u003c/code\u003e attribute to it tells the grid which slice of \u003ccode\u003eItems\u003c/code\u003e to render. The \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator&gt;\u003c/code\u003e component reads and writes the same state object; clicks on first/prev/next/last mutate \u003ccode\u003eCurrentPageIndex\u003c/code\u003e, which QuickGrid watches and re-renders on.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth components must bind to the \u003cstrong\u003esame\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e instance — they coordinate through shared state, not events.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDeclaring \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e as a local variable inside a method.\u003c/strong\u003e Each render creates a fresh instance, so page navigation never advances. The state must be a \u003ccode\u003e@code\u003c/code\u003e-block field so it survives component re-renders.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003e.ToList()\u003c/code\u003e on \u003ccode\u003e_students\u003c/code\u003e before binding.\u003c/strong\u003e QuickGrid paginates in .NET over the materialized list, losing EF Core&#39;s ability to issue \u003ccode\u003eOFFSET / FETCH\u003c/code\u003e at the database. For large tables this loads every row into memory on every page change.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The initial render produces a grid and a paginator, but clicks on the paginator do nothing because there&#39;s no client-side runtime. A static-server-rendered page can display data but cannot respond to interaction.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":8,"id":"quickgrid-filter","title":"Live filter a Blazor QuickGrid by last name","lang":"cs","tags":["blazor","quickgrid","filter"],"source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/ Q2 (variant — filter by last name only, simpler than the lab's multi-keyword matcher that searches multiple fields)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eExtend the students grid so that a text input above the grid live-filters the displayed rows by \u003ccode\u003eLastName\u003c/code\u003e. The filter is case-insensitive and updates on every keystroke. When the input is empty, the grid shows every student.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudents\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n@* TODO: add a text input bound to a filter field. *@\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@_students\" Pagination=\"@_pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.LastName)\"  Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@_pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n    private PaginationState _pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n\n    // TODO: add a filter field and a computed IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e\n    //       that filters by LastName.Contains(filter, case-insensitive).\n    //       Bind Items=\"@Filtered\" instead of \"@_students\".\n}","solution":"@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003ch1\u003eStudents\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cinput @bind=\"_filter\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" placeholder=\"Filter last name...\" /\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@Filtered\" Pagination=\"@_pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.LastName)\"  Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@_pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n    private PaginationState _pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n    private string _filter = string.Empty;\n\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e Filtered =\u003e\n        string.IsNullOrEmpty(_filter)\n            ? _students\n            : _students.Where(s =\u003e\n                s.LastName.Contains(_filter, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@bind=&quot;_filter&quot;\u003c/code\u003e round-trips the input value into the \u003ccode\u003e_filter\u003c/code\u003e field. \u003ccode\u003e@bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e changes the update trigger from the default \u003ccode\u003eonchange\u003c/code\u003e (fires on focus loss) to \u003ccode\u003eoninput\u003c/code\u003e (fires on every keystroke) — without that change, users see no filtering until they tab out of the input.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003eFiltered\u003c/code\u003e property is a computed \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. Each re-render re-evaluates it and the grid sees a new source; QuickGrid handles the diff internally.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003e@bind\u003c/code\u003e without \u003ccode\u003e@bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The filter only kicks in when the input loses focus — functional but non-obvious for users who expect instant feedback.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMaterializing to \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003e.ToList()\u003c/code\u003e inside \u003ccode\u003eFiltered\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e That destroys IQueryable and forces EF Core to pull the entire student table into memory on every keystroke. Keep the expression as IQueryable so the database does the work.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003eStateHasChanged()\u003c/code\u003e manually after setting \u003ccode\u003e_filter\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e@bind\u003c/code\u003e already triggers a re-render; manual calls are redundant and sometimes mask ordering bugs where the filter value updates after the grid has already started rendering.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":9,"id":"quickgrid-sort","title":"Sort a TemplateColumn in Blazor QuickGrid","lang":"cs","tags":["blazor","quickgrid","sort","gridsort"],"source":"Labs/W07 QuickGrid/ Q3 (variant — a single multi-key sortable TemplateColumn, simpler than the lab's combined sort-across-all-columns exercise)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eReplace the separate \u003ccode\u003eFirstName\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eLastName\u003c/code\u003e \u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003es with one \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e titled &quot;Full name&quot; that renders \u003ccode\u003e&quot;@context.FirstName @context.LastName&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. The column must be sortable by the user — clicking the header sorts by \u003ccode\u003eLastName\u003c/code\u003e first, then by \u003ccode\u003eFirstName\u003c/code\u003e as a tie-breaker.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@_students\" Pagination=\"@_pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.FirstName)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(s =\u003e s.LastName)\"  Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n    private PaginationState _pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n\n    // TODO: declare a GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e that sorts by LastName then FirstName.\n    // TODO: replace the two PropertyColumns with one TemplateColumn\n    //       that renders full name and is sortable via the GridSort.\n}","solution":"\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@_students\" Pagination=\"@_pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cTemplateColumn Title=\"Full name\" SortBy=\"@_sortByFull\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e@context.FirstName @context.LastName\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e _students = Student.GetStudents();\n    private PaginationState _pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n\n    private GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e _sortByFull =\n        GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e.ByAscending(s =\u003e s.LastName)\n                         .ThenAscending(s =\u003e s.FirstName);\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e renders arbitrary markup using the \u003ccode\u003e@context\u003c/code\u003e variable (the current row&#39;s data item). Because the template can reference any combination of properties, QuickGrid cannot infer a sort key — you must supply one via \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGridSort&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e builds the expression fluently. \u003ccode\u003eByAscending(s =&gt; s.LastName)\u003c/code\u003e picks the primary key; \u003ccode\u003eThenAscending(s =&gt; s.FirstName)\u003c/code\u003e tie-breaks ties on \u003ccode\u003eLastName\u003c/code\u003e. Chain more \u003ccode\u003e.ThenAscending\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003e.ThenDescending\u003c/code\u003e calls for additional tie-breakers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting \u003ccode\u003eSortable=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e on \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e instead of supplying \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The header shows no sort arrow because QuickGrid has no key. Remove \u003ccode\u003eSortable\u003c/code\u003e and add \u003ccode\u003eSortBy=&quot;@_sortByFull&quot;\u003c/code\u003e instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBuilding the \u003ccode\u003eGridSort&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e inside the markup.\u003c/strong\u003e Each render creates a fresh sort object; QuickGrid compares by reference and treats every render as &quot;sort changed,&quot; producing excess work. Declare the field once in \u003ccode\u003e@code\u003c/code\u003e and reuse.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSorting on a computed property inside the template\u003c/strong\u003e — e.g. \u003ccode\u003ex =&gt; $&quot;{x.FirstName} {x.LastName}&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. EF Core cannot translate a formatted string into SQL, so the sort either falls back to in-memory (loading every row) or throws. Use the two underlying properties with \u003ccode\u003eThenAscending\u003c/code\u003e chaining instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":10,"id":"localization-add-culture","title":"Register French as a supported culture in Program.cs","lang":"cs","tags":["i18n","program-cs","request-localization"],"source":"Labs/W10 Localization/ Q1 (variant — adding one additional culture to an English-only app, simpler than the lab which added four cultures plus a switcher)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eYou have an existing Razor Pages app that currently only supports English. Add French as a supported culture so that \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e loads French \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e files when \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e is \u003ccode\u003efr\u003c/code\u003e. Use \u003ccode\u003eResources/\u003c/code\u003e as the resource root. English must remain the default.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// TODO: register localization services with ResourcesPath = \"Resources\".\n// TODO: configure RequestLocalizationOptions for English and French,\n//       with English as the default.\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages()\n    .AddViewLocalization();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\n\n// TODO: enable UseRequestLocalization middleware.\n\napp.MapRazorPages();\napp.Run();","solution":"using System.Globalization;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Localization;\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nbuilder.Services.AddLocalization(opts =\u003e opts.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(opts =\u003e\n{\n    var supported = new[]\n    {\n        new CultureInfo(\"en\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"fr\"),\n    };\n    opts.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n    opts.SupportedCultures     = supported;\n    opts.SupportedUICultures   = supported;\n});\n\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages()\n    .AddViewLocalization();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\n\napp.UseRequestLocalization();\n\napp.MapRazorPages();\napp.Run();","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThree service registrations plus one middleware call are the minimum to flip a single-language app into a multi-culture app.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization(opts =&gt; opts.ResourcesPath = &quot;Resources&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e tells the framework where \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e files live. \u003ccode\u003eRequestLocalizationOptions.SupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e sets which values \u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e (formatting) may take; \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e sets which values \u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e (resource lookup) may take. Both must be set, typically to the same list, or you end up with a half-localized page.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eapp.UseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e is the middleware that runs the registered culture providers on each request and applies the result. Without it, the options are configured but nothing executes them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForgetting \u003ccode\u003eapp.UseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Services are registered, resource files exist, but no request ever has its culture set from the providers. \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e always returns the English value.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting \u003ccode\u003eSupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e but not \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Numbers format in French, but strings stay in English because \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e never changes from the default. Always set both.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImporting \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Globalization\u003c/code\u003e but omitting \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.AspNetCore.Localization\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eCultureInfo\u003c/code\u003e comes from the first namespace, but \u003ccode\u003eRequestCulture\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eCookieRequestCultureProvider\u003c/code\u003e come from the second. The code compiles only when both are imported.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"applied","n":11,"id":"localization-switcher-ui","title":"Build a culture-switcher dropdown that persists the user's choice","tags":["i18n","ui","cookie"],"source":"Labs/W10 Localization/ Q2 (variant — a single switcher in a partial that POSTs to one handler, simpler than the lab's multi-partial + multi-handler breakdown)","problem_html":"\u003cp\u003eYou have an app with \u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eRequestLocalizationOptions\u003c/code\u003e declaring \u003ccode\u003een\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003efr\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e middleware all in place. Now add a language-selector UI:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA \u003ccode\u003e&lt;select&gt;\u003c/code\u003e dropdown in the footer showing every supported culture (the user can click to change).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSelecting a culture POSTs to a handler that writes the \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e cookie and redirects back to the page the user was on.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe chosen culture persists across browser restarts (cookie \u003ccode\u003eExpires\u003c/code\u003e = 1 year).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe URL displayed is irrelevant; the switcher must work regardless of the current route. Describe the markup and the handler code, then trace what happens on the first reload after switching.\u003c/p\u003e","walkthrough_html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBuild the cultureItems list.\u003c/strong\u003e In a shared partial \u003ccode\u003e_SelectLanguagePartial.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e, inject \u003ccode\u003eIOptions&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;\u003c/code\u003e to read the declared \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e. Convert each to a \u003ccode\u003eSelectListItem\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eValue = c.Name\u003c/code\u003e (e.g. \u003ccode\u003e&quot;fr&quot;\u003c/code\u003e) and \u003ccode\u003eText = c.DisplayName\u003c/code\u003e (e.g. \u003ccode\u003e&quot;French (France)&quot;\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRender the form.\u003c/strong\u003e Use a Razor form that POSTs to an \u003ccode\u003eOnPost\u003c/code\u003e handler on the current page:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cshtml\"\u003e@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Localization\n@inject IOptions&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt; LocOpts\n\n@{\n    var current = Context.Features.Get&lt;IRequestCultureFeature&gt;();\n    var items = LocOpts.Value.SupportedUICultures!\n        .Select(c =&gt; new SelectListItem { Value = c.Name, Text = c.DisplayName })\n        .ToList();\n}\n\n&lt;form asp-page=&quot;/Index&quot; method=&quot;post&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;select name=&quot;culture&quot;\n            onchange=&quot;this.form.submit();&quot;\n            asp-for=&quot;@current!.RequestCulture.UICulture.Name&quot;\n            asp-items=&quot;items&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;/select&gt;\n    &lt;input type=&quot;hidden&quot; name=&quot;returnUrl&quot; value=&quot;@Context.Request.Path&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrite the \u003ccode\u003eOnPost\u003c/code\u003e handler.\u003c/strong\u003e In the PageModel:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003epublic IActionResult OnPost(string culture, string returnUrl)\n{\n    Response.Cookies.Append(\n        CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName,\n        CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(culture)),\n        new CookieOptions { Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddYears(1) });\n\n    return LocalRedirect(returnUrl);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eDefaultCookieName\u003c/code\u003e is the built-in value \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e that \u003ccode\u003eCookieRequestCultureProvider\u003c/code\u003e looks for. \u003ccode\u003eMakeCookieValue\u003c/code\u003e formats the string exactly the way the provider expects (\u003ccode\u003ec=&lt;culture&gt;|uic=&lt;uiculture&gt;\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrace the first reload.\u003c/strong\u003e The user selects \u003ccode\u003efr\u003c/code\u003e and the form submits. The handler writes \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture=c=fr|uic=fr\u003c/code\u003e as a cookie with a 1-year expiry, then \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect\u003c/code\u003es back to the same page. On the redirected GET, \u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization\u003c/code\u003e runs its providers in order: \u003ccode\u003eQueryStringRequestCultureProvider\u003c/code\u003e finds nothing (no \u003ccode\u003e?culture=\u003c/code\u003e), \u003ccode\u003eCookieRequestCultureProvider\u003c/code\u003e reads \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture=c=fr|uic=fr\u003c/code\u003e and returns \u003ccode\u003efr\u003c/code\u003e, so \u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e both become \u003ccode\u003efr\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e now returns French values; dates and numbers format in French.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","common_wrong_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNot passing \u003ccode\u003ereturnUrl\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect(&quot;/&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e hard-codes the home page, so switching languages on any deep page bounces the user back to the top. Pass the current path as a hidden field and redirect there instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003eRedirect(returnUrl)\u003c/code\u003e instead of \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect(returnUrl)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eRedirect\u003c/code\u003e accepts any URL, including external ones, which opens an open-redirect vulnerability if \u003ccode\u003ereturnUrl\u003c/code\u003e comes from user input. \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect\u003c/code\u003e rejects absolute URLs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting the cookie without \u003ccode\u003eCookieOptions.Expires\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Without an expiry the cookie becomes a session cookie that disappears when the browser closes. Users expect a persistent language choice — always set \u003ccode\u003eExpires\u003c/code\u003e at least months out.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003eCookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(culture, culture))\u003c/code\u003e redundantly.\u003c/strong\u003e The single-arg form already sets both \u003ccode\u003eCulture\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eUICulture\u003c/code\u003e. Adding the second arg only differs when you deliberately want dates in one locale and UI strings in another — rarely desired.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","why_html":"\u003cp\u003ePersistent language selection requires coordination between three moving parts: the UI (dropdown with \u003ccode\u003eonchange=&quot;this.form.submit();&quot;\u003c/code\u003e), the server handler (cookie write + \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect\u003c/code\u003e), and the middleware pipeline (\u003ccode\u003eCookieRequestCultureProvider\u003c/code\u003e reading \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e on subsequent requests). The cookie format is non-negotiable — the provider knows exactly which name and value shape to look for. The year-long expiry makes the choice survive browser restarts; the \u003ccode\u003eLocalRedirect\u003c/code\u003e keeps users on the page they were viewing; and the whole mechanism works on every page without per-page handler code because the form POSTs to a single \u003ccode\u003eOnPost(culture, returnUrl)\u003c/code\u003e method that sits on a base PageModel or on a dedicated \u003ccode\u003e/LanguageSwitcher\u003c/code\u003e handler.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":12,"id":"localization-translate-page","title":"Translate a Razor page's PageModel + view strings","lang":"cs","tags":["i18n","di","istringlocalizer","iviewlocalizer"],"source":"Labs/W10 Localization/ Q3 (variant — translate exactly two strings on one page, simpler than the lab's full-site string pass)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eAn \u003ccode\u003eIndex.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e page has two strings that need translation: a \u003ccode\u003e&lt;h1&gt;\u003c/code\u003e welcome heading rendered directly in markup, and a \u003ccode\u003e&lt;p&gt;\u003c/code\u003e message whose text is set in the PageModel via \u003ccode\u003eViewData[&quot;Message&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e. The page already has \u003ccode\u003e@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\u003c/code\u003e available and the PageModel already constructor-injects \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;IndexModel&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. Replace the hardcoded English strings with localized lookups that pick up translations from \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// Pages/Index.cshtml.cs\npublic class IndexModel : PageModel\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e _localizer;\n\n    public IndexModel(IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e localizer)\n        =\u003e _localizer = localizer;\n\n    public void OnGet()\n    {\n        // TODO: replace the hardcoded English with a localized lookup\n        //       using the key \"Message\".\n        ViewData[\"Message\"] = \"This is the message.\";\n    }\n}\n\n// Pages/Index.cshtml\n@page\n@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n@model IndexModel\n\n// TODO: replace the hardcoded \"Welcome\" with a localized lookup\n//       using the key \"Welcome\".\n\u003ch1\u003eWelcome\u003c/h1\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e@ViewData[\"Message\"]\u003c/p\u003e","solution":"// Pages/Index.cshtml.cs\npublic class IndexModel : PageModel\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e _localizer;\n\n    public IndexModel(IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e localizer)\n        =\u003e _localizer = localizer;\n\n    public void OnGet()\n    {\n        ViewData[\"Message\"] = _localizer[\"Message\"];\n    }\n}\n\n// Pages/Index.cshtml\n@page\n@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n@model IndexModel\n\n\u003ch1\u003e@Localizer[\"Welcome\"]\u003c/h1\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e@ViewData[\"Message\"]\u003c/p\u003e","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eYou also need two resource files, \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.en.resx\u003c/code\u003e (or no-suffix default) with keys \u003ccode\u003eWelcome → Welcome\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eMessage → This is the message.\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode\u003eWelcome → Bienvenue\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eMessage → Ceci est le message.\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe view uses \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e for strings rendered directly from markup; the PageModel uses \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;IndexModel&gt;\u003c/code\u003e for strings that are computed in code and passed through \u003ccode\u003eViewData\u003c/code\u003e. Both resolve against the same resource file — \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e — because the generic type parameter on \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;IndexModel&gt;\u003c/code\u003e and the implicit type parameter on \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e (the view&#39;s generated class) map to the same .resx naming path.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe indexer \u003ccode\u003e_localizer[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eLocalizer[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e does three things in sequence: look up the current \u003ccode\u003eCultureInfo\u003c/code\u003e from \u003ccode\u003eThread.CurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e, find the matching \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e file (falling back through the parent-culture chain), read the key. If the key isn&#39;t present in any \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e, the indexer returns the key itself as a literal string — so a missing translation shows up as &quot;Welcome&quot; instead of &quot;Bienvenue&quot; rather than blowing up.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003e@Html.Raw(Localizer[&quot;Welcome&quot;])\u003c/code\u003e unnecessarily.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e returns a \u003ccode\u003eLocalizedHtmlString\u003c/code\u003e that Razor already knows how to render. \u003ccode\u003e@Html.Raw\u003c/code\u003e is only needed when you want to bypass HTML encoding, which matters for \u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e content (not \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInjecting \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e (non-generic) into the PageModel.\u003c/strong\u003e Without the \u003ccode\u003e&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e parameter, DI can&#39;t decide which resource file to target. The correct injection is \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;IndexModel&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePutting the .resx file at \u003ccode\u003eResources/IndexModel.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e (missing the \u003ccode\u003ePages/\u003c/code\u003e subfolder).\u003c/strong\u003e Directory layout under \u003ccode\u003eResources/\u003c/code\u003e must mirror the class location. With the wrong path the file is invisible to the localizer, which silently falls back to the default culture or returns the key.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":13,"id":"filebased-json-read","title":"Deserialize students.json in a file-based app","lang":"cs","tags":["dotnet-10","file-based","json","deserialize"],"source":"Labs/W11 File Based C# Apps/ Q1 (variant — deserialize one JSON file into a typed list and print the count, simpler than the lab's multi-field filter)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eGiven a file \u003ccode\u003estudents.json\u003c/code\u003e (a JSON array of \u003ccode\u003e{ name, school, dob, gender }\u003c/code\u003e objects) in the current directory, write a file-based C# app (\u003ccode\u003ereadStudents.cs\u003c/code\u003e) that:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReads the file with \u003ccode\u003eFile.ReadAllText\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeserializes it into a \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e using \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Text.Json\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrints \u003ccode\u003eLoaded N students.\u003c/code\u003e where N is the count.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUse a \u003ccode\u003eStudent\u003c/code\u003e record declared below the top-level code.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// readStudents.cs\n\n// TODO: read students.json, deserialize into a List\u003cStudent\u003e,\n//       and print the count.\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","solution":"// readStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true });\n\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Loaded {students?.Count ?? 0} students.\");\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThree file-based-app idioms show up. First, top-level statements replace \u003ccode\u003eMain\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eFile.ReadAllText(...)\u003c/code\u003e runs at the top of the file. Second, implicit usings cover \u003ccode\u003eSystem.IO\u003c/code\u003e (for \u003ccode\u003eFile\u003c/code\u003e) and \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Collections.Generic\u003c/code\u003e (for \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e), so no \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e directives are needed for those. \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Text.Json\u003c/code\u003e is NOT implicit, so it needs an explicit \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e. Third, type declarations (the \u003ccode\u003eStudent\u003c/code\u003e record) live below top-level statements — the compiler rewrites the file so top-level code goes into an implicit \u003ccode\u003eMain\u003c/code\u003e and type declarations are compiled as peers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true\u003c/code\u003e lets your PascalCase C# record match typical camelCase JSON. Without it, deserialization returns a list where every property is null.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRun with \u003ccode\u003edotnet run readStudents.cs\u003c/code\u003e. Output: \u003ccode\u003eLoaded 6 students.\u003c/code\u003e (or whatever the file contains).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDeclaring \u003ccode\u003eStudent\u003c/code\u003e above the top-level code.\u003c/strong\u003e The compiler requires type declarations after top-level statements. Moving the record to the top of the file produces a compilation error.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting \u003ccode\u003ePropertyNameCaseInsensitive\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e JSON like \u003ccode\u003e{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Alice&quot;}\u003c/code\u003e won&#39;t bind to a property \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e by default — properties come out as their default values (null for strings). Case-insensitive matching bridges the case convention gap.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003eargs[0]\u003c/code\u003e as the filename without a fallback.\u003c/strong\u003e If the script is invoked without args (\u003ccode\u003edotnet run readStudents.cs\u003c/code\u003e), \u003ccode\u003eargs[0]\u003c/code\u003e throws IndexOutOfRange. Hardcode the filename or guard with \u003ccode\u003eargs.Length &gt; 0\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":14,"id":"filebased-filter","title":"Filter a deserialized list by keyword (case-insensitive)","lang":"cs","tags":["dotnet-10","file-based","linq","filter"],"source":"Labs/W11 File Based C# Apps/ Q2 (variant — filter by Name substring only, simpler than the lab which searched Name OR School OR Dob OR Gender)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eExtend the previous script (\u003ccode\u003ereadStudents.cs\u003c/code\u003e) to accept a \u003ccode\u003ekeyword\u003c/code\u003e command-line argument. Filter the loaded \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;Student&gt;\u003c/code\u003e to rows where the \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e property contains the keyword (case-insensitive). Print each matching student&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e. If no keyword is supplied, print every student.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// readStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\n// TODO: read an optional keyword from args and filter students by Name.\n// TODO: print each matching student's Name on its own line.\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","solution":"// readStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\nvar keyword = args.Length \u003e 0 ? args[0] : null;\n\nvar matches = keyword is null\n    ? students\n    : students.Where(s =\u003e s.Name.Contains(keyword, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n\nforeach (var s in matches)\n    Console.WriteLine(s.Name);\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eargs\u003c/code\u003e is available at the top level in every file-based app. The ternary \u003ccode\u003eargs.Length &gt; 0 ? args[0] : null\u003c/code\u003e defaults gracefully when the user invokes \u003ccode\u003edotnet run readStudents.cs -- \u003c/code\u003e without a value. \u003ccode\u003estring.Contains(..., StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)\u003c/code\u003e is the .NET 5+ overload that skips \u003ccode\u003e.ToLower()\u003c/code\u003e allocations and normalizes consistently across cultures.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eInvoke with \u003ccode\u003edotnet run readStudents.cs -- alice\u003c/code\u003e. Without the \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e, the CLI consumes \u003ccode\u003ealice\u003c/code\u003e as its own argument and your script sees empty \u003ccode\u003eargs\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003e.ToLower()\u003c/code\u003e on both sides of the comparison.\u003c/strong\u003e It works but allocates a new string per row — fine for a script, expensive in a hot loop. \u003ccode\u003eStringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase\u003c/code\u003e avoids the allocation.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForgetting the \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e when running.\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003edotnet run readStudents.cs alice\u003c/code\u003e hands \u003ccode\u003ealice\u003c/code\u003e to the CLI (which ignores it silently or errors). Everything after \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e becomes \u003ccode\u003eargs\u003c/code\u003e inside the script.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReturning the filtered query as \u003ccode\u003eIEnumerable\u003c/code\u003e and enumerating it twice.\u003c/strong\u003e LINQ queries are lazy — iterating a \u003ccode\u003eWhere\u003c/code\u003e result twice re-evaluates the predicate per row. For small data it doesn&#39;t matter; for large data, materialize with \u003ccode\u003e.ToList()\u003c/code\u003e once.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":15,"id":"filebased-spectre-table","title":"Render results as a Spectre.Console table using #:package","lang":"cs","tags":["dotnet-10","file-based","directive","spectre-console"],"source":"Labs/W11 File Based C# Apps/ Q3 (variant — single-column rendered table of names, simpler than the lab which rendered a multi-column Spectre table with borders, colors, and title)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eReplace the plain \u003ccode\u003eConsole.WriteLine(s.Name)\u003c/code\u003e output in the filter script with a bordered Spectre.Console table. The table has one column titled &quot;Name&quot; and one row per matching student. Declare the package dependency inline via \u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// filterStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\n// TODO: declare a #:package directive for Spectre.Console.\n// TODO: import Spectre.Console.\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\nvar keyword = args.Length \u003e 0 ? args[0] : null;\nvar matches = keyword is null\n    ? students\n    : students.Where(s =\u003e s.Name.Contains(keyword, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n\n// TODO: render matches as a bordered Spectre table with one \"Name\" column.\nforeach (var s in matches)\n    Console.WriteLine(s.Name);\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","solution":"// filterStudents.cs\n#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\n\nusing System.Text.Json;\nusing Spectre.Console;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\nvar keyword = args.Length \u003e 0 ? args[0] : null;\nvar matches = keyword is null\n    ? students\n    : students.Where(s =\u003e s.Name.Contains(keyword, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n\nvar table = new Table();\ntable.Border = TableBorder.Rounded;\ntable.AddColumn(\"Name\");\n\nforeach (var s in matches)\n    table.AddRow(s.Name);\n\nAnsiConsole.Write(table);\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\u003c/code\u003e is the entire package-management story for this script — the CLI downloads Spectre.Console on first run and caches it in \u003ccode\u003e~/.dotnet/runfile/\u003c/code\u003e. No NuGet restore, no \u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAnsiConsole.Write(table)\u003c/code\u003e is the Spectre pattern for rendering. Spectre tables support borders (\u003ccode\u003eTableBorder.Rounded\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eHeavy\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eDouble\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eNone\u003c/code\u003e), column alignment, styled text (\u003ccode\u003e[green]Name[/]\u003c/code\u003e), and cell colors — all out of scope for this practice but easy additions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#: package Spectre.Console@0.49.1\u003c/code\u003e (space after the colon).\u003c/strong\u003e Syntax error. The directive name must sit flush against \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e. The spaced form is the single most-tested exam distractor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting the version pin (\u003ccode\u003e@0.49.1\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/strong\u003e The CLI pulls the latest version on first run, which may subtly change the API between sessions. Pinning a version makes the script reproducible across machines and months.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCalling \u003ccode\u003eConsole.WriteLine(table)\u003c/code\u003e instead of \u003ccode\u003eAnsiConsole.Write(table)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Spectre tables don&#39;t have a meaningful \u003ccode\u003eToString()\u003c/code\u003e — you see \u003ccode\u003eSpectre.Console.Table\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eAnsiConsole.Write\u003c/code\u003e drives the actual rendering with ANSI escape codes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":16,"id":"filebased-cli-args","title":"Accept keyword from command-line args in a file-based app","lang":"cs","tags":["dotnet-10","file-based","cli","args"],"source":"Labs/W11 File Based C# Apps/ Q4 (variant — default to \"medicine\" keyword when no arg given, matching the lab's start.sh default behavior)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eModify the filter script so that when \u003ccode\u003edotnet run filterStudents.cs -- &lt;keyword&gt;\u003c/code\u003e is invoked with no keyword, the script defaults to \u003ccode\u003e&quot;medicine&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (matching the lab&#39;s \u003ccode\u003estart.sh\u003c/code\u003e convention) instead of listing every student. When a keyword IS supplied, use it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePrint the effective keyword on the first line: \u003ccode\u003eFiltering by: &lt;keyword&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// filterStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\n// TODO: determine the effective keyword — use args[0] if given,\n//       otherwise default to \"medicine\".\n// TODO: print \"Filtering by: \u003ckeyword\u003e\".\n// TODO: filter by Name OR School containing the keyword.\nforeach (var s in students)\n    Console.WriteLine(s.Name);\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","solution":"// filterStudents.cs\nusing System.Text.Json;\n\nvar json = File.ReadAllText(\"students.json\");\nvar students = JsonSerializer.Deserialize\u003cList\u003cStudent\u003e\u003e(\n    json,\n    new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = true }) ?? new();\n\nvar keyword = args.Length \u003e 0 ? args[0] : \"medicine\";\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Filtering by: {keyword}\");\n\nvar matches = students.Where(s =\u003e\n    s.Name.Contains(keyword, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase) ||\n    s.School.Contains(keyword, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n\nforeach (var s in matches)\n    Console.WriteLine($\"  {s.Name} ({s.School})\");\n\npublic record Student(string Name, string School, string Dob, string Gender);","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe default-value pattern \u003ccode\u003eargs.Length &gt; 0 ? args[0] : &quot;medicine&quot;\u003c/code\u003e mirrors what the lab&#39;s \u003ccode\u003estart.sh\u003c/code\u003e does: if the user doesn&#39;t type a keyword, apply a sensible default. This is common in CLI tools — a zero-arg run should still do something useful rather than listing everything or erroring.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExtending the predicate to search both \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eSchool\u003c/code\u003e is a single \u003ccode\u003e||\u003c/code\u003e between two \u003ccode\u003e.Contains(...)\u003c/code\u003e calls. With more than two fields, a helper method keeps the lambda readable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRun examples:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003edotnet run filterStudents.cs\u003c/code\u003e → keyword = \u003ccode\u003e&quot;medicine&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (default).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003edotnet run filterStudents.cs -- alice\u003c/code\u003e → keyword = \u003ccode\u003e&quot;alice&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003edotnet run filterStudents.cs -- &quot;St. Mary&quot;\u003c/code\u003e → keyword = \u003ccode\u003e&quot;St. Mary&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (quotes keep the space).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChecking \u003ccode\u003eargs.Length &gt;= 0\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Always true. The predicate must be \u003ccode\u003e&gt; 0\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e== 1\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAccessing \u003ccode\u003eargs[0]\u003c/code\u003e without a length guard.\u003c/strong\u003e If the user runs with no args, \u003ccode\u003eargs[0]\u003c/code\u003e throws \u003ccode\u003eIndexOutOfRangeException\u003c/code\u003e. The ternary is the idiomatic fix.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDefaulting to \u003ccode\u003estring.Empty\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003enull\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Empty-string \u003ccode\u003eContains\u003c/code\u003e matches everything (every string contains the empty string), so the filter returns the full list — technically not wrong but hides the intent. Using a real default like \u003ccode\u003e&quot;medicine&quot;\u003c/code\u003e makes the zero-arg behavior match the lab&#39;s scripted demo.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":17,"id":"xlsx-export","title":"Export a list to Excel via ClosedXML","lang":"cs","tags":["excel","closedxml","file-result","razor-pages"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/ Q2 (variant — two-column player export, simpler than the lab's multi-column FIFA game table with styling)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eOn a Razor Page handler \u003ccode\u003eOnGet\u003c/code\u003e, produce an Excel download named \u003ccode\u003eplayers.xlsx\u003c/code\u003e containing two columns — \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eScore\u003c/code\u003e — with one row per entry in \u003ccode\u003ePlayer.All()\u003c/code\u003e. Style the header row with a light-gray fill. Return the result as a \u003ccode\u003eFileResult\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"using ClosedXML.Excel;\nusing System.IO;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.RazorPages;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;\n\npublic class PlayersModel : PageModel\n{\n    public FileResult OnGet()\n    {\n        // TODO: build an XLWorkbook, add a \"Players\" worksheet,\n        //       write headers + data, style the header row with a gray fill,\n        //       save to a MemoryStream, and return as FileResult\n        //       with filename \"players.xlsx\".\n        throw new NotImplementedException();\n    }\n}","solution":"using ClosedXML.Excel;\nusing System.IO;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.RazorPages;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;\n\npublic class PlayersModel : PageModel\n{\n    public FileResult OnGet()\n    {\n        using var workbook = new XLWorkbook();\n        var sheet = workbook.Worksheets.Add(\"Players\");\n\n        sheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Name\";\n        sheet.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Score\";\n\n        var header = sheet.Range(sheet.Cell(1, 1).Address, sheet.Cell(1, 2).Address);\n        header.Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.LightGray);\n        header.Style.Font.Bold = true;\n\n        int row = 2;\n        foreach (var p in Player.All())\n        {\n            sheet.Cell(row, 1).Value = p.Name;\n            sheet.Cell(row, 2).Value = p.Score;\n            row++;\n        }\n\n        sheet.Columns().AdjustToContents();\n\n        using var ms = new MemoryStream();\n        workbook.SaveAs(ms);\n\n        return File(\n            ms.ToArray(),\n            \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\n            \"players.xlsx\");\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eFive steps — open workbook, add sheet, write headers (row 1) and data (row 2 upward), style the header range, save to a \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e, return a \u003ccode\u003eFileResult\u003c/code\u003e. The header range is styled as a group via \u003ccode\u003eIXLRange.Style\u003c/code\u003e; per-cell styling would work but repeats the Fill + Bold setup per column.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003esheet.Columns().AdjustToContents()\u003c/code\u003e auto-fits column widths after data is written. Without it, the downloaded file opens with every column at the default ~8-character width, forcing the user to drag column dividers before the data is readable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe MIME type \u003ccode\u003eapplication/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\u003c/code\u003e is the exact OpenXML spreadsheet identifier. \u003ccode\u003eapplication/excel\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003eapplication/vnd.ms-excel\u003c/code\u003e target different formats (or don&#39;t exist) and cause browsers to save the file without a proper extension.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStarting the data loop at \u003ccode\u003erow = 1\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Row 1 is the header; data starts at row 2. Starting at 1 overwrites the headers with the first player&#39;s name.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing \u003ccode\u003esheet.Cell(0, 0)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e ClosedXML cells are 1-based. \u003ccode\u003eCell(0, 0)\u003c/code\u003e either throws or is silently ignored, so the first header never appears.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReturning \u003ccode\u003eFile(ms, mime, name)\u003c/code\u003e with an unclosed \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e on the MemoryStream.\u003c/strong\u003e When using \u003ccode\u003eFile(stream, ...)\u003c/code\u003e, the framework reads from the stream asynchronously — a \u003ccode\u003eusing\u003c/code\u003e disposes the stream before the read completes and the response body is empty. Either return \u003ccode\u003ems.ToArray()\u003c/code\u003e (no stream lifetime issue) or let the framework dispose the stream.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":18,"id":"pdf-players-export","title":"Export a list to PDF via iText 7","lang":"cs","tags":["pdf","itext7","file-stream-result","razor-pages"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/ Q3 (variant — single 'Players' table without page numbering, simpler than the lab's multi-table report with centered title + per-page footer)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eOn a Razor Page handler, produce a PDF download named \u003ccode\u003eplayers.pdf\u003c/code\u003e containing a centered title &quot;Players&quot; followed by a two-column table (\u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eScore\u003c/code\u003e) with one row per entry in \u003ccode\u003ePlayer.All()\u003c/code\u003e. Return the result as a \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e. Assume both \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e NuGet packages are installed.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"using iText.Kernel.Geom;\nusing iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\nusing iText.Layout.Properties;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.RazorPages;\nusing System.IO;\n\npublic class PdfReportModel : PageModel\n{\n    public IActionResult OnGet()\n    {\n        // TODO: create a MemoryStream, wrap in PdfWriter → PdfDocument → Document.\n        // TODO: call writer.SetCloseStream(false).\n        // TODO: add a centered \"Players\" title, then a 2-column table\n        //       with headers and one row per Player.All().\n        // TODO: close the Document, rewind the stream, return as FileStreamResult.\n        throw new NotImplementedException();\n    }\n}","solution":"using iText.Kernel.Geom;\nusing iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\nusing iText.Layout.Properties;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.RazorPages;\nusing System.IO;\n\npublic class PdfReportModel : PageModel\n{\n    public IActionResult OnGet()\n    {\n        var ms = new MemoryStream();\n\n        var writer = new PdfWriter(ms);\n        var pdfDoc = new PdfDocument(writer);\n        var doc    = new Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false);\n        writer.SetCloseStream(false);\n\n        doc.Add(new Paragraph(\"Players\")\n            .SetTextAlignment(TextAlignment.CENTER)\n            .SetFontSize(20));\n\n        var table = new Table(2);\n        table.AddCell(new Cell().Add(new Paragraph(\"Name\")));\n        table.AddCell(new Cell().Add(new Paragraph(\"Score\")));\n\n        foreach (var p in Player.All())\n        {\n            table.AddCell(new Cell().Add(new Paragraph(p.Name)));\n            table.AddCell(new Cell().Add(new Paragraph(p.Score.ToString())));\n        }\n\n        doc.Add(table);\n        doc.Close();\n        ms.Position = 0;\n\n        return new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\")\n        {\n            FileDownloadName = \"players.pdf\"\n        };\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe iText pipeline is four layers: \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter(ms)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfDocument(writer)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eDocument(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)\u003c/code\u003e. Each layer wraps the previous. \u003ccode\u003eSetCloseStream(false)\u003c/code\u003e keeps the \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e open after \u003ccode\u003edoc.Close()\u003c/code\u003e so you can read it into the response.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003enew Table(2)\u003c/code\u003e creates a two-column table. \u003ccode\u003eAddCell\u003c/code\u003e fills the next cell left-to-right, wrapping to a new row when the count hits \u003ccode\u003e2 * N\u003c/code\u003e. Each \u003ccode\u003eCell\u003c/code\u003e wraps a \u003ccode\u003eParagraph\u003c/code\u003e for text content; you could also style fills, borders, and alignment per cell.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe three-line finish is the whole trap: \u003ccode\u003edoc.Close()\u003c/code\u003e writes the final PDF bytes; \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e rewinds to the start (without it, \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e reads from the end and serves an empty file); \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e produces the response with the correct filename.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForgetting \u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e The MemoryStream&#39;s cursor is at the end after writing. \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e reads from the current position, finds nothing, and the browser downloads a 0-byte PDF labelled &quot;Document is empty or corrupted.&quot;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSkipping \u003ccode\u003ewriter.SetCloseStream(false)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Default behavior closes the underlying stream when the Document closes. Subsequent attempts to read from \u003ccode\u003ems\u003c/code\u003e throw \u003ccode\u003eObjectDisposedException\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInstalling only \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e and not \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e Compilation succeeds; runtime throws when iText tries to hash or sign content. Install both packages together.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"kind":"code","variant":"starter-solution","n":19,"id":"chartjs-pie","title":"Render a Chart.js pie chart from Razor data","lang":"cs","tags":["chart","chart-js","razor","pie"],"source":"Labs/W13 Excel, PDF, Chart cocktail/ Q4 (variant — render a single pie chart of games-per-continent, simpler than the lab which stacked pie + bar charts on one page with explicit CSS)","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eOn a Razor Page whose \u003ccode\u003eModel.ChartData\u003c/code\u003e is an \u003ccode\u003eIEnumerable&lt;(string Name, int Count)&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, render a Chart.js pie chart. Each slice corresponds to one tuple — the label comes from \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e, the value from \u003ccode\u003eCount\u003c/code\u003e. Load Chart.js from the course CDN URL.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"@page\n@model IndexModel\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGames by Continent\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n@* TODO: add a \u003ccanvas\u003e with id=\"pie-chart\". *@\n\n@* TODO: load Chart.js from the CDN:\n         https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js *@\n\n@* TODO: in a \u003cscript\u003e block, build JS arrays `labels` and `counts`\n         by looping over Model.ChartData with @: directives, then\n         call `new Chart(ctx, { type: 'pie', data: { labels, datasets: [{ data: counts }] } })`. *@","solution":"@page\n@model IndexModel\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGames by Continent\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003ccanvas id=\"pie-chart\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n\n\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\n    const labels = [];\n    const counts = [];\n\n    @foreach (var item in Model.ChartData)\n    {\n        @:labels.push('@item.Name');\n        @:counts.push(@item.Count);\n    }\n\n    const ctx = document.getElementById('pie-chart');\n\n    new Chart(ctx, {\n        type: 'pie',\n        data: {\n            labels: labels,\n            datasets: [{\n                label: 'Games',\n                data: counts,\n                backgroundColor: [\n                    'rgba(255, 99, 132, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(255, 206, 86, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(153, 102, 255, 0.7)'\n                ]\n            }]\n        }\n    });\n\u003c/script\u003e","why_html":"\u003cp\u003eThree moving pieces get the chart on screen. The \u003ccode\u003e&lt;canvas&gt;\u003c/code\u003e element receives the drawing; \u003ccode\u003edocument.getElementById(&#39;pie-chart&#39;)\u003c/code\u003e fetches the reference Chart.js needs. The Chart.js \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script src&gt;\u003c/code\u003e must load before the chart-construction \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — keeping both inside \u003ccode\u003e&lt;body&gt;\u003c/code\u003e in order is simplest.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003e@foreach (...)\u003c/code\u003e block builds the JavaScript data arrays by interpolating each tuple&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eName\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eCount\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003e@:labels.push(...)\u003c/code\u003e is Razor&#39;s &quot;mixed line&quot; directive — it tells Razor to treat the line as literal output with \u003ccode\u003e@\u003c/code\u003e-expression substitutions. Without \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e, Razor tries to parse the whole line as C# and errors out (or, worse, produces malformed JS).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003enew Chart(ctx, config)\u003c/code\u003e is the library entry point. \u003ccode\u003etype: &#39;pie&#39;\u003c/code\u003e selects the shape; \u003ccode\u003edata.labels\u003c/code\u003e aligns 1:1 with \u003ccode\u003edata.datasets[0].data\u003c/code\u003e — index \u003ccode\u003ei\u003c/code\u003e of one array corresponds to index \u003ccode\u003ei\u003c/code\u003e of the other.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCommon wrong approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOmitting the \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e directive inside the \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e block.\u003c/strong\u003e Razor tries to parse \u003ccode\u003elabels.push(...)\u003c/code\u003e as C# and fails, or emits broken JS. \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e is the signal to Razor that this line mixes JS with \u003ccode\u003e@\u003c/code\u003e-expressions.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePlacing the Chart.js \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script src&gt;\u003c/code\u003e AFTER the construction \u003ccode\u003e&lt;script&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e JavaScript executes top-to-bottom. If the construction block runs before Chart.js has loaded, \u003ccode\u003eChart is not defined\u003c/code\u003e appears in the console and the canvas stays blank.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing fewer colors in \u003ccode\u003ebackgroundColor\u003c/code\u003e than data points.\u003c/strong\u003e Chart.js recycles colors in order, so slices beyond the 5th color repeat the first. For a small fixed dataset this is fine; for variable-length data, compute colors programmatically or use Chart.js plugins for palettes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"}],"cheatSheet":{"blocks":[{"heading":"Exam meta","body_md":"- 2026-04-24 · 10:30–11:30 · SE12-327 · 80 marks / 60 min\n- 60 MCQ + 10 match + 1 coding\n- Allowed: one hand-written 8.5\" × 11\" sheet, both sides","body_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2026-04-24 · 10:30–11:30 · SE12-327 · 80 marks / 60 min\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e60 MCQ + 10 match + 1 coding\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAllowed: one hand-written 8.5&quot; × 11&quot; sheet, both sides\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"AI — Semantic Kernel + MAF + Ollama + GitHub Models","body_md":"**TL;DR** — All OpenAI-compatible endpoints use the same `OpenAIClient(new ApiKeyCredential(key), new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(url) })` shape. Only URL + credential change.\n\n**Semantic Kernel wiring (W02 lab, GitHub Models):**\n\n```cs\nusing Microsoft.SemanticKernel;\nusing OpenAI;\nusing System.ClientModel;\n\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(builder.Configuration[\"AI:PAT\"]!),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(builder.Configuration[\"AI:Endpoint\"]!) });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(builder.Configuration[\"AI:Model\"]!, client);\nbuilder.Services.AddKernel();\n```\n\n- Package: `Microsoft.SemanticKernel` (only)\n- Inject `IChatCompletionService` into PageModel\n- `ChatHistory chat = new(\"system prompt\");` + `.AddUserMessage(...)` / `.AddAssistantMessage(...)`\n- Stream: `await foreach (var m in _chat.GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync(chat)) sb.Append(m.Content);`\n- Endpoint: `https://models.github.ai/inference` · Model id: `openai/gpt-4o-mini`\n- Session persistence: JSON-serialize `List\u003cChatEntry\u003e` to `HttpContext.Session`\n\n**MAF agent — two shapes:**\n\n1. Ctor (MAF.Phi3):\n```cs\nChatClientAgent agent = new ChatClientAgent(ollamaClient,\n    new ChatClientAgentOptions { Name = \"Astronomer\",\n        ChatOptions = new ChatOptions { Instructions = \"...\", Temperature = 0.7f }});\nawait agent.RunAsync(\"How far is earth from the sun?\");\n```\n\n2. `.AsAIAgent` (FunnyDockerMAF):\n```cs\nAIAgent agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(name: \"Bot\", instructions: \"...\");\nAgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();\nawait foreach (var u in agent.RunStreamingAsync(input,\n    options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(chatOptions))) Console.Write(u.Text);\n```\n\n- Package: `Microsoft.Agents.AI` + `Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI`\n- Multi-turn: `AgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync()`\n- `.AsAIAgent()` NOT `.AsAgent()` · `RunAsync`/`RunStreamingAsync` NOT `Invoke`\n\n**Ollama (local SLM):**\n\n```cs\nIChatClient chatClient = new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434/\"), \"phi3\");\nList\u003cChatMessage\u003e chatHistory = new();\nchatHistory.Add(new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, userPrompt));\nawait foreach (var u in chatClient.GetStreamingResponseAsync(chatHistory))\n    Console.Write(u.Text);\n```\n\n- Package: `OllamaSharp` + `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`\n- HTTP (not HTTPS) · port 11434 · no auth · fully local after `ollama pull phi3`\n- CLI: `ollama pull phi3:latest` · `ollama list` · `ollama run phi3:latest`\n\n**Docker local SLM (OpenAI-compatible):**\n\n```cs\nvar openAIClient = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(\"unused\"),        // local runtimes ignore credential\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(\"http://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1\") });\nvar chatClient = openAIClient.GetChatClient(\"ai/ministral3:latest\");\n// Either: await chatClient.CompleteChatAsync(prompt)\n// Or:     chatClient.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)\n```\n\n**Traps**\n\n- Credential is `ApiKeyCredential` (from `System.ClientModel`) — NOT `AzureKeyCredential`\n- W02 lab does NOT use `KernelBuilder`, `Kernel.CreateBuilder()`, `ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e`, `[KernelFunction]`, or `skprompt.txt` — those are SK features but out of the demoed scope\n- `AIFunctionFactory.Create(...)` + tool registration — NOT in any lab or demo\n- Endpoint URL shapes:\n  - GitHub: `https://models.github.ai/inference`\n  - Ollama: `http://localhost:11434/`\n  - Docker SLM: `http://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1`\n- Model id formats:\n  - GitHub: vendor prefix `openai/gpt-4o-mini`\n  - Ollama: bare tag `phi3:latest`\n  - Docker SLM: image id `ai/ministral3:latest`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTL;DR\u003c/strong\u003e — All OpenAI-compatible endpoints use the same \u003ccode\u003eOpenAIClient(new ApiKeyCredential(key), new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(url) })\u003c/code\u003e shape. Only URL + credential change.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSemantic Kernel wiring (W02 lab, GitHub Models):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing Microsoft.SemanticKernel;\nusing OpenAI;\nusing System.ClientModel;\n\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(builder.Configuration[&quot;AI:PAT&quot;]!),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(builder.Configuration[&quot;AI:Endpoint&quot;]!) });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(builder.Configuration[&quot;AI:Model&quot;]!, client);\nbuilder.Services.AddKernel();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePackage: \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.SemanticKernel\u003c/code\u003e (only)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInject \u003ccode\u003eIChatCompletionService\u003c/code\u003e into PageModel\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eChatHistory chat = new(&quot;system prompt&quot;);\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e.AddUserMessage(...)\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003e.AddAssistantMessage(...)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStream: \u003ccode\u003eawait foreach (var m in _chat.GetStreamingChatMessageContentsAsync(chat)) sb.Append(m.Content);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEndpoint: \u003ccode\u003ehttps://models.github.ai/inference\u003c/code\u003e · Model id: \u003ccode\u003eopenai/gpt-4o-mini\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSession persistence: JSON-serialize \u003ccode\u003eList&lt;ChatEntry&gt;\u003c/code\u003e to \u003ccode\u003eHttpContext.Session\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMAF agent — two shapes:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCtor (MAF.Phi3):\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eChatClientAgent agent = new ChatClientAgent(ollamaClient,\n    new ChatClientAgentOptions { Name = &quot;Astronomer&quot;,\n        ChatOptions = new ChatOptions { Instructions = &quot;...&quot;, Temperature = 0.7f }});\nawait agent.RunAsync(&quot;How far is earth from the sun?&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003col start=\"2\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e (FunnyDockerMAF):\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eAIAgent agent = chatClient.AsAIAgent(name: &quot;Bot&quot;, instructions: &quot;...&quot;);\nAgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();\nawait foreach (var u in agent.RunStreamingAsync(input,\n    options: new ChatClientAgentRunOptions(chatOptions))) Console.Write(u.Text);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePackage: \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.Agents.AI\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMulti-turn: \u003ccode\u003eAgentSession session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent()\u003c/code\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eRunAsync\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003eRunStreamingAsync\u003c/code\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003eInvoke\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOllama (local SLM):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eIChatClient chatClient = new OllamaApiClient(new Uri(&quot;http://localhost:11434/&quot;), &quot;phi3&quot;);\nList&lt;ChatMessage&gt; chatHistory = new();\nchatHistory.Add(new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, userPrompt));\nawait foreach (var u in chatClient.GetStreamingResponseAsync(chatHistory))\n    Console.Write(u.Text);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePackage: \u003ccode\u003eOllamaSharp\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.Extensions.AI\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHTTP (not HTTPS) · port 11434 · no auth · fully local after \u003ccode\u003eollama pull phi3\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCLI: \u003ccode\u003eollama pull phi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eollama list\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eollama run phi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDocker local SLM (OpenAI-compatible):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar openAIClient = new OpenAIClient(\n    new ApiKeyCredential(&quot;unused&quot;),        // local runtimes ignore credential\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(&quot;http://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1&quot;) });\nvar chatClient = openAIClient.GetChatClient(&quot;ai/ministral3:latest&quot;);\n// Either: await chatClient.CompleteChatAsync(prompt)\n// Or:     chatClient.AsAIAgent(name, instructions)\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCredential is \u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e (from \u003ccode\u003eSystem.ClientModel\u003c/code\u003e) — NOT \u003ccode\u003eAzureKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eW02 lab does NOT use \u003ccode\u003eKernelBuilder\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder()\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eImportPluginFromType&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[KernelFunction]\u003c/code\u003e, or \u003ccode\u003eskprompt.txt\u003c/code\u003e — those are SK features but out of the demoed scope\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create(...)\u003c/code\u003e + tool registration — NOT in any lab or demo\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEndpoint URL shapes:\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGitHub: \u003ccode\u003ehttps://models.github.ai/inference\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOllama: \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:11434/\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDocker SLM: \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:12345/engines/llama.cpp/v1\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eModel id formats:\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGitHub: vendor prefix \u003ccode\u003eopenai/gpt-4o-mini\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOllama: bare tag \u003ccode\u003ephi3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDocker SLM: image id \u003ccode\u003eai/ministral3:latest\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"ML.NET (TaxiFarePrediction demo)","body_md":"**Pipeline (end-to-end):**\n\n```cs\nMLContext mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);\n\nIDataView trainingData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\n    trainDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\n\nvar pipeline = mlContext.Transforms\n    .CopyColumns(outputColumnName: \"Label\", inputColumnName: \"FareAmount\")\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"RateCodeEncoded\", \"RateCode\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"PaymentTypeEncoded\", \"PaymentType\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\",\n        \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"RateCodeEncoded\", \"PassengerCount\",\n        \"TripDistance\", \"PaymentTypeEncoded\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);\nmlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, \"Model.zip\");\n```\n\n**Evaluate (separate test file — no TrainTestSplit in demo):**\n\n```cs\nIDataView testData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(testDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\nvar predictions = model.Transform(testData);\nvar metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\", \"Score\");\n// metrics.RSquared, metrics.RootMeanSquaredError\n```\n\n**Predict one row:**\n\n```cs\nvar engine = mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction\u003e(model);\nvar prediction = engine.Predict(sample);\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Predicted fare: {prediction.FareAmount:0.####}\");\n```\n\n**Load:**\n\n```cs\nDataViewSchema schema;\nITransformer loaded = mlContext.Model.Load(\"Model.zip\", out schema);\n```\n\n**Input class:** `[LoadColumn(N)]` is 0-based. E.g. `[LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId;`\n\n**Output class:** `[ColumnName(\"Score\")] public float FareAmount;`\n\n**AutoML CLI:** `mlnet regression --dataset train.csv --label-col 6 --train-time 60 --has-header true`\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- `Fit()` returns **`ITransformer`** — NOT `IDataView`\n- Column names `\"Label\"` and `\"Features\"` are hardcoded — trainers look them up by that exact string\n- `Evaluate` needs the task-matching namespace: `mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(...)` for regression\n- Read `RSquared` (0–1, variance explained, unitless) + `RootMeanSquaredError` (label units — dollars for fare, lower = better)\n\n**Traps**\n\n- `RSquared = 0.89` ≠ \"89% accuracy\" (accuracy is classification; R² is unitless variance-explained)\n- RMSE is in label units, NOT percentage\n- Demo uses only `FastTree` — no LightGbm/Sdca/FastForest shown as dev-code\n- `PredictionEnginePool` NOT demoed — keep to `CreatePredictionEngine\u003cTIn,TOut\u003e`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePipeline (end-to-end):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eMLContext mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);\n\nIDataView trainingData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile&lt;TaxiTrip&gt;(\n    trainDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: &#39;,&#39;);\n\nvar pipeline = mlContext.Transforms\n    .CopyColumns(outputColumnName: &quot;Label&quot;, inputColumnName: &quot;FareAmount&quot;)\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(&quot;VendorIdEncoded&quot;, &quot;VendorId&quot;))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(&quot;RateCodeEncoded&quot;, &quot;RateCode&quot;))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(&quot;PaymentTypeEncoded&quot;, &quot;PaymentType&quot;))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(&quot;Features&quot;,\n        &quot;VendorIdEncoded&quot;, &quot;RateCodeEncoded&quot;, &quot;PassengerCount&quot;,\n        &quot;TripDistance&quot;, &quot;PaymentTypeEncoded&quot;))\n    .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);\nmlContext.Model.Save(model, trainingData.Schema, &quot;Model.zip&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEvaluate (separate test file — no TrainTestSplit in demo):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eIDataView testData = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile&lt;TaxiTrip&gt;(testDataPath, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: &#39;,&#39;);\nvar predictions = model.Transform(testData);\nvar metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, &quot;Label&quot;, &quot;Score&quot;);\n// metrics.RSquared, metrics.RootMeanSquaredError\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePredict one row:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar engine = mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine&lt;TaxiTrip, TaxiTripFarePrediction&gt;(model);\nvar prediction = engine.Predict(sample);\nConsole.WriteLine($&quot;Predicted fare: {prediction.FareAmount:0.####}&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLoad:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eDataViewSchema schema;\nITransformer loaded = mlContext.Model.Load(&quot;Model.zip&quot;, out schema);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInput class:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(N)]\u003c/code\u003e is 0-based. E.g. \u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOutput class:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Score&quot;)] public float FareAmount;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAutoML CLI:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003emlnet regression --dataset train.csv --label-col 6 --train-time 60 --has-header true\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eFit()\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — NOT \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eColumn names \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e are hardcoded — trainers look them up by that exact string\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eEvaluate\u003c/code\u003e needs the task-matching namespace: \u003ccode\u003emlContext.Regression.Evaluate(...)\u003c/code\u003e for regression\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRead \u003ccode\u003eRSquared\u003c/code\u003e (0–1, variance explained, unitless) + \u003ccode\u003eRootMeanSquaredError\u003c/code\u003e (label units — dollars for fare, lower = better)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eRSquared = 0.89\u003c/code\u003e ≠ &quot;89% accuracy&quot; (accuracy is classification; R² is unitless variance-explained)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRMSE is in label units, NOT percentage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDemo uses only \u003ccode\u003eFastTree\u003c/code\u003e — no LightGbm/Sdca/FastForest shown as dev-code\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePredictionEnginePool\u003c/code\u003e NOT demoed — keep to \u003ccode\u003eCreatePredictionEngine&lt;TIn,TOut&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Cache + Redis","body_md":"**IMemoryCache (DataCacheDemo):**\n\n```cs\n// Register\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();\n\n// Use (cache-aside)\nif (!_memoryCache.TryGetValue(cacheKey, out Product[]? productList))\n{\n    productList = await FetchAsync();\n    var cacheExpiryOptions = new MemoryCacheEntryOptions\n    {\n        AbsoluteExpiration  = DateTime.Now.AddSeconds(50),\n        Priority            = CacheItemPriority.High,\n        SlidingExpiration   = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(20)\n    };\n    _memoryCache.Set(cacheKey, productList, cacheExpiryOptions);\n}\n```\n\n**IDistributedCache + Redis (WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final):**\n\n```cs\n// Register\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =\u003e\n{\n    options.Configuration = \"localhost\";\n    options.ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions\n    {\n        AbortOnConnectFail = true,\n        EndPoints = { options.Configuration }\n    };\n});\n\n// Consume via GetOrSetAsync extension\nvar cacheOptions = new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n    .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(20))\n    .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2));\n\nvar games = await cache.GetOrSetAsync(\n    $\"games:country:{country}\",\n    async () =\u003e await context.Games.Where(g =\u003e g.Country == country).ToListAsync(),\n    cacheOptions);\n\n// Invalidate on write\ncache.Remove(\"games\");\n```\n\n**`GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e` extension (DistributedCacheExtensions.cs):**\n\n```cs\npublic static async Task\u003cT?\u003e GetOrSetAsync\u003cT\u003e(this IDistributedCache cache, string key,\n    Func\u003cTask\u003cT\u003e\u003e task, DistributedCacheEntryOptions? options = null)\n{\n    options ??= new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n        .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30))\n        .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1));\n\n    if (cache.TryGetValue(key, out T? value) && value is not null)\n        return value;\n\n    value = await task();\n    if (value is not null)\n        await cache.SetAsync\u003cT\u003e(key, value, options);\n    return value;\n}\n```\n\nSerializes to JSON bytes internally. `TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e` returns bool, writes via `out`.\n\n**Docker Redis:** `docker run --name redis -d -p 6379:6379 redis`\n**Redis CLI:** `SETEX key 10 \"val\"` (seconds) · `GET key` · `TTL key` · `KEYS pattern:*`\n\n**Cache Tag Helper:**\n\n```cs\n\u003ccache vary-by-user=\"true\" vary-by-route=\"id\" expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\u003e\n    @await Html.PartialAsync(\"_ProductDetail\", Model)\n\u003c/cache\u003e\n```\n\n`vary-by-*`: `user`, `route`, `query`, `cookie`, `header`, custom `vary-by=\"@Model.Key\"`.\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- Registration call + injected interface:\n  - `AddMemoryCache()` → `IMemoryCache`\n  - `AddStackExchangeRedisCache(...)` → `IDistributedCache`\n- `IMemoryCache` is per-process; `IDistributedCache` is shared via Redis\n- `AbsoluteExpiration` = hard deadline. `SlidingExpiration` = idle timeout (resets on access). Entry dies at whichever fires first.\n- `Priority` is eviction-order under memory pressure, NOT TTL\n- `AbortOnConnectFail = true` → fail fast when Redis unreachable (default is `false` → swallow writes silently)\n- Invalidate with `cache.Remove(key)` from every write path\n\n**Traps**\n\n- `IMemoryCache` variant: `AbsoluteExpiration = DateTime.Now + TimeSpan` (object initializer)\n- `IDistributedCache` variant: fluent `.SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan).SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan)`\n- Lab uses `TryGetValue(out T? v)` + `Set(...)` for memory, NOT `GetOrCreateAsync`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIMemoryCache (DataCacheDemo):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// Register\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();\n\n// Use (cache-aside)\nif (!_memoryCache.TryGetValue(cacheKey, out Product[]? productList))\n{\n    productList = await FetchAsync();\n    var cacheExpiryOptions = new MemoryCacheEntryOptions\n    {\n        AbsoluteExpiration  = DateTime.Now.AddSeconds(50),\n        Priority            = CacheItemPriority.High,\n        SlidingExpiration   = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(20)\n    };\n    _memoryCache.Set(cacheKey, productList, cacheExpiryOptions);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIDistributedCache + Redis (WebApiFIFA_REDIS_Final):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// Register\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =&gt;\n{\n    options.Configuration = &quot;localhost&quot;;\n    options.ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions\n    {\n        AbortOnConnectFail = true,\n        EndPoints = { options.Configuration }\n    };\n});\n\n// Consume via GetOrSetAsync extension\nvar cacheOptions = new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n    .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(20))\n    .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2));\n\nvar games = await cache.GetOrSetAsync(\n    $&quot;games:country:{country}&quot;,\n    async () =&gt; await context.Games.Where(g =&gt; g.Country == country).ToListAsync(),\n    cacheOptions);\n\n// Invalidate on write\ncache.Remove(&quot;games&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGetOrSetAsync&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e extension (DistributedCacheExtensions.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003epublic static async Task&lt;T?&gt; GetOrSetAsync&lt;T&gt;(this IDistributedCache cache, string key,\n    Func&lt;Task&lt;T&gt;&gt; task, DistributedCacheEntryOptions? options = null)\n{\n    options ??= new DistributedCacheEntryOptions()\n        .SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30))\n        .SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan.FromHours(1));\n\n    if (cache.TryGetValue(key, out T? value) &amp;&amp; value is not null)\n        return value;\n\n    value = await task();\n    if (value is not null)\n        await cache.SetAsync&lt;T&gt;(key, value, options);\n    return value;\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSerializes to JSON bytes internally. \u003ccode\u003eTryGetValue&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e returns bool, writes via \u003ccode\u003eout\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDocker Redis:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003edocker run --name redis -d -p 6379:6379 redis\u003c/code\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eRedis CLI:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eSETEX key 10 &quot;val&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (seconds) · \u003ccode\u003eGET key\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eTTL key\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eKEYS pattern:*\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCache Tag Helper:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e&lt;cache vary-by-user=&quot;true&quot; vary-by-route=&quot;id&quot; expires-after=&quot;@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)&quot;&gt;\n    @await Html.PartialAsync(&quot;_ProductDetail&quot;, Model)\n&lt;/cache&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003evary-by-*\u003c/code\u003e: \u003ccode\u003euser\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eroute\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003equery\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003ecookie\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eheader\u003c/code\u003e, custom \u003ccode\u003evary-by=&quot;@Model.Key&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRegistration call + injected interface:\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddMemoryCache()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddStackExchangeRedisCache(...)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e is per-process; \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e is shared via Redis\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAbsoluteExpiration\u003c/code\u003e = hard deadline. \u003ccode\u003eSlidingExpiration\u003c/code\u003e = idle timeout (resets on access). Entry dies at whichever fires first.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePriority\u003c/code\u003e is eviction-order under memory pressure, NOT TTL\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAbortOnConnectFail = true\u003c/code\u003e → fail fast when Redis unreachable (default is \u003ccode\u003efalse\u003c/code\u003e → swallow writes silently)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInvalidate with \u003ccode\u003ecache.Remove(key)\u003c/code\u003e from every write path\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e variant: \u003ccode\u003eAbsoluteExpiration = DateTime.Now + TimeSpan\u003c/code\u003e (object initializer)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e variant: fluent \u003ccode\u003e.SetAbsoluteExpiration(TimeSpan).SetSlidingExpiration(TimeSpan)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLab uses \u003ccode\u003eTryGetValue(out T? v)\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eSet(...)\u003c/code\u003e for memory, NOT \u003ccode\u003eGetOrCreateAsync\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"File-based apps (.NET 10)","body_md":"**Run:** `dotnet run file.cs` · `dotnet run file.cs -- arg1 arg2` (`--` separator required)\n**Cache:** `~/.dotnet/runfile/`\n\n**Directives (NO space after `#:`):**\n\n```cs\n#!/usr/bin/env dotnet\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\n#:property TargetFramework=net10.0\n#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj\n\n// top-level code here\n```\n\n| Directive | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `#:package Name@Ver` | NuGet dependency |\n| `#:property Key=Val` | MSBuild property (TargetFramework, Nullable, LangVersion) |\n| `#:sdk SdkName` | SDK selection (`Microsoft.NET.Sdk` default, `.Web` for minimal API) |\n| `#:project ./path.csproj` | Reference a local project |\n\n**Implicit usings:** `System`, `System.Linq`, `System.Collections.Generic`, `System.Text`, `System.Threading.Tasks`\n\n**Convert to project:** `dotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder`\n\n**Minimal web API (FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs):**\n\n```cs\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenApi();\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGet(\"/\", () =\u003e new { Message = \"Hello!\" });\napp.Run();\n```\n\n**Traps**\n\n- `#: package ...` (space after colon) → parse error\n- Without `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`, `WebApplication.CreateBuilder` does not resolve\n- CLI args: `dotnet run file.cs Kevin` passes `Kevin` to `dotnet`, not script — use `--`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRun:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs -- arg1 arg2\u003c/code\u003e (\u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e separator required)\n\u003cstrong\u003eCache:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e~/.dotnet/runfile/\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirectives (NO space after \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e#!/usr/bin/env dotnet\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\n#:property TargetFramework=net10.0\n#:project ./MyLibrary/MyLibrary.csproj\n\n// top-level code here\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eDirective\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:package Name@Ver\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNuGet dependency\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:property Key=Val\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMSBuild property (TargetFramework, Nullable, LangVersion)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:sdk SdkName\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSDK selection (\u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk\u003c/code\u003e default, \u003ccode\u003e.Web\u003c/code\u003e for minimal API)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:project ./path.csproj\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eReference a local project\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImplicit usings:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eSystem\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Linq\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Collections.Generic\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Text\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eSystem.Threading.Tasks\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConvert to project:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003edotnet project convert file.cs -o Folder\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMinimal web API (FileBasedWebApi/WebApi.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:package Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi@10.0.0\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nbuilder.Services.AddOpenApi();\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGet(&quot;/&quot;, () =&gt; new { Message = &quot;Hello!&quot; });\napp.Run();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#: package ...\u003c/code\u003e (space after colon) → parse error\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWithout \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eWebApplication.CreateBuilder\u003c/code\u003e does not resolve\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCLI args: \u003ccode\u003edotnet run file.cs Kevin\u003c/code\u003e passes \u003ccode\u003eKevin\u003c/code\u003e to \u003ccode\u003edotnet\u003c/code\u003e, not script — use \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"gRPC (W09 lab)","body_md":"**`.proto` (proto3):**\n\n```proto\nsyntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"GrpcStudentsServer\";\npackage greet;\n\nservice StudentRemote {\n  rpc GetStudentInfo (StudentLookupModel) returns (StudentModel);\n  rpc RetrieveAllStudents (Empty) returns (StudentList);\n}\n\nmessage Empty {}\nmessage StudentLookupModel { int32 studentId = 1; }\nmessage StudentModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n  string firstName = 2;\n  string lastName = 3;\n  string school = 4;\n}\nmessage StudentList { repeated StudentModel items = 1; }\n```\n\n**`.csproj`:** `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos\\students.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server|Client|Both\" /\u003e`\n\n**Server (StudentsService.cs):**\n\n```cs\npublic class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\n{\n    private readonly SchoolDbContext _context;\n    public StudentsService(ILogger\u003cStudentsService\u003e logger, SchoolDbContext ctx) =\u003e _context = ctx;\n\n    public override Task\u003cStudentModel\u003e GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request, ServerCallContext ctx)\n    {\n        var s = _context.Students!.Find(request.StudentId);\n        return Task.FromResult(s is null ? new StudentModel() : new StudentModel {\n            StudentId = s.StudentId, FirstName = s.FirstName, LastName = s.LastName, School = s.School\n        });\n    }\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cStudentsService\u003e();\n```\n\n**Client (BlazorGrpcClient/Program.cs — Aspire):**\n\n```cs\nbuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cStudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient\u003e(options =\u003e\n{\n    options.Address = new Uri(\"http://backend\");      // Aspire logical name\n});\n\n// In .razor:\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpc\n\nvar reply = await _grpc.GetStudentInfoAsync(new StudentLookupModel { StudentId = 3 });\n```\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- Field tags 1–15 encode in 1 byte, 16+ take 2\n- Tags are permanent — `reserved 2;` after deletion (never reuse)\n- Unset proto3 scalars are zero-values (`0`, `\"\"`, `false`), NOT null\n- Every server override takes `(Request, ServerCallContext)` and returns `Task\u003cResponse\u003e`\n- Inherit from `ServiceName.ServiceNameBase` (generated)\n- Register with `AddGrpc()` + `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()`\n- Streaming override: `Task` return + `IServerStreamWriter\u003cT\u003e` as 2nd param (drop request payload)\n- `GrpcServices=\"Server\"` vs `\"Client\"` matters — client project uses `Client`\n\n**Traps**\n\n- gRPC requires HTTP/2 — wrong Kestrel config → cryptic connection error\n- Missing `override` keyword → method silently shadows; client gets `UNIMPLEMENTED`\n- `\"Both\"` only for projects that host both sides (rare)","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e (proto3):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-proto\"\u003esyntax = &quot;proto3&quot;;\noption csharp_namespace = &quot;GrpcStudentsServer&quot;;\npackage greet;\n\nservice StudentRemote {\n  rpc GetStudentInfo (StudentLookupModel) returns (StudentModel);\n  rpc RetrieveAllStudents (Empty) returns (StudentList);\n}\n\nmessage Empty {}\nmessage StudentLookupModel { int32 studentId = 1; }\nmessage StudentModel {\n  int32 studentId = 1;\n  string firstName = 2;\n  string lastName = 3;\n  string school = 4;\n}\nmessage StudentList { repeated StudentModel items = 1; }\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.csproj\u003c/code\u003e:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Protobuf Include=&quot;Protos\\students.proto&quot; GrpcServices=&quot;Server|Client|Both&quot; /&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eServer (StudentsService.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003epublic class StudentsService : StudentRemote.StudentRemoteBase\n{\n    private readonly SchoolDbContext _context;\n    public StudentsService(ILogger&lt;StudentsService&gt; logger, SchoolDbContext ctx) =&gt; _context = ctx;\n\n    public override Task&lt;StudentModel&gt; GetStudentInfo(StudentLookupModel request, ServerCallContext ctx)\n    {\n        var s = _context.Students!.Find(request.StudentId);\n        return Task.FromResult(s is null ? new StudentModel() : new StudentModel {\n            StudentId = s.StudentId, FirstName = s.FirstName, LastName = s.LastName, School = s.School\n        });\n    }\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService&lt;StudentsService&gt;();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eClient (BlazorGrpcClient/Program.cs — Aspire):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003ebuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpcClient&lt;StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient&gt;(options =&gt;\n{\n    options.Address = new Uri(&quot;http://backend&quot;);      // Aspire logical name\n});\n\n// In .razor:\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject StudentRemote.StudentRemoteClient _grpc\n\nvar reply = await _grpc.GetStudentInfoAsync(new StudentLookupModel { StudentId = 3 });\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eField tags 1–15 encode in 1 byte, 16+ take 2\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTags are permanent — \u003ccode\u003ereserved 2;\u003c/code\u003e after deletion (never reuse)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUnset proto3 scalars are zero-values (\u003ccode\u003e0\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e&quot;&quot;\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003efalse\u003c/code\u003e), NOT null\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEvery server override takes \u003ccode\u003e(Request, ServerCallContext)\u003c/code\u003e and returns \u003ccode\u003eTask&lt;Response&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInherit from \u003ccode\u003eServiceName.ServiceNameBase\u003c/code\u003e (generated)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRegister with \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpc()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMapGrpcService&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStreaming override: \u003ccode\u003eTask\u003c/code\u003e return + \u003ccode\u003eIServerStreamWriter&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e as 2nd param (drop request payload)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eGrpcServices=&quot;Server&quot;\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Client&quot;\u003c/code\u003e matters — client project uses \u003ccode\u003eClient\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003egRPC requires HTTP/2 — wrong Kestrel config → cryptic connection error\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMissing \u003ccode\u003eoverride\u003c/code\u003e keyword → method silently shadows; client gets \u003ccode\u003eUNIMPLEMENTED\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&quot;Both&quot;\u003c/code\u003e only for projects that host both sides (rare)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":".NET Aspire (SoccerFIFA_Aspire demo)","body_md":"**AppHost:**\n\n```cs\nvar builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar sqlServerDb = builder.AddSqlServer(\"theserver\").AddDatabase(\"sqldata\");\n\nvar api = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.WebApiFIFA\u003e(\"backend\")\n    .WithReference(sqlServerDb)\n    .WaitFor(sqlServerDb)\n    .WithEnvironment(\"ParentCompany\", builder.Configuration[\"Company\"]);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.BlazorFIFA\u003e(\"frontend\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();\n```\n\n**Service (WebApiFIFA/Program.cs):**\n\n```cs\nbuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e(\"sqldata\");\n// ...\napp.MapDefaultEndpoints();\n```\n\n**ServiceDefaults installs:** service discovery · OpenTelemetry · `/health` (readiness, all checks) + `/alive` (liveness, \"live\"-tagged only) · HttpClient resilience\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- `AddProject\u003cProjects.X\u003e(\"logical-name\")` → consumers reach as `http://logical-name/`\n- `WithReference(resource)` injects connection string as env-var (`ConnectionStrings__sqldata`)\n- `WaitFor(resource)` delays startup until healthy\n- `AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cT\u003e(\"db-name\")` reads injected connection string\n- `WithEnvironment(key, value)` for arbitrary env-vars\n- AppHost needs `dotnet add reference` to every service project (for `Projects.X` namespace)\n\n**Traps**\n\n- `AddServiceDefaults()` + `MapDefaultEndpoints()` go in EACH service, NEVER in AppHost\n- `AddDatabase` only chains off `AddSqlServer` — NOT on top-level builder\n- Dashboard on `http://localhost:15888` (or similar)","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAppHost:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar sqlServerDb = builder.AddSqlServer(&quot;theserver&quot;).AddDatabase(&quot;sqldata&quot;);\n\nvar api = builder.AddProject&lt;Projects.WebApiFIFA&gt;(&quot;backend&quot;)\n    .WithReference(sqlServerDb)\n    .WaitFor(sqlServerDb)\n    .WithEnvironment(&quot;ParentCompany&quot;, builder.Configuration[&quot;Company&quot;]);\n\nbuilder.AddProject&lt;Projects.BlazorFIFA&gt;(&quot;frontend&quot;)\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eService (WebApiFIFA/Program.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003ebuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\nbuilder.AddSqlServerDbContext&lt;ApplicationDbContext&gt;(&quot;sqldata&quot;);\n// ...\napp.MapDefaultEndpoints();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eServiceDefaults installs:\u003c/strong\u003e service discovery · OpenTelemetry · \u003ccode\u003e/health\u003c/code\u003e (readiness, all checks) + \u003ccode\u003e/alive\u003c/code\u003e (liveness, &quot;live&quot;-tagged only) · HttpClient resilience\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.X&gt;(&quot;logical-name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e → consumers reach as \u003ccode\u003ehttp://logical-name/\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eWithReference(resource)\u003c/code\u003e injects connection string as env-var (\u003ccode\u003eConnectionStrings__sqldata\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eWaitFor(resource)\u003c/code\u003e delays startup until healthy\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServerDbContext&lt;T&gt;(&quot;db-name&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e reads injected connection string\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eWithEnvironment(key, value)\u003c/code\u003e for arbitrary env-vars\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAppHost needs \u003ccode\u003edotnet add reference\u003c/code\u003e to every service project (for \u003ccode\u003eProjects.X\u003c/code\u003e namespace)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraps\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMapDefaultEndpoints()\u003c/code\u003e go in EACH service, NEVER in AppHost\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddDatabase\u003c/code\u003e only chains off \u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServer\u003c/code\u003e — NOT on top-level builder\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDashboard on \u003ccode\u003ehttp://localhost:15888\u003c/code\u003e (or similar)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Localization (W10 Sports lab)","body_md":"**Program.cs:**\n\n```cs\nbuilder.Services.AddLocalization(options =\u003e options.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(options =\u003e\n{\n    var supportedCultures = new[] {\n        new CultureInfo(\"en\"), new CultureInfo(\"de\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"fr\"), new CultureInfo(\"zh\"),\n        new CultureInfo(\"en-US\")\n    };\n    options.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n    options.SupportedCultures   = supportedCultures;\n    options.SupportedUICultures = supportedCultures;\n});\n\nbuilder.Services.AddMvc()\n    .AddViewLocalization()\n    .AddDataAnnotationsLocalization(options =\u003e\n    {\n        options.DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (type, factory) =\u003e\n            factory.Create(typeof(SharedResource));\n    });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddSingleton\u003cSharedResourceService\u003e();\n\n// Middleware — lab uses explicit options via scope\nusing (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())\n{\n    var localizationOptions = scope.ServiceProvider\n        .GetRequiredService\u003cIOptions\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e\u003e().Value;\n    app.UseRequestLocalization(localizationOptions);\n}\n```\n\n**SharedResource marker + service:**\n\n```cs\n// SharedResource.cs\nnamespace Sports;\npublic class SharedResource { }\n\n// SharedResourceService.cs\npublic class SharedResourceService\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer localizer;\n    public SharedResourceService(IStringLocalizerFactory factory)\n    {\n        var asm = new AssemblyName(typeof(SharedResource).GetTypeInfo().Assembly.FullName!);\n        localizer = factory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), asm.Name!);\n    }\n    public string Get(string key) =\u003e localizer[key];\n}\n```\n\n**Resource file paths:** `Resources/\u003cfolder\u003e/\u003cClassName\u003e.\u003cculture\u003e.resx`\n- `Pages/Index.cshtml.cs` (class `IndexModel`) → `Resources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx`\n- Shared (marker class): `Resources/SharedResource.fr.resx`\n\n**Inject:**\n\n- Code-behind text: `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` — `localizer[\"Key\"]`\n- Code-behind HTML: `IHtmlLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` (no XSS encoding)\n- Razor view: `@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer` — `@Localizer[\"Key\"]`\n\n**Culture providers (default order, first match wins):** QueryString (`?culture=fr`) → Cookie (`.AspNetCore.Culture`) → Accept-Language header\n\n**Switch cookie:**\n\n```cs\nResponse.Cookies.Append(\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName,\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(culture)),\n    new CookieOptions { Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddYears(1) });\n```\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- `CurrentCulture` = formatting (dates/numbers) · `CurrentUICulture` = which .resx loads — SET BOTH via `SupportedCultures` + `SupportedUICultures`\n- `UseRequestLocalization()` middleware is REQUIRED — without it, everything silently defaults\n- `DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (type, factory) =\u003e factory.Create(typeof(SharedResource))` routes all validation messages through the shared `.resx`\n- Positional args: `localizer[\"Greet\", name]` → `.resx` value `\"Hello, {0}!\"`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProgram.cs:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003ebuilder.Services.AddLocalization(options =&gt; options.ResourcesPath = &quot;Resources&quot;);\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;(options =&gt;\n{\n    var supportedCultures = new[] {\n        new CultureInfo(&quot;en&quot;), new CultureInfo(&quot;de&quot;),\n        new CultureInfo(&quot;fr&quot;), new CultureInfo(&quot;zh&quot;),\n        new CultureInfo(&quot;en-US&quot;)\n    };\n    options.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(&quot;en&quot;);\n    options.SupportedCultures   = supportedCultures;\n    options.SupportedUICultures = supportedCultures;\n});\n\nbuilder.Services.AddMvc()\n    .AddViewLocalization()\n    .AddDataAnnotationsLocalization(options =&gt;\n    {\n        options.DataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (type, factory) =&gt;\n            factory.Create(typeof(SharedResource));\n    });\n\nbuilder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;SharedResourceService&gt;();\n\n// Middleware — lab uses explicit options via scope\nusing (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())\n{\n    var localizationOptions = scope.ServiceProvider\n        .GetRequiredService&lt;IOptions&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;&gt;().Value;\n    app.UseRequestLocalization(localizationOptions);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSharedResource marker + service:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// SharedResource.cs\nnamespace Sports;\npublic class SharedResource { }\n\n// SharedResourceService.cs\npublic class SharedResourceService\n{\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer localizer;\n    public SharedResourceService(IStringLocalizerFactory factory)\n    {\n        var asm = new AssemblyName(typeof(SharedResource).GetTypeInfo().Assembly.FullName!);\n        localizer = factory.Create(nameof(SharedResource), asm.Name!);\n    }\n    public string Get(string key) =&gt; localizer[key];\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eResource file paths:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eResources/&lt;folder&gt;/&lt;ClassName&gt;.&lt;culture&gt;.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePages/Index.cshtml.cs\u003c/code\u003e (class \u003ccode\u003eIndexModel\u003c/code\u003e) → \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages/IndexModel.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eShared (marker class): \u003ccode\u003eResources/SharedResource.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInject:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCode-behind text: \u003ccode\u003eIStringLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003elocalizer[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCode-behind HTML: \u003ccode\u003eIHtmlLocalizer&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (no XSS encoding)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRazor view: \u003ccode\u003e@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003e@Localizer[&quot;Key&quot;]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCulture providers (default order, first match wins):\u003c/strong\u003e QueryString (\u003ccode\u003e?culture=fr\u003c/code\u003e) → Cookie (\u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e) → Accept-Language header\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSwitch cookie:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eResponse.Cookies.Append(\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName,\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(culture)),\n    new CookieOptions { Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddYears(1) });\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e = formatting (dates/numbers) · \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e = which .resx loads — SET BOTH via \u003ccode\u003eSupportedCultures\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eSupportedUICultures\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e middleware is REQUIRED — without it, everything silently defaults\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eDataAnnotationLocalizerProvider = (type, factory) =&gt; factory.Create(typeof(SharedResource))\u003c/code\u003e routes all validation messages through the shared \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePositional args: \u003ccode\u003elocalizer[&quot;Greet&quot;, name]\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e value \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Hello, {0}!&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Tag Helpers (ToonTagDemo)","body_md":"**Custom helper:**\n\n```cs\nusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers;\n\n[HtmlTargetElement(\"toon\")]\n[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = \"toonie\")]    // stacked — two bindings\npublic class ToonTag : TagHelper\n{\n    public string? FontFamily { get; set; }      // kebab-case: font-family\n    public string? FontSize { get; set; }\n    public string? ForegroundColor { get; set; }\n\n    public async override Task ProcessAsync(TagHelperContext context, TagHelperOutput output)\n    {\n        var toons = await GetToonsAsync();\n\n        string customStyle =\n            $\"font-family: {FontFamily};font-size: {FontSize};color: {ForegroundColor};\";\n        output.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"style\", customStyle);\n\n        string html = \"\u003ctable\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth\u003eName\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth\u003ePicture\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\";\n        foreach (var t in toons)\n            html += $\"\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e{t.FirstName} {t.LastName}\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cimg src='{t.PictureUrl}'/\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\";\n        html += \"\u003c/table\u003e\";\n        output.Content.SetHtmlContent(html);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:** `\u003ctoon font-family=\"arial\" font-size=\"larger\" foreground-color=\"purple\"\u003e\u003c/toon\u003e`\n\n**Registration (`_ViewImports.cshtml`):**\n\n```cs\n@using ToonTagDemo\n@namespace ToonTagDemo.Pages\n@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n@addTagHelper \"ToonTagDemo.TagHelpers.ToonTag, ToonTagDemo\"\n```\n\n- Form 1 (wildcard): `@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName`\n- Form 2 (specific type): `@addTagHelper \"FullTypeName, AssemblyName\"`\n- Built-ins: `@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers`\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- Inherit `TagHelper`; decorate with one or more `[HtmlTargetElement]`; override `ProcessAsync` (async) or `Process` (sync)\n- PascalCase property (`FontFamily`) ↔ kebab-case HTML attribute (`font-family`)\n- `output.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"key\", \"val\")` + `output.Content.SetHtmlContent(html)` = the two primary outputs in the demo\n- Without `_ViewImports.cshtml` registration, Razor emits `\u003ctoon\u003e` as literal unknown HTML","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCustom helper:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers;\n\n[HtmlTargetElement(&quot;toon&quot;)]\n[HtmlTargetElement(Attributes = &quot;toonie&quot;)]    // stacked — two bindings\npublic class ToonTag : TagHelper\n{\n    public string? FontFamily { get; set; }      // kebab-case: font-family\n    public string? FontSize { get; set; }\n    public string? ForegroundColor { get; set; }\n\n    public async override Task ProcessAsync(TagHelperContext context, TagHelperOutput output)\n    {\n        var toons = await GetToonsAsync();\n\n        string customStyle =\n            $&quot;font-family: {FontFamily};font-size: {FontSize};color: {ForegroundColor};&quot;;\n        output.Attributes.SetAttribute(&quot;style&quot;, customStyle);\n\n        string html = &quot;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Picture&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&quot;;\n        foreach (var t in toons)\n            html += $&quot;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;{t.FirstName} {t.LastName}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=&#39;{t.PictureUrl}&#39;/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&quot;;\n        html += &quot;&lt;/table&gt;&quot;;\n        output.Content.SetHtmlContent(html);\n    }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsage:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e&lt;toon font-family=&quot;arial&quot; font-size=&quot;larger&quot; foreground-color=&quot;purple&quot;&gt;&lt;/toon&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRegistration (\u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e@using ToonTagDemo\n@namespace ToonTagDemo.Pages\n@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n@addTagHelper &quot;ToonTagDemo.TagHelpers.ToonTag, ToonTagDemo&quot;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eForm 1 (wildcard): \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper *, AssemblyName\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eForm 2 (specific type): \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper &quot;FullTypeName, AssemblyName&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuilt-ins: \u003ccode\u003e@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInherit \u003ccode\u003eTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e; decorate with one or more \u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement]\u003c/code\u003e; override \u003ccode\u003eProcessAsync\u003c/code\u003e (async) or \u003ccode\u003eProcess\u003c/code\u003e (sync)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePascalCase property (\u003ccode\u003eFontFamily\u003c/code\u003e) ↔ kebab-case HTML attribute (\u003ccode\u003efont-family\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eoutput.Attributes.SetAttribute(&quot;key&quot;, &quot;val&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eoutput.Content.SetHtmlContent(html)\u003c/code\u003e = the two primary outputs in the demo\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWithout \u003ccode\u003e_ViewImports.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e registration, Razor emits \u003ccode\u003e&lt;toon&gt;\u003c/code\u003e as literal unknown HTML\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Blazor QuickGrid (W07 lab)","body_md":"**Server lab shape:**\n\n```cs\n@page \"/students\"\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject IDbContextFactory\u003cApplicationDbContext\u003e DbFactory\n@implements IAsyncDisposable\n\n\u003cinput type=\"search\" @bind=\"FilterValue\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" placeholder=\"Search...\" /\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Class=\"table\" Items=\"@FilteredStudents\" Pagination=\"@pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.FirstName\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"student =\u003e student.LastName\"  Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\n    \u003cTemplateColumn Context=\"student\"\u003e\n        \u003ca href=\"@($\"students/edit?studentid={student.StudentId}\")\"\u003eEdit\u003c/a\u003e |\n        \u003ca href=\"@($\"students/details?studentid={student.StudentId}\")\"\u003eDetails\u003c/a\u003e\n    \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    private ApplicationDbContext context = default!;\n    private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n    private string FilterValue = string.Empty;\n\n    IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e? FilteredStudents {\n        get {\n            var students = context.Students.AsQueryable();\n            if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(FilterValue))\n                students = students.Where(s =\u003e s.FirstName!.ToLower().Contains(FilterValue.ToLower()));\n            return students;\n        }\n    }\n\n    protected override void OnInitialized() =\u003e context = DbFactory.CreateDbContext();\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() =\u003e await context.DisposeAsync();\n}\n```\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- `@rendermode InteractiveServer` (or WebAssembly/Auto) required for sort/page/filter to work\n- `\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"IQueryable\u003cT\u003e\" Pagination=\"@state\"\u003e`\n- `\u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"x =\u003e x.Field\" Sortable=\"true\"\u003e` auto-sorts\n- `\u003cTemplateColumn Context=\"x\"\u003e` for custom markup with row access via `x`\n- `\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\"\u003e` (Server lab) vs `\u003cPaginator Value=\"@pages\"\u003e` (WASM BlazorSchool demo) — both valid\n- `PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }`\n- Live filter: `@bind=\"...\" @bind:event=\"oninput\"` (not default `onchange`) + computed `IQueryable` property\n- WASM variant adds `\u003cColumnOptions\u003e` with per-column search inputs and `ResizableColumns=\"true\"`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eServer lab shape:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e@page &quot;/students&quot;\n@rendermode InteractiveServer\n@inject IDbContextFactory&lt;ApplicationDbContext&gt; DbFactory\n@implements IAsyncDisposable\n\n&lt;input type=&quot;search&quot; @bind=&quot;FilterValue&quot; @bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot; placeholder=&quot;Search...&quot; /&gt;\n\n&lt;QuickGrid Class=&quot;table&quot; Items=&quot;@FilteredStudents&quot; Pagination=&quot;@pagination&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;PropertyColumn Property=&quot;student =&gt; student.FirstName&quot; Sortable=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;\n    &lt;PropertyColumn Property=&quot;student =&gt; student.LastName&quot;  Sortable=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;\n\n    &lt;TemplateColumn Context=&quot;student&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;a href=&quot;@($&quot;students/edit?studentid={student.StudentId}&quot;)&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt; |\n        &lt;a href=&quot;@($&quot;students/details?studentid={student.StudentId}&quot;)&quot;&gt;Details&lt;/a&gt;\n    &lt;/TemplateColumn&gt;\n&lt;/QuickGrid&gt;\n\n&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@pagination&quot; /&gt;\n\n@code {\n    private ApplicationDbContext context = default!;\n    private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 15 };\n    private string FilterValue = string.Empty;\n\n    IQueryable&lt;Student&gt;? FilteredStudents {\n        get {\n            var students = context.Students.AsQueryable();\n            if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(FilterValue))\n                students = students.Where(s =&gt; s.FirstName!.ToLower().Contains(FilterValue.ToLower()));\n            return students;\n        }\n    }\n\n    protected override void OnInitialized() =&gt; context = DbFactory.CreateDbContext();\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() =&gt; await context.DisposeAsync();\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e (or WebAssembly/Auto) required for sort/page/filter to work\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;QuickGrid Items=&quot;IQueryable&lt;T&gt;&quot; Pagination=&quot;@state&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;PropertyColumn Property=&quot;x =&gt; x.Field&quot; Sortable=&quot;true&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e auto-sorts\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;TemplateColumn Context=&quot;x&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e for custom markup with row access via \u003ccode\u003ex\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@pagination&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (Server lab) vs \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator Value=&quot;@pages&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (WASM BlazorSchool demo) — both valid\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLive filter: \u003ccode\u003e@bind=&quot;...&quot; @bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;\u003c/code\u003e (not default \u003ccode\u003eonchange\u003c/code\u003e) + computed \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable\u003c/code\u003e property\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWASM variant adds \u003ccode\u003e&lt;ColumnOptions&gt;\u003c/code\u003e with per-column search inputs and \u003ccode\u003eResizableColumns=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Excel / PDF / Chart (W13 FifaWorldCup)","body_md":"**Excel (ClosedXML) — Pages/Excel.cshtml.cs:**\n\n```cs\nusing ClosedXML.Excel;\n\npublic FileResult OnGet()\n{\n    var data = Game.GetGames();\n\n    using (var workbook = new XLWorkbook())\n    {\n        IXLWorksheet worksheet = workbook.Worksheets.Add(\"Games\");\n        worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Game Id\";         // 1-BASED\n        worksheet.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Year\";\n        // ... header row ...\n\n        IXLRange range = worksheet.Range(worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Address, worksheet.Cell(1, 7).Address);\n        range.Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.Almond);\n\n        int index = 1;\n        foreach (var item in data)\n        {\n            index++;\n            worksheet.Cell(index, 1).Value = item.GameId;\n            // ... fill columns ...\n        }\n\n        using (var stream = new MemoryStream())\n        {\n            workbook.SaveAs(stream);\n            var content = stream.ToArray();\n            return File(content,\n                \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\n                $\"FifaWorldCup_{DateTime.Now:yyyyMMdd}.xlsx\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**PDF (iText 7 — needs `itext7` + `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter`):**\n\n```cs\nusing iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\nusing iText.Kernel.Geom;\n\nvar ms = new MemoryStream();\nvar writer = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdfDoc = new PdfDocument(writer);\nvar document = new Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false);\nwriter.SetCloseStream(false);\n\ndocument.Add(new Paragraph(\"Report Title\")\n    .SetTextAlignment(iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.CENTER)\n    .SetFontSize(20));\n\nvar table = new Table(3);\n// ... AddCell(...) in row-major order ...\ndocument.Add(table);\n\n// Page numbers after layout\nint total = pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages();\nfor (int i = 1; i \u003c= total; i++) {\n    document.ShowTextAligned(new Paragraph($\"Page {i} of {total}\"),\n        559, 806, i,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.RIGHT,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.VerticalAlignment.TOP, 0);\n}\n\ndocument.Close();\nms.Position = 0;          // CRITICAL before FileStreamResult\n\nreturn new FileStreamResult(ms, \"application/pdf\") {\n    FileDownloadName = $\"Report_{DateTime.Now:yyyyMMdd}.pdf\"\n};\n```\n\n**Chart.js (client-side only):**\n\n```cs\n\u003ccanvas id=\"pie-chart\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\n    const Counts = [];\n    const Continents = [];\n\n    @foreach (var item in Model.ChartData)\n    {\n        @:Counts.push(@item.Count);\n        @:Continents.push('@item.Name');\n    }\n\n    new Chart(document.getElementById('pie-chart'), {\n        type: 'pie',\n        data: {\n            labels: Continents,\n            datasets: [{\n                label: 'Games',\n                data: Counts,\n                backgroundColor: [\n                    'rgba(255, 99, 132, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(255, 206, 86, 0.7)',\n                    'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.7)'\n                ]\n            }]\n        }\n    });\n\u003c/script\u003e\n```\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- Excel: `Cell(row, col)` is **1-based** (row 1 col 1 = A1 in Excel UI)\n- Excel MIME: `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet` (exact string)\n- iText pipeline: `MemoryStream` → `PdfWriter(ms)` → `PdfDocument(writer)` → `Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)` → `writer.SetCloseStream(false)`\n- `ms.Position = 0` BEFORE `FileStreamResult` (else zero-byte download)\n- Chart.js `@:` Razor directive injects JS lines: `@:Counts.push(@item.Count);`\n- Chart renders only in browser — no server fallback","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcel (ClosedXML) — Pages/Excel.cshtml.cs:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing ClosedXML.Excel;\n\npublic FileResult OnGet()\n{\n    var data = Game.GetGames();\n\n    using (var workbook = new XLWorkbook())\n    {\n        IXLWorksheet worksheet = workbook.Worksheets.Add(&quot;Games&quot;);\n        worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Value = &quot;Game Id&quot;;         // 1-BASED\n        worksheet.Cell(1, 2).Value = &quot;Year&quot;;\n        // ... header row ...\n\n        IXLRange range = worksheet.Range(worksheet.Cell(1, 1).Address, worksheet.Cell(1, 7).Address);\n        range.Style.Fill.SetBackgroundColor(XLColor.Almond);\n\n        int index = 1;\n        foreach (var item in data)\n        {\n            index++;\n            worksheet.Cell(index, 1).Value = item.GameId;\n            // ... fill columns ...\n        }\n\n        using (var stream = new MemoryStream())\n        {\n            workbook.SaveAs(stream);\n            var content = stream.ToArray();\n            return File(content,\n                &quot;application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet&quot;,\n                $&quot;FifaWorldCup_{DateTime.Now:yyyyMMdd}.xlsx&quot;);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePDF (iText 7 — needs \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\nusing iText.Kernel.Geom;\n\nvar ms = new MemoryStream();\nvar writer = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdfDoc = new PdfDocument(writer);\nvar document = new Document(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false);\nwriter.SetCloseStream(false);\n\ndocument.Add(new Paragraph(&quot;Report Title&quot;)\n    .SetTextAlignment(iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.CENTER)\n    .SetFontSize(20));\n\nvar table = new Table(3);\n// ... AddCell(...) in row-major order ...\ndocument.Add(table);\n\n// Page numbers after layout\nint total = pdfDoc.GetNumberOfPages();\nfor (int i = 1; i &lt;= total; i++) {\n    document.ShowTextAligned(new Paragraph($&quot;Page {i} of {total}&quot;),\n        559, 806, i,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.TextAlignment.RIGHT,\n        iText.Layout.Properties.VerticalAlignment.TOP, 0);\n}\n\ndocument.Close();\nms.Position = 0;          // CRITICAL before FileStreamResult\n\nreturn new FileStreamResult(ms, &quot;application/pdf&quot;) {\n    FileDownloadName = $&quot;Report_{DateTime.Now:yyyyMMdd}.pdf&quot;\n};\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChart.js (client-side only):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e&lt;canvas id=&quot;pie-chart&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; height=&quot;400&quot;&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;\n&lt;script src=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@3.9.1/dist/chart.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n\n&lt;script&gt;\n    const Counts = [];\n    const Continents = [];\n\n    @foreach (var item in Model.ChartData)\n    {\n        @:Counts.push(@item.Count);\n        @:Continents.push(&#39;@item.Name&#39;);\n    }\n\n    new Chart(document.getElementById(&#39;pie-chart&#39;), {\n        type: &#39;pie&#39;,\n        data: {\n            labels: Continents,\n            datasets: [{\n                label: &#39;Games&#39;,\n                data: Counts,\n                backgroundColor: [\n                    &#39;rgba(255, 99, 132, 0.7)&#39;,\n                    &#39;rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.7)&#39;,\n                    &#39;rgba(255, 206, 86, 0.7)&#39;,\n                    &#39;rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.7)&#39;\n                ]\n            }]\n        }\n    });\n&lt;/script&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcel: \u003ccode\u003eCell(row, col)\u003c/code\u003e is \u003cstrong\u003e1-based\u003c/strong\u003e (row 1 col 1 = A1 in Excel UI)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcel MIME: \u003ccode\u003eapplication/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\u003c/code\u003e (exact string)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eiText pipeline: \u003ccode\u003eMemoryStream\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfWriter(ms)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ePdfDocument(writer)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eDocument(pdfDoc, PageSize.A4, false)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003ewriter.SetCloseStream(false)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ems.Position = 0\u003c/code\u003e BEFORE \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e (else zero-byte download)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eChart.js \u003ccode\u003e@:\u003c/code\u003e Razor directive injects JS lines: \u003ccode\u003e@:Counts.push(@item.Count);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eChart renders only in browser — no server fallback\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"TDD — xUnit + Moq (GoodBooks project)","body_md":"**Cycle:** Red (failing test) → Green (minimum code) → Refactor (clean up with tests green)\n\n**Attributes:**\n\n```cs\n[Fact]\npublic void Add_TwoPlusTwo_ReturnsFour()\n{\n    // Arrange\n    var calc = new Calculator();\n    // Act\n    int result = calc.Add(2, 2);\n    // Assert\n    Assert.Equal(4, result);            // expected FIRST\n}\n\n[Theory]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.JournalEntry)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.PurchaseOrder)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.SalesOrder)]\npublic void WithDifferentTypes_ShouldHandleAllTypes(SequenceNumberTypes type) { ... }\n```\n\n**Assertions used in demos:** `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` · `Assert.NotNull` · `Assert.Empty` · `Assert.Null` · `Assert.Single` · `Assert.NotEmpty`\n\n**Lifecycle:** xUnit creates a new test-class instance per test. Constructor = pre-test setup. `IDisposable.Dispose()` = post-test cleanup. No `[Setup]`/`[TearDown]` attributes.\n\n**Moq patterns (GoodBooks BaseServiceTests.cs):**\n\n```cs\npublic class BaseServiceTests\n{\n    private readonly Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e\u003e _mockSequenceNumberRepo;\n\n    public BaseServiceTests()              // fresh mock per test\n    {\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e\u003e();\n    }\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void Example()\n    {\n        // Setup stub\n        var list = new List\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e();\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo\n            .Setup(r =\u003e r.Table)\n            .Returns(() =\u003e list.AsQueryable());\n\n        // Setup callback (side effect)\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo\n            .Setup(r =\u003e r.Insert(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()))\n            .Callback\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e(s =\u003e list.Add(s));\n\n        // Use the fake (note .Object)\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Object.Insert(new SequenceNumber());\n\n        // Verify\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Verify(r =\u003e r.Update(It.IsAny\u003cSequenceNumber\u003e()), Times.Once);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Static factory for fixture setup (MockRepositoryFixtures.cs):**\n\n```cs\npublic static class MockRepositoryFixtures\n{\n    public static Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e CreateEmptyRepository\u003cT\u003e() where T : BaseEntity\n    {\n        var mock = new Mock\u003cIRepository\u003cT\u003e\u003e();\n        mock.Setup(r =\u003e r.Table).Returns(new List\u003cT\u003e().AsQueryable());\n        return mock;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nTests call `MockRepositoryFixtures.CreateEmptyRepository\u003cBank\u003e()` to share boilerplate — still fresh mock per test.\n\n**Must-know**\n\n- `Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` — expected FIRST. Swapped → misleading failure messages.\n- `Moq` flow: `new Mock\u003cT\u003e()` → `.Setup(r =\u003e r.Method(It.IsAny\u003c...\u003e())).Returns(...)` or `.Callback\u003cT\u003e(...)` → `.Object` to get the fake → `.Verify(..., Times.Once)`\n- Constructor per test = fresh state; don't make mocks static fields\n- `It.IsAny\u003cT\u003e()` matches any value of type `T`; `It.Is\u003cT\u003e(x =\u003e x.Id == 1)` for specific matching","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCycle:\u003c/strong\u003e Red (failing test) → Green (minimum code) → Refactor (clean up with tests green)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttributes:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e[Fact]\npublic void Add_TwoPlusTwo_ReturnsFour()\n{\n    // Arrange\n    var calc = new Calculator();\n    // Act\n    int result = calc.Add(2, 2);\n    // Assert\n    Assert.Equal(4, result);            // expected FIRST\n}\n\n[Theory]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.JournalEntry)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.PurchaseOrder)]\n[InlineData(SequenceNumberTypes.SalesOrder)]\npublic void WithDifferentTypes_ShouldHandleAllTypes(SequenceNumberTypes type) { ... }\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAssertions used in demos:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.NotNull\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Empty\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Null\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Single\u003c/code\u003e · \u003ccode\u003eAssert.NotEmpty\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLifecycle:\u003c/strong\u003e xUnit creates a new test-class instance per test. Constructor = pre-test setup. \u003ccode\u003eIDisposable.Dispose()\u003c/code\u003e = post-test cleanup. No \u003ccode\u003e[Setup]\u003c/code\u003e/\u003ccode\u003e[TearDown]\u003c/code\u003e attributes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMoq patterns (GoodBooks BaseServiceTests.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003epublic class BaseServiceTests\n{\n    private readonly Mock&lt;IRepository&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;&gt; _mockSequenceNumberRepo;\n\n    public BaseServiceTests()              // fresh mock per test\n    {\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo = new Mock&lt;IRepository&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;&gt;();\n    }\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void Example()\n    {\n        // Setup stub\n        var list = new List&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;();\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo\n            .Setup(r =&gt; r.Table)\n            .Returns(() =&gt; list.AsQueryable());\n\n        // Setup callback (side effect)\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo\n            .Setup(r =&gt; r.Insert(It.IsAny&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;()))\n            .Callback&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;(s =&gt; list.Add(s));\n\n        // Use the fake (note .Object)\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Object.Insert(new SequenceNumber());\n\n        // Verify\n        _mockSequenceNumberRepo.Verify(r =&gt; r.Update(It.IsAny&lt;SequenceNumber&gt;()), Times.Once);\n    }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStatic factory for fixture setup (MockRepositoryFixtures.cs):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003epublic static class MockRepositoryFixtures\n{\n    public static Mock&lt;IRepository&lt;T&gt;&gt; CreateEmptyRepository&lt;T&gt;() where T : BaseEntity\n    {\n        var mock = new Mock&lt;IRepository&lt;T&gt;&gt;();\n        mock.Setup(r =&gt; r.Table).Returns(new List&lt;T&gt;().AsQueryable());\n        return mock;\n    }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTests call \u003ccode\u003eMockRepositoryFixtures.CreateEmptyRepository&lt;Bank&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e to share boilerplate — still fresh mock per test.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMust-know\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e — expected FIRST. Swapped → misleading failure messages.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eMoq\u003c/code\u003e flow: \u003ccode\u003enew Mock&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Setup(r =&gt; r.Method(It.IsAny&lt;...&gt;())).Returns(...)\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.Callback&lt;T&gt;(...)\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Object\u003c/code\u003e to get the fake → \u003ccode\u003e.Verify(..., Times.Once)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConstructor per test = fresh state; don&#39;t make mocks static fields\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eIt.IsAny&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e matches any value of type \u003ccode\u003eT\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eIt.Is&lt;T&gt;(x =&gt; x.Id == 1)\u003c/code\u003e for specific matching\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Final-hour triage","body_md":"- **`ApiKeyCredential`** (System.ClientModel) NOT `AzureKeyCredential` for OpenAIClient\n- **`.AsAIAgent()`** NOT `.AsAgent()` · **`RunAsync`** NOT `Invoke`\n- **Ollama HTTP :11434** · **GitHub HTTPS /inference** (model: `openai/gpt-4o-mini`)\n- **`ITransformer` from `Fit()`** NOT `IDataView`\n- **Column names `\"Label\"` and `\"Features\"`** are hardcoded in ML.NET\n- **`[LoadColumn(N)]` is 0-based; ClosedXML `Cell(r,c)` is 1-based**\n- **MemoryStream `Position = 0`** before `FileStreamResult` (PDF export)\n- **`Assert.Equal(expected, actual)`** — expected FIRST\n- **`AddServiceDefaults()` + `MapDefaultEndpoints()`** in each service, NOT AppHost\n- **`AbortOnConnectFail = true`** for Redis (default is false → writes swallowed)\n- **`TemplateColumn Context=\"x\"`** (row access), `\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\"\u003e` (W07 Server lab)\n- **`CurrentCulture` (formatting) + `CurrentUICulture` (resources)** — set BOTH\n- **`UseRequestLocalization()`** middleware required or localization silently no-ops\n- **iText needs `itext7` + `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter`** together\n- **`#:` directives** — no space after colon · `#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` for web\n- **`@rendermode InteractiveServer`** on Blazor pages that await (QuickGrid, gRPC)\n- **gRPC override:** `Task\u003cResponse\u003e` + `ServerCallContext`; `Task` + `IServerStreamWriter\u003cT\u003e` for streaming\n- **proto3 field tags:** 1–15 = 1 byte · permanent · `reserved N;` after delete\n- **Moq:** `.Setup().Returns/Callback` → `.Object` → `.Verify(..., Times.Once)`","body_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eApiKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e (System.ClientModel) NOT \u003ccode\u003eAzureKeyCredential\u003c/code\u003e for OpenAIClient\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e.AsAIAgent()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003e.AsAgent()\u003c/code\u003e · \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eRunAsync\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003eInvoke\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOllama HTTP :11434\u003c/strong\u003e · \u003cstrong\u003eGitHub HTTPS /inference\u003c/strong\u003e (model: \u003ccode\u003eopenai/gpt-4o-mini\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eITransformer\u003c/code\u003e from \u003ccode\u003eFit()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003eIDataView\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eColumn names \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Label&quot;\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003e&quot;Features&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e are hardcoded in ML.NET\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(N)]\u003c/code\u003e is 0-based; ClosedXML \u003ccode\u003eCell(r,c)\u003c/code\u003e is 1-based\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMemoryStream \u003ccode\u003ePosition = 0\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e before \u003ccode\u003eFileStreamResult\u003c/code\u003e (PDF export)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected, actual)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — expected FIRST\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eMapDefaultEndpoints()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e in each service, NOT AppHost\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAbortOnConnectFail = true\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e for Redis (default is false → writes swallowed)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn Context=&quot;x&quot;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e (row access), \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@pagination&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e (W07 Server lab)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/code\u003e (formatting) + \u003ccode\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/code\u003e (resources)\u003c/strong\u003e — set BOTH\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003eUseRequestLocalization()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e middleware required or localization silently no-ops\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eiText needs \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e together\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e directives\u003c/strong\u003e — no space after colon · \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e for web\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@rendermode InteractiveServer\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e on Blazor pages that await (QuickGrid, gRPC)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003egRPC override:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eTask&lt;Response&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eServerCallContext\u003c/code\u003e; \u003ccode\u003eTask\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eIServerStreamWriter&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e for streaming\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eproto3 field tags:\u003c/strong\u003e 1–15 = 1 byte · permanent · \u003ccode\u003ereserved N;\u003c/code\u003e after delete\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMoq:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e.Setup().Returns/Callback\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Object\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003e.Verify(..., Times.Once)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"}]}};
